    3517,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86822728812?pwd=A25BRQGhApDxbMdfQBrT4Bmlnb11eq.1',
    '{"id":"01KG33X396XS98CSPAAJBYFPN8","title":"Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new)","summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Goals and Pipeline Targets**\n\nThe team aligned on a **target of 50 sales-qualified leads (SQLs)** to support **$35,000 in net new monthly recurring revenue (MRR)** by year-end, recognizing this as an ambitious but critical benchmark for marketing impact (07:07).  \n- The SQL target is based on historical conversion rates of around **9% from marketing SQLs to opportunities** and a **27% win rate** on opportunities, with average deal sizes near **$10,000 to $12,000** and a **sales cycle of 137 days**.  \n- **Michael Jones** expressed skepticism due to the lack of precedent but suggested a more conservative interim goal of **25 SQLs** as a realistic milestone, maintaining alignment on the overarching **$35,000 MRR** target as a total business goal regardless of lead source (09:04).  \n- The group agreed marketing efforts would complement existing channels like trade shows, which are expected to generate **2 to 3 opportunities per event across four conferences** this year (09:54).  \n- **Justin Brown** emphasized the partnership mindset: marketing and sales are jointly responsible for the revenue goal, with flexibility in attribution and a focus on driving **more inbound engagement** rather than rigidly tracking channel-specific lead counts (13:00).  \n- The team agreed that **increasing inbound interest and direct contact from prospects** is a key success metric, reflecting a shift from purely tactical deliverables to strategic, metric-driven marketing (14:23).  \n\n## **New Marketing Infrastructure and Data Integration**\n\nA new **automated system powered by N8N and Supabase** was introduced to capture and analyze multi-channel engagement signals, enabling more personalized and timely outreach based on richer data (18:00).  \n- This system integrates tools like **Clay for data enrichment**, **Smartlead for outbound emails**, and **Bombora intent data** to identify warm prospects and trigger personalized follow-up actions via email or Slack alerts (18:52).  \n- The database captures all prospect interactions, allowing the team to segment and tailor offers, for example, creating **custom landing pages for interested accounts like M Supply** (18:52).  \n- **Justin Brown** highlighted the need to calibrate which signals warrant adding contacts into HubSpot to balance workload with sales bandwidth, emphasizing form fills as essential but also recognizing value in other engagement signals (19:51).  \n- The system aims to provide **more precise intent data at a fraction of the cost of expensive platforms like Hockey Stack**, enabling the team to act faster and avoid waiting for traditional form fills (23:00).  \n- The integration automatically updates contact records with detailed activity history, preserving marketing contact billing efficiency while improving sales visibility (24:42).  \n\n## **Innovative Offer Concepts and Validation Strategy**\n\nTwo key offer concepts were proposed to break through historically low engagement and form fill rates, emphasizing personalized, data-driven tools built on Hydrant’s proprietary data (25:28).  \n- The **Supply Chain Performance Scorecard** would let prospects benchmark their supply chain performance against peers in under five minutes, showing personalized risks and estimated costs of inefficiencies, leveraging AI to package and generate relevant insights (25:28).  \n    - **Josh Bartel** recommended piloting this with trusted existing clients first to gather qualitative feedback and validate its value before broader rollout (27:06).  \n    - Josh also stressed that for marketing content to be effective, it must surpass current manual outreach efforts in credibility and relevance, noting AI-generated content must feel genuinely personalized to succeed (28:25).  \n- The second offer is a **Tailored Inventory Action Plan**, an AI-driven multi-page playbook offering detailed, client-specific recommendations based on inputs like SKU counts, fill rates, and growth plans (42:10).  \n    - The team discussed balancing transparency with protecting Hydrant’s unique expertise, aiming to avoid generic “ebook” style content by emphasizing a dynamic, personalized approach (42:43).  \n    - **Michael Jones** liked the potential for this tool to shortcut assessments and accelerate sales conversations by giving prospects compelling data early (44:24).  \n    - Both offers could be combined or iterated upon to create an evolving ABM playbook with continuous testing and refinement (47:50).  \n- The group agreed on a clear **validation cadence**, focusing first on internal qualitative feedback from existing clients as a litmus test to justify further investment and scaling (35:22).  \n- **Josh Bartel** called for defined checkpoints with timelines and success criteria to avoid long-term commitments without measurable results, advocating for rapid MVP development and iterative testing (35:19).  \n- The team committed to incorporating **client feedback** to refine messaging and content, with a focus on understanding why prospects do or do not engage, addressing the current disconnect seen in low form fill rates (39:13).  \n\n## **Pricing, Engagement Models, and Timelines**\n\nTwo engagement options were presented:  \n- A **status quo plan** at **$5,000 per month** offering ongoing management of surveys, newsletters, social content, website, and HubSpot with some flexibility for ad hoc work (50:05).  \n- A **strategic plan** at **$7,500 per month** adding the custom interactive tool, ABM planning, messaging development, and new ad creation, including more gifted points for additional work (51:28).  \n- The **$2,500 premium** for the strategic plan reflects the investment in new AI-enabled tools and enhanced support (51:42).  \n- **Justin Brown** reassured Hydrant that the agency is willing to be flexible on scope and pricing, with options to adjust based on early results and client feedback (52:52).  \n- **Josh Bartel** requested clearer timelines and deliverables tied to the points plan, emphasizing a desire to focus on outcome-driven milestones rather than monthly point accounting (53:24).  \n- The team agreed to move away from detailed points discussions for internal management, trusting each other to communicate when workloads or expectations need adjustment (54:40).  \n- The goal is to stand up the new tools within **one month**, aiming for rollout in **March**, with a commitment to reassess after **3 to 6 months** based on campaign performance and client feedback (55:48).  \n- A final decision on the engagement approach was expected by **end of the week** to align billing and project kickoff (57:58).  \n\n## **Strategic Alignment and Partnership Philosophy**\n\nThe discussion underscored a shift from purely tactical marketing deliverables to a **strategic, metrics-focused partnership** aimed at generating measurable business growth (14:23).  \n- The agency positions itself as a **value-add partner** committed to pushing boundaries and taking calculated risks with Hydrant to unlock new inbound opportunities (15:28).  \n- Both sides recognize the importance of **building intellectual property** that can be reused across sales and marketing efforts, creating a “flywheel” effect to warm leads and shorten sales cycles (34:00).  \n- **Michael Jones** stressed the need to differentiate Hydrant from traditional consultants and generic software by emphasizing the hybrid, personalized nature of their offering (47:43).  \n- The team agreed on the importance of **iterative testing and learning**, with a culture of rapid feedback loops and willingness to pivot based on what works, avoiding long investments in unproven approaches (37:24).  \n- Transparency and trust were emphasized as key to managing expectations and adjusting tactics without getting bogged down in administrative overhead like point tracking (54:36).  \n- This alignment aims to sustain Hydrant’s growth by combining marketing innovation, sales expertise, and data-driven insights into a cohesive growth engine.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","AI-driven tools","Sales Qualified Leads","Supply Chain Performance Scorecard","Marketing Automation","HubSpot Integration"],"overview":"- **Sales Targets:** Aim for 50 SQLs to achieve $35,000 in new MRR by year-end, recognizing historical conversion rates.  \n- **Marketing Collaboration:** Emphasis on unified marketing and sales efforts driving inbound engagement instead of tracking specific lead counts.  \n- **New Data System:** Automated system introduced for enhanced prospect engagement and personalized outreach, integrating various data tools.  \n- **Innovative Offers:** Proposed Supply Chain Performance Scorecard and Tailored Inventory Action Plan for personalized client insights and quicker sales.  \n- **Engagement Pricing:** Two plans presented, ranging from $5,000 to $7,500, with a focus on value and flexibility based on results.  \n- **Strategic Partnership:** Shift towards a metrics-driven approach, emphasizing iterative feedback, transparency, and building distinctive intellectual property.","action_items":"\n**Michael Jones**\nProvide calculations and Power BI data to Marketers in Demand for AI tool build (31:59)\nWork with team to calibrate criteria for which lead signals should be passed into HubSpot for sales follow-up (22:13)\nCollaborate on designing pointed questions for lead engagement surveys and analyze reasons for low conversion (39:00)\nProvide case studies and anecdotal insights for marketing collateral and AI model content feeding (44:24)\n\n**Josh Bartel**\nEvaluate AI-generated Supply Chain Performance Scorecard and Action Plan offers with trusted clients; gather qualitative feedback (27:00)\nTest and provide feedback on prototype AI tools from Marketers in Demand (48:23)\nCoordinate with Michael on investment decisions based on meeting MVP milestones and validating results (56:00)\n\n**Justin Brown**\nLead development of AI-driven marketing tools and integrate data and models from Hydrian (31:54)\nPrepare and send detailed project timelines and milestone plans for MVP and implementation to Hydrian (57:17)\nManage points plan internally but reduce complexity in client communication (53:22)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nDesign and oversee technical implementation of automation engine (N8N), data enrichment, and lead routing system integrating HubSpot and Supabase (18:00)\nBuild out and iterate ABM plan documents specifying target segments, messaging, offers, timelines, responsibilities (37:36)\nCollaborate with Justin and Hydrian to build MVP AI Scorecard prototype and subsequent product iterations (25:28)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nPresent and manage pricing and points options, coordinate monthly deliverables (50:05)\nSupport client account management with flexibility on scope and adapt deliverables (54:00)\n"},"duration":58.61000061035156,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Michael Jones"},{"id":1,"name":"Josh Bartel"},{"id":2,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":3,"name":"Justin Brown"},{"id":4,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi, guys.","index":0,"end_time":5.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":6.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Happy Wednesday.","index":2,"end_time":7.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":7.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, Howdy.","index":3,"end_time":14.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":9.04,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"How is everyone?","index":4,"end_time":17.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yes, well.","index":5,"end_time":20.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You doing all right?","index":6,"end_time":22.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":20.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":7,"end_time":23.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":22.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Got Josh here.","index":8,"end_time":26.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":25.61,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I can see you, Michael.","index":9,"end_time":29.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"All right.","index":10,"end_time":31.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Good stuff.","index":11,"end_time":32.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, I appreciate you guys going through this with us.","index":12,"end_time":37.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":33.77,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Didn''t want anybody to feel like the last meeting was stepping on anybody''s toes.","index":13,"end_time":42.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":38.25,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we do have like one version, which was kind of what was already laid out, another version today of just some ideas that we had.","index":14,"end_time":51.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":43.45,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We will not be offended if you don''t go with our ideas.","index":15,"end_time":56.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":52.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have people, you know, when we.","index":16,"end_time":58.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":56.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''m.","index":17,"end_time":58.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":58.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''m on the sales side a lot of times, and when during the sales process, I hear people all the time say, we want an agency that''s always going to come to us with ideas.","index":18,"end_time":67.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":58.92,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so we do that.","index":19,"end_time":69.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":68.119,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And even if you don''t like them, if you do, great.","index":20,"end_time":71.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":69.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If not, also, okay.","index":21,"end_time":73.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":71.96,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But, you know, we''re trying to do our job by just when we see things, when we''re trying things, that we''re still bringing them to your attention.","index":22,"end_time":82.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":74.36,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we''ll go through a few things today and we''ll figure out where we land.","index":23,"end_time":87.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":83.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We don''t have to figure that out today, but we''ll.","index":24,"end_time":89.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":87.67,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll float a couple things and then we''ll have our kind of our annual plan in place, or at least what we''re doing over the next few months.","index":25,"end_time":96.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":89.51,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So with that, I''ll kick it over to Colin and Bailey to take us away.","index":26,"end_time":101.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":96.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":27,"end_time":102.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":101.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"All right, can everyone see my screen?","index":28,"end_time":106.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":104.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":29,"end_time":108.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yes.","index":30,"end_time":109.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Looks good.","index":31,"end_time":109.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":32,"end_time":110.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":109.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"All right.","index":33,"end_time":112.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":111.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":112.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":112.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, as Justin said, thanks for your guys time.","index":35,"end_time":115.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":112.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So after our last.","index":36,"end_time":116.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":115.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Last conversation, we went back and we built out what we think can be a pretty strong shift in how we''ve done ABM for hydrant, historically based on all of the new infrastructure that we''ve put into place and ultimately how marketing can help support business goals.","index":37,"end_time":132.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":116.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re going to walk through the goals that we aligned on, show you a few specific offer concepts that we came up with, and really ultimately try and end on a.","index":38,"end_time":143.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":134.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is this something that''ll break through the.","index":39,"end_time":146.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":144,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Historically, people haven''t filled out forms, stigma, and really, in most cases, a reality for a lot of companies.","index":40,"end_time":153.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":146.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''s why we build these campaigns.","index":41,"end_time":154.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":153.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll start with goals.","index":42,"end_time":157.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":155.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll confirm the targets that we''re looking at and show you the calculations of how we got there.","index":43,"end_time":162.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":157.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''ll go through the offer ideas.","index":44,"end_time":165.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":163.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s where we''ll spend a bulk of the conversation.","index":45,"end_time":167.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":165.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have two concepts that we''ve built and Josh, I''m really interested to see your thoughts there as well, because I wanted to rope in the Power BI model that you had showed on our last call as well and see how we can utilize that and not just running like ebooks and webinars and things like that as a main offer.","index":46,"end_time":185.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":168.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those can be fine anecdotally or as an extra, but we need something as a core piece to this and then from there we will decide on what the plan is moving forward.","index":47,"end_time":195.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":185.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The big question we really need to get to is which marketing strategy for Hydrant is going to get to 35k in net new MRR by the end of the year.","index":48,"end_time":204.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":196.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does this feel on point with everyone?","index":49,"end_time":208.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":206.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions so far?","index":50,"end_time":209.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":208.369,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looks good.","index":51,"end_time":211.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"All right, well, you guys have seen our overview before, so I''ll jump into more of the meat of our presentation.","index":52,"end_time":220.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":212.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys know how we work.","index":53,"end_time":221.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":220.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, you mentioned in the last call that we haven''t seen really any evidence of pouring money into the top of the funnel and seeing leads fall out of the bottom here.","index":54,"end_time":230.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":221.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You.","index":55,"end_time":230.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":230.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s not very surprising because, you guys, it''s not like a $99 SaaS subscription that someone is signing up for and just saying, all right, here''s my credit card.","index":56,"end_time":238.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":231.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not much damage.","index":57,"end_time":239.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":238.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are not really proposing a traditional funnel approach here.","index":58,"end_time":244.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":241.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What we are saying is we want to build a system where marketing is creating assets that are so valuable that if Michael bumps into someone at a trade show and we''ve had them in our email contact list for a few months, or Josh, you get a referral call from someone that you''re not starting these conversations from scratch.","index":59,"end_time":261.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":244.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''ve been seeing, hydrating around for months.","index":60,"end_time":265.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":262.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They maybe have filled out something from the offers that we''ve built.","index":61,"end_time":269.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":265.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''ve seen social media, they''ve seen some ads, but really making sure because as you guys mentioned, the trade shows is where we get a lot of this fruit, right?","index":62,"end_time":277.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":269.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Conversations that Michael''s having.","index":63,"end_time":278.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":277.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also if we can get them into that assessment stage, you guys are closing about 50% of those.","index":64,"end_time":284.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":279.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, Josh, you said something last week that really stuck with me and I wrote it down here.","index":65,"end_time":290.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":286.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you said we may need to move our focus from having contact with potential customers on a regular basis so familiar to them and have more credibility.","index":66,"end_time":299.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":290.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I think that''s really what we''re, what we''re trying to go for here.","index":67,"end_time":302.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":299.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So having a lot more market presence through emails, LinkedIn, paid ads, and then those offers that people can interact with.","index":68,"end_time":310.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":302.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, ultimately, by the time they have a conversation with you they are very familiar with your offerings.","index":69,"end_time":315.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":310.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions so far?","index":70,"end_time":318.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":317.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that framework kind of make sense to everyone?","index":71,"end_time":320.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":318.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It does.","index":72,"end_time":322.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"All right, so jumping into the goals.","index":73,"end_time":327.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":323,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll walk through this table here.","index":74,"end_time":331.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":329.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, working in HubSpot, we talked through a lot of the data in there last week.","index":75,"end_time":336.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":333.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Michael, you had compared kind of just on the call some of the numbers that you would run, and they were pretty close.","index":76,"end_time":344.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":337.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we feel like we''re operating from a decent set of data here to make some decisions.","index":77,"end_time":348.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":344.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The ultimate goal that we heard from you guys is generating qualified pipeline to support 35k in MRR growth by the end of the year.","index":78,"end_time":355.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":348.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That doesn''t matter if it comes from seven new clients or one new client.","index":79,"end_time":360.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":356.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really just how that is ultimately coming about for Hydrant.","index":80,"end_time":365.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":361.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think one of the companies you mentioned was M Supply.","index":81,"end_time":369.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":365.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that correct?","index":82,"end_time":373.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s correct.","index":83,"end_time":373.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":374.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":373.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":85,"end_time":374.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.13,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So what we''re looking at here then is sales qualified leads that are created.","index":86,"end_time":379.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":375.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So not just any form fill, not marketing qualified leads, but sales qualified leads that are ultimately driving the bottom line.","index":87,"end_time":385.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":379.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What that means is these are meaningful conversions that could lead to actual potential opportunities.","index":88,"end_time":391.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":386.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have requirements in place.","index":89,"end_time":392.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":391.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are explicit replies to the LinkedIn or email outreach that we''re conducting where someone is showing genuine interest.","index":90,"end_time":398.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":392.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Inbound requests, where someone is saying a little bit more than just, well, one, hey, can we clean your office?","index":91,"end_time":404.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":399.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know those spam form fills?","index":92,"end_time":406.17,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":404.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":93,"end_time":406.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But actually showing some interest or looking to further their conversation or an actual booked discovery call meeting or direct conversation.","index":94,"end_time":415.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":407.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They have to be in the target market and it''s not spam.","index":95,"end_time":418.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":415.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So does that feel how you would qualify a lead?","index":96,"end_time":424.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":420.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":97,"end_time":425.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":424.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":98,"end_time":427.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":426.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then looking at the historical data, I know we went through a little bit of this last week as well.","index":99,"end_time":430.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":427.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"23 marketing SQLs last year that turned into two opportunities.","index":100,"end_time":434.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":430.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So about a 9% conversion rate.","index":101,"end_time":436.9,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":435.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is a small sample size, so we don''t want that to control everything that we''re looking at.","index":102,"end_time":440.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":436.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You had 107 total opportunities.","index":103,"end_time":443.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":441.179,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Historically, 21 of them are closed.","index":104,"end_time":445.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":443.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"1:56 closed, lost.","index":105,"end_time":446.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":445.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that represents a 27 win rate.","index":106,"end_time":450.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":447.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With deal ranges like we talked about, they do range pretty widely.","index":107,"end_time":454.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":450.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You do have kind of an average subset, but there are extremes that are changing the average.","index":108,"end_time":458.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":454.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the median kind of falls around 8.2, the average of 11.","index":109,"end_time":461.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":459.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys said kind of like that 8 to 12 is also a very comfortable spot.","index":110,"end_time":465.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":461.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the sales cycle averaging about 137 days.","index":111,"end_time":468.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":465.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that can vary very widely based on the how much of a hurry or how much of a pain the prospect is feeling.","index":112,"end_time":478.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":468.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Josh, you had mentioned you''d rather have the revenue regardless of whether it''s from one client or several smaller ones.","index":113,"end_time":483.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":478.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where we landed here is 50 SQLs, but also an OR in here of 35k and net new monthly recurring revenue.","index":114,"end_time":492.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":483.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where we landed on the 50 SQL number is based on if we can get 50 marketing or 50 SQLs, and if you even convert just 10 of those into opportunities or we do together.","index":115,"end_time":506.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":493.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So being conservative to the conversion rates we were just talking about at a 10k average, that''s 10 to 20k towards, you know, from one client towards that 35k goal.","index":116,"end_time":516.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":506.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So does this framework make sense?","index":117,"end_time":519.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":518.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":118,"end_time":522.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":119,"end_time":524.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Michael, is there anything that you want to add there?","index":120,"end_time":526.129,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":524.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":121,"end_time":526.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":526.129,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, feel free to throw mud at it.","index":122,"end_time":527.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":526.57,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"This is just like we''re trying to make sure that we digest the goals for the year, that they equate back to number of leads, et cetera.","index":123,"end_time":538.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":527.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So.","index":124,"end_time":538.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"If we nailed it, that''s great.","index":125,"end_time":541.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":540.67,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If there are questions or comments, look.","index":126,"end_time":544.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":541.83,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I mean, I understand the math perfectly fine.","index":127,"end_time":547.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, the only.","index":128,"end_time":549.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Listen, the skepticism here is we have no president for this at all.","index":129,"end_time":554.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, so these are great.","index":130,"end_time":556.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"These are I think, incredibly ambitious goals.","index":131,"end_time":558.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":556.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So this is, you know, from obviously pure marketing.","index":132,"end_time":562.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we''ve got to be a little bit careful here because we are saying, you know, the conferences we go to.","index":133,"end_time":567.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we''re going to four conferences this year.","index":134,"end_time":570.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":567.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"One expects we''re going to get two or three opportunities, say one to one to three opportunities from each one.","index":135,"end_time":578.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":571.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So those obviously are outside of that.","index":136,"end_time":582.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":579.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But if we sort of purely said from all the marketing activities, I think your 50 is ambitious, but I understand how if you were, if this was the only thing we were doing, we were not doing anything else, this would make sense.","index":137,"end_time":596.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay.","index":138,"end_time":597.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I just want to be careful when you''re sort of looking at these things, you start beating yourself up on, you know, how many leads are we generating from that?","index":139,"end_time":605.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":597.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We haven''t been able to get anywhere near the number in the path.","index":140,"end_time":609.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Just be aware of that as we progress through this, through the year.","index":141,"end_time":614.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":142,"end_time":616.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":616.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so what number, Michael, would you feel more comfortable seeing there as a not too ambitious, like a smart goal, really?","index":143,"end_time":623.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":616.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I would say half of that is still ambitious.","index":144,"end_time":628.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But I think it''s probably better than just throwing a number out there because your numbers through the math as if nothing else was going on, that isn''t going to be the case.","index":145,"end_time":639.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I would say 25 is more real than 50 in my view.","index":146,"end_time":646.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But Josh?","index":147,"end_time":647.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s generally true.","index":148,"end_time":651.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":149,"end_time":651.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Our, our 35k net new number is a total business number.","index":150,"end_time":654.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.49,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And it''s, it''s very hard to translate because historically 100% of our new business has come from non marketing, non digital channels.","index":151,"end_time":664.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.65,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So.","index":152,"end_time":665.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":153,"end_time":666.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":666.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And Colin, when you were doing a lot of this mathing with Bailey was the.","index":154,"end_time":673.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":666.65,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Can we just make sure we''re aligned on what part of this is overarching business goals versus marketing?","index":155,"end_time":682.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":674.22,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I believe when we discussed it, you''re nodding your head yes.","index":156,"end_time":687.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":682.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Pick up.","index":157,"end_time":687.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":687.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I know what you''re asking.","index":158,"end_time":690.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":687.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":691.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":690.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the way that I was looking at this was Michael, very much based on the document that you had sent over of how marketing is really just folded into overall business goals.","index":160,"end_time":698.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":691.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why in this last column here of where''s the data?","index":161,"end_time":701.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":698.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have deals with a record source that is not offline.","index":162,"end_time":704.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":701.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because again, even if you''re talking to someone at a trade show, because we don''t have like a $100,000 terminus or hockey stack or something that''s tracking all of these tiny attribution points happening along the way, we need to come to an agreement that unless it''s like a pure conversation that, hey, referral, where your current customer said, hey, I told them to work with you and they''re going to give you a call or anything that you can track directly to something that you''ve done.","index":163,"end_time":728.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":705.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I want us to land on is that these are the company goals that both of us are working towards.","index":164,"end_time":733.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":729.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":165,"end_time":735.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":734.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So marketing is facilitating in multiple segments of this.","index":166,"end_time":738.29,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":735.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the 50 skills, like if Michael meets someone at a trade show, that''s one.","index":167,"end_time":744.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Correct.","index":168,"end_time":746.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":745.489,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Independent of evidence that they did or did not see our LinkedIn ad.","index":169,"end_time":749.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Correct.","index":170,"end_time":751.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Then I think around, yeah, we did.","index":171,"end_time":752.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":751.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Not want to go from we''ve basically gotten zero to we''re saying we''re going to get 50.","index":172,"end_time":757.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":752.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I think what we''re trying to say is, are there things that we can do to supplement to help to drive more?","index":173,"end_time":765.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":757.09,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So that is, you know, the things that Michael said would help.","index":174,"end_time":769.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":765.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then what if we also layer on an omnichannel campaign that has sales enablement materials?","index":175,"end_time":775.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":769.96,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We focus less on how much did marketers in demand New north do versus how much did Michael do versus what was at an event.","index":176,"end_time":785.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":775.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But hey, we''re all just driving towards this 35k number and if we hit it, everybody''s happy.","index":177,"end_time":790.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":785.16,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s kind of where we wanted to focus rather than the very linear what did we get versus what did you guys get?","index":178,"end_time":798.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":791.94,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I Don''t think you guys see us in that way.","index":179,"end_time":801.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":798.7,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have clients who come in and they''re like, you need to tag contacts that are marketers in demand contacts.","index":180,"end_time":809.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":801.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And at the end of the year, we''re going to evaluate how many you got versus how many Suzy paid marketer got.","index":181,"end_time":817.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":809.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And we''re going to see who.","index":182,"end_time":818.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":817.34,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Who''s $8,000 a year is more valuable to our business.","index":183,"end_time":824.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":819.1,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And one of you is going to be cut.","index":184,"end_time":826.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":824.3,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That is unfortunate, but it is the stack that we get sometimes.","index":185,"end_time":830.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":826.46,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I don''t think you guys are that way.","index":186,"end_time":832.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":830.94,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You see us more as like value add partners, but we also want to combine, drive towards the same goals and say, hey, we''re not just here to like, do what you ask of us to do.","index":187,"end_time":844.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":832.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We do want to see the numbers.","index":188,"end_time":845.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":844.04,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We do want to drive towards a goal and we want to work on those together.","index":189,"end_time":848,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":845.28,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''d love if they''re a little bit higher than maybe what you were planning on before, if we do more.","index":190,"end_time":854.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":848.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So I think that''s kind of where the, the mentality came from.","index":191,"end_time":857.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":854.4,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":192,"end_time":863.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Just quickly on that, Justin.","index":193,"end_time":865,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think the only thing we''ve got to be a little bit careful on is whatever goals you want to go ahead and consider to be a success in the relationship, I think is also important as well.","index":194,"end_time":877.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, look, from our point of view, we need to see more inbound.","index":195,"end_time":882.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":877.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And we''ve been, you know, Taylor and Bailey myself, we''ve been talking about this forever.","index":196,"end_time":886.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, we are trying to find a way of turning the corner and having people actually reach out directly to us in whichever way it may be.","index":197,"end_time":895.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I think that''s an important target because it''s not just for you.","index":198,"end_time":902.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It is incredibly important for us, you know, because, you know, we''re spending an awful lot of time.","index":199,"end_time":906.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":902.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Obviously we''re paying for you the time that you''re taking, but the time I''m taking and the team takes here in writing content, pushing content out and doing everything we possibly can to try to make a difference to the outside world where people go, that''s great.","index":200,"end_time":920.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That''s very interesting.","index":201,"end_time":921.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, let''s go ahead and reach out to those people.","index":202,"end_time":924.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Which is obviously how we.","index":203,"end_time":926.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"How we''d like to see things.","index":204,"end_time":927.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.29,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And the reason that we continue to push the envelope is that we know that like, that.","index":205,"end_time":934.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":928.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That it''s not unique to, to hydrant.","index":206,"end_time":937.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":934.21,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have two different types of clients that we like.","index":207,"end_time":939.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":937.17,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We.","index":208,"end_time":940.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We put our clients into two buckets, essentially.","index":209,"end_time":942.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":940.17,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There''s a lot of gray area between the two buckets, trust me.","index":210,"end_time":945.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":942.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But there''s Two different types of clients we have tactical and strategic.","index":211,"end_time":949.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":946.01,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Our tactical clients, we just do things for them and in that relationship, the relationship is easier.","index":212,"end_time":957.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":950.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We just do things.","index":213,"end_time":958.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":957.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They tell us what they need.","index":214,"end_time":959.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"They need an ebook, they need a blog post, a podcast episode, whatever it may be.","index":215,"end_time":964.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":959.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And we do it and we deliver it and we launch it on their website and it''s all good.","index":216,"end_time":969.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":964.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"However new CMO comes in or change of leadership or had a bad quarter, we''re the first thing that''s turned off because we don''t have the ability to point to actual thing, actual metrics that we''re helping our client to achieve in the strategic engagements we sign up for, you know, putting ourselves at a little more risk in terms of we''re signing up for goals, we''re saying we want to hit specific numbers, but at the same time when we''re able to do that, that''s when we''re able to keep clients for years.","index":217,"end_time":1003.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":970.24,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And you guys have been around for years and we''ve seen a lot of different things over those years where we''ve gone down to almost you leaving $2,000 a month investment, you know, and, and, and as good things continue to happen and now we''re like, okay, it''s time to revisit that again.","index":218,"end_time":1018.339,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1003.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We want, we, we want to see where we can take this relationship, how we can put our name on some numbers here in 2026.","index":219,"end_time":1026.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1018.339,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So that''s why we push for this.","index":220,"end_time":1029.369,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1026.66,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Okay, fair enough.","index":221,"end_time":1031.129,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1029.769,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I think we''re all like, we''re, we''re all aligned there.","index":222,"end_time":1035.849,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1032.089,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I know it''s on the slide, but we''re aligned that the best value add that we can provide to Hydrian is to be able to say that we are.","index":223,"end_time":1045.529,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1035.849,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We have metrics that we can tie our name to.","index":224,"end_time":1048.569,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1046.809,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I think that is how everybody''s able to win.","index":225,"end_time":1050.929,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1048.569,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So anyway, I keep talking.","index":226,"end_time":1052.729,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1050.929,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Go ahead.","index":227,"end_time":1053.209,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1052.729,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":228,"end_time":1054.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1054.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to take a little bit of time to go through really the behind the scenes and the architecture of how these come together.","index":229,"end_time":1061.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1055.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys will recognize a few of these tools.","index":230,"end_time":1063.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1061.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m not going to dive into all of them super in depth.","index":231,"end_time":1065.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1063.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But just as an overview, Clay in the top left is enriching target accounts with data.","index":232,"end_time":1070.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1065.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re able to get personalization from there, tie into LinkedIn, post all sorts of stuff like that.","index":233,"end_time":1075.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1070.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Smart lead is managing the outbound email sequences.","index":234,"end_time":1078.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1075.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Reach doing the same for LinkedIn ad platforms based on audience, you know, LinkedIn, retargeting through AdRoll, things like that.","index":235,"end_time":1085.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1078.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"RB2B is identifying anonymous website visitors and same with factors but as a more GDPR compliant solution because it''s account based, the biggest changes are actually in the middle and bottom of this.","index":236,"end_time":1100.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1085.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with N8N, we''ve built a pure automation engine here.","index":237,"end_time":1105.33,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1100.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is where any signal from any of these tools that we are using is flowing through one piece of technology that we have built.","index":238,"end_time":1112.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1105.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it has triggers from everything.","index":239,"end_time":1114.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1113.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It is analyzing the data, going through sentiment analysis and ultimately also sending an alert via email or Slack to us and to you guys of what the next step is to do with that contact, specifically with suggested personalized content as well.","index":240,"end_time":1131.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1114.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That is all captured in a database that we''ve built in Supabase.","index":241,"end_time":1136.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1132.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we are capturing people, engaging with the emails, filling out forms, responding to messages, whatever action they''re taking in the entire infrastructure that we''ve built here is all being captured in that database and then reported back to you guys with hey, you know how I mentioned earlier we''re seeing a lot of engagement from msupply we''ll just use as an example.","index":242,"end_time":1156.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1136.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But they''re not making the extra step of having that conversation.","index":243,"end_time":1160.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1156.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":244,"end_time":1161.24,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1160.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well now we should just have a much more personalized approach to Ms.","index":245,"end_time":1165.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1161.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Apply.","index":246,"end_time":1165.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1165.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They do seem interested.","index":247,"end_time":1166.96,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1165.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let''s make a new landing page just for them.","index":248,"end_time":1169.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1166.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s have content that is even more specific to what they''re looking for and how we promote Hydrien there.","index":249,"end_time":1174.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1169.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re able to get all of these signals just much faster and much more complete through this new engine that we''ve built.","index":250,"end_time":1180.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1174.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions there?","index":251,"end_time":1184.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1182.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s very interesting.","index":252,"end_time":1189.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, love to know more about this.","index":253,"end_time":1191.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1189.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":254,"end_time":1192.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1191.86,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I think one of the interesting things, Michael is just going to be determining where things go from N8N into either Supabase or HubSpot.","index":255,"end_time":1204.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1192.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We deal with this with a lot of our clients with smaller sales teams where it''s either founder led sales or small sales team.","index":256,"end_time":1213.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1204.75,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And you know we''re going to have to come up with the criteria of what goes into HubSpot and gets tagged for you to reach out to them and what doesn''t.","index":257,"end_time":1223.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1214.35,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Because when the teams are smaller and I know that''s why you want inbound, right?","index":258,"end_time":1226.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1223.47,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Is like, I mean I''m in the same situation, I sell our service and I don''t have the time to go look into Supabase and be like, oh, this person came to the website three times, let me build out a custom email for them.","index":259,"end_time":1239.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1226.63,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I need people to fill out a form and book on my calendar.","index":260,"end_time":1242.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1240.07,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So I''m like full contact form.","index":261,"end_time":1244.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1242.79,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But you may say you''re not that way.","index":262,"end_time":1247.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1244.63,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You may be like, look, if somebody clicks two ads, they, you know, hit the website three times and they open the email five times, I actually do want that to go into HubSpot and I want a task for myself to reach out to this person with a custom email from me because that''s what, you know, that''s what you have the bandwidth to do.","index":263,"end_time":1272.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1247.15,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so it''s about determining what that bandwidth is.","index":264,"end_time":1274.849,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1272.05,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And because as you''ve seen, not everybody fills out a form in today''s day and age.","index":265,"end_time":1280.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1274.849,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And it does not mean that they''re not interested in what Hydrant is doing.","index":266,"end_time":1284.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1280.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It doesn''t mean that they have not engaged with your content and maybe they just need that extra nudge.","index":267,"end_time":1290.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1284.17,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we''ll just need to come up with you what your comfort level is.","index":268,"end_time":1295.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1290.5,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And the great thing is also if you do not have enough in HubSpot, let''s say that you do determine just contact form is what you want to start out with, is what goes into HubSpot.","index":269,"end_time":1307.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1295.38,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You have access to Supabase so you can go in there and look and be like, okay, this person''s the top of the list.","index":270,"end_time":1313.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1308.02,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''ve got some time today.","index":271,"end_time":1315.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1314.5,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I want to go reach out to a few people.","index":272,"end_time":1317.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1315.58,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So there''s some good stuff here and some good reporting that we can give view as to who is showing signals that they are warmed up in some form or fashion.","index":273,"end_time":1329.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1317.3,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":274,"end_time":1331.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1330.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the sort of.","index":275,"end_time":1332.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1331.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, sorry, go ahead, Michael.","index":276,"end_time":1333.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1332.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I was just going to say I think that''s a good idea.","index":277,"end_time":1334.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We certainly can sort of calibrate how and what goes into HubSpot.","index":278,"end_time":1340.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, I think, you know, B can attest to this.","index":279,"end_time":1344.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1341.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Quite often we have these sort of conversations.","index":280,"end_time":1345.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1344.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So it''s like, you know, are they actually a warm lead or are they just, you know, they happen to click a couple of times but everyone does is doesn''t mean anything.","index":281,"end_time":1354.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1345.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So we don''t want to embarrass ourselves by reaching out and saying, oh, you''re really interested in what we do and go, I have no idea who you are.","index":282,"end_time":1359.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1354.69,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I might just clicked on the ad by mistake or whatever it may be.","index":283,"end_time":1362.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1359.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But I think it''s trying to find that sort of partnership between us where we go, look, this mate, this person here is ticking all the boxes.","index":284,"end_time":1371.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1362.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s hitting, it''s hit 100 points.","index":285,"end_time":1373.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1371.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yep.","index":286,"end_time":1375.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1374.86,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You should definitely go out to them and you know, we would suggest you take this approach.","index":287,"end_time":1379.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1375.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And this is what we''ve been trying to build because like Colin mentioned when he mentioned Hockey Stack and some of these other, these other tools that give this not intent data.","index":288,"end_time":1394.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1380.7,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"What is the word?","index":289,"end_time":1395.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1394.66,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Oh my gosh, it''s been a long attribution.","index":290,"end_time":1399.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1397.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you, Colin.","index":291,"end_time":1400.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1399.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"To give this level of attribution, you know, our clients in many cases aren''t paying us a retainer as big as what that technology platform costs for the month.","index":292,"end_time":1414.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1400.46,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so when you just get a piece of technology, it doesn''t even do anything for you yet, you know, if you want to get that attribution software, it''s $10,000 a month and it''s still only 60 to 70% accurate.","index":293,"end_time":1426.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1415.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so what we''ve been trying to build is something that, at a lighter weight that can give our clients more signals as to what''s going on with the people that they''re reaching out to rather than just, did I get a form fill, did I get a reply email?","index":294,"end_time":1443.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1426.56,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You''re just, I mean, then you''re sitting on your hands, you''re just waiting for things to come in and you can, you know that that''s one approach, but it is not going to lead to a big change in growth.","index":295,"end_time":1461.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1444.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You know, you''re just hoping that your marketing activities are incredibly strong, which is great.","index":296,"end_time":1466.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1461.86,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Not saying that we don''t strive for that, but there are other approaches when you have people in sales who are hungry, ambitious, looking to, you know, get after a few things, but also want to not put themselves out there to, you know, seem silly.","index":297,"end_time":1479.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1467.06,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So.","index":298,"end_time":1480.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1479.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":299,"end_time":1481.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1481.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":300,"end_time":1482.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1482.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And two quick things I just want to mention.","index":301,"end_time":1484.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1482.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here is one new piece that we''re bolting onto.","index":302,"end_time":1487.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1484.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is getting Bombora intent data actually integrated into this as well.","index":303,"end_time":1492.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1487.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So getting closer to that hockey stack or dream data type solution at that, but at a fraction of $100,000 cost that Justin was just referring to.","index":304,"end_time":1502.59,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1493.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And by default, typically how we integrate with HubSpot here, Michael, is having all of the contacts in our campaign loaded in as non marketing contact, so it doesn''t affect you guys billing.","index":305,"end_time":1514.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1503.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we update their records automatically through N8N to say first email sent, they viewed this ad, they downloaded this, they submitted this form.","index":306,"end_time":1522.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1514.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all tracked in their contact record.","index":307,"end_time":1524.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1522.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":308,"end_time":1528.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1527.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"All right, so now I want to dive into the offers.","index":309,"end_time":1533.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1528.969,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is where things get obviously the most interesting.","index":310,"end_time":1536.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1533.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As a marketer, I wanted to go through what we developed.","index":311,"end_time":1540.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1537.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so Josh, when you showed us that lead time analysis dashboard that you built from Power bi, you said, if someone offered me this data, I would absolutely be hungry for it.","index":312,"end_time":1549.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1540.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so that was our like, okay, this is what we need to work with you guys to Build and to scale out and get out into the market.","index":313,"end_time":1554.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1549.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we were thinking here is a supply chain performance scorecard.","index":314,"end_time":1561.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1555.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is something where prospects could see how their supply chain is stacking up against their industry peers in less than five minutes.","index":315,"end_time":1568.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1561.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they would go to a landing page, they''d answer questions about their industry, their revenue range, their SKU counts, current fill rates and maybe a primary challenge should take them probably 60 to 90 seconds.","index":316,"end_time":1579.88,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1569.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They hit submit and then instantly they are presented with a Hydrian branded but also to that company personalized scorecard that is showing their performance versus industry benchmarks that were able to, if I''m remembering correctly, Josh, you were using your gosh proprietary data, said that there may be a piece where you want to bring in some extra data as well and then also suggesting like three risk areas and how Hydrain would respond to those and then maybe an estimated annual cost of those performance gaps to kind of give them that, that fear of if we don''t change this, this is what we''re going to continue running into.","index":317,"end_time":1617.06,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1580.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll take a pause there.","index":318,"end_time":1621.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1620.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any, any feedback on.","index":319,"end_time":1622.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1621.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It makes sense to me.","index":320,"end_time":1627.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1626.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It feels like maybe a good test audience is our existing clients, you know, trusted contacts that we sort of can.","index":321,"end_time":1634.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1627.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"They won''t be totally unbiased, but they might give us some useful opinions.","index":322,"end_time":1639.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1635.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And then I guess, you know, the unknown piece of this is like some of it is, some of what the AI is doing is composition where it''s basically saying like I''m gonna, based on your answers you gave me, I''m gonna package up the data that I have into an attractive and useful format.","index":323,"end_time":1660.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1643.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And we, there''s, there''s probably been some training that took place so that we can give feedback on different options.","index":324,"end_time":1664.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1660.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And it generally has an idea of how to do this.","index":325,"end_time":1666.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1664.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So that is somewhat interesting.","index":326,"end_time":1668.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1667.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And then there''s the AI generating content, not just organizing it where it needs to be able to say I know who your top five competitors are.","index":327,"end_time":1677.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1668.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m not.","index":328,"end_time":1678.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1678.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That might not be true but like I''m using it as an example of yeah it actually has to go out and do some, or have some pre trained knowledge about the world.","index":329,"end_time":1686.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1678.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And so yeah, that, that to me like the combination of those two things I think is potentially interesting.","index":330,"end_time":1695.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1687.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I would want to be able to figure out how we can validate really fast.","index":331,"end_time":1700.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1696.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like is this actually because it really needs to be on the order of, you know, 10, 10 times more compelling.","index":332,"end_time":1705.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1700.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"There really isn''t a way to quantify it because we''re kind of going from near zero to more than zero.","index":333,"end_time":1710.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1705.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But, you know, that kind of order of magnitude more compelling than content we''ve been producing.","index":334,"end_time":1717.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1710.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s, it''s, it''s probably worth thinking about too.","index":335,"end_time":1719.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1718.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, the content we''ve been producing in many cases is like a phone call from Michael or repeated phone calls from Michael.","index":336,"end_time":1724.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1719.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, we.","index":337,"end_time":1725.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1724.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So it wasn''t clear to me from the earlier technical tools how much more capability we have to monitor activity of prospects.","index":338,"end_time":1732.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1726.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But right now we get pretty good intelligence, or we get intelligence from a number of sources about prospects.","index":339,"end_time":1737.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1733.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And we''re at a scale currently where it''s like, holy, someone''s actually interested.","index":340,"end_time":1741.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1737.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Michael can kind of drop everything and like, really run that down.","index":341,"end_time":1744.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1741.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And so we clear the barrier of a real person is reaching out to me who has a genuine interest in my business and knows something specific about me.","index":342,"end_time":1756.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1745.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That to me is like, again, I think in terms of the marketing I receive, that puts you in kind of a different category where I''m probably going to at least consider as opposed to even really good AI generated content.","index":343,"end_time":1770.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1757.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I mean, I''ve read some emails where it''s like, man, they really nailed, like, what I''m thinking about today.","index":344,"end_time":1774.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1770.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But they obviously scraped our whole website and like an AI wrote something clever, right?","index":345,"end_time":1779.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1775.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And I don''t respond to those things.","index":346,"end_time":1780.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1779.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I guess those are, those are.","index":347,"end_time":1782.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1780.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m spewing a lot of.","index":348,"end_time":1784.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1783.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m all over the place a bit and I''m spewing a lot of stuff.","index":349,"end_time":1785.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1784.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And I''m just kind of helping you guys understand in my mind the universe of like.","index":350,"end_time":1788.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1785.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like there''s some idea here about pooling and organizing and beautifying content, pulling in new content and incorporating that, and hopefully giving something, someone that''s interesting enough, where they feel like we''ve gained credibility and they actually read it.","index":351,"end_time":1803.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1788.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And what we''re competing against is Michael''s manual marketing efforts.","index":352,"end_time":1807.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1803.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We''re not really competing against like, oh, let''s add them to the ABM because they''re interested, or let''s fire off the video we made, you know, 18 months ago.","index":353,"end_time":1814.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1807.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I think that''s.","index":354,"end_time":1818.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1816.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"If I was going to say, why am I skeptical?","index":355,"end_time":1820.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1818.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s like, well, the low volume we have right now of people who''ve shown interest and the effort we put into each one and the lack of results we''re getting from it fuels a lot of the skepticism.","index":356,"end_time":1832.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1820.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I''m not expecting any kind of an explicit response to that, but that''s kind of where my head''s at.","index":357,"end_time":1838.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1833.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I think we''ve also got to think of timeline as well.","index":358,"end_time":1841.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1839.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"This is complex stuff you''re asking of us, you know, so we''ve got it to some degree.","index":359,"end_time":1849.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1841.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But to.","index":360,"end_time":1850.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1849.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"To take this and then produce something.","index":361,"end_time":1854.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1850.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I mean, I''m assuming you go ahead and say they have to, then they''ll sit there and 30 seconds later out spews the result.","index":362,"end_time":1861.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1854.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right?","index":363,"end_time":1861.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1861.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Is that.","index":364,"end_time":1862.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1861.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Is that what you''re thinking?","index":365,"end_time":1863.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1862.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay.","index":366,"end_time":1864.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I don''t know if we could do that.","index":367,"end_time":1867.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1865.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Michael.","index":368,"end_time":1870.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1870.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m not quite following what you mean.","index":369,"end_time":1871.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1870.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m just saying, I mean, to create a Power BI model from what these guys are asking for, I''m assuming it''s quite a bit of work on our end.","index":370,"end_time":1881.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1871.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Well, so to be clear, this is taking what you guys have built as like an MVP in Power BI and rebuilding it in a way that spits this out much faster.","index":371,"end_time":1890.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1881.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, and who''s going to do that?","index":372,"end_time":1893.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So, like Michael, the data tape.","index":373,"end_time":1895.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1893.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And guys, you''ll stop me if I''m wrong.","index":374,"end_time":1896.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1895.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"An example would be all the data tables that we use in Power bi.","index":375,"end_time":1900.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1897.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"The AI can understand what that data means.","index":376,"end_time":1903.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1900.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, oh, this is fill rate data for all of hydrants clients.","index":377,"end_time":1905.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1903.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And it''ll say, here''s a report on like, how the industry has been doing in terms of fill rate for the last 12 months.","index":378,"end_time":1911.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1905.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And here''s where you fall and make it look sexy.","index":379,"end_time":1914.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1911.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, I guess my question was, were we going to do this or no?","index":380,"end_time":1918.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1914.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We would build it.","index":381,"end_time":1919.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1918.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":382,"end_time":1920.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1919.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s my.","index":383,"end_time":1921.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1920.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We would just need the calculations from your guys.","index":384,"end_time":1923.02,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1921.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Power BI model.","index":385,"end_time":1923.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1923.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":386,"end_time":1924.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1924.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay.","index":387,"end_time":1925.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1924.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So I thought we had to build this.","index":388,"end_time":1926.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1925.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":389,"end_time":1928.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1927.21,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re actually in the process right now of even launching A AI is crazy right now, guys.","index":390,"end_time":1937.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1928.65,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I mean, Colin and Tristan, my business partner are.","index":391,"end_time":1940.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1937.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You''ve been interested a bunch of times.","index":392,"end_time":1942.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1940.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"They''re building new tools every weekend.","index":393,"end_time":1946.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1943.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Sometimes at nights, they just send me over things that they''ve created.","index":394,"end_time":1950.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1946.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re actually launching a business unit that''s going to be dedicated specifically to building these types of things for prospective clients.","index":395,"end_time":1958.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1951.3,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we''re putting a huge emphasis and investment internally on being able to build these AI tools.","index":396,"end_time":1964.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1958.74,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So no, Michael, it''s not going to be, hey, build this thing and give it to us when we can use it for our ABM campaign.","index":397,"end_time":1972.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1964.62,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s.","index":398,"end_time":1973.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1972.98,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''re going to build this thing.","index":399,"end_time":1975.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1973.78,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll want your insights.","index":400,"end_time":1976.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1975.63,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll definitely want you to test it and see if it is any good.","index":401,"end_time":1981.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1977.15,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And like, if you were a prospective client, would you have found this useful?","index":402,"end_time":1988.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1982.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Does it have good information?","index":403,"end_time":1989.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1988.59,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But it''s all about the inputs.","index":404,"end_time":1992.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1991.309,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If we can have Good inputs on both sides.","index":405,"end_time":1995.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1992.99,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There''s a lot that AI will be able to do to be able to create something of value above and beyond what has historically been able to be created for a lead magnet.","index":406,"end_time":2007.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1996.35,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, and I''m also thinking about this even more holistically of, you know, Michael, we can capture the information of their form, fill in the results, and also have that automatically added to their contact record in HubSpot.","index":407,"end_time":2022.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2010.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you have a very personalized insight into their numbers to follow up with an email or you''re at a trade show and someone''s asking you some questions, you say, hey, we actually have the scorecard.","index":408,"end_time":2032.16,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2022.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can check out, take a quiz in 90 seconds and boom, you''ve got personalized results right there.","index":409,"end_time":2036.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2032.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s how.","index":410,"end_time":2037.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2037.05,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And just so you guys know, like for the tools that we''re built, like the ones that I showed you the other day, that''s a huge place where I''m using them.","index":411,"end_time":2045.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2037.57,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Like, I''m reaching out to people who have been prospects in the past and we lost deals with.","index":412,"end_time":2051.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2045.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''m like, hey, I just want to let you know, like we built this insights tool where you could see yourself against, you know, these competitors in your space.","index":413,"end_time":2060.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2051.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And if you fill out these five forms and then I get to see who actually engaged with my email and then I can have a follow up conversation.","index":414,"end_time":2067.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2060.5,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So it''s, it''s more.","index":415,"end_time":2068.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2067.38,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I think this goes to some of what you were saying on our last call, Michael, is like.","index":416,"end_time":2073.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2068.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''Re trying.","index":417,"end_time":2075.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2074.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"To pride more than just like, okay, how many form fills do we get?","index":418,"end_time":2079.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2075.38,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We want those, we all want them.","index":419,"end_time":2080.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2079.18,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I don''t want to discount form fills, SQL is your ability to have conversations.","index":420,"end_time":2084.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2080.82,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But also how can we build IP that you can leverage in a variety of ways.","index":421,"end_time":2090.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2085.2,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It feels to me or sounds to me like that has been some of the stuff you''ve had the most success with in working with us.","index":422,"end_time":2099,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2090.48,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so if we can continue to provide you with things while also testing it against prospects and cold leads and we can warm some up, it''s like we can, you know that.","index":423,"end_time":2110.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2099,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I know it''s overused term probably, but that''s where you get your flywheel.","index":424,"end_time":2114.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2110.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"It''s like things are helping in multiple places and being able to be reused.","index":425,"end_time":2119.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2114.05,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Across.","index":426,"end_time":2119.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2119.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"You know, your sales cycle.","index":427,"end_time":2123.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2122.33,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I think an important part of this plan, and I don''t, I don''t want to cut you guys off or jump ahead because this might be part of this, but even if it''s not part of this deck, something I hope we''re focused on is we want to be able to validate really quickly.","index":428,"end_time":2136.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2126.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I would just want to have in my head really clear timelines around, you know, here''s where we get to an mvp, when and how we expect to be at an MVP for three of your trusted clients.","index":429,"end_time":2149.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2137.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And then like, what''s the evidence we require?","index":430,"end_time":2152.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2150.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So is it like they give us feedback and obviously they say this is amazing.","index":431,"end_time":2156.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2152.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I, I read the whole thing and it was great.","index":432,"end_time":2158.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2156.12,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like we can really lean on anecdotal evidence like that as like, hey, this is an investment worth continuing to make.","index":433,"end_time":2164.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2159.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But if we get no response and maybe they give us some feedback about how it could be useful and we spend a month making those fixes and still aren''t getting anything, I think at that point we kind of cut bait.","index":434,"end_time":2175.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2164.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s like, look, we, if we aren''t getting a strong anecdotal response from our existing clients, like maybe that''s a cutoff point for us.","index":435,"end_time":2181.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2175.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And then, okay, great, we got the strong response.","index":436,"end_time":2184.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2181.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We invest more in building the tool out, making it more generalizable and friendlier to random contacts inbound, interacting with it.","index":437,"end_time":2190.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2184.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What''s the next checkpoint?","index":438,"end_time":2193.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2192.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Is it okay, we''re going to run it for a month or two months or three months?","index":439,"end_time":2196.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2193.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And what evidence are we looking for?","index":440,"end_time":2198.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2196.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Are we pouring a little more gas in the ABM or not?","index":441,"end_time":2203.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2198.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Not abm, the ad roll or other sources so that we can actually get more eyeballs on this and get a little more data around how effective it is.","index":442,"end_time":2210.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2203.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, I''d love to, I know that''s not, we can''t, we''re not ready to have those numbers today.","index":443,"end_time":2217.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2210.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But I''d love for us in pretty short order to lay out what that plan looks like so that we''re all just on the same page about like, hey guys, we''re going to continue to make this investment with you and try these tools out.","index":444,"end_time":2226.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2217.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But these are the checkpoints we need to hit.","index":445,"end_time":2228.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2226.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And if we, if we fail, then we have to, we need to go back to a lower level investment.","index":446,"end_time":2234.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2228.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And so one of my hopes is that this is not something we''re going to have to like commit to for the next year before we know if it works.","index":447,"end_time":2242.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2234.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Because that wouldn''t work.","index":448,"end_time":2243.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2242.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":449,"end_time":2244.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2243.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And in today''s day and age, we can''t allow that amount of time to pass because there''s too many signals that are happening to this.","index":450,"end_time":2250.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2244.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And just to your point, the first signal is when we build this MVP and we give it to some current clients if they''re not finding any use of it.","index":451,"end_time":2256.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2250.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All Right.","index":452,"end_time":2256.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2256.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We need to go to the next offer that we can build, get in front of them, see if they''re interested.","index":453,"end_time":2260.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2256.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we run into like five of these, we''re not attacking the whiteboard in the lab in the best way that we should.","index":454,"end_time":2266.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2260.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need, we need more insights.","index":455,"end_time":2268.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2266.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t feel like we''re going to be in that direction.","index":456,"end_time":2270.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2268.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yes, having that understanding of where it could go possibly is important.","index":457,"end_time":2274.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2271.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And to answer your question of like, timeline and how all this comes together and where we''re making decisions and what data we need to collect, it all goes into a very large, comprehensive ABM plan document.","index":458,"end_time":2285.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2275.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We kind of changed how we wrote them.","index":459,"end_time":2286.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2285.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it is, who are we talking to?","index":460,"end_time":2288.38,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2286.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are we talking to them?","index":461,"end_time":2289.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2288.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are we saying to them?","index":462,"end_time":2290.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2289.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are they doing?","index":463,"end_time":2291.7,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2290.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are our timelines?","index":464,"end_time":2292.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2291.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are next steps?","index":465,"end_time":2293.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2292.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are you guys supposed to do?","index":466,"end_time":2294.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2293.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What are we doing?","index":467,"end_time":2295.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2294.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of that is clearly laid out with a table of contents, so you can jump into that as a source of truth and at any point.","index":468,"end_time":2300.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2295.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":469,"end_time":2302.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2302.31,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":470,"end_time":2303.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2303.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"To make maybe my, my ask a little more explicit for the first stage, let''s make sure we are focused on.","index":471,"end_time":2310.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2304.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"These are materials for an internal audience where we have 100% read rate and 100%, like we''re going to have, we might have.","index":472,"end_time":2318.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2310.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Have a call with you guys.","index":473,"end_time":2319.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2318.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We will certainly have a call with them ourselves to go through feedback.","index":474,"end_time":2322.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2319.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So, like, we''re going to get, we''re going to get eyeballs and we''re going to get feedback.","index":475,"end_time":2327.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2322.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Whereas a lot of the times, I mean, like, we start a marketing initiative and it''s like you put it out in the wild and you try and infer how it''s landing based on how numbers change.","index":476,"end_time":2335.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2327.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I think at least as a first step for us, it is qualitative.","index":477,"end_time":2338.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2335.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And yeah, we will get the feedback.","index":478,"end_time":2340.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2338.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like there is no question.","index":479,"end_time":2341.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2340.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Even if it''s total dog people, our clients will look at it.","index":480,"end_time":2346.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2341.589,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I mean, they like us enough that they''ll put the time into really digesting it and telling us why it''s dog or why they love it.","index":481,"end_time":2352.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2346.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":482,"end_time":2353.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2352.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And that''s our validation point.","index":483,"end_time":2354.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2353.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of the things, the key things there is when we certainly are doing validation is, you know, we need to ask more sort of pointed questions.","index":484,"end_time":2362.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2354.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Why would you not even consider looking at this?","index":485,"end_time":2364.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2362.53,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, what made you want to look at these sorts of things?","index":486,"end_time":2367.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2364.85,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because I think that''s, that''s one of the big important mystery is that I would love to see why are people not clicking and filling things in?","index":487,"end_time":2375.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2367.73,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I give you a Perfect example.","index":488,"end_time":2377.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2375.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I was looking through some of the data Bailey gave me on survey results from the newsletter.","index":489,"end_time":2382.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2377.21,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"121 people clicked.","index":490,"end_time":2385.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2383.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I think this is what it said to me.","index":491,"end_time":2387.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2385.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Clicked on the link in our newsletter that went to the survey, but no bugger went ahead and then filled it in.","index":492,"end_time":2395.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2387.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So the mindset is like.","index":493,"end_time":2396.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2395.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And we talked about this, I''m using earlier on, what the hell, you know, why would you click on it, suddenly be surprised?","index":494,"end_time":2402.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2396.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s a survey you got to do, you know what I mean?","index":495,"end_time":2404.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2402.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"There''s this real disconnect that I cannot get my head around.","index":496,"end_time":2407.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2404.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Why?","index":497,"end_time":2407.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2407.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I see great evidence.","index":498,"end_time":2409.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2408.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I see the most simplest of bloody surveys.","index":499,"end_time":2412.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2410.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, that takes you 60 seconds to go ahead and fill out is not difficult.","index":500,"end_time":2416.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2412.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I only got seven responses, you know, and two of them are people that we know really well from clients.","index":501,"end_time":2422.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2417.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And, you know, two were like, what the hell are you even filling this in for?","index":502,"end_time":2426,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2423.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I don''t even know why you''re on the list.","index":503,"end_time":2427.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2426,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, those things that do my head in.","index":504,"end_time":2431.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2428.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I would love to find ways that we measure and adapt change so we can have all the best tools in the world.","index":505,"end_time":2439.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2431.4,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I think we have been, but we haven''t been able to go ahead and get the conversions to where they need to be.","index":506,"end_time":2444.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2439.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And so I think, if anything else, I would love to have more.","index":507,"end_time":2450.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2445.41,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay, guys, our client A, B and C is in this industry.","index":508,"end_time":2455.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2451.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We think it''s a proxy to yours.","index":509,"end_time":2459.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2456.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"This has worked.","index":510,"end_time":2461.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2460.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay.","index":511,"end_time":2462.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2461.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And this is how it''s worked.","index":512,"end_time":2463.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2462.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I would love to see, you know, if that''s the sort of things that would help us hone the messaging, hone the approach and get those results up.","index":513,"end_time":2475.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2465.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"That I think is a bigger part that we''d love to see more of in 2026.","index":514,"end_time":2480.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2475.14,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, more testing iterations, more variations.","index":515,"end_time":2483.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2481.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s all very important.","index":516,"end_time":2485.62,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2484.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, totally hear you guys.","index":517,"end_time":2488.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2487.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":518,"end_time":2490.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2489.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I want to be cognizant of everyone''s time as well.","index":519,"end_time":2491.84,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2490.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The second one, I''ll be honest, I''m a little nervous to talk about because I don''t know how much you guys want to give away your secret sauce.","index":520,"end_time":2498.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2491.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is a fine balance that we''ll need to walk in this playbook.","index":521,"end_time":2501.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2498.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what the prospects would be getting here is a tailored action plan for their biggest inventory challenge built by you guys as the experts.","index":522,"end_time":2509.36,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2502.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they would submit a message field of what their top challenge is and then their current inventory estimate, fill rate targets, SKU counts, lead times, growth plans, team capacity.","index":523,"end_time":2518.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2509.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This would be a multi page playbook that we would Generate and it would take, it would basically take a lot of data that we''re putting in as one of like imperial what we can truthfully provide, but also as an analysis and training the AI model to analyze quick data based on how you guys do.","index":524,"end_time":2537.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2519.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, you guys.","index":525,"end_time":2539.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2538.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh, you had mentioned that when you showed us the lead time analysis.","index":526,"end_time":2542.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2539.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if we could imagine that we take that and build it into a tool where someone puts in their situation and it''s not just like here are five tips, but it''s like, hey, based on 2500 SKUs, $5 million in inventory investment, a 65% fill rate.","index":527,"end_time":2554.959,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2542.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Here''s your exact bottleneck that you''re running into and here''s three steps of what you should do to reduce your inventory by X and improve fill rate to.","index":528,"end_time":2563.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2554.959,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":529,"end_time":2568.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2563.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"My concern is not about giving the secret sauce because I''m happy to take.","index":530,"end_time":2572.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2568.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m not worried about someone go ahead and building my business based on anything I share and you know, one page.","index":531,"end_time":2576.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2572.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I think the concern is that it will read like it''s an ebook.","index":532,"end_time":2580.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2577.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So we have to figure out how we get away from that mental model customers will have.","index":533,"end_time":2585.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2580.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"If you say, give me some information, I''m going to give you the playbook, they''re thinking you''re giving me a PDF that maybe like, you know, has.","index":534,"end_time":2593.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2585.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Has a find and replace for my inventory investment that I put in.","index":535,"end_time":2597.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2593.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I want to make sure that we have a way to prevent that.","index":536,"end_time":2600.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2597.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m wondering too is like, should that just be a part of offer one?","index":537,"end_time":2604.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2600.69,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s like could be.","index":538,"end_time":2606.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2605.09,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Here is where you, here''s the industry, here''s you, here''s like if they''re beating the industry, like here''s where top performers are.","index":539,"end_time":2613.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2606.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What are the differences?","index":540,"end_time":2614.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2613.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What are the steps that companies take?","index":541,"end_time":2615.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2614.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And honestly the steps they take as we''re giving away the secret.","index":542,"end_time":2620.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2616.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s all, it''s our, it''s our engagement letter.","index":543,"end_time":2623.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2620.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Right?","index":544,"end_time":2623.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2623.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s what we do for clients and we can make it very passive, like, hey, it doesn''t matter who you do this with.","index":545,"end_time":2629.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2623.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Obviously we do these things, but this is the, these are the activities you need to do.","index":546,"end_time":2632.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2629.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I think that''s good content.","index":547,"end_time":2634.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2633.34,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It feels very close to kind of the stuff we''ve done today because all the content we produced is sort of that like how do you eliminate stock outs without growing your inventory?","index":548,"end_time":2644.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2634.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like that''s, that''s a playbook and it doesn''t on it.","index":549,"end_time":2647.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2644.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It doesn''t really change based on client or business.","index":550,"end_time":2650.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2647.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s all the same playbook, right?","index":551,"end_time":2652.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2651.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"The details change.","index":552,"end_time":2653.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2652.95,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like how I actually do it changes, but how I explain what I''m doing is pretty much the same.","index":553,"end_time":2658.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2653.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So those are my immediate reactions.","index":554,"end_time":2661.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2659.23,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I just want to jump in.","index":555,"end_time":2665.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2664.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I. I quite like this.","index":556,"end_time":2667.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2665.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And the reason I like this is, is that if it would even get us, and I''m totally spectacular, even get us to shortcut the assessment.","index":557,"end_time":2678.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2667.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I know, Josh, you don''t like that, but imagine it.","index":558,"end_time":2680.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2678.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Did you know, how much quicker would we actually be able to get to the point where we would think, actually that''s pretty good data?","index":559,"end_time":2687.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2680.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And we know the firm, we know the model.","index":560,"end_time":2690.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2688.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s very similar to two or three other firms.","index":561,"end_time":2695.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2692.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I could do a punt and think it''s going to be this, you know, and we could just say we think it''s going to be 12 grand and we''ll do the following for one year.","index":562,"end_time":2704.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2695.97,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"What do you think if they go, actually, that''s really quite interesting.","index":563,"end_time":2709.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2705.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then we could say, well, why don''t we validate this a little bit more?","index":564,"end_time":2712.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2709.49,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then we could just probably grab some data and make sure that, you know, we''re close enough.","index":565,"end_time":2718.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2713.01,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But we can give them something really powerful in the beginning to hopefully get them interested in what we have to say and get them to understand how the model actually works.","index":566,"end_time":2729.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2719.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because it''s not just consulting with tools.","index":567,"end_time":2733.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2729.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And it sort of irons out some of the things that we constantly struggle for people to understand as well.","index":568,"end_time":2739.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2733.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I would say it now, one of the things that we''ve been speaking about internally is sort of doing some brainstorming things about what are the sort of key challenges that we''re helping with.","index":569,"end_time":2749.493,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2739.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Cloud the client right now, that''s fairly unusual.","index":570,"end_time":2751.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2749.493,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We could quickly write a case study on that and then we would post that because that''s one of the things that we haven''t been able to do as much.","index":571,"end_time":2758.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2752.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And the last thing I wrote was four posts for LinkedIn.","index":572,"end_time":2762.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2758.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We wrote two articles for the website, and that was last year, at the end of last year.","index":573,"end_time":2770.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2763.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I do struggle trying to think what else to write.","index":574,"end_time":2774.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2770.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So, again, my point is that we can provide probably more anecdotal insights from these case study things that may feed into this sort of tool as well, that may help.","index":575,"end_time":2785.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2775.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Here''s an example of blank.","index":576,"end_time":2788.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2786.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We did it for this firm and everyone loves that we did a case study and this is what we did, and here''s the result.","index":577,"end_time":2794.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2788.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And it matches very much what your problem is.","index":578,"end_time":2797.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2794.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And we were able to do it in blank number of times in months.","index":579,"end_time":2801.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2797.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And is this interesting?","index":580,"end_time":2803.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2801.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, so that''s that personalization as well, which is something that Josh mentions and I totally agree with.","index":581,"end_time":2809.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2803.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You can try and personalize this more.","index":582,"end_time":2811.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2809.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Try and feed in different sort of cases even if we have to make one up on the spot, which isn''t difficult to go ahead and do, you know, we can, we can try to feed it more into this to make it more real time, you know and again we do want to speak to them.","index":583,"end_time":2826.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2811.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"There''s no two ways about it.","index":584,"end_time":2827.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2826.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, there''s is like they''re not buying a box that then slots in and the license begins.","index":585,"end_time":2832.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2827.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know, they.","index":586,"end_time":2833.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2832.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s serious stuff.","index":587,"end_time":2835.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2833.96,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But right get it getting them at least Got.","index":588,"end_time":2837.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2835.2,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"This is really interesting.","index":589,"end_time":2838.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2837.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I quite like how you''re thinking about these things.","index":590,"end_time":2840.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2838.36,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And the key here is that we have to differentiate ourselves from number one, a consultant and number two, another bolt on tool that says it, you know, it can make tea for you as well, solve your problems.","index":591,"end_time":2855.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2841,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We need to be clear that, you know, there is a big difference to what we do and why it''s better than the other two.","index":592,"end_time":2862.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2856.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":593,"end_time":2863.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2863.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Why it''s not consultant or software.","index":594,"end_time":2865.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2863.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s the best of both.","index":595,"end_time":2867.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2865.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":596,"end_time":2868.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2867.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right.","index":597,"end_time":2868.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2868.02,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"You know.","index":598,"end_time":2868.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2868.22,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":599,"end_time":2870.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2870.139,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":600,"end_time":2870.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2870.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Josh, one thing to something you mentioned earlier of maybe this is a bolt on to one.","index":601,"end_time":2875.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2870.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s often how these sort of flow is.","index":602,"end_time":2878.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2876.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like we have these ones that we stand up and then it''s like okay, well what if we kind of combined these elements into a new offer and repackage and we test how that performs and then we have a new AB champion that we stand up as well.","index":603,"end_time":2888.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2878.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we do constantly like tweak and iterate how these are going.","index":604,"end_time":2891.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2888.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":605,"end_time":2892.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2892.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Really quick.","index":606,"end_time":2894.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2894.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I know we have, we have 10 minutes left.","index":607,"end_time":2896.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2894.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Unfortunately I at least have a hard stop at 230 Central.","index":608,"end_time":2900.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2896.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So.","index":609,"end_time":2900.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2900.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":610,"end_time":2902.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2900.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"On this note, like these are ideas.","index":611,"end_time":2905.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2903.63,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They would be refined.","index":612,"end_time":2907.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2906.03,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin came to me and was like Justin, I want to put some just I''ve got ideas of things I would want to do.","index":613,"end_time":2912.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2907.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They''re not exact ideas but I just want to show them like where my thought process is.","index":614,"end_time":2918.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2912.92,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And so that these are here.","index":615,"end_time":2919.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2918.44,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They''re not finalized.","index":616,"end_time":2921.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2920.2,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They''re things we would iterate and work through.","index":617,"end_time":2923.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2921.56,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So yeah Colin, you can keep going.","index":618,"end_time":2925.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2923.72,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I don''t think there''s too much more in here.","index":619,"end_time":2926.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2925.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''re almost there.","index":620,"end_time":2928.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2927.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, really quick.","index":621,"end_time":2929.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2928.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I just want to throw in like I think the main things that are open because this is, this is interesting to us.","index":622,"end_time":2933.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2929.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"You know, we want to keep exploring this.","index":623,"end_time":2934.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2933.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It would really be kind of like how hard would it be to get some type of a prototype of the capabilities or an example of the capabilities of the system you''re talking about.","index":624,"end_time":2942.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2935.79,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I know.","index":625,"end_time":2943.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2943.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Justin, during our last call, you were kind of trying to get us to generate something and you showed us a quick screen share you a call and did.","index":626,"end_time":2949.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2943.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"If we could see sort of a final version of that and understanding that it''s using really rudimentary, like early days kind of inputs.","index":627,"end_time":2956.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2950.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But if we can just get a better sense for the capability, it''s.","index":628,"end_time":2960.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2957.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, here.","index":629,"end_time":2961.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2960.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Oh, just.","index":630,"end_time":2962.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2961.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think he''s talking about building a prototype for.","index":631,"end_time":2963.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2962.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For that.","index":632,"end_time":2964.08,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2963.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like the thing that we''re talking about here.","index":633,"end_time":2965.48,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2964.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, no.","index":634,"end_time":2966.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2965.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Well, the thing you wrote last week.","index":635,"end_time":2969.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2966.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That I just wants to see what.","index":636,"end_time":2970.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2969.04,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, here.","index":637,"end_time":2971.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2971.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"If it''s possible to get that.","index":638,"end_time":2973.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2972.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, I don''t know if that''s a PDF or something we can look at.","index":639,"end_time":2977.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2973.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"No, here''s Exports PDF.","index":640,"end_time":2979.6,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2978.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Go, go, go play.","index":641,"end_time":2981.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2979.6,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Go play around yourself.","index":642,"end_time":2982.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2981.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There''s three tools right there.","index":643,"end_time":2983.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2982.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I just sent it in the chat.","index":644,"end_time":2985.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2983.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Oh, great, cool.","index":645,"end_time":2986.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2985.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And then the next thing would be helping us understand obviously like what''s.","index":646,"end_time":2991.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2986.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"How much is this going to cost and what are.","index":647,"end_time":2994.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2991.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What are very rough timelines around kind of some of the milestones we''ve been talking about that you guys feel are plausible.","index":648,"end_time":2999.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2994.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve got all of that.","index":649,"end_time":3001.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2999.74,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll kick over to Bailey to take on there.","index":650,"end_time":3004.3,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3001.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, let me just share my screen.","index":651,"end_time":3008.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3005.98,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So like Justin mentioned before, we''re flexible wherever you want to land with this.","index":652,"end_time":3015.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3010.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we have kind of two options that we could go about it is option one just kind of staying status quo where.","index":653,"end_time":3021.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3015.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Where we''ve been mostly for the last couple months, so continuing to manage that survey that we''re working on, doing your monthly newsletter, the social content, managing your website, HubSpot, things like that, and then having in some room for flexibility of whether that that''s ad hoc design, some video content or supporting with paid media.","index":654,"end_time":3043.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3022.17,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like there''s.","index":655,"end_time":3044.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3043.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I mean, we do points so, you know, it''s always flexible a little bit where we can plug in with a couple things.","index":656,"end_time":3048.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3044.05,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that lands at $5,000 for 65 points.","index":657,"end_time":3052.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3049.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So we still want to gift you some points every month.","index":658,"end_time":3055.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3052.81,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that would be gifted like 15 points a month so that we can keep doing things there.","index":659,"end_time":3060.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3055.53,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then our other option is to go a more strategic approach which would be doing that custom interactive tool like Colin and Justin have been talking about, getting all the messaging for the outreach sequence, nailing down an ABM plan, deciding what verticals we''re going to go in, deciding if we''re going to start off with your current clients, and when we''re going to roll that out to everyone else and getting some new image ads and your list created.","index":660,"end_time":3087.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3061.21,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So that would be 7,500 for 100 points.","index":661,"end_time":3091.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3088.02,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So you do get a bit more gifted in this option.","index":662,"end_time":3094.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3091.38,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So 25 gifted points.","index":663,"end_time":3095.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3094.44,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we can keep doing everything else and the other option as well.","index":664,"end_time":3099.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3095.96,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Got it.","index":665,"end_time":3102.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3101.76,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So then the new capabilities we''ve been talking about are a $2,500 premium is kind of how I think about it and come with other support as well.","index":666,"end_time":3109.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3102.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Okay.","index":667,"end_time":3110.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3110.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s.","index":668,"end_time":3111.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3110.88,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s correct.","index":669,"end_time":3111.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3111.4,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And I mean, it''s a $2,500 premium.","index":670,"end_time":3115.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3111.96,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"While also, if you hadn''t been clients for as long as you have, and we''ve been through all sorts of things together, probably out of the box net, new client, it''s like 10 grand.","index":671,"end_time":3127.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3116.24,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re like, hey, look, I know we''ve talked about everything under the sun over the last four years.","index":672,"end_time":3135.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3128.57,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Whatever it''s been, you know, there''s a lot of trust built there.","index":673,"end_time":3139.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3135.53,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"There''s a lot of, hey, I''ve seen you guys do things that didn''t necessarily work.","index":674,"end_time":3142.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3139.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I''ve done things that we really like.","index":675,"end_time":3144.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3142.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we built in a little bit of.","index":676,"end_time":3146.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3144.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"A little bit of a buffer there.","index":677,"end_time":3147.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3146.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So that was.","index":678,"end_time":3148.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3148.01,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That was my conversation with Bailey.","index":679,"end_time":3150.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3149.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We want to find something that works, and we''re willing to keep taking swings.","index":680,"end_time":3154.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3151.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So those were some of my.","index":681,"end_time":3157.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3155.05,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"My thoughts on the pricing.","index":682,"end_time":3158.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3157.13,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Colin and Bailey put together the two options, and I think there is a points plan.","index":683,"end_time":3162.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3158.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You don''t need to pull that up, Bailey, but it''s in here.","index":684,"end_time":3165.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3163.05,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll send this over.","index":685,"end_time":3166.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3165.29,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The longer that I think there is.","index":686,"end_time":3167.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3166.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The points plan might be helpful to show you timelines for things.","index":687,"end_time":3172.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":3168.89,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s exactly what I was going to say.","index":688,"end_time":3173.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3172.01,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So there''s timelines in there, but we can move pretty quick.","index":689,"end_time":3175.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3173.49,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And, you know, if in three months or whatever it is, or six months, you''re like, look, we''re just not seeing the results that we would have hoped, then we can go back to the other approach as well.","index":690,"end_time":3188.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3175.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So we''re.","index":691,"end_time":3189.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3188.37,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''re willing to be flexible here, but we wouldn''t be doing our job in the way that we see it if we didn''t continue to take swings and try and help our clients grow.","index":692,"end_time":3199.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3189.89,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Cool.","index":693,"end_time":3202.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3202.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":694,"end_time":3205.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3204.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I think maybe, like, what I''d like to do is play around with some of the AI tools on your end.","index":695,"end_time":3213.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3205.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"If it''s possible to get, you know, and if it''s in the points plan, maybe just sharing the points plan.","index":696,"end_time":3217.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3213.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"But I, I think given what we''ve talked about, maybe there would be some adjustments there or just clarifying what happens when.","index":697,"end_time":3223.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3217.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"In terms of, like, here''s, you know, in month one, here''s kind of what we need from you.","index":698,"end_time":3228.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3223.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Here''s what we want to have at the end in month two, we present it to three clients, and we get feedback and we incorporate.","index":699,"end_time":3235.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3229.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Kind of walk us through that.","index":700,"end_time":3236.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3235.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That process in terms of, like, actual points.","index":701,"end_time":3242.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3237.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I definitely, you know, I appreciate you guys are willing to be flexible and gift points and all that kind of stuff.","index":702,"end_time":3247.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3243.29,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, my, My preference, if it''s possible, is for us never to talk about points and for you just to tell us, hey, guys, we are.","index":703,"end_time":3255.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3248.01,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We.","index":704,"end_time":3256.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3255.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We have room to do more work, so let us know.","index":705,"end_time":3259.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3256.1,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And hey, guys, we''ve gone over points several, you know, a number of months in a row.","index":706,"end_time":3263.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3259.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We.","index":707,"end_time":3264.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3263.86,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We have to pull back.","index":708,"end_time":3265.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3264.22,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We need to either change a timeline or move activities, but otherwise, we just don''t talk about points because, like, you know, our point reports have kind of become meaningless to me.","index":709,"end_time":3273.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3265.14,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And I. I think the overhead we both spend thinking about it is not.","index":710,"end_time":3276.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3273.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I know you have to manage them internally, but the overhead we both spend thinking about, like, how to categorize and justify points is not worth it.","index":711,"end_time":3282.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3276.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"It''s just, look, we.","index":712,"end_time":3283.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3282.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We have.","index":713,"end_time":3284.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3283.85,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We trust each other in this partnership, and we''re going to let one another know if we''re.","index":714,"end_time":3288.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3284.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"The demands are not.","index":715,"end_time":3289.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3288.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Are too high or we''re not getting what we were expecting or something like that.","index":716,"end_time":3292.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3289.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So I''m less concerned about the accounting part of it.","index":717,"end_time":3296.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3292.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And so.","index":718,"end_time":3297.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3296.77,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"So the simple thing here is, last year, when times were tough, tariffs hit.","index":719,"end_time":3303.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3297.49,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We went from four, that we went from 7,000 or 7, 500, one of the two down to 4,000, but we still delivered at that same clip.","index":720,"end_time":3311.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3303.65,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, like, to increase that.","index":721,"end_time":3314.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3312.26,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That was the conversation we had.","index":722,"end_time":3315.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3314.06,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"The amendment that was signed, it actually said that we would renegotiate that at the end of December, but I didn''t feel we were ready to do that yet.","index":723,"end_time":3322.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3315.46,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"December, holidays, everything, that''s where we are today.","index":724,"end_time":3325.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3322.1,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So there''s two options.","index":725,"end_time":3327.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3325.7,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Option one, leave points out of it.","index":726,"end_time":3329.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3327.7,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"You don''t need to look at a points plan.","index":727,"end_time":3331.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3329.98,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We could probably put together some sort of Gantt chart or something.","index":728,"end_time":3333.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3331.42,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We want to stand this up in one month, essentially.","index":729,"end_time":3336.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3334.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So that would be February and get.","index":730,"end_time":3341.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3337.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Getting this rolling out in March or not.","index":731,"end_time":3343.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3341.08,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"But either way, it''s either $5,000 to do the list of items that we have.","index":732,"end_time":3348.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3343.16,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No, I''m totally clear.","index":733,"end_time":3349.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3348.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"70.","index":734,"end_time":3349.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3349.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"We''re totally clear.","index":735,"end_time":3350.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3349.959,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":736,"end_time":3351.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3351,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I just mean, like.","index":737,"end_time":3352.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3351.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, if we''re.","index":738,"end_time":3353.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3353,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I just meant from month to month as we go forward.","index":739,"end_time":3356.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3353.68,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Like, understanding where we are on points is like.","index":740,"end_time":3358.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3356.28,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Is something you guys can keep internal.","index":741,"end_time":3360.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3359.24,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Stop talking to him about points, Bailey.","index":742,"end_time":3362.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3360.72,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No, I bring it up all the time.","index":743,"end_time":3366.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3363.56,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s how.","index":744,"end_time":3366.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3366.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"That''s how we have to know how points are being.","index":745,"end_time":3369.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3366.96,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"How our clients are being accounted for.","index":746,"end_time":3371.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3369.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Note taken.","index":747,"end_time":3372.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3371.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''ll put some stuff together for you.","index":748,"end_time":3374.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3372.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Go ahead.","index":749,"end_time":3375.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3374.64,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, go, Josh.","index":750,"end_time":3376.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3375.12,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No, that.","index":751,"end_time":3376.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3376.32,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That''s.","index":752,"end_time":3377.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3376.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"That''s what I care about is.","index":753,"end_time":3377.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3377.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I''m sorry, Michael.","index":754,"end_time":3378.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3377.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I thought he meant.","index":755,"end_time":3379.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3378.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Go ahead, Josh.","index":756,"end_time":3379.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3379.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"I was just saying all I.","index":757,"end_time":3380.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3379.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"All I care about right now is, like, what''s the.","index":758,"end_time":3381.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3380.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"What are the activities for each party and the timeline to look at some of these new tools and validate if they work.","index":759,"end_time":3386.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3381.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"And what I lean towards, though, Michael and I need to talk about it is like, we''re comfortable making that larger investment, and, you know, as long as we''re hitting those milestones and keep getting positive feedback on it and then eventually positive results, it''s a no brainer to keep it going.","index":760,"end_time":3400.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3386.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Otherwise, we would drop back down.","index":761,"end_time":3401.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3400.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":762,"end_time":3403.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3402.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Michael, I''m sorry, what were you gonna say?","index":763,"end_time":3404.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3403.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"No, what?","index":764,"end_time":3404.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3404.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I was just gonna say, Justin, to your point.","index":765,"end_time":3406.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3404.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And Bailey.","index":766,"end_time":3407.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3406.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Bailey does not go on about points.","index":767,"end_time":3409.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3407.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"She''s very, very generous to us.","index":768,"end_time":3411.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3409.39,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"She manages us incredibly well.","index":769,"end_time":3413.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3411.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I would say, you know, quite often when I go ahead and just come back with 10,000 different variations on things that I''ve asked for.","index":770,"end_time":3420.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3414.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Very patient with us.","index":771,"end_time":3421.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3420.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So please just.","index":772,"end_time":3423.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3422.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We understand the point system, and I understand where Josh is coming from as well.","index":773,"end_time":3427.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3424.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We.","index":774,"end_time":3427.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3427.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We get it.","index":775,"end_time":3428.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3427.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Very generous to us.","index":776,"end_time":3429.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3428.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So.","index":777,"end_time":3431.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3431.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s.","index":778,"end_time":3432.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3431.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''re not sort of.","index":779,"end_time":3433.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3432.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''re not that point obsessed.","index":780,"end_time":3436.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3433.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":781,"end_time":3437.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3436.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No worries.","index":782,"end_time":3437.72,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":3437.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I was just making a joke.","index":783,"end_time":3438.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3437.72,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Bailey does a great job.","index":784,"end_time":3440.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3438.72,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":785,"end_time":3441.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3441.24,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"We''ll send some stuff over to you, Bailey.","index":786,"end_time":3443.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3441.84,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Just follow up with, like, some general timelines for them, and then.","index":787,"end_time":3447.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3443.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, if you guys want to get going, just let us know.","index":788,"end_time":3450.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3447.96,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I would like to know sooner than which approach, because I do want to move off.","index":789,"end_time":3456.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3451.32,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"If possible, I would like to void the February invoice and put it to whatever the new dollar figure is, whether that''s 5 or 7,500, just let me know.","index":790,"end_time":3470.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3457.96,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And then, as you know, even though we''re not talking points, you will get the value that is built into the new price.","index":791,"end_time":3478.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3470.76,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Great.","index":792,"end_time":3480.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3480.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":793,"end_time":3482.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3481.54,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"By the end of the week, we''ll have an answer.","index":794,"end_time":3485.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3483.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Beautiful.","index":795,"end_time":3486.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3485.94,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":796,"end_time":3487.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3486.98,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":797,"end_time":3487.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":3487.42,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":798,"end_time":3488.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3487.94,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"},{"text":"Great talking by.","index":799,"end_time":3490.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3488.5,"speaker_name":"Josh Bartel"}],"dateString":"2026-02-04T19:30:00.000Z","host_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86822728812?pwd=A25BRQGhApDxbMdfQBrT4Bmlnb11eq.1","participants":["josh@hydrian.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,michael.jones@hydrian.com,taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,justin.brown@marketersindemand.com","josh@hydrian.com","michael.jones@hydrian.com","taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","justin.brown@marketersindemand.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KG33X396XS98CSPAAJBYFPN8","organizer_email":"baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Aligned on 35k net new MRR goal and clarified how marketing supports broader objectives.","Proposed two lead generation offers leveraging prior Power BI insights and AI-based tools.","Michael advised 25 SQLs as realistic versus 50; consensus formed around shared ownership.","Team committed to fast prototyping, client validation, and pivoting if engagement proves low.","New $7.5k/month plan includes ABM, creative tooling, and increased collaboration flexibility."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I would say 25 is more real than 50 in my view.","speaker":"Michael Jones"},{"quote":"We want to put our name on some numbers here in 2026.","speaker":"Justin Brown"},{"quote":"We''re comfortable making that larger investment... as long as we''re hitting those milestones.","speaker":"Josh Bartel"}],"topics":["delivery","strategy","goals","abm","attribution"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-07T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Marketing Goals and Pipeline Targets**\n\nThe team aligned on a **target of 50 sales-qualified leads (SQLs)** to support **$35,000 in net new monthly recurring revenue (MRR)** by year-end, recognizing this as an ambitious but critical benchmark for marketing impact (07:07).  \n- The SQL target is based on historical conversion rates of around **9% from marketing SQLs to opportunities** and a **27% win rate** on opportunities, with average deal sizes near **$10,000 to $12,000** and a **sales cycle of 137 days**.  \n- **Michael Jones** expressed skepticism due to the lack of precedent but suggested a more conservative interim goal of **25 SQLs** as a realistic milestone, maintaining alignment on the overarching **$35,000 MRR** target as a total business goal regardless of lead source (09:04).  \n- The group agreed marketing efforts would complement existing channels like trade shows, which are expected to generate **2 to 3 opportunities per event across four conferences** this year (09:54).  \n- **Justin Brown** emphasized the partnership mindset: marketing and sales are jointly responsible for the revenue goal, with flexibility in attribution and a focus on driving **more inbound engagement** rather than rigidly tracking channel-specific lead counts (13:00).  \n- The team agreed that **increasing inbound interest and direct contact from prospects** is a key success metric, reflecting a shift from purely tactical deliverables to strategic, metric-driven marketing (14:23).  \n\n## **New Marketing Infrastructure and Data Integration**\n\nA new **automated system powered by N8N and Supabase** was introduced to capture and analyze multi-channel engagement signals, enabling more personalized and timely outreach based on richer data (18:00).  \n- This system integrates tools like **Clay for data enrichment**, **Smartlead for outbound emails**, and **Bombora intent data** to identify warm prospects and trigger personalized follow-up actions via email or Slack alerts (18:52).  \n- The database captures all prospect interactions, allowing the team to segment and tailor offers, for example, creating **custom landing pages for interested accounts like M Supply** (18:52).  \n- **Justin Brown** highlighted the need to calibrate which signals warrant adding contacts into HubSpot to balance workload with sales bandwidth, emphasizing form fills as essential but also recognizing value in other engagement signals (19:51).  \n- The system aims to provide **more precise intent data at a fraction of the cost of expensive platforms like Hockey Stack**, enabling the team to act faster and avoid waiting for traditional form fills (23:00).  \n- The integration automatically updates contact records with detailed activity history, preserving marketing contact billing efficiency while improving sales visibility (24:42).  \n\n## **Innovative Offer Concepts and Validation Strategy**\n\nTwo key offer concepts were proposed to break through historically low engagement and form fill rates, emphasizing personalized, data-driven tools built on Hydrant’s proprietary data (25:28).  \n- The **Supply Chain Performance Scorecard** would let prospects benchmark their supply chain performance against peers in under five minutes, showing personalized risks and estimated costs of inefficiencies, leveraging AI to package and generate relevant insights (25:28).  \n    - **Josh Bartel** recommended piloting this with trusted existing clients first to gather qualitative feedback and validate its value before broader rollout (27:06).  \n    - Josh also stressed that for marketing content to be effective, it must surpass current manual outreach efforts in credibility and relevance, noting AI-generated content must feel genuinely personalized to succeed (28:25).  \n- The second offer is a **Tailored Inventory Action Plan**, an AI-driven multi-page playbook offering detailed, client-specific recommendations based on inputs like SKU counts, fill rates, and growth plans (42:10).  \n    - The team discussed balancing transparency with protecting Hydrant’s unique expertise, aiming to avoid generic “ebook” style content by emphasizing a dynamic, personalized approach (42:43).  \n    - **Michael Jones** liked the potential for this tool to shortcut assessments and accelerate sales conversations by giving prospects compelling data early (44:24).  \n    - Both offers could be combined or iterated upon to create an evolving ABM playbook with continuous testing and refinement (47:50).  \n- The group agreed on a clear **validation cadence**, focusing first on internal qualitative feedback from existing clients as a litmus test to justify further investment and scaling (35:22).  \n- **Josh Bartel** called for defined checkpoints with timelines and success criteria to avoid long-term commitments without measurable results, advocating for rapid MVP development and iterative testing (35:19).  \n- The team committed to incorporating **client feedback** to refine messaging and content, with a focus on understanding why prospects do or do not engage, addressing the current disconnect seen in low form fill rates (39:13).  \n\n## **Pricing, Engagement Models, and Timelines**\n\nTwo engagement options were presented:  \n- A **status quo plan** at **$5,000 per month** offering ongoing management of surveys, newsletters, social content, website, and HubSpot with some flexibility for ad hoc work (50:05).  \n- A **strategic plan** at **$7,500 per month** adding the custom interactive tool, ABM planning, messaging development, and new ad creation, including more gifted points for additional work (51:28).  \n- The **$2,500 premium** for the strategic plan reflects the investment in new AI-enabled tools and enhanced support (51:42).  \n- **Justin Brown** reassured Hydrant that the agency is willing to be flexible on scope and pricing, with options to adjust based on early results and client feedback (52:52).  \n- **Josh Bartel** requested clearer timelines and deliverables tied to the points plan, emphasizing a desire to focus on outcome-driven milestones rather than monthly point accounting (53:24).  \n- The team agreed to move away from detailed points discussions for internal management, trusting each other to communicate when workloads or expectations need adjustment (54:40).  \n- The goal is to stand up the new tools within **one month**, aiming for rollout in **March**, with a commitment to reassess after **3 to 6 months** based on campaign performance and client feedback (55:48).  \n- A final decision on the engagement approach was expected by **end of the week** to align billing and project kickoff (57:58).  \n\n## **Strategic Alignment and Partnership Philosophy**\n\nThe discussion underscored a shift from purely tactical marketing deliverables to a **strategic, metrics-focused partnership** aimed at generating measurable business growth (14:23).  \n- The agency positions itself as a **value-add partner** committed to pushing boundaries and taking calculated risks with Hydrant to unlock new inbound opportunities (15:28).  \n- Both sides recognize the importance of **building intellectual property** that can be reused across sales and marketing efforts, creating a “flywheel” effect to warm leads and shorten sales cycles (34:00).  \n- **Michael Jones** stressed the need to differentiate Hydrant from traditional consultants and generic software by emphasizing the hybrid, personalized nature of their offering (47:43).  \n- The team agreed on the importance of **iterative testing and learning**, with a culture of rapid feedback loops and willingness to pivot based on what works, avoiding long investments in unproven approaches (37:24).  \n- Transparency and trust were emphasized as key to managing expectations and adjusting tactics without getting bogged down in administrative overhead like point tracking (54:36).  \n- This alignment aims to sustain Hydrant’s growth by combining marketing innovation, sales expertise, and data-driven insights into a cohesive growth engine.","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","AI-driven tools","Sales Qualified Leads","Supply Chain Performance Scorecard","Marketing Automation","HubSpot Integration"],"overview":"- **Sales Targets:** Aim for 50 SQLs to achieve $35,000 in new MRR by year-end, recognizing historical conversion rates.  \n- **Marketing Collaboration:** Emphasis on unified marketing and sales efforts driving inbound engagement instead of tracking specific lead counts.  \n- **New Data System:** Automated system introduced for enhanced prospect engagement and personalized outreach, integrating various data tools.  \n- **Innovative Offers:** Proposed Supply Chain Performance Scorecard and Tailored Inventory Action Plan for personalized client insights and quicker sales.  \n- **Engagement Pricing:** Two plans presented, ranging from $5,000 to $7,500, with a focus on value and flexibility based on results.  \n- **Strategic Partnership:** Shift towards a metrics-driven approach, emphasizing iterative feedback, transparency, and building distinctive intellectual property.","action_items":"\n**Michael Jones**\nProvide calculations and Power BI data to Marketers in Demand for AI tool build (31:59)\nWork with team to calibrate criteria for which lead signals should be passed into HubSpot for sales follow-up (22:13)\nCollaborate on designing pointed questions for lead engagement surveys and analyze reasons for low conversion (39:00)\nProvide case studies and anecdotal insights for marketing collateral and AI model content feeding (44:24)\n\n**Josh Bartel**\nEvaluate AI-generated Supply Chain Performance Scorecard and Action Plan offers with trusted clients; gather qualitative feedback (27:00)\nTest and provide feedback on prototype AI tools from Marketers in Demand (48:23)\nCoordinate with Michael on investment decisions based on meeting MVP milestones and validating results (56:00)\n\n**Justin Brown**\nLead development of AI-driven marketing tools and integrate data and models from Hydrian (31:54)\nPrepare and send detailed project timelines and milestone plans for MVP and implementation to Hydrian (57:17)\nManage points plan internally but reduce complexity in client communication (53:22)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nDesign and oversee technical implementation of automation engine (N8N), data enrichment, and lead routing system integrating HubSpot and Supabase (18:00)\nBuild out and iterate ABM plan documents specifying target segments, messaging, offers, timelines, responsibilities (37:36)\nCollaborate with Justin and Hydrian to build MVP AI Scorecard prototype and subsequent product iterations (25:28)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nPresent and manage pricing and points options, coordinate monthly deliverables (50:05)\nSupport client account management with flexibility on scope and adapt deliverables (54:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"2eac287f-66d1-485e-981f-b81c5ad9002f","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
