    '{"id":"01KG5GV92RC4N4VR3PEQX51VJ0","title":"GSS // MID Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Content Strategy**\n\nThe current podcast guest booking approach is proving ineffective and needs a broader content focus to increase engagement.\n\n- **Nick S highlighted low guest interest and red tape as key barriers, with many prospects declining due to past repeated conversations and perceived relevance issues** (00:34)  \n    - Most potential guests have already shared their stories with Nick, reducing fresh content appeal  \n    - The podcast title, *The Financial Advantage*, narrows guest topics too tightly, limiting outreach success  \n    - Nick plans to expand guest profiles to include broader restaurant and hospitality perspectives, such as a VP of development, to widen appeal  \n    - This pivot aims to generate more diverse content and reengage potential guests by focusing on broader restaurant growth beyond just financial topics  \n\n- **Baylee suggested reconsidering the format by shifting from a guest podcast to a video interview series to increase content volume and SEO value** (02:54)  \n    - Video content provides more discovery opportunities and builds trust faster than guest podcasts in the current market  \n    - This change would reduce the heavy resource burden of guest booking while maintaining audience engagement  \n    - She emphasized the continued need for consistent content production to support marketing and brand presence  \n    - The team agreed to explore rebranding the podcast to a broader restaurant growth theme to better align content with audience interests  \n\n## **Target Audience Segmentation for Campaigns**\n\nClarifying client segmentation based on company size is crucial for effective targeting of CFO versus accounting services.\n\n- **Will Fleming clarified that CFO services fit smaller companies with between 10 and 50 units, while accounting services target larger operators** (08:12)  \n    - Smaller companies can be candidates for both CFO and accounting services, but larger companies usually only need accounting support  \n    - Examples included Ben’s Chili Bowl (smaller) as a CFO client and Flynn Restaurant Group (very large) only needing accounting services  \n    - Nick and Will agreed this segmentation improves targeting accuracy and resource allocation  \n    - Guilllesantana confirmed they will rebuild the CFO services list focusing on smaller operators accordingly  \n\n- **This refined segmentation will help avoid wasted outreach efforts on unsuitable leads and improve campaign conversion rates by focusing messages to the right audience** (17:21)  \n    - Top 200 companies list will be dedicated to accounting services outreach  \n    - CFO service campaigns will focus exclusively on companies with fewer than 50 units  \n    - Clear delineation supports better list building, messaging customization, and follow-up efficiency  \n    - Will emphasized the importance of audience accuracy to maximize campaign ROI and relevance  \n\n## **Benchmarking Tool Development**\n\nBuilding a financial benchmarking tool will enhance lead engagement and provide personalized data-driven conversations.\n\n- **Guillesantana proposed creating an AI-powered benchmarking calculator, similar to a prior Club tool, to offer users comparative financial snapshots based on input data** (10:50)  \n    - The tool would request data fields such as number of locations, EBITDA margin, and labor costs from users  \n    - Will offered to provide a simplified matrix with three business concept categories: full service, fast casual/QSR, and a third option to adjust labor and cost benchmarks accordingly  \n    - Baylee demonstrated an internal version with backend automation providing customized reports to support Nick’s follow-up conversations  \n    - Delivering this tool quickly after finalizing input fields will help launch the CFO service campaign with a strong value add  \n\n- **This benchmarking approach is expected to increase engagement by offering tangible insights that prompt prospects to discuss their financial performance with Nick** (14:15)  \n    - The tool’s outputs will drive personalized follow-ups highlighting specific opportunities or concerns  \n    - It helps differentiate offerings by providing actionable, data-backed insights rather than generic pitches  \n    - Early versions will be shared by Will and the team for feedback and refinement within a day or two  \n    - This initiative aligns with the broader strategy to deepen prospect relationships and accelerate lead qualification  \n\n## **Campaign Execution and Content Assets**\n\nThe accounting services campaign is ready to launch imminently, supported by new content assets and tracking infrastructure.\n\n- **Guillesantana reported the accounting services list now contains 358 qualified contacts after removing three requested names, and the outreach sequence is finalized for immediate launch** (06:50)  \n    - The team expects to start sending the sequence as soon as post-meeting reviews are complete to avoid delays  \n    - The CFO services list will be rebuilt focusing on larger clients for accounting, and smaller clients for CFO services, reflecting clarified segmentation  \n    - Baylee confirmed the accounting campaign launch target is within the next one to two days after sequence approval  \n    - Guilllesantana will share all assets and sequences via email for quick team review  \n\n- **A new landing page for the Cache Playbook ebook is live on the website with integrated tracking and a HubSpot list capturing 15 newsletter click-throughs** (14:41)  \n    - Social media assets (5-6 pieces) have been created to promote the playbook on GSS and personal accounts  \n    - Nick plans to bookmark the playbook on the corporate LinkedIn page and create a post to drive traffic  \n    - Guilllesantana will provide ongoing reports identifying visitors and engaged prospects for targeted follow-up  \n    - This content serves as a top-of-funnel engagement tool to nurture prospects and build brand visibility  \n\n## **Content Production and Thought Leadership**\n\nOngoing content development focuses on thought leadership around outsourced accounting to build credibility and support campaigns.\n\n- **Guillesantana shared progress on two upcoming blog posts derived from a recent interview with Will, centered on outsourcing accounting without losing quality** (16:50)  \n    - These posts aim to educate prospects on the benefits and safeguards of outsourcing finance functions  \n    - Content will reinforce GSS’s expertise and build trust with target audiences before direct outreach  \n    - Will approved the approach and emphasized the importance of aligning content with audience needs  \n    - This content pipeline supports the broader strategy of multi-touch engagement across formats and channels  \n\n- **The team agreed this mix of ebook, blog posts, and personalized outreach will create a layered marketing funnel driving higher quality leads and better conversion rates** (17:13)  \n    - Coordinated messaging across assets ensures prospects receive consistent, reinforcing information  \n    - Thought leadership content establishes GSS as a trusted advisor in the marketplace  \n    - This strategy also aids SEO, social proof, and long-term brand strength  \n    - Ongoing content development remains a priority to maintain momentum and audience engagement","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Strategy","Accounting Services Campaign","CFO Services Targeting","Financial Benchmarking Tool","Cash Playbook Ebook","Restaurant Industry Marketing"],"overview":"- **Podcast Strategy Needs Change:** Ineffective guest bookings require broader topics to attract diverse content and engage potential guests.  \n- **Video Interviews Proposed:** Shifting to video series could enhance content volume and audience trust, boosting SEO value.  \n- **Client Segmentation Clarified:** CFO services target smaller companies (10-50 units), while accounting serves larger operators for better outreach.  \n- **Financial Benchmarking Tool Development:** AI-powered tool to offer users financial comparisons, enhancing engagement and follow-up conversations.  \n- **Accounting Campaign Launch Ready:** 358 qualified contacts prepared for outreach, with new assets supporting the imminent campaign launch.  \n- **Content Production for Thought Leadership:** Ongoing blogs and ebooks will establish credibility, enhance SEO, and drive higher-quality leads.","action_items":"\n**Nick Stauff**\nFollow up casually with newsletter clickers to engage interested prospects (16:24)\nPost and bookmark the cash playbook ebook link on the corporate LinkedIn page (16:24)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nProvide a matrix of financial input data (concept types, labor and food costs, EBITDA margin) to support building the benchmarking tool, aiming to send within one or two days (14:00)\nConfirm CFO and accounting services prospect segmentation to guide marketing lists (17:21)\n\n**Guilles Santana**\nSend the finalized accounting services contact list (358 contacts) and accompanying outreach sequence for review immediately after the meeting (07:18)\nRebuild CFO prospect list focusing on smaller operators (under 50 units) based on clarifications from Will and Nick (07:50)\nDeliver final marketing email sequences for both accounting and CFO services campaigns promptly for launch (14:00)\nEmail all materials including social media graphics, ebook landing page link, and list of newsletter clickers for prospect follow-up (16:10)\nProvide spreadsheet data of visitors who have viewed the cash playbook landing page (15:50)\nSend follow-up blog post drafts based on recent interview for review (17:07)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nReassess podcast content strategy and guest booking approach to potentially broaden topics or explore video content alternatives for better engagement (02:54)\nShare prototype of the benchmarking survey and report tool and assist with design improvements to fit financial data needs (13:00)\nCoordinate with Guilles on campaign launches and input collection to accelerate rollout of both accounting and CFO service campaigns (14:15)\n"},"duration":18.780000686645508,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"id":1,"name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"id":2,"name":"guillesantana"},{"id":3,"name":"Will Fleming"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Morning.","index":0,"end_time":6.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":6.32,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Hey, what''s up, Nick?","index":1,"end_time":8.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":7.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"How are you?","index":2,"end_time":9.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.2,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":3,"end_time":10.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.72,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Not much here.","index":4,"end_time":12.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.28,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Nice.","index":5,"end_time":13.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, doing great here.","index":6,"end_time":15.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.92,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Good.","index":7,"end_time":17.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.8,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"How is the podcast guest stuff been going?","index":8,"end_time":33.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":27.85,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Not good.","index":9,"end_time":35.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":34.73,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah?","index":10,"end_time":36.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":35.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":11,"end_time":37.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":37.05,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"I haven''t seen an episode in a minute.","index":12,"end_time":39.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":37.37,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":40.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.09,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I mean, I''ve asked a couple people here or there, and I don''t know if the whole podcast genre is just overplayed or it''s timing of the year.","index":14,"end_time":49.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.65,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Just feels like most people are not interested.","index":15,"end_time":53.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":50.73,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":54.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":53.81,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And I mean, I''ve hit, like, some teams and they''re like, oh, let me put you in touch with the public relations team.","index":17,"end_time":63.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.97,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then I''m like, wait, they have a public relations team?","index":18,"end_time":67.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":64.45,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, you own, like, 12 restaurants.","index":19,"end_time":69.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":67.65,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m like, what?","index":20,"end_time":69.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.25,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"That''s crazy.","index":21,"end_time":70.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Wow.","index":22,"end_time":71.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":70.81,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then.","index":23,"end_time":72.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.13,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then they email me back.","index":24,"end_time":73.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":72.69,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m like, great.","index":25,"end_time":74.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.77,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And they''re like, hey, send me, you know, the link to the.","index":26,"end_time":76.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.25,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"The podcast.","index":27,"end_time":77.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":76.41,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"We''ll take a look to see if it''s a fit.","index":28,"end_time":78.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.17,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then, you know, they probably look at, like, the popularity of it, and they''re like, no, we''re good.","index":29,"end_time":83.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":79.82,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So, I don''t know.","index":30,"end_time":88.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I.","index":31,"end_time":88.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":88.22,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Too much red tape.","index":32,"end_time":90.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.26,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s like, I feel like it''s not that deep to have a conversation sometimes, but.","index":33,"end_time":97.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":91.18,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":99.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":98.94,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And it''s like, the thing is, is most of the people that I''ve.","index":35,"end_time":103.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":99.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I had in mind, I''ve already had these, you know, these conversations with, you know, like, I''m most intrigued of, you know, tell me your origin story.","index":36,"end_time":114.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.98,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Tell me some of the roadblocks you encountered and how you overcame them.","index":37,"end_time":119.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":115.48,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You know, give me some pros, some cons.","index":38,"end_time":122.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":119.72,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"What was your life before this?","index":39,"end_time":124.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":123.08,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"What''s your life now?","index":40,"end_time":125.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":124.48,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"What''s it gonna be?","index":41,"end_time":126.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":125.4,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You know, just what are some tips, trades, you know, those kind of things, things that I''m interested in.","index":42,"end_time":132.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.92,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then, you know, obviously we can plug our stuff and whatever it be.","index":43,"end_time":139.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":133.41,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But I''ve had those conversations with most of the people I''ve talked to.","index":44,"end_time":142.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.05,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, those are.","index":45,"end_time":144.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.49,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"That''s just how I generally am.","index":46,"end_time":145.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.17,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, I''m very interested in building relationships.","index":47,"end_time":149.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":145.89,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And so it''s like, hey, would you like to get on this podcast and kind of go over what we''ve been talking about for two years?","index":48,"end_time":158.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.73,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And there''s what.","index":49,"end_time":159.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":158.53,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You already talked about it.","index":50,"end_time":161.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":162.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":162.42,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, what, what, what?","index":52,"end_time":164.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And it''d be, you know, so I get.","index":53,"end_time":166.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":164.9,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I think I get a lot of, like, people thinking that way too.","index":54,"end_time":169.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.42,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And they''re just like, nah, we''re good.","index":55,"end_time":171.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.3,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":56,"end_time":173.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":172.66,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But.","index":57,"end_time":173.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":173.22,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Well, it''s something.","index":58,"end_time":175.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.82,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I don''t know, we can maybe look at, like, readdressing or, like, reassessing the strategy there because, I mean, if it''s so hard to get people booked on this show, we could take maybe a different route and look at maybe just a video series.","index":59,"end_time":194.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, we already are doing so many interviews with Will.","index":60,"end_time":197.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":194.91,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I do think video content is so valuable when it comes to, like, people discovering you and building trust.","index":61,"end_time":205.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":197.79,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And also helps with SEO to have just extra, like, multimedia assets.","index":62,"end_time":214.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":206.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So, yeah.","index":63,"end_time":216.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":215.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, if I feel like it''s not.","index":64,"end_time":220.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Not working with booking guests, we can look at a different direction to go because we still need content.","index":65,"end_time":226.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like, we still need stuff.","index":66,"end_time":227.359,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But maybe getting guests on a podcast is more work than it''s worth.","index":67,"end_time":234.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":227.359,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And maybe I''m just narrowing it, like, the.","index":68,"end_time":237.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.76,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"The topic too much, I guess, and I''m not reaching out to too many people.","index":69,"end_time":242.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.77,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s like, it''s called the Financial Advantage.","index":70,"end_time":245.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.05,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So you''re, you know, and I''m like, I''ve got to try to figure out how to spin it towards that, the name of the podcast.","index":71,"end_time":253.969,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.13,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, how can we talk a little bit about finances and, you know, financial services a little bit.","index":72,"end_time":262.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.37,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And maybe I''m just kind of pigeonhole myself and not broadening it up a little bit.","index":73,"end_time":271.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":263.82,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You know, it''s like, yeah, I''m starting to think of, like, some other people in the business that I''ve, you know, develop relationships with.","index":74,"end_time":278.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":271.02,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"For instance, like a VP of development for a brand that might be a good guy.","index":75,"end_time":284.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.46,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, I call him up and be like, you know, tell me.","index":76,"end_time":287.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.14,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Tell me, like, your story.","index":77,"end_time":289.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":287.42,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"What do you do, you know, and give me some stories of some great, you know, franchise teams and what are you looking for?","index":78,"end_time":295.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":289.54,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And financially speaking, what are you looking for?","index":79,"end_time":298.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.46,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And, you know, what do you guys need?","index":80,"end_time":301.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And that might be a good one.","index":81,"end_time":303.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.42,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''ve got a few of those guys I know really well.","index":82,"end_time":305.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":303.5,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":306.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":306.3,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And they would probably love to get on a podcast and, you know, pitch their brand, too.","index":84,"end_time":310.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":85,"end_time":311.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.1,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Just be like, yeah, let''s talk about my brand and how great it is.","index":86,"end_time":314.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.5,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And that''s a good idea.","index":87,"end_time":316.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":314.66,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m going to call my buddy Austin.","index":88,"end_time":318.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.84,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":89,"end_time":319.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.04,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We can look at rebranding the show a little bit, and maybe it''s more about just like, growing your restaurant, because obviously financials play into that.","index":90,"end_time":328.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.4,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"But there''s the brand element, like you mentioned, and other people you could talk about.","index":91,"end_time":332.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.08,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And it''s just.","index":92,"end_time":332.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.2,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You''re looking at any way you can support a restaurant to grow.","index":93,"end_time":336.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.36,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":94,"end_time":339.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":339.6,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I''m thinking, like, make it more of a broad title.","index":95,"end_time":344.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.92,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Like, you know, like, I don''t know.","index":96,"end_time":347.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.18,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m thinking.","index":97,"end_time":347.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":347.02,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And we could just talk just.","index":98,"end_time":349.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":347.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Cause you Said you want content.","index":99,"end_time":350.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So, like, just talking hospitality and talking restaurant is always good.","index":100,"end_time":356.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.98,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":101,"end_time":357.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":356.58,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"You know, obviously, when it comes to accounting and financial services.","index":102,"end_time":361.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, that perks my ears up even more.","index":103,"end_time":363.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But just talking about it is.","index":104,"end_time":366.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.46,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Is good.","index":105,"end_time":368.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.7,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"And that''ll develop content.","index":106,"end_time":369.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And you never know what you''re going to pull out of that.","index":107,"end_time":371.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.46,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":108,"end_time":374.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.26,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Because there''s still.","index":109,"end_time":375.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":374.62,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I mean, there''s so many people around.","index":110,"end_time":376.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But anyways.","index":111,"end_time":378.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.1,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"All right, I think Will''s here.","index":112,"end_time":381.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":378.86,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I''m not sure.","index":113,"end_time":382.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.38,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":114,"end_time":382.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":382.26,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Hey, Will, how are you doing?","index":115,"end_time":384.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.14,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Hi, how are you?","index":116,"end_time":386.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":385.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, doing great.","index":117,"end_time":388.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.54,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"It''s been a good week so far.","index":118,"end_time":391.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.46,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Well, Guy, do you want to share your screen and we can just get into it?","index":119,"end_time":398.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.47,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yep.","index":120,"end_time":400.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":399.87,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Wait, hold on a second.","index":121,"end_time":402.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":401.31,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Is it Guy or guy Gay?","index":122,"end_time":404.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.43,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So I say it, right?","index":123,"end_time":407.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.27,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Guy.","index":124,"end_time":407.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.23,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Right?","index":125,"end_time":407.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.59,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":126,"end_time":409.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.11,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":127,"end_time":409.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.27,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"All right.","index":128,"end_time":410.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.79,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":129,"end_time":410.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":410.43,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"All right, let''s get into it.","index":130,"end_time":413.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.79,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"So first things first.","index":131,"end_time":415.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":414.19,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"The updates on the IBM campaign.","index":132,"end_time":417.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.27,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"We send you the accounting services list.","index":133,"end_time":422.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":419.67,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"We removed the three names that you requested.","index":134,"end_time":425.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.55,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"The list now has 358 contacts.","index":135,"end_time":428.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":425.75,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"That''s a lot of contacts that we can reach out to.","index":136,"end_time":432.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":428.75,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"And we also finished the sequence.","index":137,"end_time":436.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.71,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"I will send it out when we''re done with this meeting.","index":138,"end_time":439.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":436.63,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"You guys can review it and give us your thoughts and we can just get it running asap, because I know you guys want to have something running right now so that we don''t delay anything.","index":139,"end_time":456.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.63,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"So the accounting services one that''s ready.","index":140,"end_time":460.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.84,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"And then for the CFO services list, we actually use the 200 companies list to build a lookalike audiences.","index":141,"end_time":471.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.8,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"But I think you said that we need to rebuild it, focusing on larger operators.","index":142,"end_time":478.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.16,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"So we''re doing that.","index":143,"end_time":479.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.08,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"We''re rebuilding the whole list, focusing on bigger clients so that it reflects more like what we want to do with CFO services.","index":144,"end_time":490.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.52,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Hold on a second.","index":145,"end_time":493.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":492.32,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So just so it''s clear, like, the bigger the company you go, the less of a fit it is for CFO services.","index":146,"end_time":501.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":493.44,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So the smaller companies, like between 10 and 50 are going to be the candidates for CFO.","index":147,"end_time":510.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":502.48,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The bigger ones are going to be candidates for the accounting.","index":148,"end_time":515.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":510.92,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean, the smaller ones can be a candidate for both, but typically as you move up in size, they''re not going to hire us to be their CFO.","index":149,"end_time":524.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":515.08,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"That''s.","index":150,"end_time":525.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":525.22,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"It''s 30.","index":151,"end_time":526.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":525.94,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":152,"end_time":529.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":528.74,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I don''t know if that was clear in my email.","index":153,"end_time":530.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":529.06,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So you kind of have them like the one you have right now for accounting.","index":154,"end_time":535.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":530.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Those companies are smaller.","index":155,"end_time":537.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":536.18,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They can be accounting and.","index":156,"end_time":539.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":537.74,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Or cfo.","index":157,"end_time":540.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":539.22,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"The bigger one is only going to be accounting.","index":158,"end_time":543.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":541.14,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Would you agree, Nick?","index":159,"end_time":544.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":543.46,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I totally agree.","index":160,"end_time":546.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.46,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yep.","index":161,"end_time":546.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.22,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":162,"end_time":548.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":547.54,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Okay.","index":163,"end_time":549.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.5,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"I Think that''s something we were a little confused on then.","index":164,"end_time":551.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.06,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So.","index":165,"end_time":551.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.42,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So yeah, because that company, in fact in the smaller company list you had Ben''s Chili bowl, they used to be a CFO customer and an accounting customer.","index":166,"end_time":560.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":551.83,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So that''s, I mean if you something to Flynn Restaurant Group, I mean they have more than 100,000 restaurants.","index":167,"end_time":572.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":561.91,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"They have a very high powered CFO.","index":168,"end_time":575.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":573.03,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"There''s no way they''re going to hire us.","index":169,"end_time":576.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":575.27,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean maybe they''ll give us a little piece of one of their divisions or something on the accounting.","index":170,"end_time":582.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":576.87,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean we, they would certainly fall in that accounting group.","index":171,"end_time":586.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":583.36,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But when we talk about top 200 and we talk about like Nick''s got a Prospect right now, 100 plus Popeyes, we''re talking to them exclusively about accounting and we''re talking to the cfo.","index":172,"end_time":600.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":586.64,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Got it, got it, got it.","index":173,"end_time":604.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.24,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"We''ll use that number to build to reveal the list then.","index":174,"end_time":608.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.52,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"That''s more clear now.","index":175,"end_time":610.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":609.67,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"And then for the sequence.","index":176,"end_time":614.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.11,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"In the sequence we mentioned the financial benchmark and we were, Bailey and I were thinking like how could we do this?","index":177,"end_time":622.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":614.55,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Maybe it''s a PDF, maybe it''s a calculator, I don''t know.","index":178,"end_time":626.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":622.51,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"We thought we could do like the benchmarking.","index":179,"end_time":629.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":626.71,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"We can build it with AI very easily.","index":180,"end_time":631.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":629.75,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Sort of like a calculator or like a. Yeah like a snapshot tool that you can use to compare yourself.","index":181,"end_time":639.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.27,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"We would just need your input on which data fields we could use to build it because this is something we built with club and you could input like number of locations, EBITDA margin, labor cost etc, etc.","index":182,"end_time":660.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.35,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"But maybe you guys have a better input on what we could ask people for and if you provide the data.","index":183,"end_time":668.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.32,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"So let me ask you, let me ask you a question.","index":184,"end_time":670.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":668.84,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Like who, who provides the results?","index":185,"end_time":672.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":670.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"This fellow.","index":186,"end_time":674.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":673.84,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Do you call Claude or do we have to provide that?","index":187,"end_time":677.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":674.72,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So if we could have data from like five customers that will be enough to like provide to do the benchmarking and that will calculate it.","index":188,"end_time":690.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.04,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":189,"end_time":692.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":692.16,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So I could give you a matrix.","index":190,"end_time":694.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":692.64,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So we''re going to have to ask what kind of concept it is because the labor costs for like a full service business versus the labor cost for you know, a kiosk Oscar or, or even a QSR that has limited seats is going to be different.","index":191,"end_time":711.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":694.4,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So but I can provide some high level cogs and labor and we''ll have to have maybe like three choices like full service, fast casual, slash QSR and then maybe something else.","index":192,"end_time":736.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":712,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I will have to think about that.","index":193,"end_time":738.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":736.62,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think fast casual and QSR more or less are the Same.","index":194,"end_time":743.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":739.5,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I mean their food input is not the same, but yeah, but I can try to simplify that.","index":195,"end_time":751.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":744.3,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"So there''s really only.","index":196,"end_time":753.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":751.9,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Should only probably be three different scenarios and yeah, I can help you with that.","index":197,"end_time":762.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":753.1,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"We can have like are you service or.","index":198,"end_time":765.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.22,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re going to have to ask what kind of concept it is.","index":199,"end_time":769.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":766.7,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But there are only.","index":200,"end_time":770.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":769.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"There shouldn''t be that many choices.","index":201,"end_time":772.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":770.66,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"There should be just three.","index":202,"end_time":773.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":772.06,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Right.","index":203,"end_time":774.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.24,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Is it okay if I share my screen really quick?","index":204,"end_time":777.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.6,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Gu.","index":205,"end_time":778,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":777.68,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Yeah, I think she had some links there on the screen, but I just wanted to show you like what this could look like.","index":206,"end_time":785.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":778.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"We''re doing this internally for ourselves right now.","index":207,"end_time":787.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.12,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So essentially we''d have a couple fields kind of like what Gay had on the screen, but we can design it out a little bit nicer.","index":208,"end_time":794.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.32,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So whatever fields you feel like would make the most sense.","index":209,"end_time":797.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":794.8,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then we have like all this back on back end automation to give them some sort of results based on what, what you send over to us.","index":210,"end_time":809.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.73,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And this will obviously be customized to you cause this, this stuff isn''t super relevant to, to what you''re doing but essentially it can like output some really nice like data and comparisons and things like that.","index":211,"end_time":823.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.65,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And it really just sets Nick up really well to follow up and be like, oh hey, I saw this in the report.","index":212,"end_time":830.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.93,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Like do you want to talk about that a little bit?","index":213,"end_time":832.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.57,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So it''s a great way to start a conversation with people once we get a little bit of information.","index":214,"end_time":838.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":833.13,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, if you include that in your email I can either today or tomorrow.","index":215,"end_time":846.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":840.09,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Hopefully today.","index":216,"end_time":847.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":846.49,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"It''s a little busy this afternoon, but get that back to you.","index":217,"end_time":851.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":847.37,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right.","index":218,"end_time":854.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.35,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"And I think the goal with that too kind of already mentioned is we can get the accounting services launched really quickly.","index":219,"end_time":861.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.23,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"So probably within the next day or two if the sequence looks all good to go.","index":220,"end_time":866.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.87,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"And then just once we get your inputs on that survey, we can get the CFO services one launched pretty quickly after that.","index":221,"end_time":873.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":866.71,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Okay.","index":222,"end_time":874.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":874.11,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right.","index":223,"end_time":878.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.72,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Then next for the cache playbook that we, the ebook that we built, we created a landing page on your website.","index":224,"end_time":892.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":881.56,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"I will send this over but it looks really good and you get to download this to download the playbook.","index":225,"end_time":903.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.36,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"We also designed like 5, 6 pieces for social media that you guys can use to like share on your personal social media.","index":226,"end_time":914.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":904.7,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"On GSS''s social media put the link so we can get people to visit the link.","index":227,"end_time":923.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.86,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Once RB2B is set, we will get to see who''s visiting that page and I will, we''ll send you guys like a spreadsheet of who has like seen The.","index":228,"end_time":939.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.94,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"The Playbook page.","index":229,"end_time":941.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":939.99,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"And just so you know, on the newsletter, we got 15 clicks, people that clicked on Download the ebook.","index":230,"end_time":950.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":942.23,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"I created a list on HubSpot so that you guys can see who''s more interested.","index":231,"end_time":956.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":951.59,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"We had a few clicks from your employees, like three or four.","index":232,"end_time":960.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":956.47,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"But the others are, like, people that may be interested more in your services.","index":233,"end_time":967.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":960.65,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":234,"end_time":970.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.85,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And I will send all of this in an email today.","index":235,"end_time":973.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":970.65,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"So you have the graphics, the link, and the list to see who clicked on the newsletter.","index":236,"end_time":982.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":973.37,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":237,"end_time":984.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.25,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I follow up on that newsletter myself, personally, too.","index":238,"end_time":987.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":985.21,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"I go in there and look, and I don''t build a list, but I just casually follow up with them.","index":239,"end_time":992.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.97,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"But then what I intend to do with that Playbook is I''m going to put that as, like, a bookmark on our corporate LinkedIn page, and then I''ll make a post about it, too.","index":240,"end_time":1004.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":993.46,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"So I''ll do that once you send that over.","index":241,"end_time":1006.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.22,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"And then for upcoming content, we had an interview with Will.","index":242,"end_time":1016.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1010.74,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"I forgot to capitalize it last week, and we''re developing two blog posts on it on outsourcing accounting without sacrificing.","index":243,"end_time":1027.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1017.01,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":244,"end_time":1028.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1027.77,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"But that''s pretty much it from us.","index":245,"end_time":1033.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1029.01,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":246,"end_time":1034.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1033.65,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Looks good to me.","index":247,"end_time":1037.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1036.13,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"All right, I will send everything over.","index":248,"end_time":1040.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1038.61,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Okay.","index":249,"end_time":1042.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1041.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah, so just.","index":250,"end_time":1043.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1042.54,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Just.","index":251,"end_time":1044.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1043.98,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"I think it''s really important to have the audience on the lists.","index":252,"end_time":1048.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1044.38,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Right?","index":253,"end_time":1049.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1048.78,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":254,"end_time":1049.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1049.26,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"So just to be clear, the top 200 are accountant accounting services, and the CFO is.","index":255,"end_time":1056.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1049.82,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Is going to be anybody below 50 units.","index":256,"end_time":1060.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1057.42,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Got it?","index":257,"end_time":1062.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1061.66,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":258,"end_time":1063.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.18,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"Okay.","index":259,"end_time":1069.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.03,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"All right.","index":260,"end_time":1071.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1070.79,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":261,"end_time":1073.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1072.63,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"Have a good day, buddy.","index":262,"end_time":1075.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1073.83,"speaker_name":"Nick S (GSS)"},{"text":"You, too.","index":263,"end_time":1075.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1075.19,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Bye.","index":264,"end_time":1076.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1075.71,"speaker_name":"Will Fleming"},{"text":"See you.","index":265,"end_time":1076.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1076.15,"speaker_name":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"text":"Bye.","index":266,"end_time":1077.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1076.87,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"}],"dateString":"2026-02-04T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83236942727?pwd=NaLGKm3JEGM6umJeSVS9pHPmDfNAYN.1","participants":["baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nstauff@gsslp.com,wfleming@gsslp.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","nstauff@gsslp.com","wfleming@gsslp.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KG5GV92RC4N4VR3PEQX51VJ0","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Nick acknowledged guest booking challenges and proposed broadening podcast scope to attract more participants.","Baylee recommended pivoting to a video series to streamline content creation and boost SEO visibility.","Guille confirmed accounting campaign assets are ready and will launch immediately after internal review.","Will clarified audience segmentation: CFO services target <50 units; larger groups fit accounting only.","Playbook assets and tracking tools completed; 15 clicks recorded, with follow-up planned via LinkedIn and email."],"highlights":[{"quote":"we can look at rebranding the show a little bit, and maybe it''s more about just like, growing your restaurant","speaker":"Baylee Gunnell"},{"quote":"top 200 are accountant accounting services, and the CFO is going to be anybody below 50 units","speaker":"Will Fleming"},{"quote":"I follow up on that newsletter myself, personally, too","speaker":"Nick S (GSS)"}],"topics":["content","strategy","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-vision","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-07T21:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Podcast Content Strategy**\n\nThe current podcast guest booking approach is proving ineffective and needs a broader content focus to increase engagement.\n\n- **Nick S highlighted low guest interest and red tape as key barriers, with many prospects declining due to past repeated conversations and perceived relevance issues** (00:34)  \n    - Most potential guests have already shared their stories with Nick, reducing fresh content appeal  \n    - The podcast title, *The Financial Advantage*, narrows guest topics too tightly, limiting outreach success  \n    - Nick plans to expand guest profiles to include broader restaurant and hospitality perspectives, such as a VP of development, to widen appeal  \n    - This pivot aims to generate more diverse content and reengage potential guests by focusing on broader restaurant growth beyond just financial topics  \n\n- **Baylee suggested reconsidering the format by shifting from a guest podcast to a video interview series to increase content volume and SEO value** (02:54)  \n    - Video content provides more discovery opportunities and builds trust faster than guest podcasts in the current market  \n    - This change would reduce the heavy resource burden of guest booking while maintaining audience engagement  \n    - She emphasized the continued need for consistent content production to support marketing and brand presence  \n    - The team agreed to explore rebranding the podcast to a broader restaurant growth theme to better align content with audience interests  \n\n## **Target Audience Segmentation for Campaigns**\n\nClarifying client segmentation based on company size is crucial for effective targeting of CFO versus accounting services.\n\n- **Will Fleming clarified that CFO services fit smaller companies with between 10 and 50 units, while accounting services target larger operators** (08:12)  \n    - Smaller companies can be candidates for both CFO and accounting services, but larger companies usually only need accounting support  \n    - Examples included Ben’s Chili Bowl (smaller) as a CFO client and Flynn Restaurant Group (very large) only needing accounting services  \n    - Nick and Will agreed this segmentation improves targeting accuracy and resource allocation  \n    - Guilllesantana confirmed they will rebuild the CFO services list focusing on smaller operators accordingly  \n\n- **This refined segmentation will help avoid wasted outreach efforts on unsuitable leads and improve campaign conversion rates by focusing messages to the right audience** (17:21)  \n    - Top 200 companies list will be dedicated to accounting services outreach  \n    - CFO service campaigns will focus exclusively on companies with fewer than 50 units  \n    - Clear delineation supports better list building, messaging customization, and follow-up efficiency  \n    - Will emphasized the importance of audience accuracy to maximize campaign ROI and relevance  \n\n## **Benchmarking Tool Development**\n\nBuilding a financial benchmarking tool will enhance lead engagement and provide personalized data-driven conversations.\n\n- **Guillesantana proposed creating an AI-powered benchmarking calculator, similar to a prior Club tool, to offer users comparative financial snapshots based on input data** (10:50)  \n    - The tool would request data fields such as number of locations, EBITDA margin, and labor costs from users  \n    - Will offered to provide a simplified matrix with three business concept categories: full service, fast casual/QSR, and a third option to adjust labor and cost benchmarks accordingly  \n    - Baylee demonstrated an internal version with backend automation providing customized reports to support Nick’s follow-up conversations  \n    - Delivering this tool quickly after finalizing input fields will help launch the CFO service campaign with a strong value add  \n\n- **This benchmarking approach is expected to increase engagement by offering tangible insights that prompt prospects to discuss their financial performance with Nick** (14:15)  \n    - The tool’s outputs will drive personalized follow-ups highlighting specific opportunities or concerns  \n    - It helps differentiate offerings by providing actionable, data-backed insights rather than generic pitches  \n    - Early versions will be shared by Will and the team for feedback and refinement within a day or two  \n    - This initiative aligns with the broader strategy to deepen prospect relationships and accelerate lead qualification  \n\n## **Campaign Execution and Content Assets**\n\nThe accounting services campaign is ready to launch imminently, supported by new content assets and tracking infrastructure.\n\n- **Guillesantana reported the accounting services list now contains 358 qualified contacts after removing three requested names, and the outreach sequence is finalized for immediate launch** (06:50)  \n    - The team expects to start sending the sequence as soon as post-meeting reviews are complete to avoid delays  \n    - The CFO services list will be rebuilt focusing on larger clients for accounting, and smaller clients for CFO services, reflecting clarified segmentation  \n    - Baylee confirmed the accounting campaign launch target is within the next one to two days after sequence approval  \n    - Guilllesantana will share all assets and sequences via email for quick team review  \n\n- **A new landing page for the Cache Playbook ebook is live on the website with integrated tracking and a HubSpot list capturing 15 newsletter click-throughs** (14:41)  \n    - Social media assets (5-6 pieces) have been created to promote the playbook on GSS and personal accounts  \n    - Nick plans to bookmark the playbook on the corporate LinkedIn page and create a post to drive traffic  \n    - Guilllesantana will provide ongoing reports identifying visitors and engaged prospects for targeted follow-up  \n    - This content serves as a top-of-funnel engagement tool to nurture prospects and build brand visibility  \n\n## **Content Production and Thought Leadership**\n\nOngoing content development focuses on thought leadership around outsourced accounting to build credibility and support campaigns.\n\n- **Guillesantana shared progress on two upcoming blog posts derived from a recent interview with Will, centered on outsourcing accounting without losing quality** (16:50)  \n    - These posts aim to educate prospects on the benefits and safeguards of outsourcing finance functions  \n    - Content will reinforce GSS’s expertise and build trust with target audiences before direct outreach  \n    - Will approved the approach and emphasized the importance of aligning content with audience needs  \n    - This content pipeline supports the broader strategy of multi-touch engagement across formats and channels  \n\n- **The team agreed this mix of ebook, blog posts, and personalized outreach will create a layered marketing funnel driving higher quality leads and better conversion rates** (17:13)  \n    - Coordinated messaging across assets ensures prospects receive consistent, reinforcing information  \n    - Thought leadership content establishes GSS as a trusted advisor in the marketplace  \n    - This strategy also aids SEO, social proof, and long-term brand strength  \n    - Ongoing content development remains a priority to maintain momentum and audience engagement","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast Strategy","Accounting Services Campaign","CFO Services Targeting","Financial Benchmarking Tool","Cash Playbook Ebook","Restaurant Industry Marketing"],"overview":"- **Podcast Strategy Needs Change:** Ineffective guest bookings require broader topics to attract diverse content and engage potential guests.  \n- **Video Interviews Proposed:** Shifting to video series could enhance content volume and audience trust, boosting SEO value.  \n- **Client Segmentation Clarified:** CFO services target smaller companies (10-50 units), while accounting serves larger operators for better outreach.  \n- **Financial Benchmarking Tool Development:** AI-powered tool to offer users financial comparisons, enhancing engagement and follow-up conversations.  \n- **Accounting Campaign Launch Ready:** 358 qualified contacts prepared for outreach, with new assets supporting the imminent campaign launch.  \n- **Content Production for Thought Leadership:** Ongoing blogs and ebooks will establish credibility, enhance SEO, and drive higher-quality leads.","action_items":"\n**Nick Stauff**\nFollow up casually with newsletter clickers to engage interested prospects (16:24)\nPost and bookmark the cash playbook ebook link on the corporate LinkedIn page (16:24)\n\n**Will Fleming**\nProvide a matrix of financial input data (concept types, labor and food costs, EBITDA margin) to support building the benchmarking tool, aiming to send within one or two days (14:00)\nConfirm CFO and accounting services prospect segmentation to guide marketing lists (17:21)\n\n**Guilles Santana**\nSend the finalized accounting services contact list (358 contacts) and accompanying outreach sequence for review immediately after the meeting (07:18)\nRebuild CFO prospect list focusing on smaller operators (under 50 units) based on clarifications from Will and Nick (07:50)\nDeliver final marketing email sequences for both accounting and CFO services campaigns promptly for launch (14:00)\nEmail all materials including social media graphics, ebook landing page link, and list of newsletter clickers for prospect follow-up (16:10)\nProvide spreadsheet data of visitors who have viewed the cash playbook landing page (15:50)\nSend follow-up blog post drafts based on recent interview for review (17:07)\n\n**Baylee Gunnell**\nReassess podcast content strategy and guest booking approach to potentially broaden topics or explore video content alternatives for better engagement (02:54)\nShare prototype of the benchmarking survey and report tool and assist with design improvements to fit financial data needs (13:00)\nCoordinate with Guilles on campaign launches and input collection to accelerate rollout of both accounting and CFO service campaigns (14:15)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"05552a09-72e8-4be3-acaa-911e6da3b77d","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
