INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync',
  '## **Geotargeted Advertising Strategy**

The team agreed to launch a geofencing ad campaign targeting competitors’ gym locations to increase qualified leads.

- **Milan Wagner** emphasized the need to boost leads beyond the current average of **4–5 leads per day** across both clubs, proposing a new geotagged campaign to capture members from competitor gyms in Miami (05:08).
    - The campaign will highlight unique benefits like month-to-month memberships, gym cleanliness, and group fitness classes to entice members to switch.
    - Targeting will focus on specific gym addresses and zip codes to maximize relevance and reach.
    - Milan committed to compiling a list of **6–8 competitor gyms** within a **10-minute drive radius** to segment and tailor ads effectively.
    - The campaign aims to replicate successful geofencing done previously for a freight client, which showed lasting lead generation even after campaign end.
    
- **Yefei Jin** proposed financial incentives such as discounting the first three months or partially buying out competitor contracts to attract switchers, stressing the importance of understanding competitor membership terms and cancellation policies (16:35).
    - He recommended focusing on gyms with higher prices than Powerhouse to compete mainly on price and value.
    - Milan will research competitor contract terms and pricing to develop tailored offers for each target location.
    - Yefei suggested also targeting corporate office buildings with dedicated membership offers, leveraging office proximity and employee concentration to generate leads with minimal new creative work (22:51).
    - Milan will provide a list of corporate buildings for a separate ad campaign with messaging adjusted for corporate memberships.

- **Nina Belina** confirmed technical feasibility, explaining that geo-targeting can be done at building-level addresses and highlighted prior success with such campaigns (20:21).
    - She advised broadening location scope as much as possible to avoid overly narrow audiences.
    - Nina will consult the paid media specialist for the best approach on whether to integrate geofencing into existing campaigns or create new ones.

## **Ad Creative and Campaign Structure**

The team will test multiple creative formats to determine the most effective ad types for lead generation.

- Milan requested delivery of the **group fitness video** and photo creatives to run split tests comparing video versus static image ad performance (12:23).
    - Nina confirmed that due to technical constraints, campaigns must be separated by asset type (video-only campaign and image-only campaign).
    - Yefei endorsed testing both formats over a **one-week period** to quickly identify the best performers.
    - Creative messaging for group fitness will focus on **new class formats** recently launched, leveraging Instagram content for inspiration (50:08).

- For corporate campaigns, Yefei emphasized simple messaging tweaks without needing new video production, aiming for quick deployment (23:26).
    - Leads generated from corporate ads will be routed directly to Milan for follow-up.

## **Lead Volume, Cost, and Budget Management**

Current lead volume is below target, but cost per lead metrics show promising opportunities to scale effectively.

- Nina reported that January yielded **334 total leads** across both clubs, short of the **600 leads monthly target** (about **20 leads per day**) that Milan and Yefei agreed would be sufficient to meet business goals (39:41).
    - The conversion rate for leads currently ranges between **4% and 10%**, with a goal to increase closing rates to **15–20%** by improving lead quality (37:45).
    - The current average daily ad spend is approximately **$114**, with a monthly budget of around **$4,000** for both clubs combined (31:52).
    - Cost per lead varies by audience, with the best-performing segment (18–24 years old) at **$7.37 per lead**, while older demographics cost up to **$26 per lead** (25:11).
    
- Yefei stressed the importance of rapid budget adjustments when favorable cost per lead trends emerge, recommending doubling or tripling spend on ads consistently below **$8 per lead** to maximize lead volume quickly (29:50).
    - Nina agreed to set up Slack reminders to alert Milan when cost per lead falls below this threshold for prompt action.
    - Milan monitors daily ad performance himself and will flag opportunities to increase budgets immediately.
    - The team agreed to keep ad schedules flexible, allowing ads to run outside the previous **8am–8pm window** to capture leads during off-hours if advised by the media specialist (44:31).

- Nina will have the paid media specialist review current campaigns to identify what changes (budget, targeting, ad content) are needed to reach the **20 leads per day** goal sustainably (40:15).
    - The review will also benchmark competitor ad tactics to find gaps and opportunities for improvement.
    - Milan highlighted that lead form issues from previous campaigns had suppressed lead volume and that reverting to a more reliable form workflow helped stabilize results (41:56).

## **SMS Campaign Compliance and Automation Improvements**

Compliance and workflow automation for SMS lead capture are being finalized to ensure legal and operational readiness.

- Nina is coordinating with a Squarespace developer to add a **privacy policy and terms** specific to SMS campaigns on the website, addressing previous compliance gaps (10:18).
    - The SMS privacy policy will clarify opt-in/out processes, message frequency, and data use, tailored beyond the general website terms.
    - Milan will confirm completion before final launch and integrate the updated link into the SMS form.
    
- Milan discovered irregularities in the **HubSpot lead workflow**, where Fort Lauderdale leads were incorrectly assigned and reassigned to Felipe’s list multiple times (45:51).
    - Nina will task the developer to investigate and fix automation inconsistencies causing duplicate or misrouted leads.
    - They verified that contact details are complete, indicating the issue is likely in workflow configuration rather than data gaps.

## **Process Coordination and Next Steps**

Clear assignments and timelines were established to accelerate campaign launches and improve reporting.

- Milan will compile and send lists of competitor gyms and corporate buildings with pricing and contract details for geofencing and corporate campaigns respectively (22:28, 24:00).
- Nina will confirm with the paid media specialist whether to integrate geofencing into existing campaigns or create new ones and advise on ad scheduling and budget adjustments (07:54, 44:44).
- Nina will request a comprehensive media specialist review to provide recommendations on increasing lead volume to **600 monthly**, including budget and competitor analysis (40:15).
- Milan will deliver the group fitness video and coordinate production of one or two photo creatives for split testing (12:36).
- Nina will notify Milan when SMS privacy policy updates are live to proceed with final approvals and campaign activation (12:12, 49:36).
- Milan and Nina will monitor daily lead costs and volumes, using Slack alerts to rapidly scale budgets for ads under **$8 per lead** (29:50).
- The team aims to launch targeted geofencing and corporate campaigns by **February** to maximize early-year lead growth (24:43).',
  '2026-02-03 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Provide list of competitor gym addresses and terms/conditions for Miami area geo-targeted ads (14:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Source and deliver missing yoga and boxing videos for group fitness campaign to Nina (08:06)","completed":false},{"text":"Send list of corporate office buildings for targeted corporate membership campaigns (23:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor Meta ad cost-per-lead daily and notify team to increase budget on low CPL ads (27:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Investigate and clarify issues with HubSpot lead workflow misassignments and communicate findings (45:51)","completed":false},{"text":"Consult with paid media specialist on best approach for geofencing in existing vs. new ads (07:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm addition of SMS privacy policy specific to SMS campaigns on Squarespace and notify Milan upon completion (10:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with paid media specialist to advise on increasing lead volumes to reach 20 leads/day target and review budget recommendations (40:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Request developer to investigate HubSpot lead workflow problems reported by Milan (49:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Adapt messaging for group fitness campaign based on Instagram content and prepare for launch (50:16)","completed":false},{"text":"Review geofencing strategy and proposed promotions, provide feedback on messaging and campaign direction (00:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate with Milan and Nina to finalize ad budget scaling plan based on daily CPL monitoring (27:00)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
