INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Rugged Robotics <> MiD Bi-Weekly',
  '## **Website Updates and Content Development**

The website updates have been largely completed, with a few final tweaks pending to ensure consistency and usability.

- **Demir completed the latest round of website updates**, including the About tab with a new "Meet Rugged" section and consistent styling across pages (04:01)  
    - The use cases section was reordered and one was removed per Rob’s feedback  
    - Rob plans to finish minor text and photo edits himself due to limited time before the board meeting  
    - The footer navigation alignment issue was noted and will be fixed later to match the existing site’s layout  
    - The case studies PDFs have been redesigned and are ready for deployment on the staging site once Rob confirms (06:13)  

- **Rob confirmed the redesigned case studies PDFs cover all current content**, with a new PDF expected soon to add to the system (06:29)  
    - Nathalie will proceed to develop these PDFs on the staging site without waiting for individual reviews  
    - This system aims to speed up future updates and maintain consistency across case studies  

## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Performance and Lead Management**

The ABM email campaign continues to perform steadily, with ongoing efforts to nurture engaged contacts and refine lead handling processes.

- **Since the last meeting, 1,074 leads were contacted via email, maintaining strong open and click rates** (07:23)  
    - Nathalie created an email open tracking sheet showing individual contact engagement in January 2026 for monthly review  
    - Rob and team may integrate this tracking into HubSpot to focus nurturing on highly engaged leads  
    - Baylee cautioned that open counts can be inflated by automated systems, so trends matter more than raw numbers (08:33)  

- **Paid media efforts in January yielded six Google search ad conversions and three LinkedIn conversions** (09:26)  
    - Rob is reviewing lead annotation lists to identify high-value prospects and refine targeting  
    - He highlighted green-coded leads as potential direct customers and yellow-coded leads as partner or secondary market prospects (13:11)  
    - Rob emphasized the need to update HubSpot notifications so he receives all lead form submissions promptly for better tracking and responsiveness (11:42)  

## **Lead Notification and Response Process Improvements**

There is a need to enhance the lead notification system and clarify lead response roles to improve follow-up efficiency.

- **Tristan confirmed LinkedIn leads come through website HubSpot forms, which currently lack full notification coverage for Rob’s team** (10:17)  
    - The HubSpot form notifications will be updated to include Rob and others on the alert list immediately after the meeting (11:42)  
    - Rob suspects internal follow-up gaps and some lead noise contribute to missed responses, not vendor issues (10:39)  
    - The team agreed to monitor lead quality and adjust outreach focus accordingly, especially filtering out lower-value Gmail leads (12:44)  

## **Strategic ABM Initiatives and Next Steps**

The team will pause new ABM expansions until after the board meeting, focusing on current outreach and refining lead segmentation.

- **Rob will share a “Do Not Contact” list of about seven contacts to exclude from ABM efforts** (15:27)  
    - No immediate action on new LinkedIn ad campaigns or additional passive target lists until after the board meeting workload eases  
    - The plan is to review two more weeks of ABM results before deciding on further ABM refinements or expansions (15:50)  
    - This approach prioritizes bandwidth management and ensures focus on high-value leads and campaigns  

## **Overall Team Sentiment and Forward Momentum**

The team is aligned and optimistic about progress, with clear next steps to maintain momentum post-board meeting.

- **Rob expressed excitement about the website progress and momentum despite recent time constraints** (16:19)  
    - Nathalie reassured that case studies deployment will proceed and further updates will be made after Rob’s review  
    - The team agreed to reconvene after the board meeting to refocus on ABM and website content updates (16:37)',
  '2026-02-04 15:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Complete final text and photo updates on the website homepage and other pages as time permits (04:57)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide upcoming case study PDF for upload and systematize rapid case study updates (07:11)","completed":false},{"text":"Annotate and send “Do Not Contact” list for HubSpot to Nathalie (15:12)","completed":false},{"text":"Review ABM progress after board meeting and prepare for next steps on LinkedIn campaign and contact lists (15:27)","completed":false},{"text":"Develop redesigned case study PDFs on the staging site (07:17)","completed":false},{"text":"Send email open tracking sheet to Rob monthly to support nurture efforts (08:11)","completed":false},{"text":"Update HubSpot forms to ensure Rob and his team receive lead notifications (14:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Check and adjust HubSpot form notifications to include Rob and relevant stakeholders on lead submissions (11:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Share an article on email open data reliability with Rob for reference (08:33)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
