    779,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88563318843?pwd=Y3Fp9eT4jgjKoArHQvLZmcmkPu72l6.1',
    '{"id":"01KGJJ2M3816WVQ264P1H8JTDX","title":"Nathalie Mintjens and Doug Gallagher","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Offer Development**\n\nThe team decided to center the campaign around a **\"Scaling Without Headcount\" playbook** that highlights outsourcing and technology as growth tools (07:33).  \n- **Doug** emphasized this aligns with Gallagher and Mohan’s expertise in offshore systems and real estate operations.  \n- The playbook will explain how to scale operations externally without traditional hiring, including process mapping and AI solutions.  \n- This approach aims to attract leaders managing growing portfolios who want to avoid adding internal staff.  \n- **Colin** noted playbooks have shown strong market interest, making this a solid core offer to build campaign materials around.  \n\nAdditional offer concepts like a **CAM dispute prevention checklist**, **accounting turnover hidden costs**, and an **in-house vs offshore accounting guide** were discussed but deprioritized in favor of the playbook concept (04:56).  \n- These ideas are designed to be low-friction educational resources but require further feedback from Gallagher and Mohan leadership before development.  \n\n## **Marketing Execution and Channels**\n\nThe campaign will deploy a mix of **email outreach, landing pages, LinkedIn content, and direct mail marketing** targeting the same prospect list (07:50).  \n- Colin committed to writing the email and outreach content this week for Doug’s review before launch.  \n- Doug stressed the importance of adding **direct mail**, especially postcards, as a tactile and effective touchpoint for a smaller, targeted list (08:09).  \n- The direct mail approach will replicate a successful campaign used by a $3 billion bank client, including tracking offer codes for attribution (08:30).  \n- The mailing list will focus on high-level decision-makers like **owners, partners, and C-suite executives**, avoiding lower-level contacts to optimize budget (09:54).  \n\nDoug plans to bring in cold callers later in the campaign once initial engagement is established through content and mail (10:35).  \n- Colin confirmed they have phone number enrichment tools integrated with platforms like ZoomInfo and Apollo, but acknowledged accuracy limitations (10:52).  \n- Doug intends to activate his auto-dialer and cold calling resources as a **phase B** effort after campaign launch (11:11).  \n\n## **Content and Creative Development Timeline**\n\nThe team aims to **launch the campaign as early as next week** once email content and direct mail designs are ready (07:50).  \n- Colin will produce all written materials and creative assets this week based on the playbook offer (08:04).  \n- He will also obtain quotes for direct mail production and distribution for Doug’s approval (10:04).  \n- The campaign will include A/B testing on messaging and offers to optimize engagement post-launch (11:31).  \n\nDoug’s review and feedback will be critical before finalizing and sending materials live.  \n- The focus on quick turnaround reflects the need to capitalize on market interest and start generating leads rapidly.  \n\n## **Budget and Billing Coordination**\n\nDoug requested a resend of the **credit card authorization form** to set up billing for paid ads, confirming that paid advertising is part of the overall campaign plan (11:55).  \n- Colin confirmed the form was previously sent but will resend it promptly for setup (12:06).  \n- This step is necessary to enable the paid ads component, which complements organic email, LinkedIn, and direct mail efforts.  \n\n## **Meeting Cadence and Communication**\n\nThe team agreed to maintain a **weekly meeting cadence on Mondays** but remains flexible if Doug’s schedule becomes tighter (02:37).  \n- Colin encouraged open email communication for any issues or updates between meetings (12:24).  \n- Doug will notify if Monday meetings become difficult, allowing schedule adjustments.  \n\nThis approach supports ongoing alignment and rapid decision-making as the campaign progresses.","outline":null,"keywords":["Campaign launch","Playbook offer","Direct mail marketing","Offshore accounting","Lead generation","Paid ads billing"],"overview":"- **Campaign Focus:** \"Scaling Without Headcount\" playbook will emphasize outsourcing and tech for growth.  \n- **Target Audience:** Aiming at leaders who manage growing portfolios but prefer no internal hiring.  \n- **Marketing Strategy:** Combines email, LinkedIn, landing pages, and targeted direct mail, focusing on high-level executives.  \n- **Launch Timeline:** Campaign expected to launch next week, with written content and direct mail designs ready soon.  \n- **Budget Coordination:** Need to resend credit card authorization for paid ads to enhance campaign reach.  \n- **Weekly Meetings:** Scheduled on Mondays for updates, with flexibility for Doug''s availability.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nWrite and deliver campaign email content, landing pages, and LinkedIn outreach copy based on agreed offer (07:50)\nCreate initial design drafts for direct mail postcards and obtain mailing cost quotes (10:04)\nSend Doug the credit card authorization form again for paid ad billing (11:55)\nMonitor content engagement to identify prospects for future cold calling (10:35)\n\n**Doug Gallagher**\nDiscuss campaign offer ideas with David and communicate feedback to Colin’s team (03:49)\nReview forthcoming campaign content and direct mail design drafts once received (07:50)\nCoordinate internal resources for cold calling phase after campaign launch (10:35)\nConsider signing up or completing necessary billing actions for SEO and paid ads services as guided (11:55)\n"},"duration":12.979999542236328,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Doug"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello?","index":0,"end_time":59.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.14,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Hey, Doug.","index":1,"end_time":60.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, what''s up?","index":2,"end_time":64.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":63.94,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":3,"end_time":65.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Your voice is, like, super deep.","index":4,"end_time":68.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":66.18,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s really weird.","index":5,"end_time":69.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":68.22,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Wait, let me.","index":6,"end_time":74.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":73.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Wait, say something.","index":7,"end_time":75.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":74.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Hello?","index":8,"end_time":76.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not for you guys, right?","index":9,"end_time":78.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":77.55,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s, like, normal, I''m assuming.","index":10,"end_time":79.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":78.51,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s normal to me.","index":11,"end_time":81.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":80.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, let me.","index":12,"end_time":83.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":82.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Give me a second here.","index":13,"end_time":84.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.75,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Testing, testing.","index":14,"end_time":125.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":124.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now I just can''t hear anything.","index":15,"end_time":127.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":126.04,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Great.","index":16,"end_time":128.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.81,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You say something.","index":17,"end_time":135.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":134.45,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Can you hear me now?","index":18,"end_time":136.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":135.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":19,"end_time":138.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":136.69,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I don''t know what was going on.","index":20,"end_time":140.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.41,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It was like your voice is like the.","index":21,"end_time":141.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.29,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like when you''re, like, hiding some of your identity.","index":22,"end_time":144.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":142.61,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, well.","index":23,"end_time":147.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":24,"end_time":148.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re not on a call with Anonymous.","index":25,"end_time":149.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":148.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just us.","index":26,"end_time":150.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":149.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":27,"end_time":150.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":150.33,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Great.","index":28,"end_time":151.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":151.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":29,"end_time":153.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":152.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m good.","index":30,"end_time":154.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.41,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I''m good.","index":31,"end_time":155.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.97,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"How are you guys doing?","index":32,"end_time":157.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":155.33,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right.","index":33,"end_time":157.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Appreciate you booking the time with us.","index":34,"end_time":160.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":158.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know Monday seems like.","index":35,"end_time":162.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":160.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Probably got a little hectic on your calendar.","index":36,"end_time":164.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":162.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, just kind of too much.","index":37,"end_time":167.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":165.53,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Got a little.","index":38,"end_time":168.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":167.73,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Lot of things going on.","index":39,"end_time":169.609,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.49,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, totally get it.","index":40,"end_time":170.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if we need to.","index":41,"end_time":172.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If Mondays are typically tough to get.","index":42,"end_time":175.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On the books, then we can look.","index":43,"end_time":176.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":175.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For a different day for our weekly meetings, no problem.","index":44,"end_time":179.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":176.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":45,"end_time":182.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.97,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Is joining today?","index":46,"end_time":184.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":47,"end_time":188.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.89,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Let''s see.","index":48,"end_time":189.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Probably not.","index":49,"end_time":194.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"No, it''s fine.","index":50,"end_time":195.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":194.37,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I think we can just keep.","index":51,"end_time":195.889,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.05,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Keep it rolling.","index":52,"end_time":196.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.889,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":53,"end_time":197.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, cool.","index":54,"end_time":197.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, Doug, what I really want to cover is just.","index":55,"end_time":200.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is how we can get this campaign live.","index":56,"end_time":201.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So really, I mean, we have all of the pieces into place.","index":57,"end_time":206.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":202.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The fundamental part, though, is the offer.","index":58,"end_time":209.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":206.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know we talked about the calculator, and then when we met last week, you were thinking you wanted to talk to David and.","index":59,"end_time":214.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And see what other ideas you could come up with.","index":60,"end_time":216.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":214.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also came up with a few more ideas.","index":61,"end_time":218.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":216.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So first, want to check in on the status if.","index":62,"end_time":220.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you''ve talked to David about that, if you have something else in mind, or we can jump into the ones.","index":63,"end_time":225.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we''ve come up with.","index":64,"end_time":226.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we.","index":65,"end_time":230.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.77,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"David and I didn''t really get around talking to it, to be honest.","index":66,"end_time":232.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.37,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":67,"end_time":233.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":233.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no worries.","index":68,"end_time":234.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":233.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So with this market, we''re.","index":69,"end_time":237.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":235.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re trying to find something that we.","index":70,"end_time":239.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can build that is tangible, that is very low friction for them, and that is very desirable.","index":71,"end_time":246.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":239.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Something that they''re willing to fill out a form or book a meeting with your team in order to get.","index":72,"end_time":252.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":246.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And in today''s age, that is just getting more and more difficult.","index":73,"end_time":255.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"People are treating their information on a form fill, like a currency, and same with their time of jumping onto a discovery call or anything like that.","index":74,"end_time":263.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what we go into.","index":75,"end_time":265.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":263.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These offer, like, mindsets.","index":76,"end_time":267.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":265.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With the first one is A CAM dispute prevention checklist.","index":77,"end_time":272.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":267.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this is something that we could come up from more of a educational.","index":78,"end_time":275.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We understand your space, we understand the things that you''re dealing with.","index":79,"end_time":277.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":275.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it gives them an opportunity to check whether their CAM process is exposed.","index":80,"end_time":283.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":278.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They don''t really need to submit much data, but we''re providing this more of a.","index":81,"end_time":288.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As an educational resource and showing that Gallagher and Mohan really does understand lease administration and accounting at the property level.","index":82,"end_time":295.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":288.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":83,"end_time":297.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":296.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":84,"end_time":299.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.55,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"This is something good for David to ask, I guess.","index":85,"end_time":302.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.87,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":86,"end_time":305.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":304.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Do you have something to show me about that or.","index":87,"end_time":307.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.79,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"No, no, these are more of like, we can build these pretty quickly.","index":88,"end_time":310.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":307.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are more of like, we need.","index":89,"end_time":311.789,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We wanted to get the concept in front of you guys, see how you feel that the market would react or how Gallagher and Mohan wants to position themselves on it.","index":90,"end_time":318.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.789,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we could build it pretty quickly.","index":91,"end_time":319.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":318.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":92,"end_time":321.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.67,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And you said you have other ideas as well?","index":93,"end_time":323.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":321.9,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":94,"end_time":323.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":323.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So another one is a playbook.","index":95,"end_time":325.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":323.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so this is the scaling without headcount playbook, really speaking to leaders who are growing portfolios and don''t want to keep just adding on internal team members walks through how, you know, teams hit capacity, the functions that break within their companies first and how to actually scale externally.","index":96,"end_time":345.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this would be promoting Gallagher and Mohan services all throughout as well.","index":97,"end_time":349.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I like that one more, to be honest.","index":98,"end_time":352.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":350.31,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":99,"end_time":353.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Another one is a hidden cost of accounting turnover.","index":100,"end_time":357.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":354.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this one is framing accounting turnover as an operational risk, not just hr and validating a lot of things that firms are probably feeling but haven''t quantified on their own.","index":101,"end_time":369.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":359.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, they need to know when someone leaves that like their company still has that process locked into place and that they could work with the team like algorithm O and to establish that.","index":102,"end_time":382.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":371.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":103,"end_time":384.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.51,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then the last one was in house versus offshore accounting decision guide.","index":104,"end_time":389.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So more of a guide for internal decision support.","index":105,"end_time":392.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":390.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Helps them understand whether in house or offshore or hybrid model makes sense at the current stage of their growth, I think.","index":106,"end_time":399.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":393.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":399.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.23,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So I think I like the playbook one more because like the way I kind of see it is.","index":108,"end_time":403.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.59,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s like the way I kind of see what we are experts at.","index":109,"end_time":410.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.26,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":110,"end_time":410.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.5,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Is developing offshore systems.","index":111,"end_time":412.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":410.86,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"In our specialty is real estate type of thing.","index":112,"end_time":416.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":414.58,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":113,"end_time":418.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.06,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s kind of like our MO So it''s like creating a playbook.","index":114,"end_time":420.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.02,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But how''s the best way to scale your operations with it?","index":115,"end_time":427.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.74,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We also do technology a little bit as well too.","index":116,"end_time":429.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":427.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So it''s like, how do you scale without headcount, like you said before, like.","index":117,"end_time":433.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.9,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Or, you know, it''s like, even though we are kind of headcount, but it''s like, you know, it''s like without hiring traditionally or something.","index":118,"end_time":439.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right?","index":119,"end_time":439.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.3,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":120,"end_time":440.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.7,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We do it through outsourcing.","index":121,"end_time":441.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.06,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We can do it through process mapping and documentation of roles.","index":122,"end_time":443.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.38,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"We could do it through AI, you know, solutions, things like that, and kind of like getting them interested.","index":123,"end_time":448.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":443.82,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"It''s like basically just what our pitch is.","index":124,"end_time":450.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.74,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I think that kind of makes sense.","index":125,"end_time":451.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.58,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You know, what the book.","index":126,"end_time":452.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.74,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":127,"end_time":453.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.66,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":128,"end_time":453.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":129,"end_time":453.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re seeing good success with Playbooks, drawing a lot of interest.","index":130,"end_time":456.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll move forward with building out the campaign around that as a core offer and then, you know, keep having conversations around secondary pieces that we can build onto it as well.","index":131,"end_time":466.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":132,"end_time":468.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.8,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I think that''s really where we needed to land.","index":133,"end_time":471.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That allows us to create like, write the landing pages, write the email content, the LinkedIn outreach content, and then we can build.","index":134,"end_time":477.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":471.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, I mean, we could realistically launch this next week.","index":135,"end_time":479.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so do you have like the emails actually crafted and everything?","index":136,"end_time":483.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":481.2,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That''s what I''m going to write this week, now that we have the offer in place, and then send them over to you guys to review and then.","index":137,"end_time":488.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":484.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, okay, okay.","index":138,"end_time":492.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.33,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And the other thing is direct mail marketing.","index":139,"end_time":493.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.41,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So I know it sounds like old school, but I actually did it before one time with my clients.","index":140,"end_time":497.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.85,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So it''s a little caveat, but it''s like, it actually works like, pretty well.","index":141,"end_time":501.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":497.49,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And I don''t know, I just feel like if we''re going after like a smaller base, like we could kind of create something that''s good.","index":142,"end_time":507.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And in my opinion, I think it''s a pretty good strategy, actually.","index":143,"end_time":510.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.29,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":144,"end_time":510.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.61,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve done it.","index":145,"end_time":511.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of my clients is a $3 billion bank in New York, and so that''s one of the approaches that we used.","index":146,"end_time":516.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":511.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So not only sending emails and running ads and things like that, but, you know, creating a six by nine postcard that really stands out in the rest of your mail that you''re getting with similar offer codes so that we''re tracking the attribution there.","index":147,"end_time":528.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":517.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we work with a bunch of different vendors on this.","index":148,"end_time":532.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":530.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically, we do all of the design work in.","index":149,"end_time":534.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then depending on our clients, we have list providers like Data Axle or Dun and Bradstreet, things like that.","index":150,"end_time":543.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we can build the list with all the software that we use internally.","index":151,"end_time":547.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it.","index":152,"end_time":549.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.69,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Was there anything.","index":153,"end_time":553.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":552.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there a specific geo you had in mind?","index":154,"end_time":555.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should we.","index":155,"end_time":555.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My mind would go to using the list that we are also sending emails and other communications to so that we''re.","index":156,"end_time":562.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Getting away from the direct mail marketing.","index":157,"end_time":563.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.45,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":564.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.81,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I was thinking the exact same list.","index":159,"end_time":566.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.81,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":160,"end_time":566.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.17,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yep.","index":161,"end_time":566.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":162,"end_time":567.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So next step, we don''t necessarily need.","index":163,"end_time":569.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":568.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To send it to.","index":164,"end_time":570.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.93,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I mean like, so your guys list is fine, but like, I feel like in my, in my head at least it''s like, you know, it doesn''t really hurt to like email like these like, like the executive assistant or operations associate or something like that.","index":165,"end_time":585.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.49,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"But it''s like if you''re pricing on a per person basis, I don''t think it''s like worth money to like send them, send, you know, flyers to those people though.","index":166,"end_time":594.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.62,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":167,"end_time":594.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.02,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":168,"end_time":594.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":595.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.86,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":170,"end_time":596.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So more of the owner or C.","index":171,"end_time":598.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":596.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or partner, like type C suite owner or like, or someone that just seems to be high up.","index":172,"end_time":602.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":598.38,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Right.","index":173,"end_time":602.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"You know?","index":174,"end_time":603.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.74,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":604.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So next steps there then.","index":176,"end_time":606.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Would you like us to get you some quotes and start putting together some designs for a direct mail piece?","index":177,"end_time":611.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, sure.","index":178,"end_time":612.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.14,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I think that''s a good.","index":179,"end_time":613.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.74,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, basically what I think the good playbook is, is like your email campaign, your playbook, your.","index":180,"end_time":619.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.9,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I know, we gotta get that SEO stuff right away.","index":181,"end_time":623.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.98,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then the direct mail marketing, like, that''s where I would feel the most comfortable with like what we''re doing.","index":182,"end_time":627.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.26,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And then like later on once we kind of get things rolling, you might be able to like, I could bring in one of my cold callers who might be able to help with that too.","index":183,"end_time":635.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.42,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":184,"end_time":636.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":635.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ll have a list of people.","index":185,"end_time":637.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":636.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we''re like, hey, they''re consuming every bit of content that we give them.","index":186,"end_time":641.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re downloading stuff.","index":187,"end_time":641.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They''re just not going to that extra step of a phone call.","index":188,"end_time":644.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":641.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s typically a great list that we give to a system.","index":189,"end_time":646.729,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":644.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''d be awesome.","index":190,"end_time":648.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":647.77,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":191,"end_time":649.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.05,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay, do you guys have any like cell phone finding tools or anything like.","index":192,"end_time":652.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":649.57,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That for actually uncovering phone numbers?","index":193,"end_time":655.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":652.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we use a few of them.","index":194,"end_time":658.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":655.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We have different enrichments built into clay that tag into those.","index":195,"end_time":661.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s pulling from like zoom info, Apollo, a bunch of different numbers like that.","index":196,"end_time":665.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not all.","index":197,"end_time":667.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think any of them are a hundred percent accurate, if I''m being completely honest.","index":198,"end_time":671.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s just the nature, but I think that should be like our phase B.","index":199,"end_time":676.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":671.7,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Whatever.","index":200,"end_time":676.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.34,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like once we''re kind of up and running, like, I have a guy who has plenty of bandwidth who can, who can call and we have.","index":201,"end_time":681.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.7,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"I actually bought like a, you know, an auto dialer.","index":202,"end_time":685.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.78,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So I spent a ton of money on something.","index":203,"end_time":686.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.53,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Like we need to use it on call.","index":204,"end_time":688.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.29,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":205,"end_time":690.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.69,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"And go from there.","index":206,"end_time":690.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.09,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":207,"end_time":691.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":208,"end_time":692.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":691.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so next steps on our side, we''ll.","index":209,"end_time":693.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll write out all the content based on the offer.","index":210,"end_time":696.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":693.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll start doing some designs on the direct mail, get you some quotes for sending that out, and then.","index":211,"end_time":701.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":696.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll be able to start hit go on this, and then put our, like, next a B test into place.","index":212,"end_time":707.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":213,"end_time":709.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.9,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":214,"end_time":709.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":709.18,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":215,"end_time":710.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":709.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, anything else that you needed from us?","index":216,"end_time":712.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys need me to sign up for the SEO stuff, right?","index":217,"end_time":718.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":715.46,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"For the SEO stuff, like the billing?","index":218,"end_time":722.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":719.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''t I need to put my credit card in or something?","index":219,"end_time":726.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":724.259,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Oh, the credit card authorization form that we sent over?","index":220,"end_time":728.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":729.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.82,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Oh, yeah.","index":222,"end_time":729.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you need us to send that over again?","index":223,"end_time":731.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":729.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That was more for running paid ads.","index":224,"end_time":732.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":225,"end_time":734.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.11,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"That is part of our goal, right?","index":226,"end_time":735.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.43,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"The paid ads as well.","index":227,"end_time":736.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":735.63,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":228,"end_time":736.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.59,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Okay.","index":229,"end_time":737.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.91,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":230,"end_time":737.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.07,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"So can you send that to me again, please?","index":231,"end_time":738.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":737.27,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Do it.","index":232,"end_time":739.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":739.15,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"No problem at all.","index":233,"end_time":740.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":739.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":234,"end_time":741.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":740.99,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":235,"end_time":743.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":742.43,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I''m all good, then.","index":236,"end_time":744.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":743.15,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":237,"end_time":745.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, yeah, if anything comes up between now and our meeting Monday, just send over an email.","index":238,"end_time":750.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":745.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if Monday doesn''t work for you, just let us know and we''ll adjust accordingly.","index":239,"end_time":753.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":750.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":240,"end_time":755.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.95,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":241,"end_time":755.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you very much, Doug.","index":242,"end_time":756.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, see you.","index":243,"end_time":757.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.87,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Bye.","index":244,"end_time":757.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.51,"speaker_name":"Doug"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":245,"end_time":758.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":757.95,"speaker_name":"Doug"}],"dateString":"2026-02-04T19:00:00.000Z","host_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/88563318843?pwd=Y3Fp9eT4jgjKoArHQvLZmcmkPu72l6.1","participants":["nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,dougg@gallaghermohan.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","dougg@gallaghermohan.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KGJJ2M3816WVQ264P1H8JTDX","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Agreed to use the ''scaling without headcount'' playbook as the campaign''s core offer.","Doug confirmed direct mail marketing as part of a multi-channel campaign strategy.","Colin to write and deliver email content this week for review and campaign launch.","Next steps include designing mailers, quoting costs, and integrating paid ad billing.","Doug flagged intent to integrate cold calling phase once initial outreach is live."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I like the playbook one more because... it''s basically just what our pitch is.","speaker":"Doug"},{"quote":"Direct mail marketing... actually works like, pretty well.","speaker":"Doug"},{"quote":"We could realistically launch this next week.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","offer","outreach","ads"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-0125-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-06T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Offer Development**\n\nThe team decided to center the campaign around a **\"Scaling Without Headcount\" playbook** that highlights outsourcing and technology as growth tools (07:33).  \n- **Doug** emphasized this aligns with Gallagher and Mohan’s expertise in offshore systems and real estate operations.  \n- The playbook will explain how to scale operations externally without traditional hiring, including process mapping and AI solutions.  \n- This approach aims to attract leaders managing growing portfolios who want to avoid adding internal staff.  \n- **Colin** noted playbooks have shown strong market interest, making this a solid core offer to build campaign materials around.  \n\nAdditional offer concepts like a **CAM dispute prevention checklist**, **accounting turnover hidden costs**, and an **in-house vs offshore accounting guide** were discussed but deprioritized in favor of the playbook concept (04:56).  \n- These ideas are designed to be low-friction educational resources but require further feedback from Gallagher and Mohan leadership before development.  \n\n## **Marketing Execution and Channels**\n\nThe campaign will deploy a mix of **email outreach, landing pages, LinkedIn content, and direct mail marketing** targeting the same prospect list (07:50).  \n- Colin committed to writing the email and outreach content this week for Doug’s review before launch.  \n- Doug stressed the importance of adding **direct mail**, especially postcards, as a tactile and effective touchpoint for a smaller, targeted list (08:09).  \n- The direct mail approach will replicate a successful campaign used by a $3 billion bank client, including tracking offer codes for attribution (08:30).  \n- The mailing list will focus on high-level decision-makers like **owners, partners, and C-suite executives**, avoiding lower-level contacts to optimize budget (09:54).  \n\nDoug plans to bring in cold callers later in the campaign once initial engagement is established through content and mail (10:35).  \n- Colin confirmed they have phone number enrichment tools integrated with platforms like ZoomInfo and Apollo, but acknowledged accuracy limitations (10:52).  \n- Doug intends to activate his auto-dialer and cold calling resources as a **phase B** effort after campaign launch (11:11).  \n\n## **Content and Creative Development Timeline**\n\nThe team aims to **launch the campaign as early as next week** once email content and direct mail designs are ready (07:50).  \n- Colin will produce all written materials and creative assets this week based on the playbook offer (08:04).  \n- He will also obtain quotes for direct mail production and distribution for Doug’s approval (10:04).  \n- The campaign will include A/B testing on messaging and offers to optimize engagement post-launch (11:31).  \n\nDoug’s review and feedback will be critical before finalizing and sending materials live.  \n- The focus on quick turnaround reflects the need to capitalize on market interest and start generating leads rapidly.  \n\n## **Budget and Billing Coordination**\n\nDoug requested a resend of the **credit card authorization form** to set up billing for paid ads, confirming that paid advertising is part of the overall campaign plan (11:55).  \n- Colin confirmed the form was previously sent but will resend it promptly for setup (12:06).  \n- This step is necessary to enable the paid ads component, which complements organic email, LinkedIn, and direct mail efforts.  \n\n## **Meeting Cadence and Communication**\n\nThe team agreed to maintain a **weekly meeting cadence on Mondays** but remains flexible if Doug’s schedule becomes tighter (02:37).  \n- Colin encouraged open email communication for any issues or updates between meetings (12:24).  \n- Doug will notify if Monday meetings become difficult, allowing schedule adjustments.  \n\nThis approach supports ongoing alignment and rapid decision-making as the campaign progresses.","outline":null,"keywords":["Campaign launch","Playbook offer","Direct mail marketing","Offshore accounting","Lead generation","Paid ads billing"],"overview":"- **Campaign Focus:** \"Scaling Without Headcount\" playbook will emphasize outsourcing and tech for growth.  \n- **Target Audience:** Aiming at leaders who manage growing portfolios but prefer no internal hiring.  \n- **Marketing Strategy:** Combines email, LinkedIn, landing pages, and targeted direct mail, focusing on high-level executives.  \n- **Launch Timeline:** Campaign expected to launch next week, with written content and direct mail designs ready soon.  \n- **Budget Coordination:** Need to resend credit card authorization for paid ads to enhance campaign reach.  \n- **Weekly Meetings:** Scheduled on Mondays for updates, with flexibility for Doug''s availability.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nWrite and deliver campaign email content, landing pages, and LinkedIn outreach copy based on agreed offer (07:50)\nCreate initial design drafts for direct mail postcards and obtain mailing cost quotes (10:04)\nSend Doug the credit card authorization form again for paid ad billing (11:55)\nMonitor content engagement to identify prospects for future cold calling (10:35)\n\n**Doug Gallagher**\nDiscuss campaign offer ideas with David and communicate feedback to Colin’s team (03:49)\nReview forthcoming campaign content and direct mail design drafts once received (07:50)\nCoordinate internal resources for cold calling phase after campaign launch (10:35)\nConsider signing up or completing necessary billing actions for SEO and paid ads services as guided (11:55)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"0927082c-c2ab-4bbb-8bfb-3caa18bd1b31","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
