INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Nathalie Mintjens and Doug Gallagher',
  '## **Campaign Offer Development**

The team decided to center the campaign around a **"Scaling Without Headcount" playbook** that highlights outsourcing and technology as growth tools (07:33).  
- **Doug** emphasized this aligns with Gallagher and Mohan’s expertise in offshore systems and real estate operations.  
- The playbook will explain how to scale operations externally without traditional hiring, including process mapping and AI solutions.  
- This approach aims to attract leaders managing growing portfolios who want to avoid adding internal staff.  
- **Colin** noted playbooks have shown strong market interest, making this a solid core offer to build campaign materials around.  

Additional offer concepts like a **CAM dispute prevention checklist**, **accounting turnover hidden costs**, and an **in-house vs offshore accounting guide** were discussed but deprioritized in favor of the playbook concept (04:56).  
- These ideas are designed to be low-friction educational resources but require further feedback from Gallagher and Mohan leadership before development.  

## **Marketing Execution and Channels**

The campaign will deploy a mix of **email outreach, landing pages, LinkedIn content, and direct mail marketing** targeting the same prospect list (07:50).  
- Colin committed to writing the email and outreach content this week for Doug’s review before launch.  
- Doug stressed the importance of adding **direct mail**, especially postcards, as a tactile and effective touchpoint for a smaller, targeted list (08:09).  
- The direct mail approach will replicate a successful campaign used by a $3 billion bank client, including tracking offer codes for attribution (08:30).  
- The mailing list will focus on high-level decision-makers like **owners, partners, and C-suite executives**, avoiding lower-level contacts to optimize budget (09:54).  

Doug plans to bring in cold callers later in the campaign once initial engagement is established through content and mail (10:35).  
- Colin confirmed they have phone number enrichment tools integrated with platforms like ZoomInfo and Apollo, but acknowledged accuracy limitations (10:52).  
- Doug intends to activate his auto-dialer and cold calling resources as a **phase B** effort after campaign launch (11:11).  

## **Content and Creative Development Timeline**

The team aims to **launch the campaign as early as next week** once email content and direct mail designs are ready (07:50).  
- Colin will produce all written materials and creative assets this week based on the playbook offer (08:04).  
- He will also obtain quotes for direct mail production and distribution for Doug’s approval (10:04).  
- The campaign will include A/B testing on messaging and offers to optimize engagement post-launch (11:31).  

Doug’s review and feedback will be critical before finalizing and sending materials live.  
- The focus on quick turnaround reflects the need to capitalize on market interest and start generating leads rapidly.  

## **Budget and Billing Coordination**

Doug requested a resend of the **credit card authorization form** to set up billing for paid ads, confirming that paid advertising is part of the overall campaign plan (11:55).  
- Colin confirmed the form was previously sent but will resend it promptly for setup (12:06).  
- This step is necessary to enable the paid ads component, which complements organic email, LinkedIn, and direct mail efforts.  

## **Meeting Cadence and Communication**

The team agreed to maintain a **weekly meeting cadence on Mondays** but remains flexible if Doug’s schedule becomes tighter (02:37).  
- Colin encouraged open email communication for any issues or updates between meetings (12:24).  
- Doug will notify if Monday meetings become difficult, allowing schedule adjustments.  

This approach supports ongoing alignment and rapid decision-making as the campaign progresses.',
  '2026-02-04 19:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Write and deliver campaign email content, landing pages, and LinkedIn outreach copy based on agreed offer (07:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Create initial design drafts for direct mail postcards and obtain mailing cost quotes (10:04)","completed":false},{"text":"Send Doug the credit card authorization form again for paid ad billing (11:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor content engagement to identify prospects for future cold calling (10:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Discuss campaign offer ideas with David and communicate feedback to Colin’s team (03:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Review forthcoming campaign content and direct mail design drafts once received (07:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate internal resources for cold calling phase after campaign launch (10:35)","completed":false},{"text":"Consider signing up or completing necessary billing actions for SEO and paid ads services as guided (11:55)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect (2026-02-05 13:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '6a9f190a-9e44-4b24-8f1d-d82022950bb9',
    '2026-02-05 13:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KG5NMVW6HW5Q5766BDDSEYSD',
    'Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
    '{"Nathalie Mintjens","K","Shane Billings"}'::text[],
    1929,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83663022990?pwd=R1aTMdTGv2yblYfzlB6Wv1Sup4Z47U.1',
    '{"id":"01KG5NMVW6HW5Q5766BDDSEYSD","title":"Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Engagement and Demo Scheduling**\n\nThe team is facing challenges scheduling demos due to prospects’ extreme time constraints and role limitations.\n\n- **Keenan reported no scheduled demos from the two recent form submitters despite follow-up attempts with Friday availability offered** (00:22)  \n    - Both prospects confirmed interest but failed to respond to scheduling outreach.  \n    - Keenan noted prospects are so busy they struggle even to read emails or attend 30-minute demos.  \n    - She plans to try a more direct, time-saving focused messaging approach this week to prompt demo scheduling.  \n    - Keenan will also conduct in-person visits next week to test if face-to-face engagement improves response rates compared to LinkedIn.  \n\n- **Keenan identified a key barrier: many initial contacts are not decision makers, leading to stalled engagement** (12:43)  \n    - She is now targeting operations managers, clinical operations, and RCM managers, rather than office managers or lower-level staff.  \n    - This shift aims to reach individuals with authority to move purchasing decisions forward.  \n    - Billers have shown more interest as they see direct value in saving time and improving communication transparency.  \n    - Shane and Keenan discussed the tension between billers, who want the tool, and office staff, who feel it adds work.  \n\n- **Shane suggested emphasizing time savings as a core value proposition in marketing campaigns** (02:16)  \n    - Nathalie agreed to update LinkedIn ads to test messaging around saving time and simplifying management.  \n    - They plan to create sales enablement materials highlighting key time-saving features to accelerate demo scheduling.  \n    - The team will explore recording a video walkthrough demo to provide more upfront value for busy prospects.  \n\n- **Keenan uses weekly segmented contact lists prioritizing prospects with emails and high engagement for outreach** (25:14)  \n    - She focuses on Tab 2 (emails) and Tab 3 (engaged contacts) from the shared spreadsheet.  \n    - Shane requested Nathalie highlight contacts with three or more clicks historically to identify highly interested prospects.  \n    - Nathalie will prepare a list of all contacts with three-plus clicks for targeted outreach.  \n\n## **Marketing Campaign and Website Performance**\n\nRecent campaigns show improved click engagement but limited conversion to form submissions or demos.\n\n- **Nathalie reported launching two new email campaigns yesterday targeting two new groups, expected to increase website activity** (03:58)  \n    - LinkedIn ads have seen a significant increase in clicks with cost per click reduced substantially (04:27).  \n    - Targeting has been tightened to improve message relevance, driving more qualified traffic to the website (04:39).  \n    - Despite more clicks, form completions remain low, indicating a conversion gap.  \n\n- **Website sessions from Google searches have slightly decreased, partly due to limited podcast-driven discoverability** (06:01)  \n    - A podcast episode is scheduled for tomorrow to boost search engine traffic and organic awareness (06:15).  \n\n- **The contact page is the main call to action across the site, but form fill rates are low despite nearly 200 visitors in the past 30 days** (14:19)  \n    - Nathalie will review and potentially revise the contact page copy to clarify the value of filling the form.  \n    - Shane emphasized the importance of this fix to increase conversion from high traffic volumes.  \n\n- **Storylane demo tool is used to track prospect engagement with online demos, with free and paid versions available** (05:00)  \n    - Shane shared specific engagement data: some users complete up to 100% of the demo with sessions lasting over a minute.  \n    - Keenan identified these active demo users as previously contacted prospects, validating their interest.  \n    - While Storylane does not reveal identities, it provides useful engagement metrics to prioritize outreach.  \n\n## **Product Launch and Pricing Strategy**\n\nThe team is preparing for a near-term launch of a self-service purchase feature, requiring pricing and website updates.\n\n- **Shane projected the next feature release in two to four weeks, followed by enabling direct credit card purchases online** (15:37)  \n    - This will allow users to create accounts and buy subscriptions without sales interaction.  \n    - The website will need redesign to incorporate account creation and purchasing workflows reflecting this change (16:54).  \n    - Campaigns will be updated to promote self-service sign-ups and pricing transparency.  \n\n- **Pricing discussions centered on setting the software’s price point and trial model** (18:36)  \n    - Keenan recommended a base price of **$139 per office per year** based on market research and customer conversations (18:50).  \n    - Shane cautioned against free trials per office, fearing customers would consolidate usage into one free office and avoid paying for others.  \n    - They agreed a **30-day time-limited free trial** is preferable to encourage usage without risking dilution of multi-office sales (20:06).  \n    - An early adopter promotion could offer a discounted **$100 per office for the first year** during the initial 90-day launch window (20:59).  \n\n- **Nathalie suggested targeting highly engaged prospects with multiple email clicks for the free trial campaign** (21:55)  \n    - This group includes users who have clicked on campaign emails several times but have not converted yet.  \n    - Shane noted this approach lets users self-select, reducing the need for manager approval and accelerating sales.  \n\n- **The pricing and trial model are designed to accommodate both single-office users and multi-office organizations** (21:18)  \n    - Early trials focus on single offices to demonstrate value before scaling to multiple locations.  \n    - The team plans a soft launch offering monthly payments with potential to add tiered and upfront payment options later (21:51).  \n\n## **Sales Process and Operational Insights**\n\nThe sales outreach process is evolving to meet prospect behaviors and internal scheduling constraints.\n\n- **Keenan is transitioning from slow, conversational outreach to a more direct approach emphasizing demo scheduling and key benefits** (09:59)  \n    - She experiments weekly with different messaging styles and tailors outreach based on prospect engagement.  \n    - The direct approach is intended to move beyond social media exchanges toward committed demos.  \n\n- **Keenan’s upcoming schedule changes will allow more consistent outreach, improving sales process control** (26:50)  \n    - She will finalize her own work schedule after handoffs conclude next week to better manage daily activities.  \n    - This consistency aims to enhance follow-up effectiveness and timely communication.  \n\n- **The shared contact spreadsheet is a critical tool for managing leads, but manual processing is time-consuming** (28:26)  \n    - Shane requested highlighting prospects with three or more clicks over time to identify persistent interest.  \n    - Nathalie will generate a list of these high-engagement contacts to focus outreach efforts.  \n\n- **Keenan indicated email communication is more effective than LinkedIn messaging, as prospects check work email regularly** (25:50)  \n    - LinkedIn responses tend to be delayed and fragmented, reducing conversational continuity.  \n\n- **Some prospects with high demo engagement but no contact info prompt consideration of direct phone outreach** (30:40)  \n    - Keenan plans to start calling such companies to break through communication barriers, given written outreach has failed.  \n\n## **Competitive Positioning and Market Insights**\n\nThe team is refining messaging and sales tactics to differentiate the product in a busy market.\n\n- **Shane and Nathalie acknowledged that most software competitors do not offer transparent pricing or self-service sign-ups on their websites** (17:10)  \n    - Their product’s planned shift to online purchasing aims to align with common SaaS models, making buying easier for smaller customers.  \n    - Larger enterprise deals usually involve negotiation, which they currently do not target.  \n\n- **They recognize the need to emphasize time savings as a unique selling point, addressing prospects’ pain points of being overwhelmed and too busy** (02:16)  \n    - This value prop is not yet fully leveraged in campaigns but has potential to boost demo interest and conversion.  \n\n- **The tension between billers and office staff highlights the importance of targeting the right user personas who see the tool’s value** (22:40)  \n    - Billers appreciate transparency and task tracking, while office managers may see adoption as additional work.  \n    - Targeting decision makers in operations roles is critical to overcome internal resistance and accelerate sales.  \n\n- **The team is tracking prospect engagement closely through multiple tools and metrics to better prioritize follow-up and refine messaging** (07:38)  \n    - Data from Storylane demos, email clicks, and website visits help identify high-intent users.  \n    - This data-driven approach aims to improve sales efficiency and conversion rates over time.","outline":null,"keywords":["billers campaign","time-saving value proposition","LinkedIn ads","Storylane demo analytics","product launch","online purchase","lead engagement","trial pricing"],"overview":"- **Demo Scheduling Challenges:** Prospects are too busy to engage, prompting a shift to direct messaging and in-person visits.  \n- **Targeting Decision Makers:** Focusing on operations and clinical managers to improve demo scheduling and engagement effectiveness.  \n- **Time-Saving Messaging:** Emphasizing time savings in marketing materials and exploring video demos to attract busy prospects.  \n- **Conversion Gaps Identified:** Increased web traffic but low form submissions; the contact page may need clearer messaging to enhance conversions.  \n- **New Pricing Strategies:** Launching self-service features and a 30-day trial to attract users, with incentives for early adopters.  \n- **Enhanced Sales Outreach:** Adapting outreach approach to focus on direct communication, utilizing engagement metrics to prioritize pursuits.","action_items":"\n**Keenan Toward**\nIncrease direct outreach messaging using bullet points emphasizing key time-saving features and request demo scheduling this upcoming week (10:00)\nConduct in-person visits to dental offices next week to assess engagement differences from digital outreach (11:36)\nContinue engaging contacts in tab 2 (emails) and tab 3 (highly engaged leads) from the contacts spreadsheet for outreach (26:24)\nConsider initiating phone calls to prospects who repeatedly view demos but do not respond to written communication (30:34)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nUpdate LinkedIn ads to test value propositions focusing on time savings and monitor performance outcomes (03:32)\nImprove copy and clarity of Contact Us page to increase form submission conversion rate (14:19)\nResearch competitors’ website signup and pricing display practices for the upcoming online purchase feature launch (17:31)\nProvide a summary list of contacts with 3+ demo clicks over the historical campaign period for prioritized outreach (28:26)\nContinue sending weekly contact spreadsheets with engagement data, including highlights of highly engaged leads (26:24)\n\n**Shane Billings**\nOversee planning for new feature rollout enabling direct online purchase and setup credit card payments (15:11)\nAdvise Keenan and Natalie on marketing strategy adjustments focusing on value proposition related to time savings (02:13)\nMonitor demo engagement metrics through Storylane and identify high-interest leads (07:38)\nPrepare for website modifications to support account creation and online purchase upon new feature launch (16:54)\nReview pricing and trial offer options and provide input based on market and team feedback (19:30)\n"},"duration":32.150001525878906,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":1,"name":"K"},{"id":2,"name":"Shane Billings"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Then the billers campaign.","index":0,"end_time":1.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":1,"end_time":4.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":3.52,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Hopefully we see some more form submissions.","index":2,"end_time":9.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":6.08,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"That seems to be the best avenue of conversation.","index":3,"end_time":12.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":9.24,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":4,"end_time":15.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":15.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Is there any progress on the ones that came in previously?","index":5,"end_time":19.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":16.24,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So neither of the two that submitted forms last time have scheduled yet.","index":6,"end_time":28.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.88,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"They both said they wanted to.","index":7,"end_time":30.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.57,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And then I reached out for availability and offered Friday and I have no responses from either one, so.","index":8,"end_time":37.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.97,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Bummer.","index":9,"end_time":40.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":39.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Morning.","index":10,"end_time":42.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":42.17,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Morning.","index":11,"end_time":44.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":43.93,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I was.","index":12,"end_time":46.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":46.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That was the thing I was most excited to hear about, but it''s a bummer that they didn''t haven''t responded.","index":13,"end_time":51.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":46.53,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":54.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.93,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And I''m.","index":15,"end_time":54.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.09,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I think I''m done with travel today.","index":16,"end_time":56.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.65,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I''m in my.","index":17,"end_time":58.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":57.45,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I''m in my home area.","index":18,"end_time":59.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":58.17,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"But Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday is when we do client visits and they''re doing handoff accounts.","index":19,"end_time":63.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.21,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So I''ve been meeting people at accounts the last couple of days.","index":20,"end_time":67.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":63.49,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So you''re good, Keenan.","index":21,"end_time":69.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":67.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I think she''s gonna head home today.","index":22,"end_time":71.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":69.69,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So I''m gonna get back in and try to make contact again and see if I can get those scheduled, especially the two that offered phone numbers.","index":23,"end_time":78.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":71.29,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And we''ve already had conversations and they''ve already confirmed they wanted a demo.","index":24,"end_time":84.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.98,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So hopefully we can line a couple of those up.","index":25,"end_time":87.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.58,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Today we had another one, we had Another one on LinkedIn that said this actually looks great, something we could probably use.","index":26,"end_time":99.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.86,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"But right now I''m running an office.","index":27,"end_time":101.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":99.7,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I don''t really have time to do a demo, so maybe I could give it to you at a later time.","index":28,"end_time":105.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.86,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so I offered evenings or weekends to see if that would bite.","index":29,"end_time":109.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.59,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so we''ll see how that plays out today.","index":30,"end_time":111.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.23,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Keenan, this is something.","index":31,"end_time":113.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.99,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"One of the things that''s interesting that we may be able to tap into is people are so busy they can''t even take a 30 minute demo.","index":32,"end_time":123.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":113.67,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like, I don''t know what it''s like to work in those environments, but that is fascinating across the board.","index":33,"end_time":130.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":123.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Everybody''s slammed.","index":34,"end_time":131.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":130.23,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I understand how it is and that''s why I''m not in dental anymore.","index":35,"end_time":135.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.05,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I wonder.","index":36,"end_time":137.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.81,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So the reason I bring that up, I wonder if there.","index":37,"end_time":140.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.69,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Natalie, if there''s something to be said for.","index":38,"end_time":142.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":140.29,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Hey, we can save you time.","index":39,"end_time":144.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.97,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Our tool is designed to save you time.","index":40,"end_time":146.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":144.57,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So you''re not tracking down everybody.","index":41,"end_time":149.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s save you some time.","index":42,"end_time":151.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":150.25,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"In one of our campaigns.","index":43,"end_time":154.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":152.41,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Maybe we touch on that or, or.","index":44,"end_time":158.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":154.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Maybe something to the.","index":45,"end_time":160.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.66,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"To the phrasing of simplify management or.","index":46,"end_time":163.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.58,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Yeah, something about, You know, coaching assistance, because that''s on there.","index":47,"end_time":171.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":163.46,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And I put that in the things that I put to people and I share with people and.","index":48,"end_time":176.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":171.58,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"But you''re so busy, you can''t even read this email.","index":49,"end_time":180.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":177.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s what I would say.","index":50,"end_time":181.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":180.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":51,"end_time":182.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":52,"end_time":183.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":182.42,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Well, even when they get on the call with me, two of them, they''re like talking to people in the background while they''re talking to me.","index":53,"end_time":188.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.43,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And then they''re like, oh, sorry, say that again.","index":54,"end_time":190.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.67,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And it''s like, yeah, yeah, you''re.","index":55,"end_time":193.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":190.31,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You''re so busy, you can''t even read this email, let alone take 30 minutes to meet with me and get a demo.","index":56,"end_time":198.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":193.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean, we do have the demo online.","index":57,"end_time":200.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.55,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They should be able to click through it at their own pace, but I get it.","index":58,"end_time":204.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":200.71,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":59,"end_time":207.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205.27,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So what other updates you have, Natalie?","index":60,"end_time":209.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":207.51,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"How''s the website look?","index":61,"end_time":210.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.63,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a good idea.","index":62,"end_time":214.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":212.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We actually haven''t leaned into time saving as a value prop in any of our campaigns, Shane.","index":63,"end_time":220.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think we''ve mostly focused on simplicity, organization, keeping everything together.","index":64,"end_time":225.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.85,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"But we can maybe update the LinkedIn ads that are running, test out a few that lean into time savings more, see how that performs.","index":65,"end_time":235.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.05,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":66,"end_time":236.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.97,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Just kicking around ideas.","index":67,"end_time":237.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":236.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":68,"end_time":238.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.62,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then just before you jumped on, I updated Keenan that the two new campaigns launched yesterday.","index":69,"end_time":247.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.78,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we have new emails going out to two new groups of people.","index":70,"end_time":251.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":247.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So we should start to see the website, start to kick back up a little bit.","index":71,"end_time":256.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":252.14,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay.","index":72,"end_time":257.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.26,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And then one thing I wanted to check on.","index":73,"end_time":261.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.1,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The LinkedIn numbers are looking really good, almost too good.","index":74,"end_time":265.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.5,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t know if you''ve seen them lately.","index":75,"end_time":266.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":265.18,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, they''re looking good.","index":76,"end_time":268.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":267.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We were able to get the cost per click down quite a bit.","index":77,"end_time":271.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.94,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The number of clicks went up dramatically, but we haven''t seen anybody from it.","index":78,"end_time":278.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":272.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":79,"end_time":281.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.34,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We tightened the targeting as well.","index":80,"end_time":283.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.02,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So it seems like the messaging that people are receiving is more relevant to them where they''re clicking on it.","index":81,"end_time":288.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And now these ads are taking them directly to the website for them to start moving, like, play around on the website, see if they want to fill in the form.","index":82,"end_time":298.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.09,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You know, one of the things about the Storylane and it''s $50 a month, is they''ll give you people who click on them as is.","index":83,"end_time":311.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":300.49,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I don''t know if that''s worth it.","index":84,"end_time":312.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":311.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''ll tell you the number.","index":85,"end_time":313.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.77,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right now it''s the free version, and right now the numbers two.","index":86,"end_time":319.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":314.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So I''m like, if it was more, maybe, but.","index":87,"end_time":321.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":319.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So it shows you the number of people that have done the demo, shows.","index":88,"end_time":328.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.11,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You the number of people who are interested.","index":89,"end_time":331.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":328.91,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They call them engaged users, don''t know what criteria they''re using.","index":90,"end_time":335.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":331.23,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay.","index":91,"end_time":338.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":337.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then if you upgrade, they say.","index":92,"end_time":340.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They''Ll tell you the.","index":93,"end_time":342.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Tell you they''re probably business.","index":94,"end_time":344.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.75,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t think they tell you their names.","index":95,"end_time":346.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":344.51,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Hopefully that doesn''t include me because I go in there and play with the.","index":96,"end_time":351.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.88,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Look through it.","index":97,"end_time":353.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.76,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Probably.","index":98,"end_time":354.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.96,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Let me see if I can look at it real quick, but keep talking.","index":99,"end_time":359.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.72,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":100,"end_time":361.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.56,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then one other thing for the website.","index":101,"end_time":363.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So sessions from Google are slightly down.","index":102,"end_time":366.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.8,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And then like we talked about, part of that is with our discoverability and search engines, which mostly comes from the podcast.","index":103,"end_time":374.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We got to do a podcast tomorrow.","index":104,"end_time":377.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":375.97,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We''ve got it scheduled.","index":105,"end_time":379.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":377.81,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":106,"end_time":381.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.49,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What''s story Lane?","index":107,"end_time":388.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What''s it.","index":108,"end_time":392.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":391.65,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Maybe I got it wrong.","index":109,"end_time":393.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":392.25,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What''s a website storyline?","index":110,"end_time":396.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"There it is.","index":111,"end_time":397.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":397.09,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"All right, keep talking.","index":112,"end_time":400.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":399.7,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, those are all of my updates.","index":113,"end_time":403.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.26,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, so let''s talk strategy for a little bit.","index":114,"end_time":410.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What''s our next steps in the near term?","index":115,"end_time":415.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.54,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I have something long term that I wanted to mention and get us ready for.","index":116,"end_time":419.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":415.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I think what you mentioned today about the new value prop is definitely a good idea that we can lean into.","index":117,"end_time":428.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.9,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think I need to do more brainstorming about the time savings because, I mean, if we''re running into the issue that people don''t even.","index":118,"end_time":437.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":429.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They are interested in the tool and seeing what it can do, but they don''t even have time to get on a call.","index":119,"end_time":442.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":437.91,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"What can we do from the marketing side to show them more value upfront so that they realize that they need to get on this call?","index":120,"end_time":450.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.79,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe it''s.","index":121,"end_time":451.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe the story lane demo doesn''t do enough and it''s maybe recording a video walkthrough of a demo.","index":122,"end_time":457.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.39,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Go and play with it.","index":123,"end_time":459.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":458.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You can see what it is.","index":124,"end_time":460.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":459.25,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I actually think it''s pretty good.","index":125,"end_time":461.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.37,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It actually feels like the real software.","index":126,"end_time":464.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.05,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let me share my screen.","index":127,"end_time":469.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":468.29,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Here''s what you can get from storylane.","index":128,"end_time":472.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.69,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"For example, it''ll say, one day ago, somebody in Zimbabwe had high intent.","index":129,"end_time":479.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":473.49,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It spent 1 minute, 35 seconds in the.","index":130,"end_time":482.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":479.81,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They completed 25% of it.","index":131,"end_time":485.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":482.85,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Here''s somebody in Lancaster in the United states, they completed 27%.","index":132,"end_time":493.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So.","index":133,"end_time":496.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Oh, here''s somebody who completed.","index":134,"end_time":498.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.74,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Somebody in Dallas that completed 100%.","index":135,"end_time":500.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":498.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that''s the lady that I''m talking to.","index":136,"end_time":504.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.86,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Is that right?","index":137,"end_time":505.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.14,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, because I told her she was the one that didn''t have a job listed and wasn''t saying she was working for anybody.","index":138,"end_time":511.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":506.34,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So I referred her there and then had to reach back out to me.","index":139,"end_time":515.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.54,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so she did go there.","index":140,"end_time":516.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":515.58,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"She reached back out and now she wants a demo and she says she is working with a dental organization.","index":141,"end_time":522.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":516.94,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So that''s one of the ones that was supposed to be set up on Friday.","index":142,"end_time":524.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":522.38,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I Gotcha.","index":143,"end_time":525.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.18,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I haven''t heard back from Soapley today.","index":144,"end_time":527.899,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":526.06,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"When I get in, we''ll get a response from her.","index":145,"end_time":531.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":527.899,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Here''s somebody else from Salt LAKE who did 100%.","index":146,"end_time":535.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"As far as somebody I know.","index":147,"end_time":536.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s 24 days ago.","index":148,"end_time":539.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s kind of too long.","index":149,"end_time":540.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":539.71,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So 71%, 69.","index":150,"end_time":542.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Someone else.","index":151,"end_time":543.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":542.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And Lancaster, again, 100% liked it so much to do it twice anyway.","index":152,"end_time":550.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean, account.","index":153,"end_time":551.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":550.39,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t know what that means.","index":154,"end_time":553.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":552.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I don''t know account session details.","index":155,"end_time":557.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":553.67,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Huh.","index":156,"end_time":559.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.55,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I''m wondering what it would show you.","index":157,"end_time":561.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know they.","index":158,"end_time":562.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.75,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You don''t have any idea, so I don''t know.","index":159,"end_time":565.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I.","index":160,"end_time":565.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":565.53,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"My suspicion is they''re not gonna.","index":161,"end_time":567.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":566.17,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s not gonna have a name.","index":162,"end_time":568.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.89,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":163,"end_time":570.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.93,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"There''s no way to know.","index":164,"end_time":571.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":570.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":165,"end_time":572.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":571.77,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Who are you?","index":166,"end_time":572.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.09,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You''re an IP address.","index":167,"end_time":573.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":572.89,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So anyway, so.","index":168,"end_time":579.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":574.97,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So short term, it sounds like we''re getting.","index":169,"end_time":584.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":582.41,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keenan, you''re getting some TR.","index":170,"end_time":586.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.73,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"On some of these.","index":171,"end_time":592.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":591.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I, I look at that as being promising.","index":172,"end_time":594.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":592.1,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Maybe our short term strategy is to continue down that path.","index":173,"end_time":598.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":174,"end_time":599.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.14,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So what I''m trying to do is I taken a different approach every week because I can be very direct and getting somebody to either engage or not engage.","index":175,"end_time":611.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.62,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so I''ve tried to open them up slowly over the last couple of weeks to see if I could get them to schedule a demo.","index":176,"end_time":616.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.02,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"But because time is a concern and I know how I am when I have no time, I think I am at the point where I might try a week because what I do is I pick five to eight people, depending on what their engagement was, if they responded, things of that nature, and then I decide how I want to approach them all.","index":177,"end_time":635.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.03,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And I''m kind of making a list for myself of what approach I''ve taken with them.","index":178,"end_time":638.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.27,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And I think this week what I might do is try a more direct approach and say, hey, these are the key things that it does for you in saving time.","index":179,"end_time":648.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.71,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"The coaching piece, the managing revenue.","index":180,"end_time":651.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":648.04,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So I have like four or five bullet points that I use and I might just put that in there and ask to schedule a demo this week and see if that gets a different response than the slow opening.","index":181,"end_time":664.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":652.8,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"The problem with the slow opening is they''ll respond a couple times and then they disappear.","index":182,"end_time":668.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.32,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And you might not hear from them for four or five days.","index":183,"end_time":670.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.28,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so if we don''t get to, hey, let''s have a demo or let''s get on a call together, I think that we''re just becoming a social media buddy and it runs its course.","index":184,"end_time":681.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.96,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so I think I might try a more direct approach.","index":185,"end_time":684.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.14,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"This week and try to just get demos scheduled and see if that works differently than a slow open.","index":186,"end_time":692.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.7,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":187,"end_time":694.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":693.66,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m also next week.","index":188,"end_time":698.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.3,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I don''t have in person visits for part of the week, so.","index":189,"end_time":703.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.34,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So I''m going to go to the dental offices in Farmington and see what in person response is different than LinkedIn.","index":190,"end_time":711.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":703.22,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I''m just curious if people will engage differently with somebody in front of them or if it''s going to be the sorry, we''re too busy, we can''t talk to you kind of thing.","index":191,"end_time":719.539,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.86,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":192,"end_time":720.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":720.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Might also be worthwhile going back to some old leads that we''ve let sit for a while and see if their interest has peaked again.","index":193,"end_time":726.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":720.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So some of the ones that we had emails on, I''ve already emailed too and got no responses on any of those either.","index":194,"end_time":733.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":728.98,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Okay, well, yeah, no, those all sound like we''re on the right, doing the right things.","index":195,"end_time":740.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":734.6,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"One thing I''m wondering, Keenan, as you''re having these conversations, would it be helpful to have some more sales enablement content?","index":196,"end_time":749.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.48,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You think so?","index":197,"end_time":750.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like if it''s like a one pager that describes like a grip on at a glance, these are the key features.","index":198,"end_time":756.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":750.64,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Do you think that would maybe help them understand the value more quickly and get them on a call?","index":199,"end_time":761.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":756.04,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"A one pager may, but I''m putting bullet points in a message and they''re not responding to, they''re responding to the bullet points.","index":200,"end_time":770.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":763.06,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"They''re saying, yeah, that all seems like, you know, it''d be beneficial to us.","index":201,"end_time":773.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.02,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"That''s something that we''re looking for.","index":202,"end_time":775.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.54,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"But it''s the next step of saying, okay, let''s get a demo scheduled.","index":203,"end_time":780.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.46,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And the other part of this that I''m sure we all think about, but we don''t say it out loud often enough, I don''t think is when we''re doing these campaigns, you''re not necessarily getting the person who''s a decision maker.","index":204,"end_time":793.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.74,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so a lot of these people may be interested at the point of would this help my day to day, Would this help my job?","index":205,"end_time":799.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":793.32,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"But then they still may have to go through two or three layers to get the company to make a decision to bring that on.","index":206,"end_time":805.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.88,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so I think that''s where we lose some engagement with some people.","index":207,"end_time":809.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":806.2,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And that''s why I''ve started to document the roles that they''re in to try to see if is there a certain role or level that triggers and makes these decisions.","index":208,"end_time":817.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.44,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And what I''ve started to learn is it''s more operations.","index":209,"end_time":819.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.26,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"A lot of the office managers say I can''t do anything.","index":210,"end_time":822.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.74,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I''M too busy right now.","index":211,"end_time":823.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":822.22,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I can''t talk to you.","index":212,"end_time":824.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.3,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So I''ve tried to focus on operations managers or clinical operations or RCM managers and above in order to try to get some engagement.","index":213,"end_time":833.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":824.7,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Because I was talking to some of the lower level staff in the beginning and they''re the ones that just kind of have a conversation back and forth and then disappear.","index":214,"end_time":841.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":833.86,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"It doesn''t seem like they take it anywhere.","index":215,"end_time":844.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":842.84,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And maybe that''s because they don''t feel like they''re strong enough to make a change within their organization or they don''t have the role for it, but.","index":216,"end_time":852.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.16,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So I''ve tried to focus more on the higher level.","index":217,"end_time":854.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.76,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Okay, this is what''s interesting to me is the Contact Us is just doing great, but nobody fills it in.","index":218,"end_time":873.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":859.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Why is that?","index":219,"end_time":874.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":873.36,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Are these bots?","index":220,"end_time":875.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.48,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean, like across the site, no matter what page they land on, the only.","index":221,"end_time":882.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":877.92,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Pretty much the only CTA or the place they can go is the contact page.","index":222,"end_time":886.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":883.2,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like that''s what we drive everyone toward.","index":223,"end_time":889.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe doing a diagnosis of the copy on the contact page.","index":224,"end_time":897.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe it''s unclear what exactly they''re going to get out of filling in the form.","index":225,"end_time":903.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Could be what''s causing some hesitation.","index":226,"end_time":905.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.3,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So let me work on that.","index":227,"end_time":907.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That would be good.","index":228,"end_time":909.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":908.5,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''d appreciate that.","index":229,"end_time":910.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":909.26,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"If they keep.","index":230,"end_time":912.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because we are getting a ton of traffic to the like.","index":231,"end_time":916.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.7,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s a lot.","index":232,"end_time":917.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":916.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"200 people almost in the last 30 days.","index":233,"end_time":920.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":917.94,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":234,"end_time":922.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And that''s where we want them.","index":235,"end_time":923.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":922.44,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So yeah, let''s.","index":236,"end_time":925.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.2,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Let''s look at that and see.","index":237,"end_time":927.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I think that''s another good thing to test and see if that''s something to change.","index":238,"end_time":930.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":927.24,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We don''t have any current changes to the website plan, do we?","index":239,"end_time":935.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"No, not right now.","index":240,"end_time":936.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.72,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, so yeah, that would be something to consider.","index":241,"end_time":942.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, so this is what I wanted to talk about long term.","index":242,"end_time":945.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":943.4,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I''ve talked.","index":243,"end_time":946.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.84,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Keenan, I''ve mention this to you.","index":244,"end_time":948.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.64,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right now we''re probably two weeks to a month out from finishing our next feature.","index":245,"end_time":957.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.57,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then we''re going to work on direct credit card.","index":246,"end_time":963.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":960.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I can purchase a grip on online and I don''t have to go through anybody.","index":247,"end_time":972.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":966.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I just sign up and then I can use it as much as I want.","index":248,"end_time":977.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":972.81,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We''ll have to.","index":249,"end_time":979.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":978.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So we need to start thinking price point.","index":250,"end_time":981.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":979.3,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because once we do that, our price point is pretty locked in because we''ll publish it.","index":251,"end_time":985.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":981.86,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We don''t know our price point now because no one''s purchased it.","index":252,"end_time":989.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":987.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Then the other thing is, is that we''ll need to change our website to reflect a purchase.","index":253,"end_time":998.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":991.7,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Right.","index":254,"end_time":999.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.63,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And so we''ll need.","index":255,"end_time":1007.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1004.59,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We''ll need to modify the website and potentially have campaigns around that.","index":256,"end_time":1011.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1007.35,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":257,"end_time":1014.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1014.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So directly on the website it would be basically they''d have a create an account option, right?","index":258,"end_time":1022.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1016.99,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, like just a normal, like a normal business, like a grown up business would do.","index":259,"end_time":1029.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1023.31,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah and that''s interesting because a lot of, I mean majority of software websites that I come across, they do the same thing of you know, you need to book that meeting.","index":260,"end_time":1042.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They don''t put their price very transparently on the site or allow you to sign up yourself.","index":261,"end_time":1048.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.66,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I''ll do some research on someone.","index":262,"end_time":1050.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1048.98,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So I mean.","index":263,"end_time":1052.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1051.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, do some research, see what others do.","index":264,"end_time":1054.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1052.3,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, but you know, like it''s not uncommon.","index":265,"end_time":1058.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1055.66,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like think about every website that just has you purchase within the website.","index":266,"end_time":1063.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"When I do tools like even story lane like that $50 I would just click a button, put a credit card in and good to go.","index":267,"end_time":1073.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1063.66,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":268,"end_time":1074.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.38,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"The usually companies that don''t publish or.","index":269,"end_time":1079.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1075.66,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So if I wanted to, if I was a multi billion dollar company and I was selling my software, it would be negotiations, millions of dollars.","index":270,"end_time":1091.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1080.71,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''d be like if I wanted a thousand Microsoft licenses, I wouldn''t go and purchase a thousand.","index":271,"end_time":1100.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1091.59,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''d go to Microsoft and go give me a deal.","index":272,"end_time":1102.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1100.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We''re kind of playing in that space of give me a deal.","index":273,"end_time":1106.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1103.91,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Well, we''re kind of small and it''s just not necessary to give me a deal.","index":274,"end_time":1112.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1108.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":275,"end_time":1113.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1113.18,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"And maybe that registration.","index":276,"end_time":1118.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1116.06,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"One thing to think about, and I''ll put some more thought into this as well is do we launch it as a single office.","index":277,"end_time":1127.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.3,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"For a trial with an enablement call from us or that they could sign up for for free.","index":278,"end_time":1140.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1132.22,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And if it''s multiple offices, we, we do a trial where whenever we launch it for the first 90 days we put them at a hundred dollars in office versus 139 being the price point which I think honestly 139 is the price point that I would go at, at the software based on the conversations I''ve had, what other things they use, what price points are other softwares at and what seems to trigger a response.","index":279,"end_time":1169.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1140.52,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Okay, let me, let me say this about that.","index":280,"end_time":1173.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1169.72,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And, and if you do it by office, say the first office is free, then what will happen is they''ll just pile on all their communication into one office and then, and then we''ll lose the, the.","index":281,"end_time":1190.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.64,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"In other words, they, there''s no incentive to put a second office in if they''ve got one office for free.","index":282,"end_time":1196.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1190.77,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":283,"end_time":1204.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1203.09,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"What are your thoughts on that?","index":284,"end_time":1205.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1204.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I mean I would like that not be the case because I think if you could get somebody like an office manager or an operations manager to trial one office.","index":285,"end_time":1214.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.77,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Then there is the potential conversation of adding other offices on with results.","index":286,"end_time":1219.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1216.42,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So I wish there was a way that we could prevent that from happening, but if there''s not, then it''s probably.","index":287,"end_time":1226.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.82,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"It''s probably a timed.","index":288,"end_time":1228.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1227.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Timed trial rather than a office''s trial.","index":289,"end_time":1236.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1228.66,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, if I was going to do anything free, I would give them 30 days because either you use it or you don''t.","index":290,"end_time":1242.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.98,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"If you''re not using it in the 30 days, then, then it''s over, right?","index":291,"end_time":1246.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.69,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Yeah, No, I think that''s reasonable.","index":292,"end_time":1249.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1246.69,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"30 days for free.","index":293,"end_time":1250.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1249.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And fundamentally we''ve already got that kind of in places manually, but yeah, we could do first 30 days free.","index":294,"end_time":1259.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1250.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":295,"end_time":1260.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.97,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Like you could do a single office on your own and give it a try without having the headache of talking to anybody.","index":296,"end_time":1265.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1260.29,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And you get 30 days.","index":297,"end_time":1267.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.13,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Or if you register during the opening period, opening 90 days, you get it at a hundred dollars for your first year, $100 in office for your first year.","index":298,"end_time":1278.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.34,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"We could do.","index":299,"end_time":1279.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1278.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, we could do like sign up for a year and.","index":300,"end_time":1282.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1279.46,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And get all these offices.","index":301,"end_time":1284.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1282.22,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I like that a lot.","index":302,"end_time":1288.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So that''s a good way for discounts, you know, pay up front.","index":303,"end_time":1291.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1288.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We''ll have to design the software for that.","index":304,"end_time":1294.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1292.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Currently, it''s just a very simple pay by month.","index":305,"end_time":1297.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1295.14,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We don''t have many.","index":306,"end_time":1298.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1297.38,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"We don''t have multiple options.","index":307,"end_time":1300.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1299.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And maybe we''ll do a soft launch where we just do that and then we grow into offerings.","index":308,"end_time":1305.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1300.42,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":309,"end_time":1311.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.38,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"The good news for me.","index":310,"end_time":1312.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.74,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Go ahead, Natalie.","index":311,"end_time":1314.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1313.86,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"We.","index":312,"end_time":1315.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.22,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We had the idea of.","index":313,"end_time":1317.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1315.58,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Since for a couple of months, we''ve been collecting all the people that have had a lot of email clicks.","index":314,"end_time":1321.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1317.46,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Maybe that could be the first group that we send this campaign to.","index":315,"end_time":1325.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1322.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"They now have the option to try it free for 30 days.","index":316,"end_time":1329.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1326.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":317,"end_time":1330,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.6,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The ones who have clicked on it multiple times.","index":318,"end_time":1331.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1330,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"You should just try it.","index":319,"end_time":1333.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1332.08,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, exactly.","index":320,"end_time":1335.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1333.84,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"You should just try it.","index":321,"end_time":1335.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1335.24,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And what''s interesting.","index":322,"end_time":1336.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1335.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"This is interesting to me.","index":323,"end_time":1338.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1337.36,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"If you do it at that level, I don''t need manager approval.","index":324,"end_time":1342.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.04,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I could be like a biller and be like, I like it, I want to buy it for me and just my office.","index":325,"end_time":1348.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1344.32,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yep.","index":326,"end_time":1353.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1353.09,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Those have been the better conversations, to be honest.","index":327,"end_time":1357.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1355.25,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"The billers.","index":328,"end_time":1358.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1357.73,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":329,"end_time":1359.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1359.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The people in offices immediately are busy and doing something and don''t have time.","index":330,"end_time":1367.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1360.45,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"But the billers are actually thinking about how it could save them time, how it could add transparency to their provider communication, things of that nature.","index":331,"end_time":1376.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1367.17,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So the conversations on the biller side have been much, much different than.","index":332,"end_time":1380.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1376.64,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s what We''ve noticed, too, the offices feel like you''re just giving me extra work to do.","index":333,"end_time":1385.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1380.64,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Every request to me is like, oh, I got to do more work.","index":334,"end_time":1389.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1386.6,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The biller thinks you''re not responding.","index":335,"end_time":1391.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1389.48,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s it.","index":336,"end_time":1392.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1391.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"There''s a tension between the two.","index":337,"end_time":1394.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1392.84,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Well, in an office.","index":338,"end_time":1395.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1394.92,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"An office manager can''t launch anything.","index":339,"end_time":1398.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1396.44,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Typically.","index":340,"end_time":1398.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.32,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Typically, that''s an operational decision.","index":341,"end_time":1400.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.16,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so if you went into an office like a. Brad walked in an office today, and they''re like, we''re trying this new software, and I have my.","index":342,"end_time":1407.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1401.66,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I''m coaching my team on.","index":343,"end_time":1408.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1407.18,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"He''d be like, don''t waste your time there.","index":344,"end_time":1409.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1408.26,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"We have a plan already.","index":345,"end_time":1411.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1409.82,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And then those things get shut down very quickly in offices, you know.","index":346,"end_time":1414.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1411.26,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And so I think that''s the difference as a biller is looking at it as if my team is all using this.","index":347,"end_time":1419.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1414.86,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I know what my team is doing exactly.","index":348,"end_time":1421.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1419.98,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And it provides the communication I need to go directly to a provider.","index":349,"end_time":1425.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1421.74,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"It gives me the reporting, it gives me the tools to say, these are your offices not, you know, complying with what we''re doing.","index":350,"end_time":1432.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1425.66,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"This is the offices that we''re having issues with.","index":351,"end_time":1435.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.03,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"This is the amount of revenue you have stalled right now in your communications.","index":352,"end_time":1438.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1435.27,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"This is the amount of tasks that people are taking in.","index":353,"end_time":1441.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1439.59,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"It''s all in there for them.","index":354,"end_time":1442.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.67,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So for a biller, I feel like it''s very effective and simple communication for what they''re trying to do.","index":355,"end_time":1447.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1442.83,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"But in an office, they''re.","index":356,"end_time":1449.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1447.91,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"They''re greeting a patient and they''re running stuff back to a provider, and they''re ordering office supplies, and they''re ordering dental supplies, and their operations managers coming in and telling them they need to have a meeting with them, and they''re just going in so many different directions, they never make a decision.","index":357,"end_time":1464.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1449.51,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":358,"end_time":1466.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.09,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, well, good.","index":359,"end_time":1468.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.57,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So keep that in the back of your mind.","index":360,"end_time":1470.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1468.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''ll let you know the closer we get.","index":361,"end_time":1472.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.57,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like I said, we''re two to four weeks out from hopefully releasing that last one, and we''ll start working on the other.","index":362,"end_time":1478.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1472.57,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Credit cards are actually pretty complex, so it''s going to take a little bit of time.","index":363,"end_time":1482.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1478.33,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And my developer is part time, which is also part of the problem.","index":364,"end_time":1487.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1484.73,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"The other thing that had is.","index":365,"end_time":1495.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1491.85,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Is Keenan, is that spreadsheet that has got contacts on it.","index":366,"end_time":1500.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1496.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Is that useful to you at all?","index":367,"end_time":1503.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1502.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Which spreadsheet?","index":368,"end_time":1507.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1506.73,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I have a few that I''m just.","index":369,"end_time":1510.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1507.77,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"The one that Natalie shares once a week with all the contacts.","index":370,"end_time":1513.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1510.06,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I. I glance at it, and if I glance at it, if there''s anything new in there based on roles and Things like that.","index":371,"end_time":1520.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1514.1,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"That''s how I decide who I''m going to engage in communications for that week.","index":372,"end_time":1525.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1520.98,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"The first week I communicated with all eight people and I got responses from three.","index":373,"end_time":1530.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1526.1,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I think the second week I communicated with eight people through LinkedIn and then another three through email.","index":374,"end_time":1539.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1530.98,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And email actually is once.","index":375,"end_time":1541.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1540.12,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"If I get them to email, the communication is better because it''s something I have to check for work anyway.","index":376,"end_time":1546.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1541.8,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"But LinkedIn seems like one of those things where, like, they put it away and I might hear from for a week or more and then they come back and respond to something and it''s like, I gotta go back and read the conversation again and like, what were we talking about?","index":377,"end_time":1557.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1547,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"What did we do?","index":378,"end_time":1558.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1557.72,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I guess what I''m getting at is we''d like to make that as useful to you as you can so you look at new people.","index":379,"end_time":1563.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.08,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"How about the tabs?","index":380,"end_time":1564.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1563.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Do you focus on the tabs?","index":381,"end_time":1566.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1564.92,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Any tabs stand out to you as being helpful?","index":382,"end_time":1569.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1567.01,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So the ones with the really engaged companies.","index":383,"end_time":1573.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1571.17,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"The third tab, I think is the first tab.","index":384,"end_time":1577.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1574.53,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And the third tab, I think.","index":385,"end_time":1579.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1577.89,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Which one has phone numbers?","index":386,"end_time":1581.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.13,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I''m not at a computer.","index":387,"end_time":1582.729,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1581.57,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I''m on my phone right now, so I can''t.","index":388,"end_time":1584.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1582.729,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I have it right now.","index":389,"end_time":1585.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1584.29,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I''m looking at it.","index":390,"end_time":1586.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1585.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"There''s no phone numbers on any of them that I''ve seen.","index":391,"end_time":1588.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1586.45,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So I think Tab 2 has phone numbers.","index":392,"end_time":1592.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1589.89,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Oh, no, it has the email addresses.","index":393,"end_time":1594.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1593.13,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So tab two is where I engage those two.","index":394,"end_time":1598.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1595.21,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I use their emails.","index":395,"end_time":1599.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1598.49,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So tab two and Tab three, the people that have a lot of engagement, that tells me they''re struggling with something and they''re looking for a solution.","index":396,"end_time":1607.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1600.73,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So that''s.","index":397,"end_time":1607.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.37,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I think tab three is important as well.","index":398,"end_time":1609.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1607.93,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Okay, so Tab two and tab three, I''m looking at them because they have emails.","index":399,"end_time":1615.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1610.81,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Tab one less so.","index":400,"end_time":1617.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1615.53,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because it''s not.","index":401,"end_time":1619.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1618.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":402,"end_time":1620.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1620.26,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And so is there something we can do that Natalie can do to make this more useful to you?","index":403,"end_time":1626.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1622.02,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Meaning, like highlighting stuff?","index":404,"end_time":1628.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1626.9,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Are you getting what you want, or would you change our process to highlight things or make it more useful to you?","index":405,"end_time":1633.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1628.58,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"In tabs two and three, I wouldn''t change anything yet.","index":406,"end_time":1638.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.98,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"The piece that I was adding a minute ago next week is my last week of handoffs, where I have somebody else creating my schedule.","index":407,"end_time":1646.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1639.86,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And they are not organized people.","index":408,"end_time":1648.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1647.53,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"It''s.","index":409,"end_time":1649.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1649.05,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"It''s.","index":410,"end_time":1650.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1650.41,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"It''s inhumane to tell somebody they have to be on somebody else''s timeline because they''re, they''re just not effective.","index":411,"end_time":1656.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1650.77,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So after next week, I actually am going to try to create what my schedule will normally be in consistency with this and so I don''t want to make a whole lot of changes right now because I know where things are at.","index":412,"end_time":1671.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.33,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And because this next week is going to be busy as well.","index":413,"end_time":1673.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1671.09,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I''m going to try to get through this next week where I can actually create a daily schedule of what I''m trying to accomplish that I can control.","index":414,"end_time":1682.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1675.43,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":415,"end_time":1684.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1683.27,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":416,"end_time":1686.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1685.83,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So, Natalie, I know we''re at Time.","index":417,"end_time":1688.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1686.27,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Could you do me a Favor for Tab 3?","index":418,"end_time":1691.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1688.95,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I want to see when people are.","index":419,"end_time":1694.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1691.83,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I want you to highlight when people are three or more.","index":420,"end_time":1697.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1694.19,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I see a lot of twos.","index":421,"end_time":1702,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1700.48,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":422,"end_time":1706.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1706,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":423,"end_time":1707.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1707.44,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"This.","index":424,"end_time":1708.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1707.88,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"So this is showing for the past week.","index":425,"end_time":1710.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1708.32,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Specifically, do you want to see three or more in the past week?","index":426,"end_time":1714.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1711.36,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Actually, what I would like to see if we could go back.","index":427,"end_time":1717.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1714.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Because what we do.","index":428,"end_time":1719.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1718.4,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah, what we do is I send you at the end of the month who had three or more clicks that month.","index":429,"end_time":1724.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1720.16,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Like, I get it.","index":430,"end_time":1726.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1725.59,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So for, like.","index":431,"end_time":1727.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1726.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But there are people over the.","index":432,"end_time":1729.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1727.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Over the history of this communication.","index":433,"end_time":1731.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1729.27,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They''re clicking on it multiple times.","index":434,"end_time":1733.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1731.35,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Two.","index":435,"end_time":1734.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1733.75,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"All right.","index":436,"end_time":1734.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1734.15,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But three means I''m really interested.","index":437,"end_time":1736.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1734.71,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And if we could just get a list of those people.","index":438,"end_time":1738.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1736.63,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, sure.","index":439,"end_time":1740.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1739.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":440,"end_time":1741.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1740.71,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":441,"end_time":1742.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1742.07,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It just.","index":442,"end_time":1743.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1742.79,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"It tells us they''re still looking for a solution.","index":443,"end_time":1745.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1743.43,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And if we can say, hey, you know, it''s from January to.","index":444,"end_time":1750.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1745.71,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"To March or whatever that time frame is, you know, over three months, you''ve clicked seven times.","index":445,"end_time":1755.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1750.03,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"You''re still looking for a solution.","index":446,"end_time":1756.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1755.39,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Let us have this call.","index":447,"end_time":1758.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1756.91,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"That''s.","index":448,"end_time":1759.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1758.59,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"That''s more of a direct message.","index":449,"end_time":1761.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1759.07,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"And I guess what I would.","index":450,"end_time":1763.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1761.71,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So this is a lot of information that you have to manually go through.","index":451,"end_time":1766.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1763.67,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"If you could summarize it into.","index":452,"end_time":1769.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1767.23,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Here''s the number of people that communicated three times.","index":453,"end_time":1772.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1769.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They''re the last time that they''ve communicated.","index":454,"end_time":1776.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1772.91,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Would that be useful to you, Keenan?","index":455,"end_time":1780.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1779,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be.","index":456,"end_time":1785.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1784.6,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"That''d be good.","index":457,"end_time":1786.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1785.44,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Okay.","index":458,"end_time":1787.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1786.6,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And then the other.","index":459,"end_time":1789.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1787.64,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I think we''ll just.","index":460,"end_time":1791.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1790.36,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I love.","index":461,"end_time":1791.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1791.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I love the highlight in green and.","index":462,"end_time":1794.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1791.88,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And other things.","index":463,"end_time":1795.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1795.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I think I''ve done some of that work.","index":464,"end_time":1797.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1795.88,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I think that''s really good.","index":465,"end_time":1799.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1798.28,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And I love this new prospect.","index":466,"end_time":1803.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1801.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Ruin the site.","index":467,"end_time":1803.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1803.16,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Like this notes.","index":468,"end_time":1804.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1803.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"I. I read those.","index":469,"end_time":1805.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.8,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Those really helpful medical billing.","index":470,"end_time":1807.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1805.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"This medical billing one''s interesting.","index":471,"end_time":1810.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1808.11,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"10.","index":472,"end_time":1811.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1810.91,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"10 employees.","index":473,"end_time":1812.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1811.35,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"This one''s got 51 to 20.","index":474,"end_time":1815.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1812.15,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They''ve had two.","index":475,"end_time":1816.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1815.43,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Two views.","index":476,"end_time":1816.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.23,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"This one''s had 36 views.","index":477,"end_time":1818.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1816.83,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"And they only have 10 employees.","index":478,"end_time":1820.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1818.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s why that pops up almost every week.","index":479,"end_time":1825.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1822.51,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":480,"end_time":1826.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1825.79,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So.","index":481,"end_time":1826.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1826.23,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So, Keenan, this is one Brazos Soms.","index":482,"end_time":1830.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1827.39,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s.","index":483,"end_time":1830.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1830.35,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"If you click on it, it''s actually a different one.","index":484,"end_time":1832.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1830.75,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They are viewing it 36 times since October.","index":485,"end_time":1835.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1832.47,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"They keep viewing it and they only have 10 employees.","index":486,"end_time":1839.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1835.45,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So.","index":487,"end_time":1839.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1839.53,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, so I looked up there.","index":488,"end_time":1842.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1840.49,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I looked up their website, and they have a couple of contact emails on their website, but I didn''t get a response from them.","index":489,"end_time":1848.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1842.25,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So it might be something where I just start.","index":490,"end_time":1851.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1849.61,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"I might just start calling at this point because unfortunately, written communication doesn''t seem, you know, obviously like you and I talked about.","index":491,"end_time":1864.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1851.37,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"It''s what we''re solving for with our software is they.","index":492,"end_time":1866.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1864.13,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"They''re not good at communication.","index":493,"end_time":1868.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1866.53,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"So maybe the verbal is the solution.","index":494,"end_time":1871.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1868.17,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Yeah, here''s one.","index":495,"end_time":1873.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1872.41,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Since seven.","index":496,"end_time":1874.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1873.21,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Since October, only 10.","index":497,"end_time":1875.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1874.09,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s.","index":498,"end_time":1876.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1875.61,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"It''s very similar.","index":499,"end_time":1876.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1876.05,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"So it''s hard to get in touch with them because we don''t have any contact information.","index":500,"end_time":1880.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1877.13,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"But I do like reading this and anyway, so.","index":501,"end_time":1885.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1880.73,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Yeah, all right.","index":502,"end_time":1888.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1886.65,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"That''s all I had.","index":503,"end_time":1889.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1888.82,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":504,"end_time":1892.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1890.82,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"We''ll work on making that list of everyone that''s ever had three plus clicks, and I''ll send it over when it''s ready.","index":505,"end_time":1897.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1892.42,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"That would be good.","index":506,"end_time":1899.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1898.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"All right, thank you.","index":507,"end_time":1901.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1900.34,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Okay, thanks.","index":508,"end_time":1902.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1901.5,"speaker_name":"K"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":509,"end_time":1903.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1902.74,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right, bye.","index":510,"end_time":1904.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1903.3,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Bye.","index":511,"end_time":1904.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1904.26,"speaker_name":"Shane Billings"},{"text":"Bye.","index":512,"end_time":1905.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1905.06,"speaker_name":"K"}],"dateString":"2026-02-05T13:30:00.000Z","host_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83663022990?pwd=R1aTMdTGv2yblYfzlB6Wv1Sup4Z47U.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,david.edmund.reynolds@gmail.com,shane@agrippon.com,f.dominguez@agrippon.com,j.samstag@agrippon.com,monique.king@agrippon.com,david.reynolds@agrippon.com,keenan.toward@agrippon.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","david.edmund.reynolds@gmail.com","shane@agrippon.com","f.dominguez@agrippon.com","j.samstag@agrippon.com","monique.king@agrippon.com","david.reynolds@agrippon.com","keenan.toward@agrippon.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KG5NMVW6HW5Q5766BDDSEYSD","organizer_email":"nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.9,"bullets":["Launched two new email campaigns targeting distinct user segments to boost form submissions and engagement.","Agreed to test new messaging emphasizing time-saving benefits in ads and outreach materials.","Planned upcoming site update to improve Contact Us page clarity after observing high traffic but low conversions.","Aligned on more direct outreach approach for demos to address drop-off after initial interest.","Mapped future strategy to enable in-product purchasing with pricing and trial model under discussion."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Maybe our short term strategy is to continue down that path.","speaker":"Shane Billings"},{"quote":"We actually haven''t leaned into time saving as a value prop in any of our campaigns.","speaker":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"quote":"This week and try to just get demos scheduled and see if that works differently than a slow open.","speaker":"K"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","strategy","conversion","pricing","messaging"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-06T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Engagement and Demo Scheduling**\n\nThe team is facing challenges scheduling demos due to prospects’ extreme time constraints and role limitations.\n\n- **Keenan reported no scheduled demos from the two recent form submitters despite follow-up attempts with Friday availability offered** (00:22)  \n    - Both prospects confirmed interest but failed to respond to scheduling outreach.  \n    - Keenan noted prospects are so busy they struggle even to read emails or attend 30-minute demos.  \n    - She plans to try a more direct, time-saving focused messaging approach this week to prompt demo scheduling.  \n    - Keenan will also conduct in-person visits next week to test if face-to-face engagement improves response rates compared to LinkedIn.  \n\n- **Keenan identified a key barrier: many initial contacts are not decision makers, leading to stalled engagement** (12:43)  \n    - She is now targeting operations managers, clinical operations, and RCM managers, rather than office managers or lower-level staff.  \n    - This shift aims to reach individuals with authority to move purchasing decisions forward.  \n    - Billers have shown more interest as they see direct value in saving time and improving communication transparency.  \n    - Shane and Keenan discussed the tension between billers, who want the tool, and office staff, who feel it adds work.  \n\n- **Shane suggested emphasizing time savings as a core value proposition in marketing campaigns** (02:16)  \n    - Nathalie agreed to update LinkedIn ads to test messaging around saving time and simplifying management.  \n    - They plan to create sales enablement materials highlighting key time-saving features to accelerate demo scheduling.  \n    - The team will explore recording a video walkthrough demo to provide more upfront value for busy prospects.  \n\n- **Keenan uses weekly segmented contact lists prioritizing prospects with emails and high engagement for outreach** (25:14)  \n    - She focuses on Tab 2 (emails) and Tab 3 (engaged contacts) from the shared spreadsheet.  \n    - Shane requested Nathalie highlight contacts with three or more clicks historically to identify highly interested prospects.  \n    - Nathalie will prepare a list of all contacts with three-plus clicks for targeted outreach.  \n\n## **Marketing Campaign and Website Performance**\n\nRecent campaigns show improved click engagement but limited conversion to form submissions or demos.\n\n- **Nathalie reported launching two new email campaigns yesterday targeting two new groups, expected to increase website activity** (03:58)  \n    - LinkedIn ads have seen a significant increase in clicks with cost per click reduced substantially (04:27).  \n    - Targeting has been tightened to improve message relevance, driving more qualified traffic to the website (04:39).  \n    - Despite more clicks, form completions remain low, indicating a conversion gap.  \n\n- **Website sessions from Google searches have slightly decreased, partly due to limited podcast-driven discoverability** (06:01)  \n    - A podcast episode is scheduled for tomorrow to boost search engine traffic and organic awareness (06:15).  \n\n- **The contact page is the main call to action across the site, but form fill rates are low despite nearly 200 visitors in the past 30 days** (14:19)  \n    - Nathalie will review and potentially revise the contact page copy to clarify the value of filling the form.  \n    - Shane emphasized the importance of this fix to increase conversion from high traffic volumes.  \n\n- **Storylane demo tool is used to track prospect engagement with online demos, with free and paid versions available** (05:00)  \n    - Shane shared specific engagement data: some users complete up to 100% of the demo with sessions lasting over a minute.  \n    - Keenan identified these active demo users as previously contacted prospects, validating their interest.  \n    - While Storylane does not reveal identities, it provides useful engagement metrics to prioritize outreach.  \n\n## **Product Launch and Pricing Strategy**\n\nThe team is preparing for a near-term launch of a self-service purchase feature, requiring pricing and website updates.\n\n- **Shane projected the next feature release in two to four weeks, followed by enabling direct credit card purchases online** (15:37)  \n    - This will allow users to create accounts and buy subscriptions without sales interaction.  \n    - The website will need redesign to incorporate account creation and purchasing workflows reflecting this change (16:54).  \n    - Campaigns will be updated to promote self-service sign-ups and pricing transparency.  \n\n- **Pricing discussions centered on setting the software’s price point and trial model** (18:36)  \n    - Keenan recommended a base price of **$139 per office per year** based on market research and customer conversations (18:50).  \n    - Shane cautioned against free trials per office, fearing customers would consolidate usage into one free office and avoid paying for others.  \n    - They agreed a **30-day time-limited free trial** is preferable to encourage usage without risking dilution of multi-office sales (20:06).  \n    - An early adopter promotion could offer a discounted **$100 per office for the first year** during the initial 90-day launch window (20:59).  \n\n- **Nathalie suggested targeting highly engaged prospects with multiple email clicks for the free trial campaign** (21:55)  \n    - This group includes users who have clicked on campaign emails several times but have not converted yet.  \n    - Shane noted this approach lets users self-select, reducing the need for manager approval and accelerating sales.  \n\n- **The pricing and trial model are designed to accommodate both single-office users and multi-office organizations** (21:18)  \n    - Early trials focus on single offices to demonstrate value before scaling to multiple locations.  \n    - The team plans a soft launch offering monthly payments with potential to add tiered and upfront payment options later (21:51).  \n\n## **Sales Process and Operational Insights**\n\nThe sales outreach process is evolving to meet prospect behaviors and internal scheduling constraints.\n\n- **Keenan is transitioning from slow, conversational outreach to a more direct approach emphasizing demo scheduling and key benefits** (09:59)  \n    - She experiments weekly with different messaging styles and tailors outreach based on prospect engagement.  \n    - The direct approach is intended to move beyond social media exchanges toward committed demos.  \n\n- **Keenan’s upcoming schedule changes will allow more consistent outreach, improving sales process control** (26:50)  \n    - She will finalize her own work schedule after handoffs conclude next week to better manage daily activities.  \n    - This consistency aims to enhance follow-up effectiveness and timely communication.  \n\n- **The shared contact spreadsheet is a critical tool for managing leads, but manual processing is time-consuming** (28:26)  \n    - Shane requested highlighting prospects with three or more clicks over time to identify persistent interest.  \n    - Nathalie will generate a list of these high-engagement contacts to focus outreach efforts.  \n\n- **Keenan indicated email communication is more effective than LinkedIn messaging, as prospects check work email regularly** (25:50)  \n    - LinkedIn responses tend to be delayed and fragmented, reducing conversational continuity.  \n\n- **Some prospects with high demo engagement but no contact info prompt consideration of direct phone outreach** (30:40)  \n    - Keenan plans to start calling such companies to break through communication barriers, given written outreach has failed.  \n\n## **Competitive Positioning and Market Insights**\n\nThe team is refining messaging and sales tactics to differentiate the product in a busy market.\n\n- **Shane and Nathalie acknowledged that most software competitors do not offer transparent pricing or self-service sign-ups on their websites** (17:10)  \n    - Their product’s planned shift to online purchasing aims to align with common SaaS models, making buying easier for smaller customers.  \n    - Larger enterprise deals usually involve negotiation, which they currently do not target.  \n\n- **They recognize the need to emphasize time savings as a unique selling point, addressing prospects’ pain points of being overwhelmed and too busy** (02:16)  \n    - This value prop is not yet fully leveraged in campaigns but has potential to boost demo interest and conversion.  \n\n- **The tension between billers and office staff highlights the importance of targeting the right user personas who see the tool’s value** (22:40)  \n    - Billers appreciate transparency and task tracking, while office managers may see adoption as additional work.  \n    - Targeting decision makers in operations roles is critical to overcome internal resistance and accelerate sales.  \n\n- **The team is tracking prospect engagement closely through multiple tools and metrics to better prioritize follow-up and refine messaging** (07:38)  \n    - Data from Storylane demos, email clicks, and website visits help identify high-intent users.  \n    - This data-driven approach aims to improve sales efficiency and conversion rates over time.","outline":null,"keywords":["billers campaign","time-saving value proposition","LinkedIn ads","Storylane demo analytics","product launch","online purchase","lead engagement","trial pricing"],"overview":"- **Demo Scheduling Challenges:** Prospects are too busy to engage, prompting a shift to direct messaging and in-person visits.  \n- **Targeting Decision Makers:** Focusing on operations and clinical managers to improve demo scheduling and engagement effectiveness.  \n- **Time-Saving Messaging:** Emphasizing time savings in marketing materials and exploring video demos to attract busy prospects.  \n- **Conversion Gaps Identified:** Increased web traffic but low form submissions; the contact page may need clearer messaging to enhance conversions.  \n- **New Pricing Strategies:** Launching self-service features and a 30-day trial to attract users, with incentives for early adopters.  \n- **Enhanced Sales Outreach:** Adapting outreach approach to focus on direct communication, utilizing engagement metrics to prioritize pursuits.","action_items":"\n**Keenan Toward**\nIncrease direct outreach messaging using bullet points emphasizing key time-saving features and request demo scheduling this upcoming week (10:00)\nConduct in-person visits to dental offices next week to assess engagement differences from digital outreach (11:36)\nContinue engaging contacts in tab 2 (emails) and tab 3 (highly engaged leads) from the contacts spreadsheet for outreach (26:24)\nConsider initiating phone calls to prospects who repeatedly view demos but do not respond to written communication (30:34)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nUpdate LinkedIn ads to test value propositions focusing on time savings and monitor performance outcomes (03:32)\nImprove copy and clarity of Contact Us page to increase form submission conversion rate (14:19)\nResearch competitors’ website signup and pricing display practices for the upcoming online purchase feature launch (17:31)\nProvide a summary list of contacts with 3+ demo clicks over the historical campaign period for prioritized outreach (28:26)\nContinue sending weekly contact spreadsheets with engagement data, including highlights of highly engaged leads (26:24)\n\n**Shane Billings**\nOversee planning for new feature rollout enabling direct online purchase and setup credit card payments (15:11)\nAdvise Keenan and Natalie on marketing strategy adjustments focusing on value proposition related to time savings (02:13)\nMonitor demo engagement metrics through Storylane and identify high-interest leads (07:38)\nPrepare for website modifications to support account creation and online purchase upon new feature launch (16:54)\nReview pricing and trial offer options and provide input based on market and team feedback (19:30)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"0e10959b-c3f2-47f0-a7ff-6d7d098699af","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
