INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Agrippon // New North Weekly Connect',
  '## **Lead Engagement and Demo Scheduling**

The team is facing challenges scheduling demos due to prospects’ extreme time constraints and role limitations.

- **Keenan reported no scheduled demos from the two recent form submitters despite follow-up attempts with Friday availability offered** (00:22)  
    - Both prospects confirmed interest but failed to respond to scheduling outreach.  
    - Keenan noted prospects are so busy they struggle even to read emails or attend 30-minute demos.  
    - She plans to try a more direct, time-saving focused messaging approach this week to prompt demo scheduling.  
    - Keenan will also conduct in-person visits next week to test if face-to-face engagement improves response rates compared to LinkedIn.  

- **Keenan identified a key barrier: many initial contacts are not decision makers, leading to stalled engagement** (12:43)  
    - She is now targeting operations managers, clinical operations, and RCM managers, rather than office managers or lower-level staff.  
    - This shift aims to reach individuals with authority to move purchasing decisions forward.  
    - Billers have shown more interest as they see direct value in saving time and improving communication transparency.  
    - Shane and Keenan discussed the tension between billers, who want the tool, and office staff, who feel it adds work.  

- **Shane suggested emphasizing time savings as a core value proposition in marketing campaigns** (02:16)  
    - Nathalie agreed to update LinkedIn ads to test messaging around saving time and simplifying management.  
    - They plan to create sales enablement materials highlighting key time-saving features to accelerate demo scheduling.  
    - The team will explore recording a video walkthrough demo to provide more upfront value for busy prospects.  

- **Keenan uses weekly segmented contact lists prioritizing prospects with emails and high engagement for outreach** (25:14)  
    - She focuses on Tab 2 (emails) and Tab 3 (engaged contacts) from the shared spreadsheet.  
    - Shane requested Nathalie highlight contacts with three or more clicks historically to identify highly interested prospects.  
    - Nathalie will prepare a list of all contacts with three-plus clicks for targeted outreach.  

## **Marketing Campaign and Website Performance**

Recent campaigns show improved click engagement but limited conversion to form submissions or demos.

- **Nathalie reported launching two new email campaigns yesterday targeting two new groups, expected to increase website activity** (03:58)  
    - LinkedIn ads have seen a significant increase in clicks with cost per click reduced substantially (04:27).  
    - Targeting has been tightened to improve message relevance, driving more qualified traffic to the website (04:39).  
    - Despite more clicks, form completions remain low, indicating a conversion gap.  

- **Website sessions from Google searches have slightly decreased, partly due to limited podcast-driven discoverability** (06:01)  
    - A podcast episode is scheduled for tomorrow to boost search engine traffic and organic awareness (06:15).  

- **The contact page is the main call to action across the site, but form fill rates are low despite nearly 200 visitors in the past 30 days** (14:19)  
    - Nathalie will review and potentially revise the contact page copy to clarify the value of filling the form.  
    - Shane emphasized the importance of this fix to increase conversion from high traffic volumes.  

- **Storylane demo tool is used to track prospect engagement with online demos, with free and paid versions available** (05:00)  
    - Shane shared specific engagement data: some users complete up to 100% of the demo with sessions lasting over a minute.  
    - Keenan identified these active demo users as previously contacted prospects, validating their interest.  
    - While Storylane does not reveal identities, it provides useful engagement metrics to prioritize outreach.  

## **Product Launch and Pricing Strategy**

The team is preparing for a near-term launch of a self-service purchase feature, requiring pricing and website updates.

- **Shane projected the next feature release in two to four weeks, followed by enabling direct credit card purchases online** (15:37)  
    - This will allow users to create accounts and buy subscriptions without sales interaction.  
    - The website will need redesign to incorporate account creation and purchasing workflows reflecting this change (16:54).  
    - Campaigns will be updated to promote self-service sign-ups and pricing transparency.  

- **Pricing discussions centered on setting the software’s price point and trial model** (18:36)  
    - Keenan recommended a base price of **$139 per office per year** based on market research and customer conversations (18:50).  
    - Shane cautioned against free trials per office, fearing customers would consolidate usage into one free office and avoid paying for others.  
    - They agreed a **30-day time-limited free trial** is preferable to encourage usage without risking dilution of multi-office sales (20:06).  
    - An early adopter promotion could offer a discounted **$100 per office for the first year** during the initial 90-day launch window (20:59).  

- **Nathalie suggested targeting highly engaged prospects with multiple email clicks for the free trial campaign** (21:55)  
    - This group includes users who have clicked on campaign emails several times but have not converted yet.  
    - Shane noted this approach lets users self-select, reducing the need for manager approval and accelerating sales.  

- **The pricing and trial model are designed to accommodate both single-office users and multi-office organizations** (21:18)  
    - Early trials focus on single offices to demonstrate value before scaling to multiple locations.  
    - The team plans a soft launch offering monthly payments with potential to add tiered and upfront payment options later (21:51).  

## **Sales Process and Operational Insights**

The sales outreach process is evolving to meet prospect behaviors and internal scheduling constraints.

- **Keenan is transitioning from slow, conversational outreach to a more direct approach emphasizing demo scheduling and key benefits** (09:59)  
    - She experiments weekly with different messaging styles and tailors outreach based on prospect engagement.  
    - The direct approach is intended to move beyond social media exchanges toward committed demos.  

- **Keenan’s upcoming schedule changes will allow more consistent outreach, improving sales process control** (26:50)  
    - She will finalize her own work schedule after handoffs conclude next week to better manage daily activities.  
    - This consistency aims to enhance follow-up effectiveness and timely communication.  

- **The shared contact spreadsheet is a critical tool for managing leads, but manual processing is time-consuming** (28:26)  
    - Shane requested highlighting prospects with three or more clicks over time to identify persistent interest.  
    - Nathalie will generate a list of these high-engagement contacts to focus outreach efforts.  

- **Keenan indicated email communication is more effective than LinkedIn messaging, as prospects check work email regularly** (25:50)  
    - LinkedIn responses tend to be delayed and fragmented, reducing conversational continuity.  

- **Some prospects with high demo engagement but no contact info prompt consideration of direct phone outreach** (30:40)  
    - Keenan plans to start calling such companies to break through communication barriers, given written outreach has failed.  

## **Competitive Positioning and Market Insights**

The team is refining messaging and sales tactics to differentiate the product in a busy market.

- **Shane and Nathalie acknowledged that most software competitors do not offer transparent pricing or self-service sign-ups on their websites** (17:10)  
    - Their product’s planned shift to online purchasing aims to align with common SaaS models, making buying easier for smaller customers.  
    - Larger enterprise deals usually involve negotiation, which they currently do not target.  

- **They recognize the need to emphasize time savings as a unique selling point, addressing prospects’ pain points of being overwhelmed and too busy** (02:16)  
    - This value prop is not yet fully leveraged in campaigns but has potential to boost demo interest and conversion.  

- **The tension between billers and office staff highlights the importance of targeting the right user personas who see the tool’s value** (22:40)  
    - Billers appreciate transparency and task tracking, while office managers may see adoption as additional work.  
    - Targeting decision makers in operations roles is critical to overcome internal resistance and accelerate sales.  

- **The team is tracking prospect engagement closely through multiple tools and metrics to better prioritize follow-up and refine messaging** (07:38)  
    - Data from Storylane demos, email clicks, and website visits help identify high-intent users.  
    - This data-driven approach aims to improve sales efficiency and conversion rates over time.',
  '2026-02-05 13:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Increase direct outreach messaging using bullet points emphasizing key time-saving features and request demo scheduling this upcoming week (10:00)","completed":false},{"text":"Conduct in-person visits to dental offices next week to assess engagement differences from digital outreach (11:36)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue engaging contacts in tab 2 (emails) and tab 3 (highly engaged leads) from the contacts spreadsheet for outreach (26:24)","completed":false},{"text":"Consider initiating phone calls to prospects who repeatedly view demos but do not respond to written communication (30:34)","completed":false},{"text":"Update LinkedIn ads to test value propositions focusing on time savings and monitor performance outcomes (03:32)","completed":false},{"text":"Improve copy and clarity of Contact Us page to increase form submission conversion rate (14:19)","completed":false},{"text":"Research competitors’ website signup and pricing display practices for the upcoming online purchase feature launch (17:31)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide a summary list of contacts with 3+ demo clicks over the historical campaign period for prioritized outreach (28:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Continue sending weekly contact spreadsheets with engagement data, including highlights of highly engaged leads (26:24)","completed":false},{"text":"Oversee planning for new feature rollout enabling direct online purchase and setup credit card payments (15:11)","completed":false},{"text":"Advise Keenan and Natalie on marketing strategy adjustments focusing on value proposition related to time savings (02:13)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor demo engagement metrics through Storylane and identify high-interest leads (07:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare for website modifications to support account creation and online purchase upon new feature launch (16:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Review pricing and trial offer options and provide input based on market and team feedback (19:30)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

