    '{"id":"01KG81CNQRAGZW2769K9QZJTAQ","title":"Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Branding and Business Unit Strategy**\n\nThe team is actively redefining the business unit’s brand identity to clarify market positioning post-acquisition.\n\n- **Don is leading a complete redesign of the business unit’s brand, reviving the Infutor name** to separate it from the combined branding under ActiveProspect, which merged Junaya and Infutor under Verisk (04:14)  \n    - This change reflects ActiveProspect’s previous absorption of Journeya, a competitor product, into their platform.\n    - The marketing team is providing feedback to ActiveProspect’s marketing group on the new branding direction.\n    - The goal is to clearly differentiate the data-focused business side from the absorbed competitor products.\n    - A company-wide poll confirmed Infutor as the preferred name, despite some internal reservations.\n\n## **Content Development and Marketing Assets**\n\nContent creation is progressing with careful review cycles to maintain high quality and thought leadership positioning.\n\n- **The team is preparing a customer success episode with all raw recordings completed and guest titles finalized**; the first draft will be shared soon (07:28)  \n    - Igor recommended losslessly compressing video files before upload to speed up the process without quality loss.\n    - Gab plans to experiment with compression and will seek Don’s help if needed.\n    - This technical step aims to reduce upload time from potentially a full day to a much shorter window.\n- **Top and middle funnel ad copy outlines and LinkedIn carousel content are underway, based on the customer success episode and external industry insights** (09:15)  \n    - Gab confirmed the blog title aligns well with positioning the unit as a thought leader, avoiding tying the story to a single individual.\n    - Christina agreed to take over development of the iceberg visual concept to reduce Gab’s workload and speed production.\n    - This collaborative approach ensures consistent messaging across multiple formats.\n\n## **Campaign Refresh and Timeline**\n\nThe existing campaign is paused pending creative refresh with a tight, feasible schedule aiming for early March relaunch.\n\n- **Creative refresh is scheduled for next week, targeting a relaunch before March 4th, with Thursday as the likely day for new designs delivery** (11:40)  \n    - Igor expects design drafts by Tuesday, allowing a day and a half for review and revisions.\n    - Gab confirmed feedback on ad copy will be ready today to keep the timeline intact.\n    - The refresh involves minor changes to backgrounds and copy, not full redesign, enabling faster turnaround.\n- **The campaign pause ensures quality improvements are implemented before relaunch to maximize impact** (11:40)  \n    - Christina and Gab are aligned on the need for timely feedback and clear communication to avoid delays.\n    - The refreshed creatives aim to boost engagement by updating messaging and visuals without restarting the campaign.\n\n## **CES Episode Launch Planning**\n\nThe team is managing tight deadlines for the CES episode release with contingency planning for external reviews.\n\n- **The ideal launch date for the CES episode is Thursday the 12th, but flexibility exists to push to the following Tuesday if needed** (13:28)  \n    - Igor emphasized quality is a priority, and a delay to the 19th is acceptable if revisions require more time.\n    - Gab is coordinating with Tim to confirm whether external contributors Nola and Kelly require a detailed review or can approve quickly.\n    - This approach balances timeliness with quality control for external stakeholders.\n- **The schedule aligns with other upcoming episodes Tim is recording, maintaining overall content cadence** (14:47)  \n    - Gab will update the team after discussing timelines with Tim later today.\n    - Coordination ensures smooth content delivery without bottlenecks from external dependencies.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Notes**\n\nThe team is implementing small operational improvements to streamline workflows and reduce bottlenecks.\n\n- **Uploading raw video assets will now include lossless compression to prevent excessive upload times** (07:28)  \n    - This technical adjustment will save up to a full day of upload time per video.\n    - Gab will test compression tools and coordinate with Don for technical support.\n- **Clear communication on feedback deadlines and responsibilities is emphasized to keep projects on track** (12:26)  \n    - The team agreed on review turnaround times of one to one and a half days for refreshed creatives.\n    - Delegation of visual concept creation to Christina reduces workload on Gab, improving efficiency.\n- **No activities are currently blocked awaiting Gab’s input, indicating smooth workflow progress** (13:10)  \n    - The working list of tasks is updated and shared via Slack for transparency and tracking.\n    - Regular check-ins are planned to keep everyone aligned and prevent surprises.","outline":null,"keywords":["Infutor","Rebranding","Tofu/Mofu copy","Customer Success Episode","Campaign Refresh","Iceberg Image Concept"],"overview":"- **Brand Identity Redesign:** Reviving the Infutor brand to clarify market position after ActiveProspect''s acquisitions and ensure differentiation.  \n- **Content Development Efforts:** Customer success episode ready for editing; video compression will speed uploads significantly.  \n- **Campaign Refresh Timeline:** New campaign designs due by March 4th, aiming for a quality-focused relaunch after adjustments.  \n- **CES Episode Planning:** Targeting a launch on February 12th, with flexibility for quality if needed; timelines coordinated with other episodes.  \n- **Operational Improvements:** Implementing video compression to cut upload time and enhancing communication on feedback for project efficiency.  \n- **Workflow Management:** No current bottlenecks; tasks are updated regularly for transparency and effective tracking.","action_items":"\n**Gabrielle Verzella**\nReview all deliverables related to current projects after the meeting (04:24)\nProvide feedback on TOFU and MOFU ad copy today for creative refresh (12:07)\nDiscuss with Tim Finnigan the timeline and external review requirements for the customer success episode and update the team later today (14:47)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nCoordinate and inform team when first draft of customer success episode blog is ready for review (07:28)\nCompress raw video files losslessly before uploading to drive to improve upload speed (08:44)\nSend refreshed ad creative designs to Gab by Tuesday for feedback (11:40)\n\n**Christina Bila**\nTake ownership of creating the iceberg image concept using key phrases from the blog copy, relieving Gab of this task (10:49)\nConfirm and maintain the schedule for refreshing ad creatives and campaign relaunch next week (11:40)\n\n**Team**\nPause current campaign until refreshed creatives are ready and approved (11:19)\n"},"duration":16.829999923706055,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Gab"},{"id":1,"name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"id":2,"name":"Gab"},{"id":3,"name":"Christina Bila"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":254.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.01,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hey, Gab.","index":1,"end_time":256.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"How are you?","index":2,"end_time":257.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.9,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Are you.","index":3,"end_time":258.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":257.7,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Oh, me?","index":4,"end_time":259.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.58,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I''m okay.","index":5,"end_time":261.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.34,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":262.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s great to hear that.","index":7,"end_time":263.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.58,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Been a busy morning.","index":8,"end_time":265.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":264.34,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I said in our Slack channel that.","index":9,"end_time":268.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":266.1,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I would get to a review of all the deliverables in there.","index":10,"end_time":271.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":268.02,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That just didn''t happen.","index":11,"end_time":274.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":272.98,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So Don is working on completely redesigning our business unit.","index":12,"end_time":281.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":274.9,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So the public opinion is to bring us back to the name Infutor.","index":13,"end_time":288.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":282.34,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"When we became vms, it was a combination of Junaya and Infur under the Verisk umbrella.","index":14,"end_time":297.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":291.29,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And when ActiveProspect bought us, I think they were very cognizant of the fact that Journeya part of the business was their direct competition in terms of product.","index":15,"end_time":307.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":297.45,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So it was very easy for them to just absorb our messaging and absorb.","index":16,"end_time":311.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":308.17,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Our capabilities into their existing platform.","index":17,"end_time":315.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.27,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So then what''s left is the data side of the business, which is what Don is working on branding right now.","index":18,"end_time":322.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We''re still various marketing solutions, but that can''t stand.","index":19,"end_time":325.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":322.67,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So they actually put out a poll, activeprospect to the whole company about what name idea people liked best.","index":20,"end_time":333.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.11,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And it just so happened that Infutor won out.","index":21,"end_time":336.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":333.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It wasn''t my pick.","index":22,"end_time":340.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.85,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I think it''s.","index":23,"end_time":342.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"There''s just a lot there, but.","index":24,"end_time":346.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.01,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So he''s working on that now.","index":25,"end_time":348.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":346.85,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We''re giving our input and our feedback.","index":26,"end_time":350.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.93,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And our opinion as the VMS marketing.","index":27,"end_time":352.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":350.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Team to their marketing team.","index":28,"end_time":354.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.73,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"There''s a lot up in the air, but that''s what I was working on this morning.","index":29,"end_time":357.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":354.85,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And I will review the deliverables after this call.","index":30,"end_time":363.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.41,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"That''s cool.","index":31,"end_time":366.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":365.72,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":32,"end_time":366.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"No problem.","index":33,"end_time":367.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.92,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s a. Yeah.","index":34,"end_time":369.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.64,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Tofu mofu copy and also the.","index":35,"end_time":372.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":369.36,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The outline.","index":36,"end_time":373.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.68,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":373.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.48,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We didn''t want to start on actually creating the blog without you approving the outline because it''s like, it''s.","index":38,"end_time":381,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":373.76,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s a.","index":39,"end_time":381.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"It''s not tricky, but it''s the first one that we''re doing this way, so we just want to make sure we''re on the same page and maybe if you want to make some changes, some inputs.","index":40,"end_time":393,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.8,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":41,"end_time":395.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.31,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I just.","index":42,"end_time":395.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.07,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Upon first glance, because I did open everything, I have three things open in my browser, the outline being one of them.","index":43,"end_time":401.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":395.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But just from the title alone, we''re already on the right track.","index":44,"end_time":404.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.63,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Like, we''re not tying it back to Pat Sullivan in particular.","index":45,"end_time":408.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":404.95,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"We can absolutely cite him throughout the piece.","index":46,"end_time":412.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":408.75,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But it''s positioning our business unit.","index":47,"end_time":417.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":413.79,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"As being like the thought leader in this particular topic.","index":48,"end_time":420.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":417.11,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I think we''re off to a good start.","index":49,"end_time":422.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":421.56,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I just have to go through it.","index":50,"end_time":424.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":422.84,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"With a fine tooth comb.","index":51,"end_time":425.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":424.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":52,"end_time":429.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":428.68,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, just write it down.","index":53,"end_time":431.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":429.88,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":54,"end_time":432.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.28,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hi, Christina.","index":55,"end_time":433.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.92,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Hi.","index":56,"end_time":434.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434.44,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Sorry I''m late.","index":57,"end_time":436.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":435.48,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Oh, you''re fine.","index":58,"end_time":437.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.76,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It is okay.","index":59,"end_time":438.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.04,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Tim is not going to make it today.","index":60,"end_time":440.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":438.8,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay.","index":61,"end_time":442.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":441.4,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"He just let me know.","index":62,"end_time":443.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":442.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay, so let''s go through the.","index":63,"end_time":451.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Through the agenda and feel free to add.","index":64,"end_time":455.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.35,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Your thoughts.","index":65,"end_time":460.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":459.55,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So quite a few assets we''re working on at the moment, CS episode being one of them.","index":66,"end_time":472.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":465.15,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We finally have all the.","index":67,"end_time":475.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.1,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"All the RAW recordings and the team is working on that.","index":68,"end_time":479.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":475.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"We have the guest titles also.","index":69,"end_time":481.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.62,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And when the first draft is done, we''ll let you know and send it over.","index":70,"end_time":488.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":482.5,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gab, just a little side note for you.","index":71,"end_time":491.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":488.66,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So next time when uploading RAW assets to our drive, just to prevent the endless upload, maybe it would be best to losslessly compress videos offline.","index":72,"end_time":505.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.54,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Of course, if you have an option to do that, so not to just re upload it somewhere and that would also take a day.","index":73,"end_time":512.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.29,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So yeah, just basically losslessly compress the.","index":74,"end_time":517.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.73,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The RAW videos before uploading and that will.","index":75,"end_time":519.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":517.29,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"That should significantly accelerate the.","index":76,"end_time":523.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":519.77,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"The upload.","index":77,"end_time":523.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":523.17,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I''ve seen like compression.","index":78,"end_time":526.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":524.65,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Options when you just right click on the video, even on your desktop.","index":79,"end_time":530.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.77,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So I will.","index":80,"end_time":531.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.33,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I could even do an experiment and.","index":81,"end_time":533.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":531.54,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Try uploading a video to the mid drive after I try compressing.","index":82,"end_time":538.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":533.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But if I need help, I''ll just tap Don.","index":83,"end_time":541.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.66,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"He knows what that means.","index":84,"end_time":542.3,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":541.22,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay, sure.","index":85,"end_time":543.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":542.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":86,"end_time":544.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":543.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Basically just losslessly.","index":87,"end_time":545.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":544.06,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Just me.","index":88,"end_time":545.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.42,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":89,"end_time":546.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":545.98,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So there are no like, there''s no reduced quality basically.","index":90,"end_time":552.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.3,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":91,"end_time":553.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":552.7,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":92,"end_time":553.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.14,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And then the copy for two for tofu and mofu for ad, creative package, the outline based on the episode, including the aspects from the episode, and also other industry, industry insights and thought leadership.","index":93,"end_time":576.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.66,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And also we''re working on the LinkedIn carousel based on the HR 2808 guideline.","index":94,"end_time":583.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":576.89,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":95,"end_time":584.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.43,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And just to clarify, based on this working list, I keep me honest, we talked about this like iceberg image concept.","index":96,"end_time":592.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.07,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Did I say that I was gonna put together some copy for that and then send it over?","index":97,"end_time":598.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.87,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Or was it opposite or.","index":98,"end_time":600.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.31,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"With that?","index":99,"end_time":603.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":602.75,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, it might have been like a misunderstanding.","index":100,"end_time":607.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.71,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"What I understood it was that.","index":101,"end_time":610.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.27,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So you sent the blog in the document and then I think that in the meeting you said that like, you still need to think about some ideas for the visual.","index":102,"end_time":622.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Maybe we can set that though, if you think the blog is enough, we can go.","index":103,"end_time":629.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":623.82,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Yeah, definitely.","index":104,"end_time":630.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":629.78,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":105,"end_time":631.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":630.86,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":106,"end_time":631.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.22,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"I. Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":633.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.38,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"You know, because I. I''ve been thinking about it and I''m like, I could just go through that blog and pick out some key phrases and try to work it that way into the iceberg concept.","index":108,"end_time":642.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.38,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"But since y'' all have it.","index":109,"end_time":644.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.96,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Can I ask that to be added to the working list?","index":110,"end_time":648.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":111,"end_time":649.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":649.24,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Considering all the things you mentioned earlier that you''re working on, happy to take that off your plate.","index":112,"end_time":655.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":649.72,"speaker_name":"Christina Bila"},{"text":"Love that.","index":113,"end_time":656.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So, yeah, we''ll just make sure we.","index":114,"end_time":658.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":657.4,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Add that to this working list.","index":115,"end_time":660.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.56,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"And you guys have the.","index":116,"end_time":663.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.2,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"The copy.","index":117,"end_time":665,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":663.32,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"I put it in the Slack channel, right?","index":118,"end_time":666.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"It''s in Slack.","index":119,"end_time":668.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":667.24,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":120,"end_time":668.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":668.04,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Excellent.","index":121,"end_time":669.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.06,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Okay, Sounds great.","index":122,"end_time":671.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"So this is then redundant, basically.","index":123,"end_time":676.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":677.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.14,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":125,"end_time":679.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":679.06,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"So we''re switching that to.","index":126,"end_time":682.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.82,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Y'' all take the first stab, and then we''ll kind of work together from there.","index":127,"end_time":685.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.42,"speaker_name":"Gab"},{"text":"Yes, yes, definitely.","index":128,"end_time":687.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.94,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"And then just a quick.","index":129,"end_time":690.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.98,"speaker_name":"Igor Zagradjanin"},{"text":"Not an update, but just like a note on the.","index":130,"end_time":693.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":690.58,"s