    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Branding and Business Unit Strategy**\n\nThe team is actively redefining the business unit’s brand identity to clarify market positioning post-acquisition.\n\n- **Don is leading a complete redesign of the business unit’s brand, reviving the Infutor name** to separate it from the combined branding under ActiveProspect, which merged Junaya and Infutor under Verisk (04:14)  \n    - This change reflects ActiveProspect’s previous absorption of Journeya, a competitor product, into their platform.\n    - The marketing team is providing feedback to ActiveProspect’s marketing group on the new branding direction.\n    - The goal is to clearly differentiate the data-focused business side from the absorbed competitor products.\n    - A company-wide poll confirmed Infutor as the preferred name, despite some internal reservations.\n\n## **Content Development and Marketing Assets**\n\nContent creation is progressing with careful review cycles to maintain high quality and thought leadership positioning.\n\n- **The team is preparing a customer success episode with all raw recordings completed and guest titles finalized**; the first draft will be shared soon (07:28)  \n    - Igor recommended losslessly compressing video files before upload to speed up the process without quality loss.\n    - Gab plans to experiment with compression and will seek Don’s help if needed.\n    - This technical step aims to reduce upload time from potentially a full day to a much shorter window.\n- **Top and middle funnel ad copy outlines and LinkedIn carousel content are underway, based on the customer success episode and external industry insights** (09:15)  \n    - Gab confirmed the blog title aligns well with positioning the unit as a thought leader, avoiding tying the story to a single individual.\n    - Christina agreed to take over development of the iceberg visual concept to reduce Gab’s workload and speed production.\n    - This collaborative approach ensures consistent messaging across multiple formats.\n\n## **Campaign Refresh and Timeline**\n\nThe existing campaign is paused pending creative refresh with a tight, feasible schedule aiming for early March relaunch.\n\n- **Creative refresh is scheduled for next week, targeting a relaunch before March 4th, with Thursday as the likely day for new designs delivery** (11:40)  \n    - Igor expects design drafts by Tuesday, allowing a day and a half for review and revisions.\n    - Gab confirmed feedback on ad copy will be ready today to keep the timeline intact.\n    - The refresh involves minor changes to backgrounds and copy, not full redesign, enabling faster turnaround.\n- **The campaign pause ensures quality improvements are implemented before relaunch to maximize impact** (11:40)  \n    - Christina and Gab are aligned on the need for timely feedback and clear communication to avoid delays.\n    - The refreshed creatives aim to boost engagement by updating messaging and visuals without restarting the campaign.\n\n## **CES Episode Launch Planning**\n\nThe team is managing tight deadlines for the CES episode release with contingency planning for external reviews.\n\n- **The ideal launch date for the CES episode is Thursday the 12th, but flexibility exists to push to the following Tuesday if needed** (13:28)  \n    - Igor emphasized quality is a priority, and a delay to the 19th is acceptable if revisions require more time.\n    - Gab is coordinating with Tim to confirm whether external contributors Nola and Kelly require a detailed review or can approve quickly.\n    - This approach balances timeliness with quality control for external stakeholders.\n- **The schedule aligns with other upcoming episodes Tim is recording, maintaining overall content cadence** (14:47)  \n    - Gab will update the team after discussing timelines with Tim later today.\n    - Coordination ensures smooth content delivery without bottlenecks from external dependencies.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Notes**\n\nThe team is implementing small operational improvements to streamline workflows and reduce bottlenecks.\n\n- **Uploading raw video assets will now include lossless compression to prevent excessive upload times** (07:28)  \n    - This technical adjustment will save up to a full day of upload time per video.\n    - Gab will test compression tools and coordinate with Don for technical support.\n- **Clear communication on feedback deadlines and responsibilities is emphasized to keep projects on track** (12:26)  \n    - The team agreed on review turnaround times of one to one and a half days for refreshed creatives.\n    - Delegation of visual concept creation to Christina reduces workload on Gab, improving efficiency.\n- **No activities are currently blocked awaiting Gab’s input, indicating smooth workflow progress** (13:10)  \n    - The working list of tasks is updated and shared via Slack for transparency and tracking.\n    - Regular check-ins are planned to keep everyone aligned and prevent surprises.","outline":null,"keywords":["Infutor","Rebranding","Tofu/Mofu copy","Customer Success Episode","Campaign Refresh","Iceberg Image Concept"],"overview":"- **Brand Identity Redesign:** Reviving the Infutor brand to clarify market position after ActiveProspect''s acquisitions and ensure differentiation.  \n- **Content Development Efforts:** Customer success episode ready for editing; video compression will speed uploads significantly.  \n- **Campaign Refresh Timeline:** New campaign designs due by March 4th, aiming for a quality-focused relaunch after adjustments.  \n- **CES Episode Planning:** Targeting a launch on February 12th, with flexibility for quality if needed; timelines coordinated with other episodes.  \n- **Operational Improvements:** Implementing video compression to cut upload time and enhancing communication on feedback for project efficiency.  \n- **Workflow Management:** No current bottlenecks; tasks are updated regularly for transparency and effective tracking.","action_items":"\n**Gabrielle Verzella**\nReview all deliverables related to current projects after the meeting (04:24)\nProvide feedback on TOFU and MOFU ad copy today for creative refresh (12:07)\nDiscuss with Tim Finnigan the timeline and external review requirements for the customer success episode and update the team later today (14:47)\n\n**Igor Zagradjanin**\nCoordinate and inform team when first draft of customer success episode blog is ready for review (07:28)\nCompress raw video files losslessly before uploading to drive to improve upload speed (08:44)\nSend refreshed ad creative designs to Gab by Tuesday for feedback (11:40)\n\n**Christina Bila**\nTake ownership of creating the iceberg image concept using key phrases from the blog copy, relieving Gab of this task (10:49)\nConfirm and maintain the schedule for refreshing ad creatives and campaign relaunch next week (11:40)\n\n**Team**\nPause current campaign until refreshed creatives are ready and approved (11:19)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"96982081-b8f0-4de1-b6ec-a2d8d00d3128","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
