INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Verisk // New North Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Branding and Business Unit Strategy**

The team is actively redefining the business unit’s brand identity to clarify market positioning post-acquisition.

- **Don is leading a complete redesign of the business unit’s brand, reviving the Infutor name** to separate it from the combined branding under ActiveProspect, which merged Junaya and Infutor under Verisk (04:14)  
    - This change reflects ActiveProspect’s previous absorption of Journeya, a competitor product, into their platform.
    - The marketing team is providing feedback to ActiveProspect’s marketing group on the new branding direction.
    - The goal is to clearly differentiate the data-focused business side from the absorbed competitor products.
    - A company-wide poll confirmed Infutor as the preferred name, despite some internal reservations.

## **Content Development and Marketing Assets**

Content creation is progressing with careful review cycles to maintain high quality and thought leadership positioning.

- **The team is preparing a customer success episode with all raw recordings completed and guest titles finalized**; the first draft will be shared soon (07:28)  
    - Igor recommended losslessly compressing video files before upload to speed up the process without quality loss.
    - Gab plans to experiment with compression and will seek Don’s help if needed.
    - This technical step aims to reduce upload time from potentially a full day to a much shorter window.
- **Top and middle funnel ad copy outlines and LinkedIn carousel content are underway, based on the customer success episode and external industry insights** (09:15)  
    - Gab confirmed the blog title aligns well with positioning the unit as a thought leader, avoiding tying the story to a single individual.
    - Christina agreed to take over development of the iceberg visual concept to reduce Gab’s workload and speed production.
    - This collaborative approach ensures consistent messaging across multiple formats.

## **Campaign Refresh and Timeline**

The existing campaign is paused pending creative refresh with a tight, feasible schedule aiming for early March relaunch.

- **Creative refresh is scheduled for next week, targeting a relaunch before March 4th, with Thursday as the likely day for new designs delivery** (11:40)  
    - Igor expects design drafts by Tuesday, allowing a day and a half for review and revisions.
    - Gab confirmed feedback on ad copy will be ready today to keep the timeline intact.
    - The refresh involves minor changes to backgrounds and copy, not full redesign, enabling faster turnaround.
- **The campaign pause ensures quality improvements are implemented before relaunch to maximize impact** (11:40)  
    - Christina and Gab are aligned on the need for timely feedback and clear communication to avoid delays.
    - The refreshed creatives aim to boost engagement by updating messaging and visuals without restarting the campaign.

## **CES Episode Launch Planning**

The team is managing tight deadlines for the CES episode release with contingency planning for external reviews.

- **The ideal launch date for the CES episode is Thursday the 12th, but flexibility exists to push to the following Tuesday if needed** (13:28)  
    - Igor emphasized quality is a priority, and a delay to the 19th is acceptable if revisions require more time.
    - Gab is coordinating with Tim to confirm whether external contributors Nola and Kelly require a detailed review or can approve quickly.
    - This approach balances timeliness with quality control for external stakeholders.
- **The schedule aligns with other upcoming episodes Tim is recording, maintaining overall content cadence** (14:47)  
    - Gab will update the team after discussing timelines with Tim later today.
    - Coordination ensures smooth content delivery without bottlenecks from external dependencies.

## **Process Improvements and Operational Notes**

The team is implementing small operational improvements to streamline workflows and reduce bottlenecks.

- **Uploading raw video assets will now include lossless compression to prevent excessive upload times** (07:28)  
    - This technical adjustment will save up to a full day of upload time per video.
    - Gab will test compression tools and coordinate with Don for technical support.
- **Clear communication on feedback deadlines and responsibilities is emphasized to keep projects on track** (12:26)  
    - The team agreed on review turnaround times of one to one and a half days for refreshed creatives.
    - Delegation of visual concept creation to Christina reduces workload on Gab, improving efficiency.
- **No activities are currently blocked awaiting Gab’s input, indicating smooth workflow progress** (13:10)  
    - The working list of tasks is updated and shared via Slack for transparency and tracking.
    - Regular check-ins are planned to keep everyone aligned and prevent surprises.',
  '2026-02-06 17:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Review all deliverables related to current projects after the meeting (04:24)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide feedback on TOFU and MOFU ad copy today for creative refresh (12:07)","completed":false},{"text":"Discuss with Tim Finnigan the timeline and external review requirements for the customer success episode and update the team later today (14:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate and inform team when first draft of customer success episode blog is ready for review (07:28)","completed":false},{"text":"Compress raw video files losslessly before uploading to drive to improve upload speed (08:44)","completed":false},{"text":"Send refreshed ad creative designs to Gab by Tuesday for feedback (11:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Take ownership of creating the iceberg image concept using key phrases from the blog copy, relieving Gab of this task (10:49)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm and maintain the schedule for refreshing ad creatives and campaign relaunch next week (11:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Pause current campaign until refreshed creatives are ready and approved (11:19)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: MiD // Autobytes: Weekly Meeting (2026-02-06 14:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '4aa1e0b0-c66a-4025-b0a2-2d1b998c8d99',
    '2026-02-06 14:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KGFST4KDN188VF1GRSBDPWXK',
    'MiD // Autobytes: Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Joe Ragno","Joe Ragno","Colin Costigan"}'::text[],
    1424,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86201644028?pwd=6OnG3xETXYQDUbYxGAVH8T5gQNSYa5.1',
    '{"id":"01KGFST4KDN188VF1GRSBDPWXK","title":"MiD // Autobytes: Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Product Development and Platform Strategy**\n\nThe team is advancing a patient-treatment center platform focused on usability, data security, and integration to improve mental health care access.  \n\n- **Joe Ragno** demonstrated the treatment center portal which tracks **bed capacity, available beds, specialties, insurance plans, and levels of care** (13:11)  \n    - The portal supports editing insurance networks at both company-wide and individual center levels to ensure accuracy.  \n    - Team management features allow setting user access levels and invite controls to maintain secure collaboration.  \n    - Integration with EMR/CRM systems like **Khipu, Salesforce, Best Notes, and Sunwave** is in place to streamline data flow.  \n    - Joe emphasized ongoing work on preference settings and fine-tuning to make onboarding smoother and more actionable.  \n\n- The **patient-facing web portal** currently captures insurance and assessment data but still lacks a fully integrated pre-admission assessment to avoid redundant questions (12:49)  \n    - Joe highlighted efforts to reduce repetitive queries that frustrate users by consulting treatment centers for feedback.  \n    - A mobile app is planned to give patients control over their data and improve privacy, addressing a key barrier to using mental health resources via employers (13:38)  \n    - Strong encryption and data safety are priorities to build trust and increase engagement.  \n\n- On infrastructure, the backend relies on **Supabase** for database and CMS functionality, though HIPAA compliance concerns persist regarding integration with **Lovable** (15:24)  \n    - Joe noted that Supabase offers HIPAA compliance at approximately **$1,000/month**, but compliance on Lovable’s side remains uncertain.  \n    - Colin and Joe plan to explore alternative platforms like **Manus** and evaluate technical limitations of tools like **Cursor** for Salesforce development (15:55)  \n    - The team agreed to prioritize the overall project goals over specific tools, maintaining flexibility in tech choices (16:33).  \n\n- Joe shared plans to develop proprietary AI models using his high-spec local hardware, aiming to build a “crisis companion” feature that avoids misinterpretation as therapy (19:00)  \n    - This approach reflects a strategic focus on unique AI capabilities to differentiate the product and enhance user support.  \n\n## **Branding and Marketing Materials**\n\nThe group is aligning on brand identity and marketing assets to support platform launch and client outreach.  \n\n- Joe presented a **simplified logo** that conveys the desired vibe with minimal design, which the team found promising for initial use (06:00)  \n    - The logo’s green color could be an accent alongside the existing **Autobytes color palette**, maintaining brand familiarity while introducing freshness (07:23)  \n    - Colin tasked Santi with creating **EPS files** of the logo in multiple color versions for flexible use across materials (07:45).  \n\n- Colin will send a **mini website with auto-generated offers** built using Lovable and Clawed tools to spark ideas for client campaigns (04:28)  \n    - These marketing assets highlight automated report generation and scraping functionalities that showcase tech capabilities.  \n\n- The team plans to develop **one-pagers** once the logo and brand colors are finalized, focusing on clear messaging and security benefits (22:14)  \n    - Joe is proactively drafting content questions and considering AI-generated material to address common client concerns about usefulness and security (22:40).  \n\n## **Market Engagement and Strategic Insights**\n\nOngoing market research and outreach are shaping product positioning and customer understanding.  \n\n- Joe joined a LinkedIn group focused on **men’s mental health** and is meeting with CEOs, angel investors, and HR professionals to gather feedback (16:48)  \n    - He uses these conversations as informal focus groups to understand what features or offers would motivate purchase decisions (17:27).  \n\n- Colin shared personal context about the **Orenda Center of Wellness**, indicating the product’s emotional and strategic significance in the mental health space (10:39)  \n    - This connection underscores the team’s commitment to meaningful impact beyond commercial success.  \n\n## **Operational Coordination and Collaboration**\n\nThe team is organizing workflows and access to accelerate development and maintain alignment.  \n\n- Joe granted the marketing team user access to the Lovable platform to streamline collaboration and reduce reliance on screenshots (18:05)  \n    - Colin and Santi will review the live platform to finalize UI updates and design framework for the website (17:45)  \n    - The shared access supports faster iteration on branding, product UI, and content development.  \n\n- Joe and Colin discussed travel plans for in-person meetings during the week of **January 21st to 25th**, aiming to strengthen team coordination (21:14)  \n    - Joe also shared positive feedback from testers of his handcrafted blueberry and strawberry wines, reinforcing personal rapport with stakeholders (21:37).  \n\n- The team is cautious about adopting new AI tools like **Cowork Claude** due to privacy concerns, preferring to isolate experiments on virtual machines (18:27)  \n    - Colin and Joe expressed wariness of apps linked to foreign data policies, citing tools like **DeepSeek** as risky (20:54).  \n\n## **Next Steps and Priorities**\n\nClear immediate actions are defined to maintain momentum on branding and product refinement.  \n\n- Joe will send the logo image and invite marketing users into Lovable to enable collaborative design and development (08:07)  \n- Colin and Santi will produce branding assets, including EPS logo files and website design concepts, after reviewing the current platform UI (07:45)  \n- One-pager content will be developed by Joe, leveraging AI where possible to answer security and usage questions (22:24)  \n- The team will explore HIPAA-compliant backend options beyond Supabase to ensure platform security and regulatory adherence (15:55)  \n- Mobile app development remains a priority to boost user trust and engagement by controlling personal data (13:38)","outline":null,"keywords":["Mental Health","Treatment Center Portal","Lovable Platform","UI/UX Design","HIPAA Compliance","AI Integration"],"overview":"- **Patient-treatment center portal:** Tracks bed capacity, insurance plans, and levels of care for better mental health access. \n- **Insurance editing feature:** Allows accurate edits at company and individual levels, ensuring data precision and security.  \n- **Upcoming mobile app:** Aims to enhance user privacy and data control, addressing key barriers in mental health resource access.  \n- **Logo development:** New simplified design will maintain brand familiarity while introducing a fresh look for marketing materials.  \n- **Market engagement:** Conversations with industry leaders are shaping product features and improving understanding of customer needs.  \n- **Collaboration tools access:** Marketing team now has Lovable access to streamline design efforts and accelerate branding initiatives.","action_items":"\n**Joe Ragno**\nSend logo image files to Marketers In Demand team for EPS file creation and variations (08:07)\nProvide either screenshots or direct user access to Lovable platform for UI review and collaborative improvement (18:05)\nAdd Marketers In Demand production user to Lovable instance for easier collaboration (18:09)\nStart drafting and generating content addressing pager usefulness and security, possibly using AI tools for relevant questions (22:24)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare mini website with automated report examples built on Lovable and Claude to Joe post-call (04:28)\nUpon receiving logo and screenshots, create EPS files and initiate website framework and design process (07:45)\nFollow up with Joe offline regarding travel plans for potential in-person meeting (21:14)\nExplore backend infrastructure options ensuring HIPAA compliance and database integration for platform development (13:12)\n\n**Santiago Serrano**\nCollaborate on logo EPS file preparation and website design per discussion with Colin and Joe (07:45)\n"},"duration":23.729999542236328,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Joe Ragno"},{"id":1,"name":"Joe Ragno"},{"id":2,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Joe.","index":0,"end_time":83.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":83.55,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":1,"end_time":93.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.43,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":2,"end_time":94.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":93.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":3,"end_time":96.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.23,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Good to see you, Joe.","index":4,"end_time":97.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":96.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good to see you.","index":5,"end_time":98.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.95,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Have the last few weeks been for you, man?","index":6,"end_time":101.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Busy.","index":7,"end_time":103.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":103.08,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Very busy.","index":8,"end_time":104.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.64,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I was happy that we were able to actually get out on that flight.","index":9,"end_time":107.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.32,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"We were the last flight out.","index":10,"end_time":108.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.32,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Wow.","index":11,"end_time":109.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it was.","index":12,"end_time":111.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.52,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It was great.","index":13,"end_time":112.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.32,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I.","index":14,"end_time":112.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.36,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And I. I was telling Kim, honestly, if I wasn''t married and had all the attachments that I do here, I. I would have probably stayed.","index":15,"end_time":122.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.84,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It''s expensive as hell to eat there because they have to import everything.","index":16,"end_time":128.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":124.6,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Like a sleeve of Ritz crackers is like $12, but outside of that, man, it is gorgeous.","index":17,"end_time":134.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.2,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Have you ever been to like, one of the islands or anything like that?","index":18,"end_time":137.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.48,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I have not.","index":19,"end_time":138.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I thought it was going to be worse than Florida because, you know, I lived in Florida for 10 years, so I''m like, all right.","index":20,"end_time":146.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":138.92,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So the closer we''re getting to the equator, the more humid and the more hot it''s going to get.","index":21,"end_time":151.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":147,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And that was not the case at all, apparently.","index":22,"end_time":154,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.6,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It''s like year round.","index":23,"end_time":155.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":154,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"60% humidity and the low is like 74 to 76 and the high is like 84 to 85.","index":24,"end_time":166,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":156.04,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Like year round.","index":25,"end_time":167.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":166,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It never changes.","index":26,"end_time":168.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":167.08,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So.","index":27,"end_time":168.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.4,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Ideal.","index":28,"end_time":169.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":168.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":169.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":169.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s like beautiful and perfect and.","index":30,"end_time":172.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":169.84,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Especially as we have like a foot of snow on the ground outside.","index":31,"end_time":174.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":172.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right, right.","index":32,"end_time":176.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":174.88,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":176.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":176.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In two weeks.","index":34,"end_time":177.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":176.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":35,"end_time":178.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":177.92,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And I heard it''s.","index":36,"end_time":180.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":178.28,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"It''s been so cold that I heard it get referred to as a. I heard a new term that I never heard before.","index":37,"end_time":185.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":180.08,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"So everybody knows concrete, but I''ve never heard of snow creep before.","index":38,"end_time":188.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.28,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Apparently that''s what we'' dealing with at this point.","index":39,"end_time":191.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.2,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Oh, dude, you should have seen my to my daughter''s her in one year and she had her appointment.","index":40,"end_time":196.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":191.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We had to go get her shots and everything.","index":41,"end_time":197.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":196.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I had to dig the car out like the night before.","index":42,"end_time":200.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":198.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, God.","index":43,"end_time":201.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.1,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"And it was frozen solid like, all across.","index":44,"end_time":205.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":202.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was out there, like, just trying to attack the snow.","index":45,"end_time":209.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":205.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I just like, worked out a path and got out.","index":46,"end_time":211.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I was like, finally.","index":47,"end_time":213.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":211.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Jesus.","index":48,"end_time":214.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.98,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah, it.","index":49,"end_time":216.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":215.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It takes a while, too, with this.","index":50,"end_time":218.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":216.71,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"With the way that it is.","index":51,"end_time":219.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":218.71,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":220.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With the.","index":53,"end_time":221.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How cold it''s been.","index":54,"end_time":222.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":55,"end_time":224.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.15,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Well, that''s great to hear.","index":56,"end_time":225.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":224.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe feeling a little refreshed, hopefully.","index":57,"end_time":227.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":58,"end_time":229.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":228.47,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"I mean, there''s been a lot of catch up this last.","index":59,"end_time":230.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.19,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Definitely, definitely feeling pretty refreshed.","index":60,"end_time":234.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.07,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":61,"end_time":235.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.71,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Well, I want to introduce you to Santi.","index":62,"end_time":237.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":235.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Santi''s a strategist on our team.","index":63,"end_time":238.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":237.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s been working here, I think.","index":64,"end_time":240.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":238.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Santi, did you join in, like probably about six months, right?","index":65,"end_time":242.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":240.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, almost a year Almost a year.","index":66,"end_time":245.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":243.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, color me wrong there, but yeah, Santi''s.","index":67,"end_time":250.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":245.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s a great asset on our team.","index":68,"end_time":253.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":251.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s been working a lot on internal marketing as well.","index":69,"end_time":255.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":253.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So he''s seen a lot of what we''ve been doing with like Lovable and Nan and Claude and what we''re able to do there.","index":70,"end_time":261.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":255.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I felt like he would be a great fit for this account.","index":71,"end_time":263.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":72,"end_time":264.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.12,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Nice to meet you, Joe.","index":73,"end_time":265.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":264.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Likewise.","index":74,"end_time":266.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":265.88,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"Nice to meet you, Santi and Joe.","index":75,"end_time":268.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":266.4,"speaker_name":"Joe Ragno"},{"text":"One thing I want to send over to you after this call is we built this just mini website of some of the offers that we''re putting together and we feel like this helps get the, the ideas flowing for things that we can build for our clients as well.","index":76,"end_time":283.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":268.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send this over to you.","index":77,"end_time":284.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":283.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can just mess around with some of the reports, but all of these are clawed and lovable, built auto generated, doing like scraping and all sorts of automations.","index":78,"end_time":294.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7