    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Aligned on refining branding with consensus to reuse Autobytes color palette for faster setup.","Colin will generate EPS logo files and begin website layout after user access is granted.","Joe demoed the provider and patient portals, including referral handling and insurance matching.","Joe is actively networking via LinkedIn groups to understand employer needs and refine positioning.","Santi will assist with strategic input as the team prepares one-pagers post-brand alignment."],"highlights":[{"quote":"It''s something that''s actionable, that we can onboard people with.","speaker":"Joe Ragno"},{"quote":"You''re doing basically focus groups, which is awesome.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"Having our own proprietary models will be beneficial.","speaker":"Joe Ragno"}],"topics":["branding","delivery","marketing","infrastructure"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-06T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Product Development and Platform Strategy**\n\nThe team is advancing a patient-treatment center platform focused on usability, data security, and integration to improve mental health care access.  \n\n- **Joe Ragno** demonstrated the treatment center portal which tracks **bed capacity, available beds, specialties, insurance plans, and levels of care** (13:11)  \n    - The portal supports editing insurance networks at both company-wide and individual center levels to ensure accuracy.  \n    - Team management features allow setting user access levels and invite controls to maintain secure collaboration.  \n    - Integration with EMR/CRM systems like **Khipu, Salesforce, Best Notes, and Sunwave** is in place to streamline data flow.  \n    - Joe emphasized ongoing work on preference settings and fine-tuning to make onboarding smoother and more actionable.  \n\n- The **patient-facing web portal** currently captures insurance and assessment data but still lacks a fully integrated pre-admission assessment to avoid redundant questions (12:49)  \n    - Joe highlighted efforts to reduce repetitive queries that frustrate users by consulting treatment centers for feedback.  \n    - A mobile app is planned to give patients control over their data and improve privacy, addressing a key barrier to using mental health resources via employers (13:38)  \n    - Strong encryption and data safety are priorities to build trust and increase engagement.  \n\n- On infrastructure, the backend relies on **Supabase** for database and CMS functionality, though HIPAA compliance concerns persist regarding integration with **Lovable** (15:24)  \n    - Joe noted that Supabase offers HIPAA compliance at approximately **$1,000/month**, but compliance on Lovable’s side remains uncertain.  \n    - Colin and Joe plan to explore alternative platforms like **Manus** and evaluate technical limitations of tools like **Cursor** for Salesforce development (15:55)  \n    - The team agreed to prioritize the overall project goals over specific tools, maintaining flexibility in tech choices (16:33).  \n\n- Joe shared plans to develop proprietary AI models using his high-spec local hardware, aiming to build a “crisis companion” feature that avoids misinterpretation as therapy (19:00)  \n    - This approach reflects a strategic focus on unique AI capabilities to differentiate the product and enhance user support.  \n\n## **Branding and Marketing Materials**\n\nThe group is aligning on brand identity and marketing assets to support platform launch and client outreach.  \n\n- Joe presented a **simplified logo** that conveys the desired vibe with minimal design, which the team found promising for initial use (06:00)  \n    - The logo’s green color could be an accent alongside the existing **Autobytes color palette**, maintaining brand familiarity while introducing freshness (07:23)  \n    - Colin tasked Santi with creating **EPS files** of the logo in multiple color versions for flexible use across materials (07:45).  \n\n- Colin will send a **mini website with auto-generated offers** built using Lovable and Clawed tools to spark ideas for client campaigns (04:28)  \n    - These marketing assets highlight automated report generation and scraping functionalities that showcase tech capabilities.  \n\n- The team plans to develop **one-pagers** once the logo and brand colors are finalized, focusing on clear messaging and security benefits (22:14)  \n    - Joe is proactively drafting content questions and considering AI-generated material to address common client concerns about usefulness and security (22:40).  \n\n## **Market Engagement and Strategic Insights**\n\nOngoing market research and outreach are shaping product positioning and customer understanding.  \n\n- Joe joined a LinkedIn group focused on **men’s mental health** and is meeting with CEOs, angel investors, and HR professionals to gather feedback (16:48)  \n    - He uses these conversations as informal focus groups to understand what features or offers would motivate purchase decisions (17:27).  \n\n- Colin shared personal context about the **Orenda Center of Wellness**, indicating the product’s emotional and strategic significance in the mental health space (10:39)  \n    - This connection underscores the team’s commitment to meaningful impact beyond commercial success.  \n\n## **Operational Coordination and Collaboration**\n\nThe team is organizing workflows and access to accelerate development and maintain alignment.  \n\n- Joe granted the marketing team user access to the Lovable platform to streamline collaboration and reduce reliance on screenshots (18:05)  \n    - Colin and Santi will review the live platform to finalize UI updates and design framework for the website (17:45)  \n    - The shared access supports faster iteration on branding, product UI, and content development.  \n\n- Joe and Colin discussed travel plans for in-person meetings during the week of **January 21st to 25th**, aiming to strengthen team coordination (21:14)  \n    - Joe also shared positive feedback from testers of his handcrafted blueberry and strawberry wines, reinforcing personal rapport with stakeholders (21:37).  \n\n- The team is cautious about adopting new AI tools like **Cowork Claude** due to privacy concerns, preferring to isolate experiments on virtual machines (18:27)  \n    - Colin and Joe expressed wariness of apps linked to foreign data policies, citing tools like **DeepSeek** as risky (20:54).  \n\n## **Next Steps and Priorities**\n\nClear immediate actions are defined to maintain momentum on branding and product refinement.  \n\n- Joe will send the logo image and invite marketing users into Lovable to enable collaborative design and development (08:07)  \n- Colin and Santi will produce branding assets, including EPS logo files and website design concepts, after reviewing the current platform UI (07:45)  \n- One-pager content will be developed by Joe, leveraging AI where possible to answer security and usage questions (22:24)  \n- The team will explore HIPAA-compliant backend options beyond Supabase to ensure platform security and regulatory adherence (15:55)  \n- Mobile app development remains a priority to boost user trust and engagement by controlling personal data (13:38)","outline":null,"keywords":["Mental Health","Treatment Center Portal","Lovable Platform","UI/UX Design","HIPAA Compliance","AI Integration"],"overview":"- **Patient-treatment center portal:** Tracks bed capacity, insurance plans, and levels of care for better mental health access. \n- **Insurance editing feature:** Allows accurate edits at company and individual levels, ensuring data precision and security.  \n- **Upcoming mobile app:** Aims to enhance user privacy and data control, addressing key barriers in mental health resource access.  \n- **Logo development:** New simplified design will maintain brand familiarity while introducing a fresh look for marketing materials.  \n- **Market engagement:** Conversations with industry leaders are shaping product features and improving understanding of customer needs.  \n- **Collaboration tools access:** Marketing team now has Lovable access to streamline design efforts and accelerate branding initiatives.","action_items":"\n**Joe Ragno**\nSend logo image files to Marketers In Demand team for EPS file creation and variations (08:07)\nProvide either screenshots or direct user access to Lovable platform for UI review and collaborative improvement (18:05)\nAdd Marketers In Demand production user to Lovable instance for easier collaboration (18:09)\nStart drafting and generating content addressing pager usefulness and security, possibly using AI tools for relevant questions (22:24)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare mini website with automated report examples built on Lovable and Claude to Joe post-call (04:28)\nUpon receiving logo and screenshots, create EPS files and initiate website framework and design process (07:45)\nFollow up with Joe offline regarding travel plans for potential in-person meeting (21:14)\nExplore backend infrastructure options ensuring HIPAA compliance and database integration for platform development (13:12)\n\n**Santiago Serrano**\nCollaborate on logo EPS file preparation and website design per discussion with Colin and Joe (07:45)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"3163f450-8807-40a3-9e4d-0317a9d10d3b","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
