-- Meeting: Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync (2026-02-06 15:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '059db008-bde9-43e2-b5ea-2d8080194a92',
    '2026-02-06 15:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KG8J2T7YSRRNT8J4J7YAFSNX',
    'Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync',
    '{"christinazanca","Colin Costigan","christinazanca","Colin Costigan","gabrielbencosme","gabrielbencosme"}'::text[],
    2466,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82807622497?pwd=1oWxQKkVvrj4tRTln1UgER5pencHWv.1',
    '{"id":"01KG8J2T7YSRRNT8J4J7YAFSNX","title":"Ponce Bank // MiD: HubSpot Sync","summary":{"notes":"## **Integration and API Development**\n\nThe core integration between **Salesforce** and **HubSpot** is now established with working API endpoints, focusing on live syncing lead and contact data (07:11).\n\n- **Gabriel Bencosme** built a private app with webhooks and HTTP listeners enabling real-time data flow when a lead status changes to qualified in HubSpot.\n    - He created two main flows for VISCI checks and email validations, now being modularized into subflows for easier maintenance.\n    - API security remains a key focus, with plans to implement **RAML specification** and encryption using **hash 256** protocols to restrict access to valid POST requests from HubSpot.\n    - The system currently processes limited triggers but will expand to handle complex business rules governing data updates and validations.\n- The next step is defining exact data payloads for sync, including what fields update from HubSpot to Salesforce and vice versa, to avoid overwrites like name or VIS key changes that cause data conflicts (09:17).\n    - This includes setting restrictions on fields that should never change and creating case notifications in Salesforce for exceptions.\n    - Gabriel requested support from Salesforce admins for setting up validation and automation rules in HubSpot to enforce data integrity.\n- **Colin Costigan** emphasized the need to finalize which data points—like income ranges or campaign tags—should flow between systems, ensuring Salesforce remains the system of record for core contact data (09:29).\n    - He confirmed assistance would be provided for HubSpot configuration as needed, especially for automation and permissions.\n- Duplicate record prevention is being addressed through Salesforce’s duplicate checks on email and phone number, with plans to enhance matching criteria based on further data fields (28:25).\n    - The team acknowledged imperfect data entry from users and discussed transformation rules in MuleSoft to normalize fields like gender to accepted picklist values and default unknowns for invalid inputs (30:21).\n    - For free-text fields such as addresses and names, challenges remain due to inconsistent input formatting; automated enrichment in HubSpot helps with company data but not for personal names (33:31).\n\n## **Lead Capture and Qualification Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to refine lead capture forms and qualification criteria to better route prospects to marketing or sales funnels based on their readiness and needs (18:00).\n\n- **Christina Zanca** proposed using targeted questions on forms, such as home buying stage or prequalification status, to segment leads into discovery (marketing) or ready-to-purchase (sales) funnels.\n    - This approach aligns with business input, particularly from sales leads like **Sunita**, who may want only highly qualified prospects routed directly to sales.\n- **Gabriel** suggested creating specific opportunity record types in Salesforce to store answers from qualifying questions, enabling clear lead segmentation without complex text parsing (20:00).\n    - These opportunity fields would serve as flags visible to sales reps for prioritizing leads.\n- **Colin** explained HubSpot supports multi-step forms collecting basic info first, then optional deeper qualification data, allowing dynamic lead scoring and routing (23:28).\n    - This method respects user privacy by letting prospects choose how much info to share before sales engagement.\n- The group recognized the need to sync business processes with these forms, ensuring Salesforce workflows assign leads to queues or branches based on product interest and qualification status (15:52).\n    - Notifications and dashboards will be built so sales can track lead assignments and conversion activities, reducing duplicate data entry and missed follow-ups.\n\n## **Salesforce and HubSpot Data Architecture**\n\nThe integration architecture is designed to sync individual contacts and eventually business accounts, with a flexible API structure that can extend to multiple record types without rebuilding processes (14:04).\n\n- Gabriel created a simplified flow diagram showing Salesforce on one side and HubSpot on the other, with MuleSoft integrations handling data transformations and sync triggers.\n    - The current trigger is lead qualification in HubSpot, which pushes data to Salesforce.\n    - The Salesforce side links contacts to opportunities reflecting product interest, enabling sales tracking and reporting.\n- The team discussed adding custom sections or related lists in Salesforce contact records to display marketing campaign flags, engagement history, and lead scoring attributes passed from HubSpot (36:53).\n    - This provides sales reps with context on customer journey and behavior without switching systems.\n    - If data volume grows, new custom objects may be created and linked rather than cluttering contact pages.\n- The long-term vision includes capturing multiple customer touchpoints—such as campaign interactions, website visits, and branch visits—to create a dynamic lifecycle profile driving personalized marketing and sales outreach (38:43).\n- Salesforce’s duplicate detection and merge suggestions will be refined to handle imperfect data input, supported by transformation rules in MuleSoft to standardize key fields and avoid sync errors (28:25, 30:21).\n\n## **Process and Workflow Enhancements**\n\nImproving the lead management process involves standardizing data entry, avoiding duplicates, and aligning marketing and sales workflows for better conversion (16:50).\n\n- The team identified that many sales reps currently do not use the lead generator tool, leading to duplicate records and missed opportunities.\n    - Automating data sync and validation between HubSpot and Salesforce aims to reduce manual updates and errors.\n- Christina highlighted the need to capture complete customer journey data, including campaign involvement and behavioral signals, to help sales prioritize leads and personalize outreach (36:53).\n- The planned workflows include alerts for invalid or conflicting data (e.g., VIS key mismatches) and escalation to cases in Salesforce to resolve issues quickly (12:27).\n- The team agreed on a phased approach: start with basic lead qualification and routing, then incrementally add campaign tracking, lead scoring, and richer customer profiles.\n- Training and documentation will be needed as new validation rules and form structures roll out to ensure consistent data capture across branches and marketing teams.\n\n## **Timelines, Ownership, and Next Steps**\n\nThe first direct mail campaign is targeted for **February 20** with a second wave around **March 2**, pending final location selections and compliance reviews (05:05).\n\n- Christina is coordinating with Jane and branch managers to finalize mailing lists for these campaigns.\n- Gabriel has completed the core API connectivity and is now focusing on data structure, security, and detailed field mapping to support live sync.\n- Colin committed to providing technical support for HubSpot admin tasks and Salesforce automation setup as the integration matures.\n- The team will review the integration flow diagram with broader stakeholders to clarify responsibilities and refine the end-to-end process (13:07).\n- Follow-ups include defining the exact payload fields, building validation rules in HubSpot, enhancing duplicate detection in Salesforce, and planning multi-step form questions based on business input.\n- Christina and Colin will continue working with business leads to finalize qualifying questions and marketing funnel segmentation criteria before expanding the integration scope.","outline":null,"keywords":["Lead synchronization","API integration","HubSpot","Salesforce","data validation","marketing funnel"],"overview":"- **API Integration Established:** Salesforce and HubSpot integration works through API endpoints for live contact data syncing.  \n- **Data Payload Definitions Needed:** Identify which fields sync in both directions to avoid conflicts and data overwrites.  \n- **Lead Capture Refinement:** Implement targeted questions to route leads based on readiness, improving sales and marketing alignment.  \n- **Salesforce Customization Discussed:** Consider adding custom sections to contact records for better visibility of marketing engagement and lead scoring.  \n- **Training and Workflow Phases:** Focus on training and phased approach for integrating new validation rules and capturing customer journey data.  \n- **Direct Mail Campaign Timeline:** First campaign scheduled for February 20; finalizing mailing lists and automation processes with branch managers.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nCoordinate with Jane and branch managers to finalize and send location lists for postcard mail campaigns (05:05)\nSync with business team leads to define key qualifying questions for web forms that determine marketing funnel or direct sales routing for leads (19:20)\nDiscuss with Colin options for Salesforce fields to store marketing campaign flags, customer journey data, and related engagement notes for sales visibility (27:09)\nFollow up and communicate any scheduling or project delays promptly to the team via email (40:09)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nContinue development to implement API security for MuleSoft HTTP listener endpoint, ensuring payload encryption and validation against HubSpot standards (07:58)\nRefactor current large MuleSoft flows into manageable modular subflows for better maintainability and debugging (07:11)\nDefine specifics of data fields and payload transformations to manage bi-directional sync and avoid duplicate records or unwanted overwrites, including immutable fields like VIS key (09:17)\nEngage with Salesforce and HubSpot system admins to establish proper validation rules and field-level restrictions compatible between platforms (10:44)\nProvide ongoing updates to the team on API integration progress and contribute to refining the integration process diagrams for team clarity (14:03)\nLead in setting up logic to create Salesforce cases for data anomalies detected during sync (12:20)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nAssist Gabriel and the team in implementing HubSpot-side automation and validation rules, clarifying technical requirements and platform capabilities (10:52)\nSupport lead form design by suggesting multi-step HubSpot forms to incrementally collect customer info and improve lead qualification (23:52)\nCollaborate with Christina on Salesforce campaign and customer profile field mapping to enrich sales insights from marketing data (27:09)\nProvide expertise on duplicate detection logic within Salesforce and options for improvements in data quality and matching rules (28:25)\nAdvise on lead scoring model designs and organic growth of integrated marketing-sales workflows (39:50)\n\n**Ashley Taska**\nAssist with creation of Salesforce fields, sections, or related lists to display marketing and engagement data linked to leads and customers (37:10)\n"},"duration":41.099998474121094,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"christinazanca"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"id":5,"name":"gabrielbencosme"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, colleen.","index":0,"end_time":180.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":179.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":181.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":180.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Did you see Barb''s email?","index":2,"end_time":191.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I just messaged you back that.","index":3,"end_time":192.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":191.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll check it out after this meeting.","index":4,"end_time":194.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":192.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It.","index":5,"end_time":204.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":204.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good morning, guys.","index":6,"end_time":234.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":233.61,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"How are you?","index":7,"end_time":234.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":234.21,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Hey, Gabe.","index":8,"end_time":235.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":9,"end_time":236.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":235.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":10,"end_time":238.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":238.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Can''t complain.","index":11,"end_time":239.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":238.65,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s Friday.","index":12,"end_time":240.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":240.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a good thing, right?","index":13,"end_time":243.85,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":242.65,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":244.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hopefully we don''t get any more snow.","index":15,"end_time":248.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I keep hearing that we''re going to get like a dusting or something.","index":16,"end_time":250.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, man.","index":17,"end_time":251.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":251.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And on top of all the stuff we have already.","index":18,"end_time":253.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":251.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m gonna be dangerous.","index":19,"end_time":255.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":253.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Good morning, Christina.","index":20,"end_time":258.209,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.329,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Quick.","index":21,"end_time":260.049,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.929,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know we''re.","index":22,"end_time":260.689,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.049,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re just waiting for.","index":23,"end_time":262.369,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.249,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Can I just mention Colin and Guille we sent over or compliance sent over comments on the 207postcard.","index":24,"end_time":272.369,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":265.489,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you could just take a look at those.","index":25,"end_time":274.489,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":273.089,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They did catch something that I. I don''t know how I didn''t even catch.","index":26,"end_time":276.889,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":274.489,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think I was just looking at it too many times.","index":27,"end_time":278.849,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":276.889,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But we have the minimum.","index":28,"end_time":281.009,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":279.009,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"No minimum balance, but there is a minimum balance just for this promotion.","index":29,"end_time":284.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.009,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we just can''t mention it.","index":30,"end_time":286.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just like little things like asterisks that need to go.","index":31,"end_time":289.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But overall, like the new layout design looks really good.","index":32,"end_time":294.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.3,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":33,"end_time":294.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":34,"end_time":296.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And with that, Christina, I know that you mentioned Jane was going to send over a few locations that we could use to expand the list.","index":35,"end_time":302.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":296.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t seen those come through.","index":36,"end_time":304.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re still waiting for a little bit of back and we have a little bit of back and forth with the branch manager on that.","index":37,"end_time":309.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.06,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll sync with Jane.","index":38,"end_time":310.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":309.58,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"She''s out today.","index":39,"end_time":310.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":310.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But.","index":40,"end_time":312.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.24,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But that is going to come.","index":41,"end_time":315.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":312.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think.","index":42,"end_time":315.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"223 is going to be our mail or 220 is going to be like our drop date for the first round and like I think like 3, 2 is for the second so we should be okay to get that.","index":43,"end_time":323.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":315.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So.","index":44,"end_time":325.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":325.12,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":45,"end_time":325.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":46,"end_time":326.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":325.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":47,"end_time":327.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":326.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":48,"end_time":328.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":327.92,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Hey, Victor.","index":49,"end_time":329.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Ashley.","index":50,"end_time":329.8,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":329.12,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":51,"end_time":330.32,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":329.8,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Hello.","index":52,"end_time":331,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":330.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Good boy, Deke.","index":53,"end_time":331.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":331,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Good morning.","index":54,"end_time":334.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":333.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy Friday.","index":55,"end_time":334.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so last week you guys got access or I think maybe it was even earlier this week where for the super admin so that you could build the custom app.","index":56,"end_time":344.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So want to just check in on our progress there?","index":57,"end_time":346.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":344.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I think that''ll take that.","index":58,"end_time":350.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":348.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I was able to.","index":59,"end_time":352.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":350.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Well, I don''t have an easy way to explain the things that I''ve done here.","index":60,"end_time":357.14,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":353.62,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I''m not sure if I have any type of visual at this point, but yeah.","index":61,"end_time":361.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":357.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":62,"end_time":362.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":361.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So what I. I was able to create a.","index":63,"end_time":364.1,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":362.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"The private app so that the triggers that are happening from Salesforce are able.","index":64,"end_time":370.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":365.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"To send information over to Hotspot.","index":65,"end_time":372.37,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":370.17,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s one.","index":66,"end_time":373.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":372.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Then I also created a webhook on that private app so that when the only trigger that I have right now is when a lead changes from.","index":67,"end_time":383.49,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":373.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I had to add a another pick list value or what you call a.","index":68,"end_time":386.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":383.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Radio field I think is what you call it in hotspot, but another value.","index":69,"end_time":391.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":386.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s when the lead is qualified.","index":70,"end_time":393.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":391.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Information is sent over to Salesforce.","index":71,"end_time":396.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":393.27,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I did create what we call an HTTP listener that is listening to that webhook call and then depending on the payload that comes from on that hotspot, the process follows and if it matches, depending.","index":72,"end_time":409.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":396.71,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so I did create all the flows that are needed for visci checks.","index":73,"end_time":414.59,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":409.87,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And email checks to ensure that the.","index":74,"end_time":417.31,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":414.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Records are created or updated accordingly.","index":75,"end_time":420.58,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":417.31,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that''s happening in both things.","index":76,"end_time":422.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":420.58,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":77,"end_time":422.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":422.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We have.","index":78,"end_time":423.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":422.98,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I have two big flows right now.","index":79,"end_time":425.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":423.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m gonna break down those flows into sub because I know I''m using within those flows and processes that I''m kind of repeated.","index":80,"end_time":431.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":425.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I''m actually taking those processes and.","index":81,"end_time":435.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":431.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Putting them into what we call subflow so that I could call them instead of having to code this all.","index":82,"end_time":439.26,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":435.26,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So good news there.","index":83,"end_time":442.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":439.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"One of the things that I have to do is build the API security.","index":84,"end_time":446.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":443.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For the endpoint that I created.","index":85,"end_time":448.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":446.55,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":86,"end_time":448.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":448.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that HTTP listener is actually a public cloud.","index":87,"end_time":451.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":448.55,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s basically.","index":88,"end_time":452.55,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":451.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s on the cloud.","index":89,"end_time":454.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":453.11,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I have to create a RAML specification file that actually takes only a post request that is coming from HubSpot and so build that.","index":90,"end_time":462.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":454.39,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I know there''s a bunch of hotspot documentation regarding some type of security protocols.","index":91,"end_time":468.39,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":462.39,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So it''s like you have to encrypt the payload combined with the date, with the stamps of the dates.","index":92,"end_time":474.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":468.39,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And I hate encryption, to be honest with you guys.","index":93,"end_time":476.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":474.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But that''s something that I have to work with.","index":94,"end_time":478.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":476.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":95,"end_time":478.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":478.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can''t remember if HubSpot does RLS or what the other type of encryption that they do is.","index":96,"end_time":483.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, was one of the new hashes 256something.","index":97,"end_time":488.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":485.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I have to look into that documentation a little more deeply to kind of create security behind it at this point.","index":98,"end_time":493.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":488.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Even if you send some type of information to that endpoint, it it''s not going to process a lot because I have a specific.","index":99,"end_time":499.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":493.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s only processing when there is at a specific field from hotspot that''s there.","index":100,"end_time":504.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":499.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So even if somebody''s trying to send.","index":101,"end_time":506.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":504.65,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Information to it and right now, of.","index":102,"end_time":509.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":506.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Course the process is very limited.","index":103,"end_time":511.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":509.21,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s only updating certain things on the record.","index":104,"end_time":514.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":511.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So the connectivity has been created to.","index":105,"end_time":516.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":514.21,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Be Kind of summarize that.","index":106,"end_time":518.61,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":516.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think now it''s more important to.","index":107,"end_time":521.25,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":519.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Start getting into the nitty gritty of.","index":108,"end_time":522.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":521.25,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What specifics data should come over when.","index":109,"end_time":527.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":523.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''S a hotspot record and is a.","index":110,"end_time":529.74,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":527.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Hotspot records created and what data is going to come over from our record when it''s updated.","index":111,"end_time":535.7,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":529.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I think that''s most important because if we sending for example a name change, that''s something that we shouldn''t be able.","index":112,"end_time":541.86,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":535.7,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"To do for the contact level.","index":113,"end_time":543.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":541.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":114,"end_time":543.66,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":543.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because if you change the name at that point the next morning the core is going to send information about that.","index":115,"end_time":549.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":543.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Name change and it''s going to replace it again.","index":116,"end_time":550.78,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":549.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So kind of have to take a.","index":117,"end_time":553.48,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":550.78,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Little bit of more time digging into what''s necessary on those calls.","index":118,"end_time":557.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":553.48,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But good news is the connectivity exists.","index":119,"end_time":560.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":557.52,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so the endpoints are actually working back and forth.","index":120,"end_time":564,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":560.88,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So the triggers that I created actually there I think we just got to get into the specifics at this point.","index":121,"end_time":569.4,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":564,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, this is awesome.","index":122,"end_time":570.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":569.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":123,"end_time":571.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":570.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah we can work out the specifics for the payload.","index":124,"end_time":573.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean at a high level HubSpot is really just for the marketing engine and Salesforce is going to own most of the information as far as you know, we need to set a string for example for the the income ranges that we agreed on instead of the exact value of their income.","index":125,"end_time":588.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":574.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just making those decisions.","index":126,"end_time":590.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":127,"end_time":592.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":590.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So in that sense it''s just kind of like right now my APIs look like a really long process and the reason for that is because I want to test each process and I have.","index":128,"end_time":600.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":592.1,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"A bunch of loggers, loggers connected to each process.","index":129,"end_time":603.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":600.38,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I know what''s happening and where the flows are going.","index":130,"end_time":605.54,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":603.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So eventually I''m going to break those things down as we know closer to go live.","index":131,"end_time":612.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":605.54,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But yeah, I just getting about specifics at this point of the data flow.","index":132,"end_time":617.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":612.1,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And to ensure that I think that the API is going to be able.","index":133,"end_time":623.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":618.58,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"To do what it does.","index":134,"end_time":624.34,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":623.5,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But I think in order to avoid duplicates we have to create some type of restrictions.","index":135,"end_time":629.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":624.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So one of my questions Colin, I haven''t.","index":136,"end_time":632.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":629.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For example I added a pick list.","index":137,"end_time":634.82,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":633.14,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Value on on hotspot and that''s not a problem.","index":138,"end_time":637.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":634.82,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I could do little minimal admin, system admin, stuff like that.","index":139,"end_time":641.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":637.67,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But you know, when it comes to.","index":140,"end_time":642.79,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":641.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Building maybe some type of automation behind I''m not sure how to do that about go about that yet in hot spot so I might need to help with those things.","index":141,"end_time":650.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":642.79,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":142,"end_time":651.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just to let you guys know that.","index":143,"end_time":654.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":652.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You know right now the triggers are very simple.","index":144,"end_time":655.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":654.03,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I know they''re Going to be more complex down the line specifically, you know, depending on the specificity of things.","index":145,"end_time":661.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":655.87,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But yeah, just want to make sure that, you know, we can get a line into getting some assistance on the hotspot side on that sense because.","index":146,"end_time":669.23,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":661.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":147,"end_time":670.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No Salesforce.","index":148,"end_time":671.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":671.15,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"To be honest, I just got acquainted with Hotspot and I''m doing a pretty good job reading documentation, but there''s also.","index":149,"end_time":677.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":671.99,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"A lot to go through as well.","index":150,"end_time":678.309,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":677.27,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, reading documentation when you, when.","index":151,"end_time":682.15,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":678.309,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You could do it in two seconds.","index":152,"end_time":683.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":682.15,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You know what I mean?","index":153,"end_time":683.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":683.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, exactly.","index":154,"end_time":684.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":683.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds good.","index":155,"end_time":686.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, just let me know as soon as you need us to hop in and do something from that side.","index":156,"end_time":691.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pretty much the only thing that we''re expecting from you guys inside of HubSpot''s platform Platform is what you''re doing with the private app and the API connection and the webhooks that you''re setting up.","index":157,"end_time":698.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":158,"end_time":698.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":698.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, that''s kind of set at this point.","index":159,"end_time":700.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":698.93,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s just about getting the API structure completely defined.","index":160,"end_time":704.57,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":700.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":705.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":704.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, so that we can actually start getting some type of workload.","index":162,"end_time":709.69,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":705.53,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean just workflow just from the, on the Hotspot side, but also in Salesforce.","index":163,"end_time":713.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":709.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":164,"end_time":713.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":713.33,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because we know we gotta understand that I''m gonna have to put some restrictions on emails depending so that nobody can change it so that make sure that those contacts keep in sync.","index":165,"end_time":721.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":713.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So those kind of kind of things that we also going to need help on the hotspot side.","index":166,"end_time":724.98,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":722.14,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So building that, those kind of, I don''t know, they call it validation rules in Salesforce.","index":167,"end_time":729.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":724.98,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I don''t know if Hotspot supports some type of field level restrictions or things like that.","index":168,"end_time":734.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":729.02,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m pretty sure it does.","index":169,"end_time":735.1,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":734.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":170,"end_time":735.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":735.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s.","index":171,"end_time":736.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":735.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s permission sets and then there''s even like field restrictions that we can put on.","index":172,"end_time":739.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":736.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":173,"end_time":740.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":739.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":174,"end_time":741.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":740.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":175,"end_time":742.66,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":742.3,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because right now part of my testing is changing that vis key.","index":176,"end_time":745.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":742.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":177,"end_time":746.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":746.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to make sure that if something gets, for example, if somebody changes the viz key, I have a process of just checking that and then if it doesn''t match, check the email.","index":178,"end_time":756.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":747.66,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But then I also created, I said, you know what?","index":179,"end_time":757.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":756.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Visky should never change.","index":180,"end_time":759.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":757.94,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But then I created something that creates a case in Salesforce and says, you know what, a vis key was existed in Hotspot but a record was created in Salesforce.","index":181,"end_time":767.34,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":759.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s a rare case that should never happen.","index":182,"end_time":769.02,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":767.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Ideally.","index":183,"end_time":769.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":769.02,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But we know users have a tendency.","index":184,"end_time":773.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":770.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Of finding things that we overlooked as developers.","index":185,"end_time":777.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":773.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So you know, that''s one of the things that I want to know that you Know, maybe putting restrictions behind those specific fields.","index":186,"end_time":783.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":777.03,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, I need help with those kind of things so that we can move them.","index":187,"end_time":787.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":783.51,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, happy to.","index":188,"end_time":788.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Happy to dive in there, Gabe.","index":189,"end_time":790.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":788.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it might also be useful to pull up the diagram we were going through last week with Betty just to show Christina, unless you guys have shown her between last call and this call of like the flow between the systems.","index":190,"end_time":800.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":790.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know we needed a big conversation around the Salesforce side of the automations happening there.","index":191,"end_time":805.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":800.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I sent it over, but I''m not sure if Christina had an opportunity to take a look at it.","index":192,"end_time":809.18,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":805.34,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''s been kind of hectic on our end.","index":193,"end_time":810.94,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":809.18,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, I haven''t.","index":194,"end_time":812.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":811.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So if you can bring that up, take a look at it.","index":195,"end_time":817.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":196,"end_time":817.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then outside of that, definitely want to see the.","index":197,"end_time":823.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":820.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"See where we''re tracking on the project plan.","index":198,"end_time":825.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, absolutely.","index":199,"end_time":826.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anyway, this.","index":200,"end_time":828.94,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":826.94,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This is not it, right?","index":201,"end_time":830.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":829.1,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Oh, no, this is the.","index":202,"end_time":830.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":830.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"No.","index":203,"end_time":831.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":830.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless it''s an updated version.","index":204,"end_time":832.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, this is a complex one.","index":205,"end_time":834.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":832.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This is what I''m using to kind of determine on a high level which how I''m designing the APIs.","index":206,"end_time":840.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":834.27,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But I think what we got to look is this.","index":207,"end_time":842.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":840.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This is it, right?","index":208,"end_time":843.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":842.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":209,"end_time":843.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":843.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There you go.","index":210,"end_time":843.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":843.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes.","index":211,"end_time":844.27,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":843.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":212,"end_time":844.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''re.","index":213,"end_time":845.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The top left was something that Ponce needed to work through.","index":214,"end_time":847.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":215,"end_time":848.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":848.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So, Christina, I know you''re seeing a lot here.","index":216,"end_time":852.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":849.79,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Don''t know how to keep this simple.","index":217,"end_time":853.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":852.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Like, we kind of went over it.","index":218,"end_time":855.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":853.87,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But this is basically defining the Salesforce system on this side.","index":219,"end_time":859.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":855.07,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Hotspot on the right middle, of course, is basically, I call it me also integrations.","index":220,"end_time":864.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":860.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But this is basically the hotspot processing API.","index":221,"end_time":867.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":864.81,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So essentially what we''re doing right now, since this part of the project, I created a sync between the person relationships and the contacts in HubSpot.","index":222,"end_time":878.33,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":867.53,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":223,"end_time":878.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.33,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I know eventually we''re going to start creating businesses, but this is a little more complex because this has to deal with associations in HubSpot and also lookups in Salesforce.","index":224,"end_time":889.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":879.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So if we build something solid, which what I''ve created is essentially the process that creates a person, since the APIs are very similar, as you progress through the flow, the payload and the actual endpoint of the API are being constructed.","index":225,"end_time":908.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":889.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Along with the flow.","index":226,"end_time":909.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":908.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":227,"end_time":909.97,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":909.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so for a person account, it''ll detect that it''s a person account and then from there it''ll go to that.","index":228,"end_time":915.28,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":909.97,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Call out that specific API for the contact.","index":229,"end_time":917.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":915.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":230,"end_time":917.83,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":917.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So trying to build something very similar to business so that when we have to make the updates, we don''t have.","index":231,"end_time":922.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":917.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"To rebuild the whole process.","index":232,"end_time":923.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":922.51,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But essentially right now, this Portion is what has been kind of built.","index":233,"end_time":927.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":924.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m not sure this is more or less on a high level what''s happening on the hotspot side.","index":234,"end_time":932.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":928.23,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I know something gets created on the website, it gets created on hotspot.","index":235,"end_time":936.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":932.55,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You have a lead process.","index":236,"end_time":937.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":936.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"You know, I''m not sure if the.","index":237,"end_time":939.71,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":937.67,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Team wants to create something that has more details that I could add onto this, but essentially this is how I created the flow.","index":238,"end_time":946.74,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":939.71,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And the only trigger is that when a lead becomes qualified, then let''s pass that contact over to Salesforce.","index":239,"end_time":952.38,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":946.74,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Now one of the things that we were discussing and what column is alluding to is this portion right here, the sales process.","index":240,"end_time":959.26,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":952.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So when something comes into Salesforce, specifically.","index":241,"end_time":962.5,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":959.5,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"A brand new contact, right.","index":242,"end_time":963.82,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":962.5,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That contact is going to have some basic information and then it''s going to have an opportunity attached to it which is going to contain basically, I don''t know, the products and the interest of that contact.","index":243,"end_time":975.41,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":963.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Contact.","index":244,"end_time":975.68,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":975.48,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":245,"end_time":976.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":975.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so the idea is behind all of this is we need to create notifications and flows that are gonna assign this to a queue or maybe a brand on the branch level or to the sales team.","index":246,"end_time":987.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":976.28,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so they''re gonna get notified.","index":247,"end_time":989.84,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":988.2,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And then besides that, we also need to create kind of reporting and dashboards that are gonna happen so that they could actually, if they''re gonna book this contact at one point in time, they''re actually pick that because we have seen that a lot of the times, even.","index":248,"end_time":1002.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":989.84,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"On the lending side of the house.","index":249,"end_time":1004.2,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1002.88,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Which is outside of this.","index":250,"end_time":1005.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1004.52,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But it''s from experience that they, they don''t typically search for the users.","index":251,"end_time":1010.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1005.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":252,"end_time":1010.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1010.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the lead generator is not being used now because we.","index":253,"end_time":1013.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If certain information like phone, email, name and things like that are coming from Hotspot that is already somewhat of a, of a, of a lift that the, the sales even have to update.","index":254,"end_time":1026.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1015.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So they, if they pick the record itself, not only are they going through the workflow, they''re not creating a duplicate record.","index":255,"end_time":1032.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1026.29,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":256,"end_time":1032.89,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1032.49,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So this is the kind of like the instance where we need to kind of define the process so that that.","index":257,"end_time":1037.73,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1033.29,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Duplicate never gets created.","index":258,"end_time":1039.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1037.73,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":259,"end_time":1039.45,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1039.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":260,"end_time":1040.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1039.45,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m putting the checks and the, and the, and the safeguards so that we can get notified when something of that nature happens.","index":261,"end_time":1045.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1040.17,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And the reason for that, of course a live sync.","index":262,"end_time":1047.85,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1046.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we want to be notified of a record created again for example, that if something has a VIS key, it comes with a VS key value.","index":263,"end_time":1056.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1047.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That means that it exists in both systems.","index":264,"end_time":1059.01,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1057.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But let''s change that this key and now it doesn''t find it on a record gets Created, I mean, yeah.","index":265,"end_time":1063.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1059.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And then you can''t and you can'' align it to a campaign order.","index":266,"end_time":1066.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1063.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So this is the kind of things that we kind of want to ensure that this is happening in Salesforce.","index":267,"end_time":1071.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1067.51,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So let me ask you a question.","index":268,"end_time":1073.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1072.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":269,"end_time":1074.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1074.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right now there is the lead generator, I guess, functionality in place because Victor was testing it, I guess.","index":270,"end_time":1083.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1075.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But what happened was there was some thing in the background with campaigns that got wonky.","index":271,"end_time":1088.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1083.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I''m thinking is that right now when a rep brings up sort of like a new customer or when they''re adding a new customer into the system, what fields are they capturing?","index":272,"end_time":1108.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1090.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because then knowing that we can then build our forms in a way that kind of essentially captures similar fields.","index":273,"end_time":1115.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1108.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So typically now our lead web to lead forms are very general, so they''ll just capture.","index":274,"end_time":1123.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1117.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And Victor, correct me if I''m wrong, but it''s typically like first name, last name, I think a phone number, maybe email.","index":275,"end_time":1129.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":276,"end_time":1129.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What we may want to do is thinking about the product type determine, well, what are the questions that if they answer would be the trigger points to determine whether or not they''d go to the marketing funnel for a lead or they go directly to this to the sales team for a lead.","index":277,"end_time":1147.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.26,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then by product we would just have to determine what either funnel or what person on the team would get the leads if that.","index":278,"end_time":1158.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1147.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If those checkboxes were checked off.","index":279,"end_time":1161.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1159.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":280,"end_time":1162.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1161.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for.","index":281,"end_time":1163.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1162.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I''ll use lending for an example.","index":282,"end_time":1164.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1163.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":283,"end_time":1164.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1164.57,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If we were to add a couple of questions like what stage of the home buying process are you in?","index":284,"end_time":1169.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1165.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or do you have a pre qualification?","index":285,"end_time":1171.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or do you need a pre qualification?","index":286,"end_time":1174.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.81,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like are you ready to buy a home?","index":287,"end_time":1178.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1177.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yes.","index":288,"end_time":1179.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Now or six months from now?","index":289,"end_time":1181.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like, all of those questions would help us determine whether or not like they''re really ready or are they looking.","index":290,"end_time":1187.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1181.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":291,"end_time":1187.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.19,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I''ve come up with those questions.","index":292,"end_time":1191.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Then you would use those questions to basically kind of have Museoff figure out which route they''re going, is that right?","index":293,"end_time":1199.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1191.91,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, yeah, at one point, yes.","index":294,"end_time":1202.91,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1200.87,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean, okay, it, it depends the level of information of those questions.","index":295,"end_time":1208.99,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1202.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":296,"end_time":1209.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1208.99,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because I mean, I''m not gonna have me.","index":297,"end_time":1210.75,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1209.19,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Also, it can get really complex if those questions I''m reading through, you know, a description field.","index":298,"end_time":1216.95,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1210.75,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":299,"end_time":1217.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1216.95,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean, if I''m reading checkbox or something like that, and things are specifically, for example, like if you need it, if, if we have a process like just what you just mentioned, we have a, A process for the lending side or, or, or more.","index":300,"end_time":1234.87,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1217.15,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Or questions that are more related to.","index":301,"end_time":1236.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1234.87,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"The lending side or that than the deposit.","index":302,"end_time":1238.35,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1236.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":303,"end_time":1238.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1238.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So if Those questions are answered.","index":304,"end_time":1240.67,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1238.67,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What, what would be something that we could do on our side is maybe have MuleSoft create a specific opportunity record type that assigns that.","index":305,"end_time":1248.79,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1240.67,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Have that.","index":306,"end_time":1249.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1248.79,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That specific values there or, you know, you know what I mean?","index":307,"end_time":1253.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1249.27,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Like, I don''t have to read questions, but if some of those questions are answered or any.","index":308,"end_time":1259.6,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1253.11,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Or they''re populated, at least I could pass the information over to a specific field in the opportunity record.","index":309,"end_time":1265.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1259.6,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":310,"end_time":1265.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1265.08,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And then when the contact is created or updated and they see the opportunity, then they could see the answers to those questions that you guys have answers.","index":311,"end_time":1273.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1265.28,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, so then maybe based on that, then instead of, instead of driving it in the original way, I said maybe.","index":312,"end_time":1280.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1273.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We should drive it in like, what.","index":313,"end_time":1283.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1280.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Does the customer need?","index":314,"end_time":1284.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1283.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we could, we could say customer is just looking.","index":315,"end_time":1289.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1285.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":316,"end_time":1290.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1290.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Or just has interest based off of whatever.","index":317,"end_time":1293.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1290.41,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They either click on the website or they fill out the form.","index":318,"end_time":1295.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1293.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We could take those.","index":319,"end_time":1296.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1295.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If there''s a way, we could build out a funnel to say if the customer needs a, let''s just say pre qualification or they''re ready to apply, they would go into one funnel.","index":320,"end_time":1310.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1296.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If a customer just needs some general information or, you know, is ready to get started, then they would go into another form.","index":321,"end_time":1319.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1311.45,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so we can make it super easy and only give three or two or three options.","index":322,"end_time":1325.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1319.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Basically.","index":323,"end_time":1326.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We could drive it off of that.","index":324,"end_time":1329.65,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1328.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s.","index":325,"end_time":1330.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1329.65,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":326,"end_time":1331.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1330.01,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll just, I''ll just want to sync with the business teams to determine like, well, what would they.","index":327,"end_time":1336.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1331.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Essentially, I''m making an assumption right now that Sunita would say, I only want to get people that are 100 ready to buy or 100 ready for a pre qualification.","index":328,"end_time":1348.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1337.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":329,"end_time":1348.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1348.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because that''s just my assumption.","index":330,"end_time":1350.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1348.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So in the content phase, what I would want to talk to the team leads is especially the ones that deal with the leads.","index":331,"end_time":1358.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1351.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What really is your sweet spot for conversion?","index":332,"end_time":1361.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1358.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":333,"end_time":1361.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1361.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And if Sunita says, well, if somebody is definitely looking to buy, I want them, or if they''re kind of in the consideration phase, I want them because maybe that''s my ability to kind of educate them through the process.","index":334,"end_time":1378.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1362.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":335,"end_time":1378.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1378.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe she feels like she could do it better than marketing could with a bunch of just emails.","index":336,"end_time":1384.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1380.38,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":337,"end_time":1384.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so I think what we can do is call the lead, like almost like interested, like in the discovery phase and that''s marketing.","index":338,"end_time":1396.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1385.18,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And if they''re like ready to purchase or apply based off of like that one or two questions that we set up, then they could just go to the, to the, to the business.","index":339,"end_time":1405.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1396.87,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Does that make sense?","index":340,"end_time":1407.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":341,"end_time":1409.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1408.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if I Could mention something here too.","index":342,"end_time":1412.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1410.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one thing, Christina, that we''ve done, especially with HubSpot because it''s much easier in that platform is set up like a multi step form.","index":343,"end_time":1418.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where we could even have like the basic, like first name, last name, email, phone number that we collect and they submit, we capture that and then it takes them to a next step if they do want to fill out more information.","index":344,"end_time":1428.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1418.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like the what, what stage are you at?","index":345,"end_time":1430.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1428.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And all of those are just stored as properties to that contact record.","index":346,"end_time":1434.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we could just have an add or update like upsert type node.","index":347,"end_time":1438.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1435.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gabe, that old catch that like.","index":348,"end_time":1440.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1439.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, they, they actually did submit more information.","index":349,"end_time":1443.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So now it''s a hot lead or however we want to refer to it.","index":350,"end_time":1446.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1443.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":351,"end_time":1446.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1446.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean that, that is a, is an interesting thing like thinking that we.","index":352,"end_time":1450.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1446.7,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Would drive it based off of like the types of questions that they fill in.","index":353,"end_time":1454.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1450.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But you''re right, if, if they take the interest to give us more information than what''s general on the initial inquiry.","index":354,"end_time":1461.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1454.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":355,"end_time":1461.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then I think that, you know, it''s safe to say that they should go to the business.","index":356,"end_time":1465.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1462.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So maybe we take that approach.","index":357,"end_time":1466.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1465.52,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I didn''t realize that we could do those.","index":358,"end_time":1468.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1466.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s a few things that so like just because of how people are so like guarded with their information.","index":359,"end_time":1474.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1468.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean their information is their currency.","index":360,"end_time":1475.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":361,"end_time":1476.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1475.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we also give them options of like, I don''t want to fill this out right now.","index":362,"end_time":1480.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1477.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''d rather have someone from your team call me, you know, for the people who are like scared to put information in.","index":363,"end_time":1485.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1480.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And it''s like, okay, cool, send that hot lead over to Salesforce with the phone number and information they''ve put in and say like they need to call.","index":364,"end_time":1492.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1485.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":365,"end_time":1493.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"All right.","index":366,"end_time":1493.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So there''s, there''s a few different.","index":367,"end_time":1494.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1493.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need the business process of what you guys want and we can build it.","index":368,"end_time":1498,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1495.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":369,"end_time":1499.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1498.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So then I think, Gabe, what you set up here, I know it looks like, it looks complex, but I, I''m, I''m following because you know, I''ve looked at these kind of things before, so I think this looks really good.","index":370,"end_time":1510.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1499.4,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"To your point, we would just need to tell you which I guess incoming workflows you''d have to account for based off of the questions that we''re going to use and then whatever that is.","index":371,"end_time":1524.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1510.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And you would just build something in the middle, in the, in the mulesoft to kind of validate and then separate.","index":372,"end_time":1529.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1524.51,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":373,"end_time":1530.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1529.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is that what I''m doing at this point?","index":374,"end_time":1531.72,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1530.03,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"The connections are made, I just have to kind of enforce security on them.","index":375,"end_time":1536,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1531.72,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s fine with that.","index":376,"end_time":1536.92,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1536,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That grows as a process, you know, as we go, as we move along.","index":377,"end_time":1540.44,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1537.32,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"The process down here that I highlighted.","index":378,"end_time":1543.12,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1541.16,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Is essentially what I built.","index":379,"end_time":1544.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1543.12,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And the reason for record checks is because we want, you know, it''s a.","index":380,"end_time":1548.04,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1544.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''S a sync, right.","index":381,"end_time":1548.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1548.04,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It says directional sync and it''s going to be live.","index":382,"end_time":1551.16,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1548.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So the reason for those record check is to ensure that, you know, it''s.","index":383,"end_time":1556.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1551.32,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Going to the right places and their data is coming either for new or updates.","index":384,"end_time":1560.76,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1556.08,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, that is kind of been built now the actual data that''s supposed.","index":385,"end_time":1566.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1560.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"To come that need.","index":386,"end_time":1566.98,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1566.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yes.","index":387,"end_time":1567.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1566.98,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I basically created simple payloads to test the process and it''s working.","index":388,"end_time":1572.62,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1567.58,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So once I think that now is.","index":389,"end_time":1575.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1572.7,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Now we have to define what information.","index":390,"end_time":1576.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1575.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Is coming over from sales from house.","index":391,"end_time":1578.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1576.86,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Start making those transformations, adding those fields and where specifically we want to see.","index":392,"end_time":1584.14,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1579.42,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Them in Salesforce as well.","index":393,"end_time":1585.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1584.14,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Maybe we might have to create a.","index":394,"end_time":1587.06,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1585.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Section on the, on the, on the contact level or on the personal or.","index":395,"end_time":1591.42,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1587.06,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Business level where you guys are actually looking at that, you know, or the sales team can actually open at that relationship and see that section for you.","index":396,"end_time":1598.78,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1591.42,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"From that, that came from hotspot similar.","index":397,"end_time":1600.46,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1598.78,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"To how it was for marketing Cloud at one point.","index":398,"end_time":1602.42,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1600.46,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, that, that''s what I''m thinking like that there, there needs to be something because for example, like, let''s just say, you know, we want to put in additional clarity for, for them to determine.","index":399,"end_time":1613.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1602.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like okay, like with the form they came from a campaign, they looked at a couple pages on the website.","index":400,"end_time":1620.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1613.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like I, you know, Colin, how much we can pass over that gives the.","index":401,"end_time":1625.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1620.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sales team some insights into like the.","index":402,"end_time":1627.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1625.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Journey that the customer already had with.","index":403,"end_time":1629.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1627.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean we can pass a lot.","index":404,"end_time":1631.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1629.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean we can have fields for campaigns they''re currently enrolled in everything.","index":405,"end_time":1635.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":406,"end_time":1636.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1635.6,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So I think that that would be an interesting thing because also you have to understand like, so somebody might, you know, call them and then you know, their initial call was because they were leave for mortgage.","index":407,"end_time":1647.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But maybe they, through the conversation they opened up a checking account.","index":408,"end_time":1649.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1647.2,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just so happens.","index":409,"end_time":1650.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1650.02,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":410,"end_time":1650.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1650.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"They, they, they ended up talking about something else.","index":411,"end_time":1652.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1650.82,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":412,"end_time":1653.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1653.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, because they realized that they were in some other campaign.","index":413,"end_time":1656.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1653.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That could be an interesting thing to to follow.","index":414,"end_time":1658.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1656.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So let''s think that through a little bit or let me think that through a little bit more.","index":415,"end_time":1663.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1659.78,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe Colin, we can talk through some of the options.","index":416,"end_time":1665.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.46,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think that that would help.","index":417,"end_time":1667.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1665.94,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But when you talked about before the, the conversion component where you know, marketing, if we''re starting to track I guess information through either prospect lists or form input fields, things of that nature that would be eventually something that the sales team could instead of inputting, use as a lead converter.","index":418,"end_time":1691.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1667.62,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Is there a pop up in Salesforce when they go into entering a new record that would kind of almost cross check between what''s already in the system and almost like stop them sometimes.","index":419,"end_time":1703.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1691.65,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Now, I mean, Gabe could elaborate on that, but at times it lets you know when there''s a duplicate depending on certain values.","index":420,"end_time":1711.64,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1705.16,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Like I''ve, I''ve seen emails sometimes where it encourages, it encourages you at that point to kind of merge those leads.","index":421,"end_time":1717.52,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1711.64,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But we''ll have to create or we have to like we, we couldn''t do that, right?","index":422,"end_time":1721.68,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1717.52,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We have to.","index":423,"end_time":1722.36,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1721.68,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right now it''s basically a simple check is check to see at least on.","index":424,"end_time":1725.96,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1722.52,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"The elite level, I think it''s the.","index":425,"end_time":1727.12,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1725.96,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Only check it to see if there''s.","index":426,"end_time":1728.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1727.12,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Email and phone number are similar.","index":427,"end_time":1730.11,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1728.24,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If.","index":428,"end_time":1730.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1730.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay.","index":429,"end_time":1731.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1730.99,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But if we have to kind of get more, we refine that or add more fields, we actually can actually enhance.","index":430,"end_time":1737.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1731.51,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"The, the, the duplicate checks.","index":431,"end_time":1740.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1737.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":432,"end_time":1740.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1740.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So Salesforce does, does have that.","index":433,"end_time":1742.83,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1740.67,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we can.","index":434,"end_time":1743.39,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1742.83,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Okay, so maybe we can think about, you know, enhancing that, that process.","index":435,"end_time":1748.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1743.63,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"You know, I also want to, you know, caveat that, you know, a lot of the times what, what I saw just in the, you know, in the past and, and also just in trying to do a ma.","index":436,"end_time":1759.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1749.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"The data isn''t perfect.","index":437,"end_time":1762.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1761.75,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so we have to kind of think about the, the input from you know, various different people.","index":438,"end_time":1769.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1762.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for example, how are we fact.","index":439,"end_time":1774.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Checking if somebody enters in something misspelled or incorrect or abbreviated or let''s just say like the system forces an abbreviation.","index":440,"end_time":1784.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1774.15,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For example, like we had a couple of instances where like a system association, it was cut off and it only took ass.","index":441,"end_time":1791.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1784.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so we were actually going to send a direct mail to somebody that says like associate instead of association.","index":442,"end_time":1797.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1791.56,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like an imperfect, not so great kind of reference.","index":443,"end_time":1801.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1797.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":444,"end_time":1801.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1801.32,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like how are we planning for, for those two?","index":445,"end_time":1804.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1801.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because that would impact I think the validation process and the connection process between.","index":446,"end_time":1811.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1804.68,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like the two systems.","index":447,"end_time":1812.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1811.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because if we call it one thing and then the, the sales team enters.","index":448,"end_time":1817.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1812.96,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It as another, is it going to connect?","index":449,"end_time":1821.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1817.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Well, one of the things, for example, that''s a pretty good point that you bring up Christina, because I was using the gender field in, in, in in the records because you know, it''s there and Salesforce is for us it''s a pickless value pick list.","index":450,"end_time":1838.04,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1821.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Means that you choose an option and it''s already is set A set of.","index":451,"end_time":1840.88,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1838.04,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It has a set of options that are there already.","index":452,"end_time":1842.64,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1840.88,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So you know, for for example I think I just, this just became smaller, you know, this mail, right.","index":453,"end_time":1850.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1842.64,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For example, this record right here.","index":454,"end_time":1852.21,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1850.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But on the other hand, the hotspot system, this is a, a text field.","index":455,"end_time":1858.05,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1852.85,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This is something that you could just type whatever.","index":456,"end_time":1859.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1858.05,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So like you said, they could type female, they could type females or males and then put it as a, you.","index":457,"end_time":1864.77,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1859.81,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Know, you know, like.","index":458,"end_time":1866.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1864.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":459,"end_time":1866.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1866.05,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"A couple of letters in there.","index":460,"end_time":1868.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1866.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I think the best way we can go about that is I could have transformations that say, for example, something that I did is if it''s female or male, pass it.","index":461,"end_time":1877.54,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1868.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"If not, just pass it as unknown.","index":462,"end_time":1879.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1877.54,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That''s just maybe for me.","index":463,"end_time":1882.22,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1880.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that.","index":464,"end_time":1882.58,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1882.22,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Because Salesforce is going to give me an error when I try to update.","index":465,"end_time":1885.9,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1882.58,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"This field and that value is not there.","index":466,"end_time":1887.5,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1885.9,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"What''s happening is that we can maybe enforce the pick list rules across the field so that you can have data that the users can actually pick from.","index":467,"end_time":1896.93,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1888.3,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so the beauty about that is if something gets added on one system, all we have to do is add it on the other.","index":468,"end_time":1902.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1897.32,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And we don''t have to change the API because.","index":469,"end_time":1904.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1902.2,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":470,"end_time":1904.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1904.36,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We don''t have to account for people trying to putting abbreviations and things of that nature.","index":471,"end_time":1909.24,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1905.08,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, of course the more fields that we can have having pick list values and maybe that''s the best.","index":472,"end_time":1914.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1909.24,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean, again, the information is limited.","index":473,"end_time":1916.92,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1914.36,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But for example, if you need something that MuleSoft allows pretty well is they use software that is called Data Weave and that data we''ve allows a lot.","index":474,"end_time":1926.29,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1917.16,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Of transformation on the field level.","index":475,"end_time":1927.89,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1926.29,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So you can pretty much do, you know, you can get very granular on that, on that aspect, but it can also get very convoluted.","index":476,"end_time":1935.13,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1927.89,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so I don''t know if you want to, for a specific field, do a lot of processing on that end.","index":477,"end_time":1940.769,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1935.13,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean, it just depends on what.","index":478,"end_time":1943.09,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":1940.769,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, it was more for like, you know, more for like the fields that are up to the, you know, the customer to enter in like first name, last name, address, you know, business name, things like that.","index":479,"end_time":1955.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1943.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Sometimes where that, you know, there''s a limitation on a number of characters, right.","index":480,"end_time":1959.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1955.16,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Cases where there''s like multiple lines.","index":481,"end_time":1962.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1960.92,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So for like address line 1, 2, I noticed that, you know, some people, some people had addresses or apartments were in the first name or the first line, then some had them in the second line.","index":482,"end_time":1973.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1962.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so like what we had to do was even pick up address line 1, 2 and 3 because there was missing information.","index":483,"end_time":1981.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1973.64,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":484,"end_time":1981.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1981.48,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so it wasn''t consistent.","index":485,"end_time":1983.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1981.8,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so what I, I guess I''m asking is like for the instances like when we''re trying to validate from system to system where the data is imperfect.","index":486,"end_time":1993.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1983.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We may have things that ever error out or don''t necessarily convert accurately.","index":487,"end_time":2000.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.66,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I don''t know how easy that is to solve for because we''re relying on, you know, at least 100 different, you know, people to input the data.","index":488,"end_time":2010.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2000.22,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":489,"end_time":2011.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2011.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":490,"end_time":2012.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2011.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I will say is first name, last name is, is pretty difficult to control.","index":491,"end_time":2016.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2012.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, as far as like if they spell their own name wrong for businesses, it''s a little simpler because with HubSpot you guys also have breeze which is enriching that contact''s data.","index":492,"end_time":2027.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2016.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s finding their domain and then it''ll update their company name based on that.","index":493,"end_time":2031.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2027.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like it would instead of someone putting in like ass as an abbreviation, it would find the company domain like that they put in and then update the company name to match.","index":494,"end_time":2040.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2032.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, but yeah, but that''s in HubSpot.","index":495,"end_time":2043.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2040.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But I don''t know if that happens in Salesforce.","index":496,"end_time":2045.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2043.23,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I mean, that''s the data that would sync back to Salesforce though, like if they filled out a form on the website.","index":497,"end_time":2049.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2045.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got it, got it.","index":498,"end_time":2050.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2049.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, so then maybe then, you know, that that might help if we start to do more prospecting.","index":499,"end_time":2055.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2050.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But right now, Gabe, I think it''s like a limited thing because marketing is only going to get, you know, leads that were come.","index":500,"end_time":2064.659,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2055.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Are going to come through the form to start.","index":501,"end_time":2066.499,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2064.659,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Once we start doing more prospecting with the purchase list and all that kind of stuff.","index":502,"end_time":2070.779,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2067.299,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like that''s where we''re going to get, you know, those records uploaded into HubSpot and then they''ll pass over to Salesforce only when I guess they''re a true lead.","index":503,"end_time":2081.139,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2070.779,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So Salesforce would just have to be able to store the leads, have someone in the, the sales team follow up with the leads and then connecting it to the branch process on the retail side when they open up an account to be able to query first versus enter.","index":504,"end_time":2099.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2081.859,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s just I think a little bit of a process change for them.","index":505,"end_time":2102.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2099.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But all of this stuff I think looks, looks really good.","index":506,"end_time":2106.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2102.79,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think when you get into the end part, leads become qualified.","index":507,"end_time":2114.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2107.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It goes through the marketing process.","index":508,"end_time":2118.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2116.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What I built doesn''t necessarily highlight the complete process that you guys are making.","index":509,"end_time":2124.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2118.65,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''m pretty sure there''s a lot more convoluted than, than this simple diagram.","index":510,"end_time":2127.69,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2124.65,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So, you know, I was able to add more information in Salesforce because I.","index":511,"end_time":2130.37,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2127.69,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Know exactly what''s happening.","index":512,"end_time":2131.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2130.37,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":513,"end_time":2131.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2131.49,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Rather than I, you know, I know this is a system that''s currently being.","index":514,"end_time":2135.17,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2132.09,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Built on the process is being defined.","index":515,"end_time":2136.77,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2135.17,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, just for me at a.","index":516,"end_time":2138.65,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2136.77,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"High level though, Gabe, like this is the simplified way to think about it, right?","index":517,"end_time":2142.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2138.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":518,"end_time":2142.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2142.09,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So that''s, you know, that''s just me.","index":519,"end_time":2143.81,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2142.41,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Just kind of thinking about it and so.","index":520,"end_time":2146.13,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2143.81,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, because the marketing process, like you''re not going to, like the marketing process is going to have like a bunch of tentacles, but you''re not going to necessarily have to connect back to it in Salesforce because at the end of the day you''re only connecting to like the lead where, where the, where the lead came from per se, like what journey they went on, whether they had, you know, a specific email or workflow.","index":521,"end_time":2170.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2146.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like that''s more of the thing that''s going to come in HubSpot.","index":522,"end_time":2173.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2170.21,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"What we may just want to do is I would love to account for the ability to pass over some of the marketing campaign flags and the tags for just different things.","index":523,"end_time":2185.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2173.01,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Maybe even down, you know, down the line to say to the team, even just to capture like notes.","index":524,"end_time":2194,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2186.72,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"For example, like we may be able to, based off of how many times a customer comes to our website and visits a certain page, we may be able to like auto categorize them as a prospect or hot lead without them having to fill out a form.","index":525,"end_time":2210,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2194,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, we could build a lead scoring object.","index":526,"end_time":2212.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2210.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":527,"end_time":2213.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2212.88,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Goodness gracious.","index":528,"end_time":2213.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2213.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Lead scoring logic into it.","index":529,"end_time":2215.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2213.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":530,"end_time":2216.76,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2216.4,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I''m just sure that that visibility you will want to see on the actual person or the actual record for that.","index":531,"end_time":2223.08,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2216.76,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"For that contact.","index":532,"end_time":2223.92,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2223.08,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So I guess Ashley and I would.","index":533,"end_time":2226.2,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2224.16,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Have to create a field and sections and things in Salesforce Attack when somebody goes into that, they could, you know, reference all that information on that specific page and not necessarily on a different object like the opportunity.","index":534,"end_time":2236.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2226.2,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that''s something that can be done.","index":535,"end_time":2238.35,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2236.15,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And so there''s no issues there on.","index":536,"end_time":2240.43,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2238.35,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"That side because of course the nightly sync is not going to update those fields at all.","index":537,"end_time":2244.15,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2240.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So they''re going to remain with that data.","index":538,"end_time":2245.67,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2244.15,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So yeah, it''s just something as easy as like almost like setting up, you know, how you set up like a profile for the customer where it lists kind of like it''s a page list like all their accounts that they have and all that kind of stuff.","index":539,"end_time":2256.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2245.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Stuff?","index":540,"end_time":2256.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2256.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it something where you, you know, it''s almost like they have like a marketing profile where it''s like something that you could attach that would just be like every, like a laundry list of stuff like all of the engagements that happen to the customer.","index":541,"end_time":2269.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2257.34,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So we can eventually like track.","index":542,"end_time":2271.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2269.5,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Okay, for one customer, they, they received, you know, this email on this date and opened it or not.","index":543,"end_time":2277.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2271.42,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And we''re probably going to be able to do that in HubSpot but like something in Salesforce where we will have.","index":544,"end_time":2284.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2277.74,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Create what we call a related list, something like that.","index":545,"end_time":2287.51,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2284.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"We call this call out a related list which could be like a different object.","index":546,"end_time":2291.19,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2287.51,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"It''ll kind of show in the.","index":547,"end_time":2293.51,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2291.99,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I haven''t been one in a while but I, I think it''s called related.","index":548,"end_time":2297.03,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2294.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Listen.","index":549,"end_time":2297.43,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2297.03,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"And you can actually see though all.","index":550,"end_time":2298.99,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2297.43,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Those in a different object.","index":551,"end_time":2300.07,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2298.99,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"But that will kind of display on the side on, on if you add it to the page layout.","index":552,"end_time":2305.27,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2300.07,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So that''s correct.","index":553,"end_time":2306.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2305.27,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":554,"end_time":2306.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2306.47,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Right.","index":555,"end_time":2307.91,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2307.59,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"So we could either do that or actually put it in the object itself.","index":556,"end_time":2310.63,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2307.91,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I''ll depending.","index":557,"end_time":2311.11,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2310.63,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"I mean if it''s going to be.","index":558,"end_time":2312.31,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2311.11,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"A whole bunch of fields, I think we could just do a related.","index":559,"end_time":2314,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":2312.31,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":560,"end_time":2316.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2314.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"It depends on the number of fields.","index":561,"end_time":2317.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2316.03,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":562,"end_time":2317.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2317.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Because if it''s going to be a big list, we don''t want to just throw it down the relationship.","index":563,"end_time":2320.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2317.59,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We might as well create a new object and just link it.","index":564,"end_time":2323.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2320.83,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right?","index":565,"end_time":2323.47,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2323.11,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":566,"end_time":2323.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2323.47,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":567,"end_time":2326.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2326.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And maybe down the line it goes.","index":568,"end_time":2328.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2326.67,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Into that route because eventually, you know.","index":569,"end_time":2330.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2328.55,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''Re going to be starting to do more campaigns.","index":570,"end_time":2332.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2330.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I think at the get go we''re.","index":571,"end_time":2333.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2332.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Going to do, you know, just the basic ones.","index":572,"end_time":2335.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2333.27,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So like we''re going to set up and Colin, as part of the next phase, this is what we''re going to start to build out.","index":573,"end_time":2341.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2335.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"But essentially it''s like, okay, customer opens up in a new account.","index":574,"end_time":2344.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2341.07,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like this is kind of the, the complete like life cycle for them, you know, until they close an account.","index":575,"end_time":2350.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2344.29,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":576,"end_time":2351.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2350.85,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s like they''re going to kind of ebb and flow between different offers and different lead list based off of their behavior.","index":577,"end_time":2360.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2351.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s really like we just have to identify the types of things we want to market and then like let the behavior kind of push them through the flow of the campaigns.","index":578,"end_time":2370.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2360.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Right.","index":579,"end_time":2371.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2370.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And so it''s like.","index":580,"end_time":2372.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2371.17,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Open.","index":581,"end_time":2373.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2373.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"If they come in new customer, they.","index":582,"end_time":2376.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2373.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Would automatically get welcome, you know, welcome letter.","index":583,"end_time":2378.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2376.37,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"And then like down the line they.","index":584,"end_time":2381.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2379.69,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Would get like an anniversary, you know.","index":585,"end_time":2383.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2381.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Email and they would get like a birthday email depending on their birthday.","index":586,"end_time":2386.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2383.13,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like if they visited new branch location.","index":587,"end_time":2389.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2386.25,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"That''S close to them, like all sorts of stuff.","index":588,"end_time":2390.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2389.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, right, right.","index":589,"end_time":2391.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2390.93,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Like if they came in and visited.","index":590,"end_time":2393.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2391.77,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Something that they would get another thing.","index":591,"end_time":2394.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2393.53,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"So it''s like might be too complex to like build out everything to match but we can at least just give them something in sales.","index":592,"end_time":2401.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2394.97,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean it''s an organic system that we''re building.","index":593,"end_time":2403.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2401.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s going to keep growing.","index":594,"end_time":2404.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2403.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we wanted to go through the spreadsheet.","index":595,"end_time":2407.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2405.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Christina, I am six minutes late to another meeting.","index":596,"end_time":2409.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2407.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, no, no, we''re.","index":597,"end_time":2410.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2409.31,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"We''re good.","index":598,"end_time":2410.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2410.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Just call out if you can, in an email.","index":599,"end_time":2413.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2410.95,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Guille or.","index":600,"end_time":2413.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2413.11,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"I don''t know if she dropped, but if we''re running behind on anything, and.","index":601,"end_time":2420.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2414.39,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Then we''ll address those just to keep things moving.","index":602,"end_time":2424.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2420.43,"speaker_name":"christinazanca"},{"text":"Yeah, on the hubs outside, we''re progressing well.","index":603,"end_time":2426.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2424.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, if you can follow up, that''d be great.","index":604,"end_time":2428.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2426.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you guys all so much.","index":605,"end_time":2429.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2428.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was a great conversation.","index":606,"end_time":2430.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2429.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye, guys.","index":607,"end_time":2431.18,"speaker_id":5,"start_time":2430.54,"speaker_name":"gabrielbencosme"}],"dateString":"2026-02-06T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82807622497?pwd=1oWxQKkVvrj4tRTln1UgER5pencHWv.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net,christina.zanca@poncebank.net,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,ashlie.taska@poncebank.net,betty.campiz@poncebank.net,victor.garcia@poncebank.net","gabriel.bencosme@poncebank.net","christina.zanca@poncebank.net","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","ashlie.taska@poncebank.net","betty.campiz@poncebank.net","victor.garcia@poncebank.net"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KG8J2T7YSRRNT8J4J7YAFSNX","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Established working API integrations between HubSpot and Salesforce for lead data transfer.","Identified February 20 as the postcard drop date; Christina to sync locations with Jane.","Gabriel requested assistance with HubSpot automation and field restrictions as complexity grows.","Discussed segmenting lead form traffic using multi-step forms and behavior-driven routing.","Confirmed lead qualification logic will inform opportunity type creation and sales routing."],"highlights":[{"quote":"Good news is the connectivity exists and so the endpoints are actually working back and forth.","speaker":"gabrielbencosme"},{"quote":"I think this looks really good.","speaker":"christinazanca"},{"quote":"On the HubSpot side, we''re progressing well.","speaker":"colincostigan"}],"topics":["integration","delivery","lead-routing","data-quality"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-06T17:11:17Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Integration and API Development**\n\nThe core integration between **Salesforce** and **HubSpot** is now established with working API endpoints, focusing on live syncing lead and contact data (07:11).\n\n- **Gabriel Bencosme** built a private app with webhooks and HTTP listeners enabling real-time data flow when a lead status changes to qualified in HubSpot.\n    - He created two main flows for VISCI checks and email validations, now being modularized into subflows for easier maintenance.\n    - API security remains a key focus, with plans to implement **RAML specification** and encryption using **hash 256** protocols to restrict access to valid POST requests from HubSpot.\n    - The system currently processes limited triggers but will expand to handle complex business rules governing data updates and validations.\n- The next step is defining exact data payloads for sync, including what fields update from HubSpot to Salesforce and vice versa, to avoid overwrites like name or VIS key changes that cause data conflicts (09:17).\n    - This includes setting restrictions on fields that should never change and creating case notifications in Salesforce for exceptions.\n    - Gabriel requested support from Salesforce admins for setting up validation and automation rules in HubSpot to enforce data integrity.\n- **Colin Costigan** emphasized the need to finalize which data points—like income ranges or campaign tags—should flow between systems, ensuring Salesforce remains the system of record for core contact data (09:29).\n    - He confirmed assistance would be provided for HubSpot configuration as needed, especially for automation and permissions.\n- Duplicate record prevention is being addressed through Salesforce’s duplicate checks on email and phone number, with plans to enhance matching criteria based on further data fields (28:25).\n    - The team acknowledged imperfect data entry from users and discussed transformation rules in MuleSoft to normalize fields like gender to accepted picklist values and default unknowns for invalid inputs (30:21).\n    - For free-text fields such as addresses and names, challenges remain due to inconsistent input formatting; automated enrichment in HubSpot helps with company data but not for personal names (33:31).\n\n## **Lead Capture and Qualification Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed to refine lead capture forms and qualification criteria to better route prospects to marketing or sales funnels based on their readiness and needs (18:00).\n\n- **Christina Zanca** proposed using targeted questions on forms, such as home buying stage or prequalification status, to segment leads into discovery (marketing) or ready-to-purchase (sales) funnels.\n    - This approach aligns with business input, particularly from sales leads like **Sunita**, who may want only highly qualified prospects routed directly to sales.\n- **Gabriel** suggested creating specific opportunity record types in Salesforce to store answers from qualifying questions, enabling clear lead segmentation without complex text parsing (20:00).\n    - These opportunity fields would serve as flags visible to sales reps for prioritizing leads.\n- **Colin** explained HubSpot supports multi-step forms collecting basic info first, then optional deeper qualification data, allowing dynamic lead scoring and routing (23:28).\n    - This method respects user privacy by letting prospects choose how much info to share before sales engagement.\n- The group recognized the need to sync business processes with these forms, ensuring Salesforce workflows assign leads to queues or branches based on product interest and qualification status (15:52).\n    - Notifications and dashboards will be built so sales can track lead assignments and conversion activities, reducing duplicate data entry and missed follow-ups.\n\n## **Salesforce and HubSpot Data Architecture**\n\nThe integration architecture is designed to sync individual contacts and eventually business accounts, with a flexible API structure that can extend to multiple record types without rebuilding processes (14:04).\n\n- Gabriel created a simplified flow diagram showing Salesforce on one side and HubSpot on the other, with MuleSoft integrations handling data transformations and sync triggers.\n    - The current trigger is lead qualification in HubSpot, which pushes data to Salesforce.\n    - The Salesforce side links contacts to opportunities reflecting product interest, enabling sales tracking and reporting.\n- The team discussed adding custom sections or related lists in Salesforce contact records to display marketing campaign flags, engagement history, and lead scoring attributes passed from HubSpot (36:53).\n    - This provides sales reps with context on customer journey and behavior without switching systems.\n    - If data volume grows, new custom objects may be created and linked rather than cluttering contact pages.\n- The long-term vision includes capturing multiple customer touchpoints—such as campaign interactions, website visits, and branch visits—to create a dynamic lifecycle profile driving personalized marketing and sales outreach (38:43).\n- Salesforce’s duplicate detection and merge suggestions will be refined to handle imperfect data input, supported by transformation rules in MuleSoft to standardize key fields and avoid sync errors (28:25, 30:21).\n\n## **Process and Workflow Enhancements**\n\nImproving the lead management process involves standardizing data entry, avoiding duplicates, and aligning marketing and sales workflows for better conversion (16:50).\n\n- The team identified that many sales reps currently do not use the lead generator tool, leading to duplicate records and missed opportunities.\n    - Automating data sync and validation between HubSpot and Salesforce aims to reduce manual updates and errors.\n- Christina highlighted the need to capture complete customer journey data, including campaign involvement and behavioral signals, to help sales prioritize leads and personalize outreach (36:53).\n- The planned workflows include alerts for invalid or conflicting data (e.g., VIS key mismatches) and escalation to cases in Salesforce to resolve issues quickly (12:27).\n- The team agreed on a phased approach: start with basic lead qualification and routing, then incrementally add campaign tracking, lead scoring, and richer customer profiles.\n- Training and documentation will be needed as new validation rules and form structures roll out to ensure consistent data capture across branches and marketing teams.\n\n## **Timelines, Ownership, and Next Steps**\n\nThe first direct mail campaign is targeted for **February 20** with a second wave around **March 2**, pending final location selections and compliance reviews (05:05).\n\n- Christina is coordinating with Jane and branch managers to finalize mailing lists for these campaigns.\n- Gabriel has completed the core API connectivity and is now focusing on data structure, security, and detailed field mapping to support live sync.\n- Colin committed to providing technical support for HubSpot admin tasks and Salesforce automation setup as the integration matures.\n- The team will review the integration flow diagram with broader stakeholders to clarify responsibilities and refine the end-to-end process (13:07).\n- Follow-ups include defining the exact payload fields, building validation rules in HubSpot, enhancing duplicate detection in Salesforce, and planning multi-step form questions based on business input.\n- Christina and Colin will continue working with business leads to finalize qualifying questions and marketing funnel segmentation criteria before expanding the integration scope.","outline":null,"keywords":["Lead synchronization","API integration","HubSpot","Salesforce","data validation","marketing funnel"],"overview":"- **API Integration Established:** Salesforce and HubSpot integration works through API endpoints for live contact data syncing.  \n- **Data Payload Definitions Needed:** Identify which fields sync in both directions to avoid conflicts and data overwrites.  \n- **Lead Capture Refinement:** Implement targeted questions to route leads based on readiness, improving sales and marketing alignment.  \n- **Salesforce Customization Discussed:** Consider adding custom sections to contact records for better visibility of marketing engagement and lead scoring.  \n- **Training and Workflow Phases:** Focus on training and phased approach for integrating new validation rules and capturing customer journey data.  \n- **Direct Mail Campaign Timeline:** First campaign scheduled for February 20; finalizing mailing lists and automation processes with branch managers.","action_items":"\n**Christina Zanca**\nCoordinate with Jane and branch managers to finalize and send location lists for postcard mail campaigns (05:05)\nSync with business team leads to define key qualifying questions for web forms that determine marketing funnel or direct sales routing for leads (19:20)\nDiscuss with Colin options for Salesforce fields to store marketing campaign flags, customer journey data, and related engagement notes for sales visibility (27:09)\nFollow up and communicate any scheduling or project delays promptly to the team via email (40:09)\n\n**Gabriel Bencosme**\nContinue development to implement API security for MuleSoft HTTP listener endpoint, ensuring payload encryption and validation against HubSpot standards (07:58)\nRefactor current large MuleSoft flows into manageable modular subflows for better maintainability and debugging (07:11)\nDefine specifics of data fields and payload transformations to manage bi-directional sync and avoid duplicate records or unwanted overwrites, including immutable fields like VIS key (09:17)\nEngage with Salesforce and HubSpot system admins to establish proper validation rules and field-level restrictions compatible between platforms (10:44)\nProvide ongoing updates to the team on API integration progress and contribute to refining the integration process diagrams for team clarity (14:03)\nLead in setting up logic to create Salesforce cases for data anomalies detected during sync (12:20)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nAssist Gabriel and the team in implementing HubSpot-side automation and validation rules, clarifying technical requirements and platform capabilities (10:52)\nSupport lead form design by suggesting multi-step HubSpot forms to incrementally collect customer info and improve lead qualification (23:52)\nCollaborate with Christina on Salesforce campaign and customer profile field mapping to enrich sales insights from marketing data (27:09)\nProvide expertise on duplicate detection logic within Salesforce and options for improvements in data quality and matching rules (28:25)\nAdvise on lead scoring model designs and organic growth of integrated marketing-sales workflows (39:50)\n\n**Ashley Taska**\nAssist with creation of Salesforce fields, sections, or related lists to display marketing and engagement data linked to leads and customers (37:10)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"805fa925-1ccf-474f-8c62-c4adf61398a8","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
