WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    '52b3ee0f-cbad-4031-a387-79ecb54874fb',
    '2026-02-06 16:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KG8J2T7ZNC7H16HKQ3A1Z2ZQ',
    'AQI // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting',
    '{"Colin Costigan","bwillans","Erik Larsen","Safya","guillesantana"}'::text[],
    1705,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1',
    '{"id":"01KG8J2T7ZNC7H16HKQ3A1Z2ZQ","title":"AQI // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Strategy and Technology Stack**\n\nThe meeting established a clear, updated account-based marketing (ABM) framework leveraging advanced AI tools and multi-channel outreach to increase engagement and lead quality (00:05).\n\n- **Colin Costigan detailed the revamped ABM infrastructure**, started in early Q4 last year, integrating AI enrichment tools like **Clay** to identify target accounts and personas with personalized messaging based on job titles and seniority (06:44).  \n    - This personalization aims to address specific pain points and buying processes, increasing conversion rates by making communications relevant.  \n    - The approach avoids loading cold contacts directly into HubSpot to protect domain reputation by using non-marketing contacts and custom domains for outreach.  \n    - Multi-channel outreach includes **email sequences**, **LinkedIn automation via Heyreach**, and **paid ads with retargeting**, hitting prospects where they engage most.  \n    - This layered tech stack reflects a strategic shift towards more sophisticated, personalized engagement rather than broad, generic messaging.\n\n- **The middle automation layer, powered by N8N, captures and analyzes engagement signals**, including sentiment analysis to triage replies automatically and optimize follow-up actions (11:47).  \n    - Positive replies trigger immediate sales notifications, negative ones unsubscribe prospects, and out-of-office replies delay re-engagement.  \n    - This reduces manual workload and increases responsiveness, improving conversion chances.  \n    - Data is stored in a proprietary **Supabase database** for detailed reporting and attribution without costly third-party tools.  \n    - Colin highlighted this as a cost-effective, scrappy solution surpassing many standard attribution tools in capturing multi-signal engagement data.\n\n- **Integration with HubSpot and Salesforce ensures seamless lead scoring and CRM updates**, with non-marketing contacts updated in HubSpot and qualified leads pushed into Salesforce workflows for sales follow-up (12:27).  \n    - This maintains data hygiene while providing clear sales triggers, improving pipeline efficiency.\n\n## **Offers and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed on a focused and flexible approach to developing ABM offers aligned with product lines and target industries, emphasizing relevance over quantity (14:20).\n\n- **Colin proposed offers that provide personalized insights, such as AI-generated competitor benchmarking and industry reports**, to entice prospects to engage (14:20).  \n    - He recommended leveraging existing tools like the website ROI calculator and building mini compliance or data readiness assessments tailored to the water data space.  \n    - This approach aims to give prospects clear, personalized value that overcomes the typical resistance in B2B environments.\n\n- **Regarding the number of communications, Colin advised starting with a sequence of four emails pushing toward an offer or a simple conversation, then expanding with personalized content if needed** (15:03).  \n    - This allows rapid deployment with agility to add depth based on response, balancing volume with quality.  \n    - Barb clarified that the focus products for ABM will be the **Aquarius platform** and **Hawk Wins**, with messaging kept high-level to avoid confusing nuances around product naming and positioning (16:00).  \n    - Eric offered to help refine messaging consistency and handle any pushback from stakeholders on terminology (18:00).\n\n- **The team acknowledged the complexity of product suites and the need to keep offers straightforward and aligned with buyer readiness**, especially in new markets like mining (17:00).  \n    - Eric emphasized caution about calling Aquarius a platform due to legacy perceptions and suggested working with L1 stakeholders for messaging approval.\n\n## **Market and Persona Insights**\n\nThe discussion highlighted the importance of understanding buyer psychology and industry-specific behaviors to maximize ABM impact (05:00 - 06:00; 23:00).\n\n- **Colin stressed that modern buyers value their information highly, so messaging must provide strong, relevant reasons to engage, emphasizing empathy maps and pain points** (05:19).  \n    - This aligns with the multi-channel approach, aiming to catch prospects in various contexts with tailored content.\n\n- **Eric shared insights from past ABM efforts, including a manual, high-touch pandemic campaign sending physical branded demo devices, which achieved a 33% conversion rate (10 out of 30)** (22:40).  \n    - This old-school approach underscored the power of personalized, tangible engagement in certain segments.  \n    - He also noted that print media remains surprisingly effective for this audience, often consumed during downtime, making magazines and branded swag valuable touchpoints (24:00).  \n    - This informs the team''s willingness to include physical mailers and swag in the ABM mix as a complement to digital outreach.\n\n- **Colin and Eric agreed that hitting prospects across multiple channels and formats increases brand impressions and the chance of success**, especially during critical moments like system crises or procurement cycles (26:00).  \n    - This psychological layering strategy aims to build familiarity and trust over time.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Details**\n\nThe meeting underscored automation, data integration, and workflow improvements to increase efficiency and responsiveness in ABM campaigns (11:47; 12:27; 27:00).\n\n- **N8N automation workflows centralize engagement signals across platforms, enabling AI-driven reply triage and lead scoring** (11:47).  \n    - This reduces manual effort and improves follow-up speed, which is critical to conversion rates in B2B sales cycles.\n\n- **Data flows securely into HubSpot as non-marketing contacts and triggers Salesforce workflows when leads meet thresholds, maintaining CRM hygiene and clear sales handoffs** (12:27).  \n    - This structured process supports scalable campaign management and pipeline tracking.\n\n- **Colin noted the team''s ability to develop custom offers and tools internally, such as AI competitor analysis and calculators, to differentiate the ABM experience** (14:20).  \n    - This internal capability creates agility in offer development and supports rapid iteration based on market feedback.\n\n- **Barb mentioned ongoing work to finalize webinar landing pages and HubSpot forms, indicating active content deployment alongside ABM efforts** (26:36).  \n    - This points to a coordinated content and campaign strategy supporting lead capture and nurturing.\n\n## **Timelines, Team Roles, and Next Steps**\n\nThe meeting clarified roles, upcoming collaboration, and iterative planning to accelerate ABM launch and refinement (00:23; 19:53; 27:43).\n\n- **Safya and Eric are primary content leads for Aquarius and Hawk Wins respectively, focusing on messaging and offer development for their product areas** (16:00).  \n    - Barb will coordinate with them on messaging consistency and approval processes.\n\n- **A follow-up internal team call is scheduled for next Tuesday to refine offers and build on the meeting’s strategic foundation** (19:53).  \n    - This session will help finalize offer concepts and align on messaging before broader campaign execution.\n\n- **Colin emphasized readiness to dive into technical specifics and tool demonstrations as needed, indicating continued hands-on support** (20:36).  \n    - This ensures the team can move quickly from planning to implementation with expert guidance.\n\n- **The group expressed enthusiasm for learning and adapting to the rapidly evolving ABM landscape, recognizing significant shifts even in the past year** (21:00).  \n    - Eric acknowledged the need to catch up on new tools and approaches, signaling openness to innovation and collaboration.\n\n- **Barb is resolving access issues to finalize webinar-related content, demonstrating progress on integrated marketing initiatives supporting ABM** (26:36).","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","ABM Technology Stack","Lead Scoring","Multi-Channel Outreach","Messaging Strategy","Mining and Water Sector"],"overview":"- **ABM Framework Update:** Revamped strategy with AI enrichment tools for targeted, personalized outreach to improve engagement and lead quality.  \n- **Automation Layer:** N8N captures engagement signals for efficient follow-ups, increasing responsiveness and reducing manual workload.  \n- **Integrated CRM:** Seamless updates in HubSpot and Salesforce maintain lead hygiene, enhancing sales pipeline efficiency and clarity.  \n- **Focused Offers:** Personalized insights and tailored assessments will drive engagement, balancing volume with quality in communications.  \n- **Market Understanding:** Emphasizing buyer psychology is crucial; multiple touchpoints increase brand familiarity and trust, especially in crises.  \n- **Collaboration Ahead:** Key content leads are defined, with follow-up meetings planned to refine offers and support campaign execution.","action_items":"\n**Barb Willans**\nCoordinate a follow-up team meeting next Tuesday to discuss ABM offers and content development (19:53)\nResolve two-factor authentication issue and update simulive webinar landing page on WordPress, making on-demand content private and adding HubSpot form (26:36)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare link to the interactive offer/testing tools for prospect engagement to review customizable, AI-driven reports (13:06)\nProvide a technical demo or further explanation of the N8N workflow automation capabilities in a future session (11:31)\n\n**Erik Larsen**\nCollaborate on messaging refinement for Aquarius and Wins platforms to align with L1 team preferences and ensure consistency (16:14)\nReview historical ABM efforts and suggest potential pivots leveraging learnings across physical and digital outreach channels (23:40)\n\n**Guilly Santana**\nConfirm availability of WordPress landing page and assist Barb with form integration or content updates as needed (27:00)\n"},"duration":28.420000076293945,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"bwillans"},{"id":2,"name":"Erik Larsen"},{"id":3,"name":"Safya"},{"id":4,"name":"guillesantana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":1.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Doing great.","index":1,"end_time":2.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"How about you?","index":2,"end_time":2.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":3,"end_time":4.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":3.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":5.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":4.64,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Made it through another cold week.","index":5,"end_time":7.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":8.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And apparently we''re supposed to get another dusting this weekend.","index":7,"end_time":10.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":8.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What I heard.","index":8,"end_time":12.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I. I came back to Vancouver.","index":9,"end_time":14.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Couldn''t take it.","index":10,"end_time":14.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I love the cold.","index":11,"end_time":16.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I love the cold.","index":12,"end_time":17.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But it was.","index":13,"end_time":18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":17.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s cold.","index":14,"end_time":18.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":19.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":16,"end_time":20.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":19.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hey, Sofia.","index":17,"end_time":22.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":21.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hey, Eric.","index":18,"end_time":23.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":22.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hey, good morning.","index":19,"end_time":24.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":23.92,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Hi.","index":20,"end_time":25.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":24.68,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"Hello.","index":21,"end_time":26.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":26.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And Barb on the hub spot thing, I''m pretty close to fixing the issue there.","index":22,"end_time":35.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":30.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":23,"end_time":36.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":35.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s about those duplicates that were brought over when 17,000 got reduced to like 3,500.","index":24,"end_time":44.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":36.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":25,"end_time":44.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":44.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I appreciate you and Guillen, you are lightning quick, like unbelievably fast.","index":26,"end_time":53.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So thank you for.","index":27,"end_time":54.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":53.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I know everybody seemed to freak out yesterday and this morning, so.","index":28,"end_time":58.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Calm down everybody.","index":29,"end_time":60.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":59.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s all good.","index":30,"end_time":60.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":60.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hey, Eric, you there?","index":31,"end_time":63.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":62.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m here.","index":32,"end_time":64.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":63.87,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":33,"end_time":65.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":64.59,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Forgive me, team.","index":34,"end_time":66.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":65.31,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I''m.","index":35,"end_time":66.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.27,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I''m not feeling the best today so I''m going to stay off camera to not frighten anybody.","index":36,"end_time":71.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":66.67,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"But it''s so nice to meet y''.","index":37,"end_time":73.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":71.83,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"All.","index":38,"end_time":74.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":73.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Barbara''s told me such amazing things and I''m really looking forward to meeting you and, and just seeing how we can work together.","index":39,"end_time":81.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":74.27,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So thanks Barb, for inviting me today.","index":40,"end_time":83.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":81.94,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah, no, happy to.","index":41,"end_time":85.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And, and hope you''re feeling better.","index":42,"end_time":87.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":85.82,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Maybe just a quick round of introductions.","index":43,"end_time":89.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just wanted you and Safiya, you''re going to be a big part of content building for abm.","index":44,"end_time":95.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.62,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And this is brand new the way that we''re going to do this and these two are like, I''ve known Colin for five years now, worked with him at Rico Innovante, and, and I''ve never missed my numbers.","index":45,"end_time":107.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":95.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you to Colin.","index":46,"end_time":108.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":107.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"This guy.","index":47,"end_time":109.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So they just don''t get any better than this team.","index":48,"end_time":113.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":109.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They don''t.","index":49,"end_time":114.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":113.62,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So wanted great people to meet great people and see how we can work together.","index":50,"end_time":118.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I''ll turn it over to you guys and do your introductions.","index":51,"end_time":121.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":118.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":52,"end_time":124.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":123.54,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"I''m happy to go first.","index":53,"end_time":126.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":124.58,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"So I''m the new marketing coordinator with AQI and I''ve been with the team for a little less than a month, but my background is in brick, brand and content marketing.","index":54,"end_time":137.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":127.3,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"I''ve done that for around seven years.","index":55,"end_time":138.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":137.3,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"So yeah, just really excited to see how I can help and, and work with the team on this.","index":56,"end_time":143.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":138.82,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":57,"end_time":144.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":143.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great to meet you.","index":58,"end_time":144.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":144.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Nice to meet you as well.","index":59,"end_time":146.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":145.38,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":147.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.3,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Hey, team, Eric Larson here.","index":61,"end_time":149.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":147.66,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I''m the strategic marketing manager for aqi.","index":62,"end_time":152.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":149.34,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"This is my fifth year, my anniversary will be in June.","index":63,"end_time":156.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":152.18,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So.","index":64,"end_time":156.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.34,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah, really glad to meet you.","index":65,"end_time":159.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":157.38,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I started in entertainment and then moved over to Consulting.","index":66,"end_time":167.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":159.7,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So I''ve been a product marketer for, oh, gosh, about 12 years at this point.","index":67,"end_time":173.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":167.12,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And so my, my role at AQI is largely around messaging, positioning, Persona building, and then commercial launch activity.","index":68,"end_time":183.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":174.2,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So we do a lot of not only new product development, but we do continuous delivery products.","index":69,"end_time":188.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":183.64,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So when we launch new features or move into new markets, I work on the commercialization side of that with my friends on the product team.","index":70,"end_time":197.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":189.08,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So really, really excited to be working with y'' all on the ABM side of things.","index":71,"end_time":201.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.17,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And yeah, like, like I said earlier, you come highly recommended from Barb, so just really excited to check out everything we''re going to work on together.","index":72,"end_time":210.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.73,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And yeah, thanks for taking the time and thanks for the invite.","index":73,"end_time":214.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":210.77,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, likewise.","index":74,"end_time":216.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":214.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks to you both for joining.","index":75,"end_time":217.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":216.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m Colin.","index":76,"end_time":219.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As Barb said, I have been working with her for about five years across a few different business.","index":77,"end_time":223.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":219.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m the head of client operations at Marketers in Demand and our four agencies that we own.","index":78,"end_time":230.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I handle really a lot of strategy and technical platform assistance.","index":79,"end_time":236.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like, the ABM that we''re going to walk through is a infrastructure that we kind of revamped at the beginning of Q4 last year with all of the advances in AI and a lot more, you know, flow and logic that we''re able to put into everything.","index":80,"end_time":250.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":236.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''m really excited to show you guys that.","index":81,"end_time":252.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But with that, I''ll, I''ll let Yay introduce herself as well.","index":82,"end_time":256.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":253.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m Guilly Santana.","index":83,"end_time":259.19,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":256.95,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"I''m a marketing strategist.","index":84,"end_time":262.87,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":260.95,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Marketers in demand and being here for three months, four months already, but excited to see how we can work together.","index":85,"end_time":272.47,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":263.11,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":86,"end_time":275.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.47,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"Barb, do you want me to just kind of like, talk about abm?","index":87,"end_time":278.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":275.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Should I go into like a diagram that might make it a little bit more helpful?","index":88,"end_time":281.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How high level do we want to start here?","index":89,"end_time":283.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":281.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s Safya how, like, are you familiar with abm?","index":90,"end_time":289.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Should we just assume nothing and start from ground zero?","index":91,"end_time":291.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I know Eric''s done ABM in his past life, but we can just start like right from definition, what it is, what the goals are.","index":92,"end_time":300.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":291.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Safiyeh, if you''d rather start kind of.","index":93,"end_time":303.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"At the beginning, I have done a little bit in my past roles, so if you do want to jump right in, like, that''s, that''s totally fine and I''m sure I can keep up.","index":94,"end_time":314.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":303.07,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"But yeah, either or is great with me, so sounds good.","index":95,"end_time":319,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":314.68,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"Okay.","index":96,"end_time":319.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, well, Eric hit on a few of the key terms.","index":97,"end_time":322.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":319.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Icp, messaging.","index":98,"end_time":323.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":322.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Safi, you mentioned those as well.","index":99,"end_time":325.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those are really the core foundation.","index":100,"end_time":327.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":325.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we also need a tech stack in place to be able to accomplish all of this.","index":101,"end_time":330.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The way that we approach account based marketing is we identify target accounts within target industries and create those target Personas so that we can understand an empathy map.","index":102,"end_time":340.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What do they want to hear?","index":103,"end_time":342.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":341.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is going to intrigue them?","index":104,"end_time":343.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":342.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To hop onto a call with the sales team because if we''re being completely honest, kind of industry agnostic people are more value or valuing their information much higher nowadays.","index":105,"end_time":356.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The the form submission and meeting to them that is their currency.","index":106,"end_time":361.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":356.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we need to give them a lot of reason.","index":107,"end_time":363.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to entice them to convert and move forward and move down the funnel.","index":108,"end_time":367.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll pull up a diagram right here to kind of walk through the tools that we typically use here.","index":109,"end_time":373.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":368.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So because of HubSpot''s policies we wouldn''t be loading in contacts to send cold emails because that would get HubSpot into a pinch.","index":110,"end_time":383.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":375.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we use another series of tools.","index":111,"end_time":385.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Barb.","index":112,"end_time":386.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.29,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"The one update we did make here is that all of these contacts actually do get imported into HubSpot as non marketing contacts.","index":113,"end_time":393.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":386.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So they don''t hurt your guys threshold but they are being updated with activity from the ABM campaign even though it''s happening in other platforms.","index":114,"end_time":402.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome, that''s good news.","index":115,"end_time":404.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":116,"end_time":405.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":404.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So where we start on the left here is we use Clay.","index":117,"end_time":408.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":405.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is an AI enrichment tool that connects to platforms like Zoom, Info, Apollo, you name it, LinkedIn, sales, navigator, all sorts of things.","index":118,"end_time":417.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":408.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we put in the account parameters and then we send that list over to you guys.","index":119,"end_time":422.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Make sure hey, we''re all buttoned up here, everything that we''re looking for.","index":120,"end_time":425.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":422.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we add identify the people at that company with the job titles that we''re trying to get in with.","index":121,"end_time":430.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":425.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we could even have a lot of personalization baked into these.","index":122,"end_time":433.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":430.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know depending on seniority level they''re going to have different pain points, they''re going to have different conversations that they want to have.","index":123,"end_time":441.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":434.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe they need to get financial buy in but they need to have a conversation before they can do so.","index":124,"end_time":446.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can personalize a lot of our messaging based on that.","index":125,"end_time":449.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":446.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We then use a series of tools to get messaging out.","index":126,"end_time":454.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":451.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of those is Smart lead.","index":127,"end_time":456.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we set up email accounts and domains that are similar to aquaticinformatics.com but not a direct match because if anyone reports as spam that would hurt your guys domain which we do not want.","index":128,"end_time":468.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":456.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"When we do set up the domains they redirect to aquaticinformatics.com so there''s no loss of process there.","index":129,"end_time":475,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":469.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''d be sending those emails out to that contact list.","index":130,"end_time":479.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":476.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We would also be utilizing paid advertising with that contact list.","index":131,"end_time":483.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":479.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So LinkedIn, maybe some other channels if we determine that there''s a good opportunity there.","index":132,"end_time":489.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Retargeting would probably be a big portion of this as well.","index":133,"end_time":492.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":489.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Heyreach is another cool tool that you see here and that is to automate LinkedIn outreach.","index":134,"end_time":498.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can actually have your sales team log in.","index":135,"end_time":501.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":498.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can have any number of profiles that you guys want and we can upload the list into a flow that sends connection requests, does a view profile notification, sends messages, can like posts.","index":136,"end_time":514.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":501.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because really we need to hit these people.","index":137,"end_time":517.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As you can see, we have email, we have ads, we have LinkedIn outreach.","index":138,"end_time":520.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need to hit these people where they are and when they''re there.","index":139,"end_time":523.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":520.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s why we take this multi channel approach.","index":140,"end_time":526.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":523.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll take a break there before I dig into some of the other tools.","index":141,"end_time":529.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":526.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions so far?","index":142,"end_time":530.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":529.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All good on my end.","index":143,"end_time":534.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":533.09,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":144,"end_time":535.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":534.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so then moving a little further to the right, Barb, you''ll recognize Factors.","index":145,"end_time":540.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":535.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We actually have some cool new features with them as we''ve enhanced our partnership.","index":146,"end_time":543.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"RB2B and factors.","index":147,"end_time":545.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":544.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys probably seen Adam Robinson, the RB2B guy, all over LinkedIn.","index":148,"end_time":551.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you haven''t, you''re lucky.","index":149,"end_time":553.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":551.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s.","index":150,"end_time":553.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He''s a crazy person, but he made a pretty cool tool.","index":151,"end_time":555.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it is IP and device level de anonymization.","index":152,"end_time":559.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And inside the US because we do not have GDPR compliance issues, that does actually filter down to a person level de anonymization once they accept cookies.","index":153,"end_time":569.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":560.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Factors, is the GDPR compliant.","index":154,"end_time":573.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Actually, they are both GDPR compliant.","index":155,"end_time":574.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to be clear about that.","index":156,"end_time":575.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any person outside of the United States comes to the website and RPDB picks them up, it will not de anonymize them.","index":157,"end_time":581.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll only de anonymize their company.","index":158,"end_time":582.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Factors is purely GDPR compliant.","index":159,"end_time":587.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As in it will never enrich a person.","index":160,"end_time":589.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It will only be contact or I''m sorry, account level.","index":161,"end_time":592.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":589.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So based on their ip, device id, geolocation, everything like that, it''ll determine what their company is from millions of millions of pixels that they have in their network.","index":162,"end_time":601.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":592.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Barb, the cool new thing there is now, Factors doesn''t only de anonymize website traffic, but it integrates via a API to LinkedIn to also track who is viewing ads and who has clicked on ads.","index":163,"end_time":616.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Very cool.","index":164,"end_time":617.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":616.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":618.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all things to consider filtering into our lead scoring.","index":166,"end_time":621.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":618.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We do that in our base model, but we may have a Custom lead scoring that we want to build.","index":167,"end_time":624.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, no, that sounds great.","index":168,"end_time":626.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":169,"end_time":627.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":626.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The big improvement here is in this middle layer.","index":170,"end_time":632.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we use N8N which is a workflow automation tool that connects all of these things that are happening.","index":171,"end_time":637.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So someone engages with an email, someone clicks on an ad, someone visits the website.","index":172,"end_time":643.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All of that activity is being captured in N8N through various workflows.","index":173,"end_time":648.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.569,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s actually one workflow with several different signals.","index":174,"end_time":650.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I can show an example maybe on another call as it''s very highly technical.","index":175,"end_time":654.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":651.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But there''s cool things in here like sentiment analysis.","index":176,"end_time":659.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if someone replies to an email previously we would say like whether it was out of office or hey you guys suck, stop emailing me or hey, I want to move forward and pay you guys right away.","index":177,"end_time":668.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We got notifications everywhere about everything.","index":178,"end_time":672.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now we have AI enhancing.","index":179,"end_time":674.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we have sentiment analysis baked into this to say hey, this was just an out of office reply.","index":180,"end_time":678.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":674.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So let''s just send them another email in a week instead when they''re back in house.","index":181,"end_time":682.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":678.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or hey, this is a really positive reply.","index":182,"end_time":684.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s get this over to the sales team right away way.","index":183,"end_time":686.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":684.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or hey, this is a negative reply.","index":184,"end_time":688.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":687.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s unsubscribe them from all communications because that''s what they asked for.","index":185,"end_time":691.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So all of those are being tracked and pulled through N8N based on those signals and we store them all in a database that we own called Supabase that is so that we can report to you based on hey, they got this email, they clicked on this ad, all of these things.","index":186,"end_time":707.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":692.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is the scrappy way that we can build this level of attribution without you guys having to pay for like a hundred thousand dollar attribution tool like Hockey Stack or Dream data.","index":187,"end_time":717.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we won''t capture everything because people have privacy, but we are capturing a lot more than anyone else at this level considering if, if they don''t have a Hockey Stack or a Dream data type solution.","index":188,"end_time":730.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Barb, like I mentioned at the beginning, this all filters into HubSpot to update non marketing contacts and we can have triggers in there to say, you know, once they''ve hit this threshold, submitted forms xyz, send over to Salesforce and take next steps.","index":189,"end_time":746.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":731.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":190,"end_time":747.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.02,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Quick question.","index":191,"end_time":748.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.74,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If like this is, I mean a huge improvement since the last time we worked on this together.","index":192,"end_time":755.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So what have you seen in terms of results putting in that middle layer and, and you know, direct to HubSpot non marketing, like did it.","index":193,"end_time":762.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Have you seen the results for other clients increase?","index":194,"end_time":766.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":763.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, we have.","index":195,"end_time":767.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":766.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we also, you know, hooked up with all new mail providers, so we''re seeing a lot less spam hits.","index":196,"end_time":772.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":767.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ve we''ve just seen because of all the signals that we''re able to capture much more personalized content which leads to more engagement.","index":197,"end_time":781.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":774.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, sounds great.","index":198,"end_time":784.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":783.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Any questions around the tech stack?","index":199,"end_time":788.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":786.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":200,"end_time":791.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":790.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, and then one other really crucial piece to this and I''ll share this link with you guys so you can play around with it.","index":201,"end_time":798.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":793.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is the offer.","index":202,"end_time":799.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":798.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is.","index":203,"end_time":800.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are we going to entice this prospect to have a conversation with aqi?","index":204,"end_time":804.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":800.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll send over this link.","index":205,"end_time":807.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are three offers that we''ve built just as kind of testing grounds for our, for our clients to use, but because we do a lot of custom coding, I''ve even been building a lot of these tools myself.","index":206,"end_time":819.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":807.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bar, me and Tristan are mainly the ones that are building these.","index":207,"end_time":822.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Someone goes in and the mindset is what are just a few basic questions that we can ask them to fill in.","index":208,"end_time":828.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":823.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then they will get an automatically generated report that is customized to them.","index":209,"end_time":833.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":828.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Has AI going out and scraping competitor websites giving them an industry benchmark report.","index":210,"end_time":838.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Barb, maybe there''s something we need to do with the gallons per million or million.","index":211,"end_time":843.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I, I can never remember the acronym that you guys had in place there, but you know, maybe that''s some sort of data we need to collect and maybe we can give them some sort of analysis or a comparison of what it would be like currently versus what it could look like with aqi.","index":212,"end_time":856.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":843.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s a lot of different things that we can build here.","index":213,"end_time":860.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just need to understand what do these people need to see to move forward.","index":214,"end_time":863.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":860.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":215,"end_time":865.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, so I''ll take a pause there.","index":216,"end_time":868.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any questions so far?","index":217,"end_time":869.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":868.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, in, in an average abm, I mean how many, how many offers should there be?","index":218,"end_time":880.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, we''ve done in the past, we''ve done like four to 10 communications per ABM.","index":219,"end_time":887.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":881.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So these are brand new areas for us.","index":220,"end_time":889.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":887.74,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So food and bed and mining is 100% new to us.","index":221,"end_time":892.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":889.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So should they be longer or we do shorter on the communications firm up the offers should they be long and then we do retargeting like I guess just looking for your expertise here.","index":222,"end_time":903.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":223,"end_time":904.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":903.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''re actually able to move a lot faster now.","index":224,"end_time":906,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s not like setting up the seven email sequence.","index":225,"end_time":908.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":906,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically we start out with four emails in a sequence mainly pushing towards that offer or just an open ended conversation which is a little less of a hurdle for someone to respond to.","index":226,"end_time":918.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so Barb, once someone goes through those Four emails.","index":227,"end_time":921.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If we''re not seeing the engagement, then we generate more personalized content to continue adding to the flow.","index":228,"end_time":925.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''m sorry, what was the first part of your question?","index":229,"end_time":929.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Before that?","index":230,"end_time":929.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it was the number of communications.","index":231,"end_time":933.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":931.46,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":232,"end_time":933.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":933.38,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"Oh, and how many offers?","index":233,"end_time":934.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":933.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so for the offer side, I would say we have different product offerings that we''re going to be baking into this.","index":234,"end_time":942.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously for targeting.","index":235,"end_time":943.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Typically I would like an offer per product, but I don''t know how crazy that''s going to be with how many products we''re going to be setting up initially.","index":236,"end_time":952.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":945.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I think right now like we have the whimsical right wings and Aquarius.","index":237,"end_time":957.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":954.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":238,"end_time":958.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think Sofia, you''re going to be focusing on Aquarius and then Eric whims.","index":239,"end_time":963.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":958.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And Eric, would it be whims or whims?","index":240,"end_time":965.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Rio, You''re on mute.","index":241,"end_time":971.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":965.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, of course I am.","index":242,"end_time":973.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":972.15,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"No problem there.","index":243,"end_time":974.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":973.23,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":244,"end_time":975.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So technically for abm we can just use Hawk Wins because we''re talking about the platform itself and we don''t want to assume that they would already be ready for the cloud enabled solution.","index":245,"end_time":991.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":975.91,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Some folks are very touchy about wanting to keep that on prem redundancy.","index":246,"end_time":998.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":991.87,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So yeah, I think we''re good if we just keep it at the highest possible level and just say, you know, HAWK wins or you know, wins platform.","index":247,"end_time":1005.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":998.75,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Either one is fine.","index":248,"end_time":1006.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1005.47,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":249,"end_time":1007.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1007.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And for you, Safiya, like so just Aquarius, like the Aquarius software platform is there.","index":250,"end_time":1017.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1009.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean, we''re brand new to this mining thing, so I''m just not being very eloquent here, but you know, we do have a lot of products and a lot of M A happening, but really I think it''s the Winds platform and Aquarius platform.","index":251,"end_time":1029.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1018.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Correct.","index":252,"end_time":1029.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"From my understanding, at least.","index":253,"end_time":1032.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1030.56,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"Great.","index":254,"end_time":1033.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, usually we just call it Aquarius, but yeah, I think the Aquarius platform can work in this context too.","index":255,"end_time":1041.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1034,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"We might want to workshop the.","index":256,"end_time":1044.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1041.99,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Some folks on the L1 level get a little touchy when we start calling things a platform.","index":257,"end_time":1051.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1046.23,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I had some pushback on whims and we finally got clearance from wims.","index":258,"end_time":1054.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1051.59,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So if we want to move fast, we''ll just call it Aquarius.","index":259,"end_time":1058.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.79,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"But if we want to maintain consistency across both product offerings, let me know.","index":260,"end_time":1064.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1059.03,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Barb and Safia and I can put together a little bit of messaging and run it past the L1 team and make sure they''re cool with us calling it the Aquarius platform.","index":261,"end_time":1073.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1064.7,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Because like wims, there''s a lot of different nuance to Aquarius.","index":262,"end_time":1079.819,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1073.98,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Technically there''s five products in the suite.","index":263,"end_time":1082.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1079.819,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Most mining operations would just need time series, maybe time series and web portal.","index":264,"end_time":1087.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.7,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"But some of them might need connect.","index":265,"end_time":1088.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1087.34,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Some of them might need samples.","index":266,"end_time":1090.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1088.94,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"You know, there''s a.","index":267,"end_time":1091.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1090.54,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"There''s a whole lot of nuance to Aquarius too.","index":268,"end_time":1094.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1092.13,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So I think leaving it at the high level is a good idea as well.","index":269,"end_time":1098.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.85,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s cross that bridge when we get to it.","index":270,"end_time":1103.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1100.85,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Okay, now that sounds good.","index":271,"end_time":1105.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1103.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think it''s me that have.","index":272,"end_time":1106.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ve been calling it platform and not getting.","index":273,"end_time":1109.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s not you, it''s everybody.","index":274,"end_time":1111.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1109.57,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Barb.","index":275,"end_time":1111.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.09,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah, don''t, don''t throw yourself under the bus.","index":276,"end_time":1113.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1111.49,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"It''s.","index":277,"end_time":1114.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1113.73,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Everybody calls everything something different.","index":278,"end_time":1116.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1114.17,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And yeah, don''t, don''t worry.","index":279,"end_time":1118.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1116.77,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"There''s not like one set so standard that you''re supposed to call the products.","index":280,"end_time":1121.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1118.05,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And that''s been something we''ve been trying to, you know, it''s like we''ve been trying to unwind that knot for probably four years at this point of like, what do we call everything?","index":281,"end_time":1132.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1121.93,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So, yeah, don''t worry if you''re like, I''m not quite sure.","index":282,"end_time":1136.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1134.37,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Let''s just ask Eric.","index":283,"end_time":1138.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1136.93,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Like, that''s fine.","index":284,"end_time":1139.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1138.37,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Don''t worry.","index":285,"end_time":1139.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1139.25,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I can make the decision and I can take the heat if there''s an issue.","index":286,"end_time":1143.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1140.05,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":287,"end_time":1144.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1144.45,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"We''ll deal with it.","index":288,"end_time":1145.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1144.93,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"No worries.","index":289,"end_time":1146.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1145.98,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Okay, sounds good.","index":290,"end_time":1149.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":291,"end_time":1150.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1149.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Barb, I know we have like the calculator on the website that could be used as well.","index":292,"end_time":1155.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, that''s always fun for people to play around with.","index":293,"end_time":1158.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1156.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Case studies I think are going to be good to point to and I know you guys are still working on getting a lot of those out.","index":294,"end_time":1163.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some other things that I was just jotting down as notes is like, I know compliance is huge in this space.","index":295,"end_time":1169.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1165.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if we could do some sort of mini compliance audit and like readiness assessment for someone looking to make a transformation or using the ROI calculator maybe.","index":296,"end_time":1179.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1169.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How confident are they in their data versus what the industry benchmark should be?","index":297,"end_time":1183.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1179.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, just some things like that Water data management, maturity assessment.","index":298,"end_time":1188.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1185.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So again, benchmark where they are versus competitors or best practices.","index":299,"end_time":1192.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1188.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":300,"end_time":1195.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1193.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We have a small team call next Tuesday just to the three of us and maybe Viv might join as well.","index":301,"end_time":1201.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1195.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But to kind of go over, like to springboard off of this conversation and really just, you know, chat about what kind of things we would like to build.","index":302,"end_time":1209.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1201.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right?","index":303,"end_time":1210.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1209.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":304,"end_time":1211.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so various offers and things.","index":305,"end_time":1213.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1211.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I mean, B2B, it''s never going to be a discount.","index":306,"end_time":1215.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1213.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, this isn''t an iPhone and it''s like there''s nothing like that.","index":307,"end_time":1218.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1215.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":308,"end_time":1218.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1218.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So you know, what is it that will, you know, turn a person''s head, you know?","index":309,"end_time":1223.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1218.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":310,"end_time":1223.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":311,"end_time":1223.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Something that stops them from scrolling.","index":312,"end_time":1225.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1223.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Something that they feel like, you know, I would be dumb if I didn''t just give them my email to download this.","index":313,"end_time":1231.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1225.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":314,"end_time":1233.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1232.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":315,"end_time":1235.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.02,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, that''s ABM at a high level.","index":316,"end_time":1238.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1236.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can get into technical specifics at any point you guys want to, but I feel like for the purpose of where we''re at with this stage, feel like that was a good conversation.","index":317,"end_time":1248.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1238.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think so too.","index":318,"end_time":1249.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And thanks for that.","index":319,"end_time":1250.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1249.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":320,"end_time":1250.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s just there were some new tools in there for me.","index":321,"end_time":1253.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So when I was talking to Eric about this and, you know, he explained he does have a lot of ABM experience.","index":322,"end_time":1258.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1253.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I said to him, cut.","index":323,"end_time":1259.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1258.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Even just from a year ago when I left.","index":324,"end_time":1262.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1259.74,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Wasn''t it even a year ago?","index":325,"end_time":1264.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t know, six months ago I left Avanti.","index":326,"end_time":1266.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1264.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And everything has changed since then.","index":327,"end_time":1268.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, it''s.","index":328,"end_time":1269.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s crazy when we look back to the first RICO ones we did, and it''s.","index":329,"end_time":1273.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1269.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s a different world, you know, and it''s exciting, you know, I get to.","index":330,"end_time":1277.309,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1273.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Learn tools are changing every day.","index":331,"end_time":1278.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1277.309,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":332,"end_time":1279.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I get to learn something new, you know, which is awesome.","index":333,"end_time":1282.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":334,"end_time":1283.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1282.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":335,"end_time":1284.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1283.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":336,"end_time":1285.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1285.11,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"For your expertise.","index":337,"end_time":1286.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1285.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":338,"end_time":1287.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":339,"end_time":1288.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1288.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":340,"end_time":1289.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Eric, I''m interested in, like, what tools maybe you''ve used in the past.","index":341,"end_time":1292.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1289.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was it more like the sixth sense level of tools or.","index":342,"end_time":1296.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1292.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think, Colin, I did it as about as old school as a human being possibly can.","index":343,"end_time":1302.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1296.89,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So.","index":344,"end_time":1302.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1302.49,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah, during the pandemic, I was tasked with.","index":345,"end_time":1306.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1302.81,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"We had an AI tool for your.","index":346,"end_time":1309.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1307.37,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Any of your home automation assistants.","index":347,"end_time":1313.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1309.65,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I won''t say the female name of it because I have one right here in my office.","index":348,"end_time":1317.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1313.09,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I tend to call her Belinda when I don''t want her to activate.","index":349,"end_time":1320.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1317.94,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Anyway, so what we did was we had a software that we needed to be able to do a software demo of.","index":350,"end_time":1328.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1320.94,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And that was typically done in person, but it was the pandemic.","index":351,"end_time":1331.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1328.26,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And so what I did was I just worked with our team and we did the segmentation, targeting, messaging, everything manually and then just did.","index":352,"end_time":1342.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1331.1,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"We essentially combed our database and found all the folks that we needed to send a demo to.","index":353,"end_time":1349.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1343.39,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And then we hard coded this demo onto a dot device and then branded it with that company''s material and then sent it over to them and just said, hey, keep this.","index":354,"end_time":1361.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1349.67,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"But there''s a little card in here that gives you the entire demo.","index":355,"end_time":1366.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1362.19,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Here''s how you start the demo.","index":356,"end_time":1368.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1366.91,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And then we got like, of the 30 of them that I sent out, we had 10 people convert.","index":357,"end_time":1375.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1369.84,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And so that was my, really, my very rudimentary attempt at ABM was sending out physical mailers, but then there was a lot of hyper technical stuff on the back end.","index":358,"end_time":1387.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1375.76,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So.","index":359,"end_time":1388.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1388,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah, I have a lot of stuff to Google here.","index":360,"end_time":1391.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1388.8,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Colin, from.","index":361,"end_time":1391.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1391.2,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Well, that means that you understand.","index":362,"end_time":1392.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1391.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, but if you understand, like that whole framework, I mean, these tools will be quicker to grasp.","index":363,"end_time":1397.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1393.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s what I''m thinking.","index":364,"end_time":1398.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.81,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":365,"end_time":1398.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1398.69,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"From what.","index":366,"end_time":1399.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1398.97,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"The rundown you gave was super helpful.","index":367,"end_time":1401.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1399.49,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So, yeah, thank you for that.","index":368,"end_time":1403.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1401.81,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"As you can tell, it''s been, what, six years at this point?","index":369,"end_time":1407.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1403.33,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So, yeah, from what Barb has seen change exponentially in a year.","index":370,"end_time":1412.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1407.89,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I''ve got a lot of catching up to do.","index":371,"end_time":1414.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.33,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"But it''s really, really excellent stuff and I really appreciate the.","index":372,"end_time":1418.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1414.85,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"The overview you guys put together.","index":373,"end_time":1420.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1418.53,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":374,"end_time":1421.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1420.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Barb, that''s another thing is we''ve been doing physical mailers also a little bit more recently and seeing some success with those.","index":375,"end_time":1426.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1421.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And these are old school organizations, so it could be something we take a look at.","index":376,"end_time":1431.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1427.7,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Because, I mean, when we do.","index":377,"end_time":1433.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1431.9,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"A lot of.","index":378,"end_time":1435.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1434.74,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"What I also do, team, is the PR side of things.","index":379,"end_time":1438.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1435.22,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So I''ll put together customer case studies, get those published in magazines and things, and we get requests for, hey, can you put us on the physical list for this wastewater digest magazine or whatever?","index":380,"end_time":1454.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1438.94,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Right.","index":381,"end_time":1454.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.02,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I''m like, you want the physical?","index":382,"end_time":1456.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.06,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Like, sure, fine, but why?","index":383,"end_time":1458.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1457.3,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Right?","index":384,"end_time":1459.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I''ll say, oh, yeah, well, we actually like to read them.","index":385,"end_time":1462.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1459.62,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And what we''ve noticed is people will actually read them when there''s a problem or systems are down.","index":386,"end_time":1470.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1462.18,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"They''ll just sit down and read them.","index":387,"end_time":1471.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.5,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":388,"end_time":1472.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1471.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or they''ll sit down and read them in places where you would think that people used to read magazines, you know, and they instead don''t take their phone with them and they check out these magazines, you know, while they''re in the restroom.","index":389,"end_time":1483.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1472.3,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And you''re like, I can''t believe that you''re reading this and absorbing information and you''re actually going, okay, yeah, I''m gonna reach out and find out more about this product.","index":390,"end_time":1494.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1483.45,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":391,"end_time":1495.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1494.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Read about in the bathroom.","index":392,"end_time":1496.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1495.33,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And you''re like, this is crazy.","index":393,"end_time":1498.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1497.17,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"I wouldn''t think that this would still be happening, you know, like maybe the 90s, you know, early 2000.","index":394,"end_time":1505.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1498.85,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Sure, that print media was huge, but this is a Persona set where print media still resonates.","index":395,"end_time":1512.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1505.41,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And they love.","index":396,"end_time":1513.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1512.64,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"If they come to our booth and we''ve got a trucker cap with a logo on it, they want it, they want to be into it, they want to figure out.","index":397,"end_time":1523.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1514.16,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"What do I need to do to win the camo hat?","index":398,"end_time":1526.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1523.28,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And you''re like, oh, you don''t have to do anything to win it.","index":399,"end_time":1530.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1527.52,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"You can just.","index":400,"end_time":1531.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1530.72,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"We''ll do a demo with you, right?","index":401,"end_time":1533.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1531.68,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":402,"end_time":1533.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1533.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they''re like, oh, yeah, let''s do that.","index":403,"end_time":1535.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1533.6,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And we get so many conversions off of silly things like that where we didn''t think about that for a long time.","index":404,"end_time":1541.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1535.28,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"We''re like, we''re a tech company.","index":405,"end_time":1542.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1541.21,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"We should be advertising at the tech company level.","index":406,"end_time":1546.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1542.97,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"So.","index":407,"end_time":1546.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1546.09,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":408,"end_time":1546.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1546.57,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Glad you''re.","index":409,"end_time":1547.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1546.97,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"You''re open to that as well.","index":410,"end_time":1548.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1547.57,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":411,"end_time":1549.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I would be super down to review the success you''ve had and see where we could pivot and, you know, figure that part of it out because, yeah, it''s surprising.","index":412,"end_time":1559.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1549.25,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":413,"end_time":1559.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.33,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"And like I said when I was going through the tools, it''s really about hitting them in as many places as we can when they''re there.","index":414,"end_time":1564.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1559.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, like.","index":415,"end_time":1564.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1564.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":416,"end_time":1564.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1564.57,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"You know, the magazine, like, they''re going through a crisis, and that magazine they know is, like, sitting downstairs.","index":417,"end_time":1569.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1565.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They could flip through for some answers, and the next time they get an email or see an ad, like, it''s just.","index":418,"end_time":1575,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1569.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s all about the psychology of it.","index":419,"end_time":1576.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1575,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So giving them, you know, more.","index":420,"end_time":1578.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1576.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What is it?","index":421,"end_time":1580.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1579.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just more impressions on, like, the brand and how many different mediums we''re communicating through.","index":422,"end_time":1586.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1581.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just the higher chance of success.","index":423,"end_time":1588.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1587.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"100%.","index":424,"end_time":1590.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1589.6,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":425,"end_time":1590.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1590.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":426,"end_time":1591.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1590.89,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":427,"end_time":1592.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1591.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":428,"end_time":1592.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1592.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything else that you wanted to go through, Barb?","index":429,"end_time":1595.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think that''s it.","index":430,"end_time":1597.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I.","index":431,"end_time":1597.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1597.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, I''ve got one more webinar to get up that simulive gay.","index":432,"end_time":1601.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1597.93,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''ll.","index":433,"end_time":1603.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"James just gave me.","index":434,"end_time":1605.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m having two factor problems again.","index":435,"end_time":1608.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1605.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So he opens.","index":436,"end_time":1609.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1608.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"He opened it up, he took it off.","index":437,"end_time":1611.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1610.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''m now back in.","index":438,"end_time":1612.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1611.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''ll go take a look and see.","index":439,"end_time":1614.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1612.73,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, go ahead.","index":440,"end_time":1616.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1615.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":441,"end_time":1618.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1617.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Just one quick question on that one, Barb.","index":442,"end_time":1622.22,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1620.06,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"The landing page.","index":443,"end_time":1623.86,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1622.78,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"I''m not finding it on WordPress, just the thank you page.","index":444,"end_time":1627.58,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1623.86,"speaker_name":"guillesantana"},{"text":"Might have done it in my head.","index":445,"end_time":1629.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1628.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s possible.","index":446,"end_time":1632.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1631.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":447,"end_time":1633.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There were six of them and I''m like, I think I did that, but then I couldn''t get in.","index":448,"end_time":1636.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1633.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There''s a really good chance I didn''t do it.","index":449,"end_time":1638.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1637.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I''m going to take the on demand one today.","index":450,"end_time":1642.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1638.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Now that I have access, I''m going to make that private.","index":451,"end_time":1644.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1642.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Then I''m going to flip it and.","index":452,"end_time":1647.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1644.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, so we just need a HubSpot form on it.","index":453,"end_time":1651.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1647.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I got it.","index":454,"end_time":1652.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1651.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":455,"end_time":1654.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1652.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":456,"end_time":1654.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.03,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll ping you when I''m ready, but I swear I did it in my head.","index":457,"end_time":1658.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1654.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I did it in my head.","index":458,"end_time":1659.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1658.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s how it rolls sometimes.","index":459,"end_time":1662.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1660.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":460,"end_time":1663.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1663.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thanks, guys.","index":461,"end_time":1664.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1663.59,"speaker_name":"Safya"},{"text":"All right, well, amazing to meet you both and really looking forward to next steps here.","index":462,"end_time":1668.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, likewise.","index":463,"end_time":1670.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1669.73,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Thanks, team.","index":464,"end_time":1671.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1671.01,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"},{"text":"Have a great weekend, everyone.","index":465,"end_time":1673.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1672.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Take care.","index":466,"end_time":1674.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1674.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Take care.","index":467,"end_time":1675.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1674.65,"speaker_name":"Erik Larsen"}],"dateString":"2026-02-06T16:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/89786281993?pwd=li2lwrSFpmITXPKEdOBBgaXPwh8ONO.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","barb.willans@aquaticinformatics.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KG8J2T7ZNC7H16HKQ3A1Z2ZQ","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.94,"bullets":["Resolved HubSpot deduplication reduced 17,000 records to 3,500; data syncing issue fixed.","Outlined end-to-end ABM tech stack including Clay, Smartlead, Heyreach, and N8N workflows.","Defined product-level ABM segmentation; Safya assigned Aquarius, Erik assigned WINs messaging.","Introduced compliance-safe intent tracking via Factors and RB2B with GDPR filters.","Agreed to explore direct mail as high-conversion tactic for traditional target segments."],"highlights":[{"quote":"These are brand new areas for us... So food and bed and mining is 100% new.","speaker":"bwillans"},{"quote":"We''ve just seen... much more personalized content which leads to more engagement.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"We get so many conversions off of silly things like that... where we didn’t think about that.","speaker":"Erik Larsen"}],"topics":["abm","tools","targeting","delivery","personalization"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-02-06T20:24:15Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Strategy and Technology Stack**\n\nThe meeting established a clear, updated account-based marketing (ABM) framework leveraging advanced AI tools and multi-channel outreach to increase engagement and lead quality (00:05).\n\n- **Colin Costigan detailed the revamped ABM infrastructure**, started in early Q4 last year, integrating AI enrichment tools like **Clay** to identify target accounts and personas with personalized messaging based on job titles and seniority (06:44).  \n    - This personalization aims to address specific pain points and buying processes, increasing conversion rates by making communications relevant.  \n    - The approach avoids loading cold contacts directly into HubSpot to protect domain reputation by using non-marketing contacts and custom domains for outreach.  \n    - Multi-channel outreach includes **email sequences**, **LinkedIn automation via Heyreach**, and **paid ads with retargeting**, hitting prospects where they engage most.  \n    - This layered tech stack reflects a strategic shift towards more sophisticated, personalized engagement rather than broad, generic messaging.\n\n- **The middle automation layer, powered by N8N, captures and analyzes engagement signals**, including sentiment analysis to triage replies automatically and optimize follow-up actions (11:47).  \n    - Positive replies trigger immediate sales notifications, negative ones unsubscribe prospects, and out-of-office replies delay re-engagement.  \n    - This reduces manual workload and increases responsiveness, improving conversion chances.  \n    - Data is stored in a proprietary **Supabase database** for detailed reporting and attribution without costly third-party tools.  \n    - Colin highlighted this as a cost-effective, scrappy solution surpassing many standard attribution tools in capturing multi-signal engagement data.\n\n- **Integration with HubSpot and Salesforce ensures seamless lead scoring and CRM updates**, with non-marketing contacts updated in HubSpot and qualified leads pushed into Salesforce workflows for sales follow-up (12:27).  \n    - This maintains data hygiene while providing clear sales triggers, improving pipeline efficiency.\n\n## **Offers and Messaging Strategy**\n\nThe team agreed on a focused and flexible approach to developing ABM offers aligned with product lines and target industries, emphasizing relevance over quantity (14:20).\n\n- **Colin proposed offers that provide personalized insights, such as AI-generated competitor benchmarking and industry reports**, to entice prospects to engage (14:20).  \n    - He recommended leveraging existing tools like the website ROI calculator and building mini compliance or data readiness assessments tailored to the water data space.  \n    - This approach aims to give prospects clear, personalized value that overcomes the typical resistance in B2B environments.\n\n- **Regarding the number of communications, Colin advised starting with a sequence of four emails pushing toward an offer or a simple conversation, then expanding with personalized content if needed** (15:03).  \n    - This allows rapid deployment with agility to add depth based on response, balancing volume with quality.  \n    - Barb clarified that the focus products for ABM will be the **Aquarius platform** and **Hawk Wins**, with messaging kept high-level to avoid confusing nuances around product naming and positioning (16:00).  \n    - Eric offered to help refine messaging consistency and handle any pushback from stakeholders on terminology (18:00).\n\n- **The team acknowledged the complexity of product suites and the need to keep offers straightforward and aligned with buyer readiness**, especially in new markets like mining (17:00).  \n    - Eric emphasized caution about calling Aquarius a platform due to legacy perceptions and suggested working with L1 stakeholders for messaging approval.\n\n## **Market and Persona Insights**\n\nThe discussion highlighted the importance of understanding buyer psychology and industry-specific behaviors to maximize ABM impact (05:00 - 06:00; 23:00).\n\n- **Colin stressed that modern buyers value their information highly, so messaging must provide strong, relevant reasons to engage, emphasizing empathy maps and pain points** (05:19).  \n    - This aligns with the multi-channel approach, aiming to catch prospects in various contexts with tailored content.\n\n- **Eric shared insights from past ABM efforts, including a manual, high-touch pandemic campaign sending physical branded demo devices, which achieved a 33% conversion rate (10 out of 30)** (22:40).  \n    - This old-school approach underscored the power of personalized, tangible engagement in certain segments.  \n    - He also noted that print media remains surprisingly effective for this audience, often consumed during downtime, making magazines and branded swag valuable touchpoints (24:00).  \n    - This informs the team''s willingness to include physical mailers and swag in the ABM mix as a complement to digital outreach.\n\n- **Colin and Eric agreed that hitting prospects across multiple channels and formats increases brand impressions and the chance of success**, especially during critical moments like system crises or procurement cycles (26:00).  \n    - This psychological layering strategy aims to build familiarity and trust over time.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Operational Details**\n\nThe meeting underscored automation, data integration, and workflow improvements to increase efficiency and responsiveness in ABM campaigns (11:47; 12:27; 27:00).\n\n- **N8N automation workflows centralize engagement signals across platforms, enabling AI-driven reply triage and lead scoring** (11:47).  \n    - This reduces manual effort and improves follow-up speed, which is critical to conversion rates in B2B sales cycles.\n\n- **Data flows securely into HubSpot as non-marketing contacts and triggers Salesforce workflows when leads meet thresholds, maintaining CRM hygiene and clear sales handoffs** (12:27).  \n    - This structured process supports scalable campaign management and pipeline tracking.\n\n- **Colin noted the team''s ability to develop custom offers and tools internally, such as AI competitor analysis and calculators, to differentiate the ABM experience** (14:20).  \n    - This internal capability creates agility in offer development and supports rapid iteration based on market feedback.\n\n- **Barb mentioned ongoing work to finalize webinar landing pages and HubSpot forms, indicating active content deployment alongside ABM efforts** (26:36).  \n    - This points to a coordinated content and campaign strategy supporting lead capture and nurturing.\n\n## **Timelines, Team Roles, and Next Steps**\n\nThe meeting clarified roles, upcoming collaboration, and iterative planning to accelerate ABM launch and refinement (00:23; 19:53; 27:43).\n\n- **Safya and Eric are primary content leads for Aquarius and Hawk Wins respectively, focusing on messaging and offer development for their product areas** (16:00).  \n    - Barb will coordinate with them on messaging consistency and approval processes.\n\n- **A follow-up internal team call is scheduled for next Tuesday to refine offers and build on the meeting’s strategic foundation** (19:53).  \n    - This session will help finalize offer concepts and align on messaging before broader campaign execution.\n\n- **Colin emphasized readiness to dive into technical specifics and tool demonstrations as needed, indicating continued hands-on support** (20:36).  \n    - This ensures the team can move quickly from planning to implementation with expert guidance.\n\n- **The group expressed enthusiasm for learning and adapting to the rapidly evolving ABM landscape, recognizing significant shifts even in the past year** (21:00).  \n    - Eric acknowledged the need to catch up on new tools and approaches, signaling openness to innovation and collaboration.\n\n- **Barb is resolving access issues to finalize webinar-related content, demonstrating progress on integrated marketing initiatives supporting ABM** (26:36).","outline":null,"keywords":["Account-Based Marketing","ABM Technology Stack","Lead Scoring","Multi-Channel Outreach","Messaging Strategy","Mining and Water Sector"],"overview":"- **ABM Framework Update:** Revamped strategy with AI enrichment tools for targeted, personalized outreach to improve engagement and lead quality.  \n- **Automation Layer:** N8N captures engagement signals for efficient follow-ups, increasing responsiveness and reducing manual workload.  \n- **Integrated CRM:** Seamless updates in HubSpot and Salesforce maintain lead hygiene, enhancing sales pipeline efficiency and clarity.  \n- **Focused Offers:** Personalized insights and tailored assessments will drive engagement, balancing volume with quality in communications.  \n- **Market Understanding:** Emphasizing buyer psychology is crucial; multiple touchpoints increase brand familiarity and trust, especially in crises.  \n- **Collaboration Ahead:** Key content leads are defined, with follow-up meetings planned to refine offers and support campaign execution.","action_items":"\n**Barb Willans**\nCoordinate a follow-up team meeting next Tuesday to discuss ABM offers and content development (19:53)\nResolve two-factor authentication issue and update simulive webinar landing page on WordPress, making on-demand content private and adding HubSpot form (26:36)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare link to the interactive offer/testing tools for prospect engagement to review customizable, AI-driven reports (13:06)\nProvide a technical demo or further explanation of the N8N workflow automation capabilities in a future session (11:31)\n\n**Erik Larsen**\nCollaborate on messaging refinement for Aquarius and Wins platforms to align with L1 team preferences and ensure consistency (16:14)\nReview historical ABM efforts and suggest potential pivots leveraging learnings across physical and digital outreach channels (23:40)\n\n**Guilly Santana**\nConfirm availability of WordPress landing page and assist Barb with form integration or content updates as needed (27:00)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"74aaefe8-ace7-4f53-97de-1ab492e47723","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
