    '{"id":"01KG82RD56587CH57DGXB65J97","title":"Data Assessment // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Outreach**\n\nThe initial outreach campaigns have launched with early engagement metrics showing room for growth.\n\n- **21 LinkedIn connection requests and 52 emails were sent this morning**, yielding **3 out-of-office auto-responses and no accepted connections yet** (06:00)  \n    - The LinkedIn outreach is managed under **Bettina’s account**, making her the primary contact for progress tracking.  \n    - The low response rate at this early stage is expected, as the campaign just started during the team’s morning hours.  \n    - **Colin** and **Axel** agreed to monitor these metrics closely to assess engagement trends over the coming weeks.  \n    - This initial step sets the foundation for refining messaging and targeting based on feedback and response rates.\n\n- **New ads and landing page updates are ready to be implemented and aligned with current outreach efforts** (08:00)  \n    - Updated ad copy and visuals are consistent across channels, maintaining a unified brand message.  \n    - The landing page was built and integrated into the client’s **WordPress**, with all prior feedback incorporated.  \n    - **Axel** noted the need to synchronize visuals and script changes to maintain message coherence across ads and landing page.  \n    - The team plans rapid deployment of these updated assets to improve conversion rates and user experience.\n\n## **Content and Creative Alignment**\n\nContent updates focus on ensuring messaging consistency and relevance across all campaign touchpoints.\n\n- **The outreach script was revised substantially in German to better align with visuals and ads, with some parts pending translation and clarification** (09:43)  \n    - **Axel** added new screenshots to the script and flagged areas needing further input, especially where animations or call-out bubbles replace static images.  \n    - Collaboration on script refinement will continue, with the option to suggest alternative legends or descriptions for unclear visuals.  \n    - This adjustment aims to increase the clarity and impact of the campaign’s storytelling.  \n    - **Colin** will review the changes and coordinate any needed translations or modifications.\n\n- **Access issues for creative assets like the Figma file were resolved to enable ongoing edits and collaboration** (10:38)  \n    - **Nathalie** regained edit permissions after a temporary loss, allowing her to contribute effectively to ad designs.  \n    - This ensures the creative team can respond quickly to feedback and update assets without delay.  \n    - Maintaining access continuity supports a smoother creative workflow and faster iteration cycles.\n\n## **Contractual and Partnership Strategy**\n\nA formal contract cancellation notice is pending, with discussions underway to reshape the partnership and internal capabilities.\n\n- **The 90-day contract extension includes a 30-day lead time, effectively extending the partnership by 120 days unless canceled promptly** (11:40)  \n    - **Axel** emphasized the importance of formally canceling now to avoid unintended automatic renewal.  \n    - The length of this extension was seen as too long given current uncertainties and the desire to pivot the working relationship.  \n    - This formal step is meant to clear the path for new collaboration models and avoid contractual confusion.\n\n- **A strategic shift toward building an internal marketing team with coaching and knowledge transfer was proposed by Axel** (12:50)  \n    - Max is transitioning into leading marketing internally, highlighting the need for foundational training on marketing principles and workflows.  \n    - Coaching would reduce translation delays and improve agility by empowering the in-house team.  \n    - Colin agreed to arrange a detailed discussion with leadership, including Tristan and Justin, to explore coaching and strategic support options.  \n    - This shift reflects a long-term vision to develop internal capabilities rather than solely outsourcing execution.\n\n## **Upcoming Planning and Coordination**\n\nThe team committed to scheduling in-depth discussions next week to finalize new strategic directions and accelerate campaign progress.\n\n- **A meeting involving Colin, Axel, Tristan, and Justin is planned for Thursday afternoon to discuss strategic options and coaching models** (15:40)  \n    - Monday and Tuesday were less feasible due to travel and time zone differences, making Thursday the optimal choice.  \n    - The call will aim to clarify roles, responsibilities, and the balance between tactical execution and strategic guidance.  \n    - This planning ensures alignment among key stakeholders before contract changes take effect.  \n    - The meeting will also address improving response times and operational velocity, which had been slower than desired.\n\n- **Campaign updates will continue alongside strategic discussions, with a focus on improving speed and reducing translation hurdles** (15:59)  \n    - Axel acknowledged recent delays impacted momentum, underscoring the need for faster turnaround.  \n    - Colin committed to optimizing workflows and communication to enhance overall project velocity.  \n    - These improvements aim to maintain campaign relevance and capitalize on early outreach learnings.  \n    - Both parties emphasized transparency and responsiveness as key to future success.","outline":null,"keywords":["Campaign Launch","Landing Page","Marketing Automation","Script Update","Contract Cancellation","Team Coaching"],"overview":"- **Campaign Launch Metrics:** 21 LinkedIn requests and 52 emails sent; 3 auto-responses, no connections yet. \n\n- **Creative Updates Ready:** New ad copy, visuals synchronized; landing page updated based on prior feedback, ready for rapid deployment. \n\n- **Content Alignment:** Outreach script revised in German; aims for consistency and clarity across campaign visuals. \n\n- **Contract and Partnership Changes:** 90-day extension needs prompt cancellation to avoid automatic renewal; strategic focus shifts to internal marketing team development. \n\n- **Strategic Meeting Scheduled:** Key stakeholders will discuss strategic options and coaching models to enhance campaign effectiveness next Thursday. \n\n- **Commitment to Speed:** Efforts to improve workflows, translation efficiency, and campaign responsiveness highlighted as priority moving forward.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare new landing page link in Teams chat for the team’s easy access (07:42)\nUpdate ads with new copy and visuals and send them back for approval to expedite going live (08:26)\nReview script comments and updated screenshots; address any questions with Axel to finalize video/edit content alignment (09:02)\nSchedule and lead a strategic marketing call with Axel, Tristan, and Justin early next week to discuss marketing team coaching and automation approaches (13:35)\nClarify contract extension and cancellation process with Axel to prevent confusion, ensure formal notice is in place (11:29)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nApprove Nathalie’s edit access request to the Figma ad files (10:53)\nProvide feedback on script and visuals, especially on sections needing animation or call-out bubbles for AI bot representation (09:06)\nSend the formal cancellation notice to clarify contract terms and timeline (15:59)\nConfirm availability for the planned strategic call on Monday or Thursday afternoon (14:34)\nAssist Colin on marketing coaching topics and provide guidance on aligning ads and campaign materials with new messaging (10:20)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nRequest edit access to Figma file for ads to continue collaborative updates (10:38)\n"},"duration":17.309999465942383,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"id":2,"name":"Axel Völker"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hello.","index":0,"end_time":250.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, how''s it going?","index":1,"end_time":253.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":255.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.89,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Hello.","index":3,"end_time":337.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":336.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hi, how you doing?","index":4,"end_time":339.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey max, How you bet doing?","index":5,"end_time":346.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, pretty good so far.","index":6,"end_time":350.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":348.01,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Well, the campaigns are live on email and LinkedIn outreach.","index":7,"end_time":357.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":352.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"LinkedIn also.","index":8,"end_time":359.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":358.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, so we''ve sent out 21 connections so far.","index":9,"end_time":363.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":360.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"None of them have been accepted yet.","index":10,"end_time":365.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":364.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But that just started this morning, your guys time.","index":11,"end_time":368.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":365.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that is under Bettina''s account so she would see that.","index":12,"end_time":373.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":370.02,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, correct.","index":13,"end_time":374.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":373.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we''ve sent out 52 emails as well.","index":14,"end_time":377.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":374.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ve gotten three replies but all out.","index":15,"end_time":379.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":377.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Of Office auto responses.","index":16,"end_time":381.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":379.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, so let''s see how that goes.","index":17,"end_time":384.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":383.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we made the first step basically.","index":18,"end_time":387.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And we have the new landing page live as well.","index":19,"end_time":390.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":388.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then where''s that?","index":20,"end_time":393.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can I see that?","index":21,"end_time":393.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":393.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Can you send the link?","index":22,"end_time":395.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that in our WordPress?","index":23,"end_time":398.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It is.","index":24,"end_time":399.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":25,"end_time":401.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Didn''t even know that.","index":26,"end_time":402.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":401.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Did you do that or did you.","index":27,"end_time":404.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":403.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Did someone on our side?","index":28,"end_time":405.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":404.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No, we built it.","index":29,"end_time":406.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":406.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How did you get it in our WordPress?","index":30,"end_time":409.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You invited us to your WordPress.","index":31,"end_time":411.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":410.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that was my question.","index":32,"end_time":413.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":411.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, good.","index":33,"end_time":414.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":413.57,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, all, all feedback was incorporated in here.","index":34,"end_time":419.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can you share.","index":35,"end_time":421.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You put the link in the chat?","index":36,"end_time":423.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":421.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":37,"end_time":423.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":423.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we did previously add this to email 2 in the sequence, but then there was a comment yesterday to remove it.","index":38,"end_time":436.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":430.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":39,"end_time":437.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, where''s the story?","index":40,"end_time":444.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":441.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There was what?","index":41,"end_time":444.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":444.29,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we had this page linked in email 2 of the sequence originally, but we.","index":42,"end_time":452.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":447.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There was a comment to remove that link.","index":43,"end_time":453.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":452.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, okay.","index":44,"end_time":454.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":453.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, if you just can share the link.","index":45,"end_time":458.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":455.45,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh yeah, I put it in the zoom chat.","index":46,"end_time":459.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":458.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you want me to put it in the teams chat?","index":47,"end_time":460.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":459.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, in the teams chat.","index":48,"end_time":461.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.89,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That would be good.","index":49,"end_time":462.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":461.93,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem then.","index":50,"end_time":464.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":462.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I just dropped it in there.","index":51,"end_time":470.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":468.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, thanks.","index":52,"end_time":472.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Good.","index":53,"end_time":475.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":475.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So yeah, that''s progress.","index":54,"end_time":476.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":475.77,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s good.","index":55,"end_time":477.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Oh, that''s the, that''s the effect that you mentioned.","index":56,"end_time":480.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":478.81,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s where it trolls.","index":57,"end_time":482.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":480.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":58,"end_time":483.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":482.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, awesome.","index":59,"end_time":486.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":60,"end_time":488.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":487.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know that we have new ads and so there''s comments Max.","index":61,"end_time":492.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":488.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That I see left.","index":62,"end_time":493.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":492.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll go through and make these.","index":63,"end_time":496.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":494.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Updates with the new copy.","index":64,"end_time":497.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":496.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so basically just it''s the same text.","index":65,"end_time":502.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So everywhere.","index":66,"end_time":504.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.58,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yep.","index":67,"end_time":505.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":504.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Same picture everywhere.","index":68,"end_time":506.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":505.3,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yep.","index":69,"end_time":507.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":506.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":70,"end_time":510.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":510.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then so we''ll get those updated and sent back over to you guys so we can get those live right away.","index":71,"end_time":516.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":510.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know that you guys provided some new screenshots, so just wanted to check if, when you were providing those, if you compared them against the script, if the script has to change at all.","index":72,"end_time":526.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":516.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have added them to the script, I think, I''m pretty sure in the Word document or I put some comments in there.","index":73,"end_time":536.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Which ones to use.","index":74,"end_time":537.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":536.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, Sorry, I think I did it in your Google Doc actually.","index":75,"end_time":541.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":538.43,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":76,"end_time":543.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It didn''t, but there''s some where we.","index":77,"end_time":549.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":546.28,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Where it''s not so clear where you probably can make some suggestion because there are some that don''t have screenshots.","index":78,"end_time":555.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":549.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re more like animation.","index":79,"end_time":558.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":555.32,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"They''re more like this, what do you call that?","index":80,"end_time":562.119,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.76,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This call out bubbles or something like that for the AI bot.","index":81,"end_time":565.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.119,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, all right, I see this, the comments here.","index":82,"end_time":567.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":565.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":83,"end_time":568.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":567.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s interesting that Google didn''t notify me.","index":84,"end_time":572.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we should be able to move.","index":85,"end_time":574.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":572.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Forward with that then.","index":86,"end_time":575.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":574.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so you can check that and if there''s questions just let me know.","index":87,"end_time":580.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":576.36,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":88,"end_time":581.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":580.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":89,"end_time":583.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I actually rewrote it quite a bit so it''s.","index":90,"end_time":586.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":583.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It''s all German.","index":91,"end_time":586.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.12,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I haven''t translated it, but you can probably just translate that with Google or something.","index":92,"end_time":591.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.92,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So the story has changed a bit to be also more in line with.","index":93,"end_time":598.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.08,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"With the ads and the page.","index":94,"end_time":599.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":598.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And that''s why the visuals also need to change a bit.","index":95,"end_time":605.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":600.75,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s not exactly the same storyline as it was before.","index":96,"end_time":611.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":606.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Just review that.","index":97,"end_time":612.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":612.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you need help with different legends, just let us know.","index":98,"end_time":615.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":613.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But I guess it''s.","index":99,"end_time":616.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":615.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, no problem.","index":100,"end_time":617.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":616.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Straightforward.","index":101,"end_time":620.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":102,"end_time":621.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":103,"end_time":623.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":622.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, Axel, pretty much the only other thing that I wanted to go through was I was just hoping that you and I could have a few minutes on this call to just connect one on one.","index":104,"end_time":631.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":623.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can.","index":105,"end_time":632.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":631.87,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Sure.","index":106,"end_time":632.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":632.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, sure.","index":107,"end_time":633.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Great.","index":108,"end_time":634.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":633.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max.","index":109,"end_time":634.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Natalie, anything else from your guys side?","index":110,"end_time":636.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":634.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":111,"end_time":639.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.27,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think I just requested edit access to the Figma file for the ads.","index":112,"end_time":643.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":639.03,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I think if you could share that.","index":113,"end_time":646.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":644.43,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"I know I did have it before but somehow it''s gone again and it doesn''t let me edit.","index":114,"end_time":651.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.59,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"Okay, I can check.","index":115,"end_time":654.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":653.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":116,"end_time":655.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":654.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I usually send edit request.","index":117,"end_time":658.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":656.03,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, I just got it approved request.","index":118,"end_time":660.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.91,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I can just approve it here.","index":119,"end_time":662.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.83,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, it should be approved now.","index":120,"end_time":669.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":667.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":121,"end_time":670.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well, thank you.","index":122,"end_time":673.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.47,"speaker_name":"Nathalie Mintjens"},{"text":"All right.","index":123,"end_time":674.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":674.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"All right.","index":124,"end_time":675.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":674.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, thanks Natalie.","index":125,"end_time":677.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":676.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can jump whenever and then.","index":126,"end_time":679.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":677.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Max, unless there was anything else.","index":127,"end_time":680.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":679.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I think everything yesterday.","index":128,"end_time":684.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":129,"end_time":685.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":130,"end_time":686.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":686.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":131,"end_time":688.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687.97,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Have a good weekend as well.","index":132,"end_time":689.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":688.53,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Thanks, Max.","index":133,"end_time":690.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":689.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Bye bye.","index":134,"end_time":692.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":690.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey Axel.","index":135,"end_time":695.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":695.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I got your email this morning so I just wanted to take a.","index":136,"end_time":698.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":695.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Few minutes to talk through that.","index":137,"end_time":699.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think we mentioned that when we started the contract.","index":138,"end_time":702.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.05,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"This is a bit not tricky for us because the problem is that you have.","index":139,"end_time":710.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":702.85,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So Stefan notified me about that today.","index":140,"end_time":715.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":711.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You have a 30 days lead per period for the 90 days extension which makes it 120 days basically that it would extend.","index":141,"end_time":726.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":715.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"If you don''t cancel now, we would just have another 120 days.","index":142,"end_time":730.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":726.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And 120 days is like, it''s pretty long.","index":143,"end_time":734.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And at this point we''re not.","index":144,"end_time":738.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I cannot just say we''re going to do another 120 days.","index":145,"end_time":743.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":739.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And the only way I can prevent that is by canceling that request.","index":146,"end_time":748.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":743.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That''s just how you made it your.","index":147,"end_time":750.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":748.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Your contract, basically.","index":148,"end_time":751.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":750.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":149,"end_time":751.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":751.51,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So that''s why we''ll do this formally.","index":150,"end_time":755.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"But then we should just discuss how we want to proceed.","index":151,"end_time":760.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.15,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I have some other ideas that I would like to discuss with you or Tristan.","index":152,"end_time":768.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So what we.","index":153,"end_time":770.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":769.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I think it is important.","index":154,"end_time":773.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.37,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I want to build up marketing team here.","index":155,"end_time":777.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.61,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Essentially we don''t have one really.","index":156,"end_time":780.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":777.65,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So Max is moving into that and he needs to understand marketing and how things works and the basics.","index":157,"end_time":788.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.13,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And I think it will also be easier if in the long run we can do more stuff here because when we don''t have the translation issues and all those things.","index":158,"end_time":796.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":789.25,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":159,"end_time":796.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wonder if you could maybe change the direction a bit or extend it a bit so that you do like coaching for our people and explain how things work and how marketing works.","index":160,"end_time":814.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":796.98,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, so what I want to do is pull.","index":161,"end_time":819.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":815.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to set up a call maybe early next week where you, me, Tristan and Justin can dive into some of these things.","index":162,"end_time":825.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":820.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But what I will say is actually one of our businesses under our umbrella, we''re kind of reshaping to do exactly that.","index":163,"end_time":834.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":826.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like a consultative, like work with the internal marketing team, develop automations.","index":164,"end_time":839.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":834.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a few ways that people can go.","index":165,"end_time":841.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":839.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They can either like automate their marketing team where they only need one person, or not even one person internally, or we could just give the internal team the skill, skills and, and the systems and things in place.","index":166,"end_time":852.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":841.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So yeah, we could absolutely explore that.","index":167,"end_time":854.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":852.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We also have strategic and tactical approaches to our accounts.","index":168,"end_time":859.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":854.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like, if you just want us to do a bunch of design and development and writing and anything like that, we can do that.","index":169,"end_time":864.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":859.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or if we want to lead strategy.","index":170,"end_time":866.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":864.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can, we can go with that route either.","index":171,"end_time":868.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, I think, I think having a more in depth conversation early next.","index":172,"end_time":873.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":868.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Week would be great.","index":173,"end_time":873.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, just next week.","index":174,"end_time":878.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":874.9,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So I am traveling on Tuesday, Wednesday.","index":175,"end_time":882.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":878.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"That makes it a bit challenging next week because essentially in Friday I''m pretty much.","index":176,"end_time":892.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":882.56,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we can.","index":177,"end_time":892.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":892.16,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or maybe we take our Friday call and, and use the time for that and I can just.","index":178,"end_time":900.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":894.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can do Friday or we can have it.","index":179,"end_time":902.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":901.2,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we can do Monday later, like probably 2:00 o''clock your time.","index":180,"end_time":913.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":902.84,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":181,"end_time":914.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":914.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or no, hold on.","index":182,"end_time":916.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.78,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"It is what you are.","index":183,"end_time":917.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":916.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"No, it''s 12 o'' clock, so you are six hours.","index":184,"end_time":920.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":917.42,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I think ahead.","index":185,"end_time":920.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":920.18,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Right.","index":186,"end_time":921.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":920.86,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So it''s nine now or what is it?","index":187,"end_time":923.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":921.82,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or it is nine now.","index":188,"end_time":925.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":923.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":189,"end_time":925.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":925.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unfortunately, 12 o'' clock''s not gonna work.","index":190,"end_time":928.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":925.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we can do on Thursday there.","index":191,"end_time":934.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":928.94,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"I''m pretty flexible.","index":192,"end_time":935.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":934.14,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay, maybe the same time on Thursday?","index":193,"end_time":939.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":936.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The same time.","index":194,"end_time":941.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Maybe an hour later.","index":195,"end_time":944.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":943.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Would that work?","index":196,"end_time":945.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":944.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Or half an hour later?","index":197,"end_time":947.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, later would be good.","index":198,"end_time":948.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":947.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Okay.","index":199,"end_time":949.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that works.","index":200,"end_time":950.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":949.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"You sent me.","index":201,"end_time":951.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":950.79,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":202,"end_time":952.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":952.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":203,"end_time":953.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":204,"end_time":953.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So looking forward to that.","index":205,"end_time":955.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":953.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll have more campaign updates, obviously, we just launched today, so.","index":206,"end_time":959.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":956.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s probably going to send you the formal cancellation notice, but that''s really so.","index":207,"end_time":963.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":959.07,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Because we want to just be like, have the formalities kind of.","index":208,"end_time":969.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":963.59,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, clarify.","index":209,"end_time":971.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I totally hear you.","index":210,"end_time":972.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":971.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":211,"end_time":972.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":212,"end_time":973.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":973.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just wanted to cut through that just so we''re on the same page.","index":213,"end_time":977.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":974.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to make sure that there wasn''t any confusion or anything and that, you know, that we can move with more velocity.","index":214,"end_time":984.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":977.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The translations were obviously.","index":215,"end_time":986.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":985.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":216,"end_time":986.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":986.39,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So we were not.","index":217,"end_time":987.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":986.67,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Honestly, it was a bit slow, our feeling how it went the last weeks with the response time.","index":218,"end_time":995.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":987.55,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"And so I think we can be faster.","index":219,"end_time":998.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":995.47,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"So that is also something we can maybe discuss.","index":220,"end_time":1002.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1000.27,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Yeah, we can definitely move faster.","index":221,"end_time":1004.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1002.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think the translations were a hurdle that we were working through, but we can definitely talk more through that as well.","index":222,"end_time":1010.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1004.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":223,"end_time":1012.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1011.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Axel, thank you for your time, and have a great weekend.","index":224,"end_time":1015.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1012.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you too.","index":225,"end_time":1015.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.23,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":226,"end_time":1016.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1015.95,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"},{"text":"Bye.","index":227,"end_time":1016.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1016.31,"speaker_name":"Axel Völker"}],"dateString":"2026-02-06T14:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86344108572?pwd=qdakcUFJbrjywReJlBZ3DxNLrBYqXb.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com,voelker@data-assessment.com,bebinger@decidalo.com,osbaldeston@data-assessment.com,pollex@data-assessment.com,rabeler@data-assessment.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","joachim.giesen@uni-jena.de","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","nathalie.mintjens@marketersindemand.com","voelker@data-assessment.com","bebinger@decidalo.com","osbaldeston@data-assessment.com","pollex@data-assessment.com","rabeler@data-assessment.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KG82RD56587CH57DGXB65J97","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
