    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Outreach**\n\nThe initial outreach campaigns have launched with early engagement metrics showing room for growth.\n\n- **21 LinkedIn connection requests and 52 emails were sent this morning**, yielding **3 out-of-office auto-responses and no accepted connections yet** (06:00)  \n    - The LinkedIn outreach is managed under **Bettina’s account**, making her the primary contact for progress tracking.  \n    - The low response rate at this early stage is expected, as the campaign just started during the team’s morning hours.  \n    - **Colin** and **Axel** agreed to monitor these metrics closely to assess engagement trends over the coming weeks.  \n    - This initial step sets the foundation for refining messaging and targeting based on feedback and response rates.\n\n- **New ads and landing page updates are ready to be implemented and aligned with current outreach efforts** (08:00)  \n    - Updated ad copy and visuals are consistent across channels, maintaining a unified brand message.  \n    - The landing page was built and integrated into the client’s **WordPress**, with all prior feedback incorporated.  \n    - **Axel** noted the need to synchronize visuals and script changes to maintain message coherence across ads and landing page.  \n    - The team plans rapid deployment of these updated assets to improve conversion rates and user experience.\n\n## **Content and Creative Alignment**\n\nContent updates focus on ensuring messaging consistency and relevance across all campaign touchpoints.\n\n- **The outreach script was revised substantially in German to better align with visuals and ads, with some parts pending translation and clarification** (09:43)  \n    - **Axel** added new screenshots to the script and flagged areas needing further input, especially where animations or call-out bubbles replace static images.  \n    - Collaboration on script refinement will continue, with the option to suggest alternative legends or descriptions for unclear visuals.  \n    - This adjustment aims to increase the clarity and impact of the campaign’s storytelling.  \n    - **Colin** will review the changes and coordinate any needed translations or modifications.\n\n- **Access issues for creative assets like the Figma file were resolved to enable ongoing edits and collaboration** (10:38)  \n    - **Nathalie** regained edit permissions after a temporary loss, allowing her to contribute effectively to ad designs.  \n    - This ensures the creative team can respond quickly to feedback and update assets without delay.  \n    - Maintaining access continuity supports a smoother creative workflow and faster iteration cycles.\n\n## **Contractual and Partnership Strategy**\n\nA formal contract cancellation notice is pending, with discussions underway to reshape the partnership and internal capabilities.\n\n- **The 90-day contract extension includes a 30-day lead time, effectively extending the partnership by 120 days unless canceled promptly** (11:40)  \n    - **Axel** emphasized the importance of formally canceling now to avoid unintended automatic renewal.  \n    - The length of this extension was seen as too long given current uncertainties and the desire to pivot the working relationship.  \n    - This formal step is meant to clear the path for new collaboration models and avoid contractual confusion.\n\n- **A strategic shift toward building an internal marketing team with coaching and knowledge transfer was proposed by Axel** (12:50)  \n    - Max is transitioning into leading marketing internally, highlighting the need for foundational training on marketing principles and workflows.  \n    - Coaching would reduce translation delays and improve agility by empowering the in-house team.  \n    - Colin agreed to arrange a detailed discussion with leadership, including Tristan and Justin, to explore coaching and strategic support options.  \n    - This shift reflects a long-term vision to develop internal capabilities rather than solely outsourcing execution.\n\n## **Upcoming Planning and Coordination**\n\nThe team committed to scheduling in-depth discussions next week to finalize new strategic directions and accelerate campaign progress.\n\n- **A meeting involving Colin, Axel, Tristan, and Justin is planned for Thursday afternoon to discuss strategic options and coaching models** (15:40)  \n    - Monday and Tuesday were less feasible due to travel and time zone differences, making Thursday the optimal choice.  \n    - The call will aim to clarify roles, responsibilities, and the balance between tactical execution and strategic guidance.  \n    - This planning ensures alignment among key stakeholders before contract changes take effect.  \n    - The meeting will also address improving response times and operational velocity, which had been slower than desired.\n\n- **Campaign updates will continue alongside strategic discussions, with a focus on improving speed and reducing translation hurdles** (15:59)  \n    - Axel acknowledged recent delays impacted momentum, underscoring the need for faster turnaround.  \n    - Colin committed to optimizing workflows and communication to enhance overall project velocity.  \n    - These improvements aim to maintain campaign relevance and capitalize on early outreach learnings.  \n    - Both parties emphasized transparency and responsiveness as key to future success.","outline":null,"keywords":["Campaign Launch","Landing Page","Marketing Automation","Script Update","Contract Cancellation","Team Coaching"],"overview":"- **Campaign Launch Metrics:** 21 LinkedIn requests and 52 emails sent; 3 auto-responses, no connections yet. \n\n- **Creative Updates Ready:** New ad copy, visuals synchronized; landing page updated based on prior feedback, ready for rapid deployment. \n\n- **Content Alignment:** Outreach script revised in German; aims for consistency and clarity across campaign visuals. \n\n- **Contract and Partnership Changes:** 90-day extension needs prompt cancellation to avoid automatic renewal; strategic focus shifts to internal marketing team development. \n\n- **Strategic Meeting Scheduled:** Key stakeholders will discuss strategic options and coaching models to enhance campaign effectiveness next Thursday. \n\n- **Commitment to Speed:** Efforts to improve workflows, translation efficiency, and campaign responsiveness highlighted as priority moving forward.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nShare new landing page link in Teams chat for the team’s easy access (07:42)\nUpdate ads with new copy and visuals and send them back for approval to expedite going live (08:26)\nReview script comments and updated screenshots; address any questions with Axel to finalize video/edit content alignment (09:02)\nSchedule and lead a strategic marketing call with Axel, Tristan, and Justin early next week to discuss marketing team coaching and automation approaches (13:35)\nClarify contract extension and cancellation process with Axel to prevent confusion, ensure formal notice is in place (11:29)\n\n**Axel Völker**\nApprove Nathalie’s edit access request to the Figma ad files (10:53)\nProvide feedback on script and visuals, especially on sections needing animation or call-out bubbles for AI bot representation (09:06)\nSend the formal cancellation notice to clarify contract terms and timeline (15:59)\nConfirm availability for the planned strategic call on Monday or Thursday afternoon (14:34)\nAssist Colin on marketing coaching topics and provide guidance on aligning ads and campaign materials with new messaging (10:20)\n\n**Nathalie Mintjens**\nRequest edit access to Figma file for ads to continue collaborative updates (10:38)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"7043e51a-cbb1-4264-98d1-b749f3b7527e","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
